A CAPITAL was a European midcap growth fund, leading on Euro-Asia private equity transactions. The firm used to co-invest with Chinese groups into leading European midcap firms with strong growth potential in China. The firm had offices in Beijing, Brussels and Hong Kong.

A&E Investments is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm seeks to invest in information technology sectors.

Founded in 2013, A-Force Ventures is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm prefers to invest in female-led consumer internet and mobile startups operating in the travel, health, entertainment, consumer products, dating, fashion, and education sectors.

Founded in 2010, A-Grade Investments is a venture capital investment firm based in Los Angeles, California. The firm primarily invests in the consumer-based internet and consumer-oriented technology sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).
A-LIVE Holdings is a venture management firm based in Canada.

Founded in 2014, A.Capital Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Menlo Park, California. The firm seeks to invest in B2B, B2C, information technology & SaaS sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

A10 Networks is a provider of security and infrastructure solutions for on-premises, hybrid cloud, and edge-cloud environments of its multinational enterprise, communication, cloud, and web service provider customers who strive to provide business-critical applications and networks that are secure, available, and efficient. As cyber-attacks increase in volume and complexity, the company integrates security and artificial intelligence (AI) enabled capabilities in its solutions that enable its customers to continue to adapt to market trends in hybrid cloud, AI-ready data centers, and the ever-increasing need for high-performance, high availability, and low latency. The company generates the maximum of its revenue from the Americas.

AAON is a manufacturer of air-conditioning and heating equipment. The products include rooftop units, chillers, packaged outdoor mechanical rooms, air-handling units, makeup air units, energy-recovery units, condensing units, geothermal heat pumps, and self-contained units and coils. The company operates through three segments: AAON Oklahoma, AAON Coil Products, and BASX. It generates the majority of its revenue from the AAON Oklahoma segment, which engineers, manufactures, and sells semi-custom and custom HVAC systems, designs and manufactures control solutions, and sells retail parts to customers through retail part stores and online.

Mr. Aaron Harris is a Co-Founder of Magid & Company. Mr. Harris is an Angel Investor. He also Co-Founded TutorSpree and worked at Bridgewater Associates, where he managed product and operations for an analytics group. He has an AB in History and Literature from Harvard. He also worked at a hedge fund in New York.

Mr. Aaron Iba is a Co-Founder and serves as Board Member at PayGarden. Mr. Iba serves as Advisor at Taskade. He is the Founder of Symmetry Group. Prior to that, he founded PayGarden and AppJet (Etherpad). He also served as a Partner for YCombinator, as a Software Engineer for Google, Director for BattleCode and as a Program Manager (Intern) for Microsoft.

Dr. Aaron Lee is a Co-Founder & serves as Chief Executive Officer at Smith. Dr. Lee serves as Advisor at Easy Paint. He on Product Design and Engineering at Redbeacon. Prior to Redbeacon, he was one of the founding engineers on Google Video. He later became the Tech Lead on YouTube monetization, building products that spanned AdSense, AdWords and YouTube. He was also a Launch Engineer, helping launch many other Google products and mentoring and promoting engineers. Before joining Google, he worked at Bosch building one of the most advanced 3D navigation systems for in-car infotainment. He received his Ph.D. in Computer Graphics from Princeton and has interned at NVIDIA, Microsoft Research (where he received a Microsoft Fellowship), NASA Ames Research Center and Lucent Technologies. He has published papers in SIGGRAPH, IEEE conferences, sciencedaily.com and gamasutra.com. He earned an M.A and B.A. from University of Cambridge with first honors in Computer Science. He holds four patents with seven others currently pending.

Mr. Aaron Levie is the Founder and serves as Chief Executive Officer at Box (IT Services). Mr. Levie served as Board Member and Advisor at Helium. He previously served as an Advisor at Formation Data Systems. He has served on the Board of Directors since April 2005. He attended the University of Southern California from 2003 to 2005 before leaving to found Box. He also serves as an Advisor at 8VC. He serves as Board Member and Advisor at Helium. He served as Advisor at ZeroDown.

Mr. Aaron Patzer is a Co-Founder & serves as Chief Executive Officer at Vital (Enterprise Systems). Mr. Patzer co-founded Mint. He co-founded and served as Chief Executive Officer at Fountain. Prior to founding Mint, he was an architect and technical lead for the San Jose division of Nascentric. Before Nascentric, he worked for IBM and founded two web development and online marketing companies. He is hugely experienced in Machine Learning, having about a dozen patents in algorithms.

Mr. Aaron Ross is a Co-Founder of Predictable Revenue. He serves as a Board Member at ValueCore. He served as a Chief Revenue Officer at Predictable Revenue. He was a Venture Advisor at Spidal. He also serves as an Advisor and Director at AfterCollege. He founded BlackBox Revenue and PebbleStorm. He served as an Advisor at Sales Bootcamp. Previously, he was an EIer CapitR (Entrepreneur-in-Residence) at Alloy Ventures. Prior to that he was at salesforce.com, where he built a 'Cold Calling 2.0' sales team that has sourced $100 million in recurring revenue, and spent a year in the acquisitions and investments team, helping acquire and launch the AppExchange Mobile and Salesforce for Google AdWords products. Aaron was CEO of LeaseExchange, an online equipment leasing marketplace. As an entrepreneur, he has been in Time, Businessweek, and The Red Herring. Prior to LeaseExchange, Aaron worked at Pandemic, an Intel/SAP joint venture, did M&A at the investment bank Robertson Stephens and graduated from Stanford University with a degree in Environmental Civil Engineering. Aaron is on the advisory boards of Clickability, 4INFO, ConnectAndSell, Personiva, and Flywheel Ventures. He is an Ironman triathlete, a graduate of the Boulder Outdoor Survival School, and a volunteer mentor at SCORE, "Counselors to America's Small Business".

Aastra Technologies was a provider of enterprise communication technology. The company used to develop and market internet protocol (IP) based as well as traditional communications networking products and systems. On Janruary 31, 2014 the firm was acquired by Mitel Networks.

Founded in 1999, AAVIN Private Equity is a private equity firm based in Cedar Rapids, Iowa. The firm prefers to invest in medical services and devices, telecommunication, manufacturing, distribution, industrial products, computer, and software sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 2014, ABACO is a private equity firm based in New York, New York. The firm focuses on acquiring businesses as well as under-performing real estate properties throughout North America. The firm prefers to invest in industrial and mixed-use properties in New Jersey, New York, and Florida.

ABB is a supplier of electrical equipment and automation products. Founded in the late 19th century, the company was created out of the merger of two old industrial companies: ASEA and BBC. Its products include electrical equipment, industrial robots and equipment used for industrial automation that are sold via approximately 19 business divisions. ABB is the number one or two supplier in two-thirds of its product segments.

Abbott manufactures and markets cardiovascular and diabetes devices, adult and pediatric nutritional products, diagnostic equipment and testing kits, and branded generic drugs. Products include pacemakers, implantable cardioverter defibrillators, neuromodulation devices, coronary stents, catheters, infant formula, nutritional liquids for adults, continuous glucose monitors, and immunoassays and point-of-care diagnostic equipment. Abbott derives approximately 60% of its sales outside the United States.

AbbVie is a pharmaceutical firm with a strong exposure to immunology (with Humira, Skyrizi, and Rinvoq) and oncology (with Imbruvica and Venclexta). The company was spun off from Abbott in early 2013. The 2020 acquisition of Allergan added several new products and drugs in aesthetics (including Botox).

Founded in 2009, AbbVie Ventures is the corporate venture arm of AbbVie based in Cambridge, Massachusetts. The firm seeks to invest in the oncology, immunology, neuroscience, eye care, and aesthetics sectors.

AbCellera Biologics is an antibody discovery and development engine that's specifically designed to address the barriers of conventional discovery, finding the optimal clinical candidate with greater precision and speed, and getting to the clinic and patients sooner. With the integrated AbCellera platform, the company's experts search a wide range of diverse antibodies to select effective and developable leads quickly and set partners up for enduring success. The company has extensive experience forging partnerships with emerging biotechs and pharmaceutical companies. AbCellera leverages proprietary hardware, software, and tools along with the latest data science to operate as a strategic partner and help develop optimized solutions faster for any program.

The Abell Foundation is an independent non-profit foundation located in Baltimore, Maryland. Founded in 1953, the foundation's primary function is to provide maximum sustainable support from the allocated grants for schools, hospitals and human service organizations reaching out to the disadvantaged in the Baltimore community and the region. The assets of the foundation are managed by the board of trustees.

Cellular Biomedicine Group is a biotechnology company focused on the development of proprietary cell therapies for the treatment of cancer and degenerative diseases. The company has two major cell platforms: immune cell therapy for treating a broad range of cancers using cancer vaccines, Chimeric Antigen Receptor T-cell technologies, and anti-PD-1 technologies; and human-adipose-derived mesenchymal progenitor cells for the treatment of joint and autoimmune diseases. The immuno-oncology and stem cell research team is based in both China and the United States.

Abeo is a France-based sports and leisure equipment company. It is involved in developing and retailing sporting equipment for gymnastics, climbing, and locker rooms and bathrooms. The company also offers equipment for basketball and combat sports throughout Europe.

Aberration! Ventures was a private equity and venture capital firm focused on investing in all stages of growth, from pre-revenue startups to liquidation capital, with a maximum investment of $1,000,000 per transaction. The firm primarily invested in the business services, biomedical, retail, media, and real estate sectors.

Developer of medical devices that provide circulatory and respiratory support by enabling the heart to rest and recover by improving blood flow and temporarily assisting with the pumping function. The company offers temporary mechanical circulatory support devices that are primarily used by interventional cardiologists and heart surgeons. The firm's products are used for patients in need of hemodynamic support before, during, or after angioplasty and heart surgery procedures. Abiomed receives the majority of revenue from its Impella product portfolio, which includes percutaneous micro heart pumps with integration motors and sensors and percutaneous catheter-based axial flow pumps. Abiomed generates the majority of its revenue in the United States.

Founded in 2015, ABN AMRO Ventures is the corporate venture arm of ABN AMRO Bank headquartered in Amsterdam, Netherlands. The firm seeks to invest in technology companies in Europe, the United States, and Israel.

Founded in 1982 ABS Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Waltham, Massachusetts. The firm focuses on both primary and secondary direct investing strategies for mid-stage technology companies. The firm prefers to invest in growth-oriented businesses and typically remains active post-investment. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Acacia Research is focused on acquiring and operating businesses across the industrial, energy, and technology sectors where it believes it can leverage its expertise, capital base, and deep industry relationships to drive value. The company has four reportable business segments: Intellectual Property Operations, Industrial Operations, Energy Operations and Manufacturing Operations. It derives revenue from Intellectual Property Operations segment. Geographically, it operates in Americas, Europe, Middle East and Africa, China, India, and Asia-Pacific, excluding China and India.

Founded in 2005, Acadia Woods Partners is a venture capital investment firm based in New York, New York. The firm prefers to invest in companies operating in the technology, software, media, and life science sectors.

Founded in 1999, Acartha Technology Partners was a private equity firm based in Chesterfield, Missouri. The firm typically invested in technology and service companies whose products and services are sold in the financial services sector.

Founded in 2008, Accelerace is an accelerator based in Copenhagen, Denmark. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in fintech, education tech, cleantech, sound tech, the internet of things, digital health, food tech, biotech, medical tech, utilities, and media sectors.

Founded in 2009, Accelerant Venture Capital was a private equity and venture capital firm. It made venture investments in early-stage companies operating in the healthcare, consumer products and services, information technology sectors. The company was acquired by Panoramic Ventures on April 11, 2017.

Founded in 2012, AccelerateBaltimore was an accelerator firm based in Baltimore, Maryland. The firm used to invest in the modern technology sectors. The firm used to provide office space, mentorship, and connections.

Founded in 2002, Acceleration International is a growth equity firm based in Boston, Massachusetts. The firm seeks to invest in the healthcare and life sciences sectors across the United States and Europe regions.
Founded in 2003, Accelerator Life Science Partners is a venture capital firm based in Seattle, Washington. The firm prefers to invest in medicine and healthcare companies.

Accelerator Technology Holdings was an accelerator based in Amman, Jordan with an additional office in Manama, Bahrain. Founded in 2008, Accelerator Ventures is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage technology companies.

Founded in 2009, Accelmed Partners is a private equity firm based in Miami, Florida. The firm specializes in the health tech sector (medical devices, tools, diagnostics, digital health, and technology-enabled services). The firm focuses on buyout/control transactions involving scaling companies with commercially validated products, re-invigorating commercial growth in mature companies, assisting companies undergoing a turnaround, remediating complex capital structures, corporate carve-outs, and late-stage growth capital investments. The firm typically acquires control or invests in small and mid-cap private and public health technology companies in the United States. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Accenture is a leading global IT services firm that provides consulting, strategy, and technology and operational services. These services run the gamut from aiding enterprises with digital transformation to procurement services to software system integration. The company provides its IT offerings to a variety of sectors, including communications, media and technology, financial services, health and public services, consumer products and resources. Accenture employs just under 500,000 people throughout 200 cities in 51 countries.
Accera Venture Partners was a venture capital firm based in Mannheim, Germany.

Operator of a holding and global investment firm intended to support businesses across biotechnology, entertainment, global media, real estate, strategic equity and technology ventures. The company identifies companies with strong business models and management teams and optimizes their value through financial backing and expertise, thereby fostering growth and innovation across diverse industries.

Issuer Direct is a communications and compliance company. It focuses on the needs of corporate issuers. It provides disclosure management solutions, shareholder communications tools and cloud-based compliance technologies. The company serves a diverse range of client base in the financial services industry, including brokerage firms, banks, mutual funds, accounting and the legal communities. Its current brands and products include the following: issuer direct, access wire, investor network, blueprint, classify, iProxy direct, iR direct, and annual report service. Its primary geographic markets are North America and Europe of which North America contributes the vast majority of total revenue.

Founded in 2015, Access Technology Ventures is a corporate venture capital investment arm of Access Industries based in New York, New York. The firm prefers to invest in companies operating in the technology sector.

Founded in 1999, Access Venture Partners is a venture capital firm based in Westminster, Colorado with a regional office based in Denver, Colorado. The firm prefers to make seed and series A startup investments in information technology, cybersecurity, and big data sectors.

Founded in 2015, Accomplice VC is a venture capital firm based in Boston, Massachusetts. The firm seeks to invest in cybersecurity, eSports, data analytics, server message block-class software, emerging hardware platforms, and marketplace sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Accton Technology develops, manufactures and sells innovative high-quality products for computer network systems and wireless land area network (LAN) hardware and software products and renders related technical consulting and engineering design services. The products and services offered by the company are switches, network applications, metro access switches and wireless. Roughly half of the firm's revenue is generated in the United States, with the rest coming from Taiwan, the rest of Asia, Europe and other regions.

Developer of weather forecasting platform designed to provide various weather updates. The company's platform provides maps, news and video, climate updates and social weather information, enabling users to stay updated of the current weather reports and also receive weather forecasts of various locations.
Founded in 2013, ACE Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Geneva, Switzerland. The firm prefers to invest in early-stage climate tech, deep tech, fintech, and artificial intelligence sectors.

Provider of a management and information technology consulting services. The company's services include strategic planning, program management, infrastructure operations, infrastructure relocation, network engineering and architecture, information assurance and software development.

ACI Worldwide develops, markets, and installs a portfolio of software products focused on facilitating electronic payments. The firm also leverages its distribution network in America, Europe, the Middle East, and Africa, or EMEA, and the Asia-Pacific regions to sell software developed by third parties. ACI software products process payment transactions for retail banking clients, billers such as utilities and healthcare providers, and community banks and credit unions. ACI's customers are financial institutions all over the world, but the majority of the revenue is generated in the United States and EMEA regions.

ACME Communications engaged in owning and operating broadcast television stations. The company was founded in 1997 and was headquartered in Irvine, California. It acquired companies that aired morning news programs and operated television stations.

Acme Packet was a provider of session delivery network solutions that enabled the delivery of interactive communications, such as voice, video and multimedia sessions. It also made session border controllers, session aware load balancers, session routing proxies and multiservice security gateways among others. The company was founded in 2000 and was headquartered in Bedford, Massachusetts. It acquired other companies that made products for the voip industry and developed communications software.

Acorda Therapeutics Inc is a biopharmaceutical company focused on developing therapies that restore function and improve the lives of people with neurological disorders. Acorda uses scientific, clinical, and commercial expertise in neurology as strategic points of access in additional nervous system markets, including stroke, Parkinson's disease, and epilepsy. The company does not operate separate lines of business with respect to any of its products or product candidates. All of its net product revenue is derived from the United States.
Founded in 2000 Acorn Capital Partners is a private equity investment firm based in Buxton, United Kingdom. The firm seeks to invest in the B2B and technology sectors.
Founded in 1994, Act Venture Capital is a venture capital firm based in Dublin, Ireland. The firm seeks to invest in the technology sector.

Founded in 2002, Acta Wireless is a venture capital investment firm based in Washington DC, District of Columbia. The firm specializes in providing seed-stage funding to wireless and telecom companies.

Founded in 2002, Active Venture Partners is a venture capital firm based in Barcelona, Spain. The firm prefers to invest in enterprise software and services, consumer products, the internet, media, communication, security, and clean technology sectors.

The Company is a provider of digital identity assurance solutions for the enterprise, government, healthcare and financial services markets worldwide for employer-to-employee, business-to-consumer and government-to-citizen solutions.

Founded in 1999, Acton Capital is a venture capital investment firm based in Munich, Germany. The firm focuses on tech-enabled business models and companies operating in B2B marketplaces, finance, legal, virtual healthcare, or direct-to-consumer based in Europe and North America.

Provider of multi-vertical,cloud-based software products. The company offered SaaS-based enterprise platforms for the following verticals: government communications, wealth management, compliance, and insurance.

Actuate was a reporting, analytic and customer communications software company. The company was engaged in the design and development of software for business intelligence, performance management and reporting applications. The company provided analytical software that were used to analyze business data and distribute report content through the company network and the internet. Their primary commercial offerings included BIRT Designer™, BIRT iHub™, BIRT Analytics™ and the Actuate Customer Communications Suite™. Founded in 1993, the company was acquired by the OpenText Corporation. The company sought to acquire businesses through mergers, acquisitions and investments which would have helped the firm to expand and consolidate its presence in the analytic and customer communications software sectors.

Actuate Partners provided private equity funding and consulting to technology sector, focusing on cloud computing, big data and analytics, SaaS business models, social media and mobility along with services sectors such as retail, restaurants and hospitality providers. The firm made investments in everything from seed capital to large buyouts. The firm was founded in 2011 and was based in Atlanta, Georgia. The firm ceased operations in February of 2016.

Founded in 2000, Ad-Venture Capital Management is a venture capital firm based in Denver, Colorado. The firm seeks to invest in B2C, energy, healthcare, information technology, SaaS, gaming, clean technology, real estate technology, infrastructure, and oil sectors.

Mr. Adam Bain serves as a Board Member at Opendoor Technologies. He is the Investor & serves as a Board Member at Navan. He also serves as an advisory board at Hakluyt Capital,He was the Chief Operating Officer of Twitter from September 2015 until November 2016, and President, of Global Revenue & Partnerships from 2010 to 2015, where he was responsible for the business lines at the public company, building one of the fastest revenue ramps past $2 billion in history. He is a Co-Founder and serves as Managing Partner at 01 Advisors. He served as Board Member at Autograph. He also serves as a Board Member at Opendoor. He served as an Advisor at Luma Partners. He serves as a Board Observer at Braid. He also served as Director at Social Capital Hedosophia Holdings Corp II. He oversaw 2,500 employees in 20 countries ranging from Product teams, Business Operations, Business Development, and Media Partnerships, Developer Relations, Twitter's International business, and all of the go-to-market Sales teams for the advertising and data businesses. Previously, he was the President of the Fox Audience Network at Newscorp, responsible for monetizing all of Fox's digital assets. He started his career running product and engineering teams at Fox Sports and the Los Angeles Times. He earned his BA in English Journalism from Miami University, in Ohio. He served as an Advisor at Mythical Games. He serves as Advisor at OpenEnvoy.

Mr. Adam Draper is a Co-Founder & serves as Managing Director at Boost VC. Mr. Draper serves as Advisor at 7shifts, Momentum Capital & Ava. He is an Angel Investor. He served as an Advisor at Alpha Investing. He was a Board Member of Make School. He co-founded and served as Director and Board Member at Ender's Fund. He is a member of the board for several firms including Makegameswith.us and Xpert Financial where he is also the Founder. He served as an advisor at Coinage. In 2009, the same year that he graduated from UCLA, he founded Xpert Financial, a secondary market for private securities. After settling millions of dollars in private security transactions and becoming a registered broker-dealer, he left Xpert Financial in late 2012 and began angel investing, where he backed such startups as Coinbase, Plangrid, and Amplitude. He then partnered up with Brayton Williams to change the face of global startup mentorship. He holds a Degree in English from the University of California, Los Angeles (UCLA) in 2009.

Mr. Adam Knight is a Co-Founder of Social and Sustainable Capital. Mr. Knight is an Angel Investor. He served as Chairman at Coinfloor. Mr. Knight serves as Chairman at BeZero Carbon, Fleximize and SASC Bridge Finance. Mr. Knight started his career at Goldman Sachs and progressed to be the Managing Director and Global Head of Base and Precious Metals. Mr. Knight moved to the Credit Suisse-Glencore Global Commodity Alliance in 2007 where he ran the business and was a Member of the Credit Suisse Global Fixed Income Operating Committee until January 2011. He was a Board Member and Advisor of Limejump.

Mr. Adam Pisoni is the Founder & serves as Executive Chairman at Abl. Mr. Pisoni formerly co-founded and served as CTO of the enterprise messaging company Yammer. He was a Mentor at Alchemist Accelerator. He oversees engineering and the development of all software at Yammer. Before Yammer, he served as Software Architect at Geni - the company in which Yammer was originally created. Prior to Geni, He was Director of Web Engineering at Shopzilla, playing a pivotal role in systems architecture and product development. He also co-founded and served as CTO of Cnation, a web development consultancy with clients including CBS MarketWatch, BizRate.com, Fox Interactive, Nissan of Japan, and Honda. Cnation's work for Honda earned them the 1997 Clio award for interactive design.

Mr. Adam Ross is an Angel Investor. He served as Chief Revenue Officer at WebPT. Mr. Ross served as Chief Revenue Officer at Procurement Partners. He served as Vice President of sales at ClearVoice. Mr. Ross was a Co-Founder and Chief Customer Officer at Ryver. Before Contatta, Adam was the SVP of Sales and Business Development at Infusionsoft, where he oversaw business development, and indirect and direct sales teams along with the customer success teams. He has also served as Channel Chief for NetSuite, National Sales Director for Sage Software's CRM division, and was one of the first members of the SalesLogix staff.

Mr. Adam Schwartz is the Founder and serves as Chief Executive Officer & Executive Chairman at Articulate. He also served as Advisor at TrueFort and Merida Capital Partners. He is a Board Member of New Frontier Data. He founded Articulate in 2002 with a vision to create innovative technologies that make it easier for the world to learn. Under his direction, Articulate has grown from a groundbreaking idea into an award-winning company that was recognized by Deloitte as one of the fastest-growing technology companies in North America. He is an active angel investor in more than 100 innovative tech companies and serves on the boards of Embedly, Videolicious, and others.

Mr. Adam Wiggins co-founded & served as Chief Executive Officer and Board Member at Muse. He served as Advisor at Clue. He serves as advisor at Theatre.js. He was an Advisor of Contentful. He also served as Advisor at Bloc. He also founded BioWink. He co-founded TrustCommerce. He was also the Co-founder of Heroku. He also served as Advisor at Chromatic.

Founded in 1994, Adams Capital Management is a venture capital firm based in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage applied technology companies. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

ADC Telecommunications was a provider of broadband communications network infrastructure products and services that enabled the profitable delivery of high-speed internet, data, video, and voice services to consumers and businesses worldwide. The company was headquartered in Eden Prairie, Minnesota. ADC Telecommunications aimed to grow the company strategically through merger & acquisitions, and investments. It primarily acquired companies that manufactured datacom equipment.

Add Partners was a venture capital firm based in London, United Kingdom. The firm used to invest in seed, start up, early and mid stage companies operating in the information technology and communication sectors.
Founded in 2020, Addition is a venture capital firm based in New York, New York. The firm invests in founder-led, technology-enabled companies. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).
Founded in 2008, AddVenture is a venture capital fund based in Limassol, Cyprus. The fund invested in the horizontal marketplaces, vertically integrated services, food tech, and health tech sectors.

Provider of vision-guided robotics systems and services. The company manufactures industrial robots, configurable linear modules, machine controllers for robot mechanisms and other flexible automation equipment, machine vision and applications software.

Adesto Technologies developer of conductive bridging RAM memory technology. The company develops ultralow-power, embedded, non-volatile memory technology for the medical and healthcare industry, non-volatile memory devices, serial flash memory products, standard serial flash products, legacy products and boot memory products. The company was founded in 2006 and is headquartered in Sunnyvale, California. It seeks to acquire other companies whose businesses can be integrated into its existing operations.

Founded in 2012, Adidas Ventures was a corporate venture capital investment arm of Adidas and was headquartered in Amsterdam, Netherlands. The firm sought to invest in seed-stage, early-stage, growth-stage, and later-stage companies.

ADIP was a Tel-Aviv, Israel based family investment fund focusing on venture capital and real estate investments. The firm focused on start-ups operating in the life sciences, cyber, cleantech, IT and enterprise software, semiconductors and communications sectors.
Founded in 2007, Aditya Birla Capital is a private equity firm based in Mumbai, India. The firm prefers to invest in insurance, financial services, and mutual fund sectors.

Aditya Birla Nuvo Limited was incorporated in 1956. The Company together with its subsidiaries was engaged in the financial services, telecom, fashion and lifestyle, IT-ITeS, and manufacturing businesses. Financial services business included life insurance, which was engaged in life insurance services; Other financial services included asset management, non-bank financial services, private equity, equity and commodity broking, wealth management and general insurance advisory; telecom business included telecommunication services; fashion & lifestyle business offered branded apparel and accessories, and IT-ITeS, which was engaged in business process outsourcing services and software services. Manufacturing included Agri-business, which is engaged in fertilizers, agrochemicals and seeds.

Adobe provides content creation, document management, and digital marketing and advertising software and services to creative professionals and marketers for creating, managing, delivering, measuring, optimizing,g and engaging with compelling content on multiple operating systems, devices, and media. The company operates with three segments: digital media content creation, digital experience for marketing solutions, and publishing for legacy products (less than 5% of revenue).

Adobe Marketo Engage is a provider of a marketing platform. The company offers the ability to create, manage, and execute personalized engagement at scale through email, web, mobile and more. The company was founded in 2006 and is headquartered in San Jose, California.

Founded in 1994, Adobe Ventures is the corporate venture capital arm of Adobe based in San Jose, California. The firm prefers to invest in software, creativity, digital experiences, and document productivity sectors.
Founded in 2014, Adopt A Startup is an accelerator based in Dublin, Ireland. It offers a program of 12 weeks of hands-on mentoring and access to exclusive lectures and workshops.

Mr. Adrian Aoun is an Angel Investor. Mr. Aoun founded & served as Chief Executive Officer at Forward. He serves as Advisor at BioAge Labs. He co-founded Sidewalk Labs. He also serves as the Special Projects Executive at Google. Previously, he founded and served as Chief Executive Officer at Wavii. He also served as an Advisor at AltSchool.

Adtalem Global Education Inc is an American for-profit education company that operates various university and educational programs. The company runs eight colleges and universities that specialize in business, medicine, education, and nursing degree programs. DeVry Education Group has over 90 campuses as well as online courses that offer associate, bachelor, and postgraduate degrees. Enrollment in its business colleges represents almost half of overall student enrollment, followed by technology and healthcare. The company derives the majority of its revenue from student enrollment fees using federal financial aid programs such as Pell Fund grants.

Founded in 1922, Advance Publications is a private equity investment firm based in New York, New York. The firm seeks to invest in media, entertainment, communications, technology, education, and other growth sectors.

Founded in 2015, Advance Venture Partners is a venture capital firm headquartered in San Francisco, California. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in technology with a focus on the software and consumer sectors.

Advanced Energy Industries provides precision power-conversion measurement and control solutions that transform power into various forms for use in manufacturing and industrial equipment and applications. The firm serves original equipment manufacturers and end customers in the semiconductor, flat panel display, solar panel and other industrial capital equipment markets. Products include thin-film power-conversion systems, which control and modify raw electrical power into a customizable, predictable power source and power control modules, which control and measure temperature during manufacturing cycles. A majority of the firm's revenue is generated in the United States, with the rest from Mexico, Taiwan, China and all others.

Advanced Equities was a venture capital investment bank specializing in late-stage private equity finance for the U.S. technology sector. The firm serves as a strategic co-investor with some of the world's leading venture capital firms with a goal of building and realizing maximum shareholder value. Advanced Equities bridges the gap between venture money and traditional corporate finance, providing investors with access to the technology sector's elusive late-stage investments.

Advanced Micro Devices designs a variety of digital semiconductors for markets such as PCs, gaming consoles, data centers, industrial, and automotive applications. AMD's traditional strength was in central processing units and graphics processing units used in PCs and data centers. Additionally, the firm supplies the chips found in prominent game consoles such as the Sony PlayStation and Microsoft Xbox. In 2022, the firm acquired field-programmable gate array leader Xilinx to diversify its business and augment its opportunities in key end markets such as data center and automotive.

Founded in 1980, Advanced Technology Development Center is an accelerator based in Atlanta, Georgia. The firm seeks to provide acceleration services to early-stage science and technology-based companies based in Georgia, United States.
Founded in 1979, Advanced Technology Ventures is a venture capital investment firm based in Boston, Massachusetts. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 2009, AdvancedStage Capital was a venture capital investment firm based in Naples, Florida. The firm preferred to invest in the publishing, software, environmental education, and printing sectors.

Founded in 2011, Advancit Capital is a venture capital firm based in Norwood, Massachusetts. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage companies operating in the media, entertainment, web3, and technology sectors.

Advent Venture Partners was a London, United Kingdom based venture capital firm and was founded in 1981. The firm focused on investing in early and mid-stage companies based in the United Kingdom, Europe and United States and operates within the information technology, healthcare, drug discovery & development, diagnostics, manufacturing, media, retail, manufacturing and mobile sectors.

Founded in 2016, Advisors.Fund is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm seeks to invest in the health and wellness, SaaS, enterprise software, artificial intelligence & machine learning, and digital health sectors.
Founded in 2013, Aeon Group is a growth equity investment firm based in Miami, Florida. The firm seeks to invest in the technology sector.

Aeroflex wass a provider of high technology solutions to the aerospace, defense, and broadband communication markets. The company operated in two segments, Aeroflex Microelectronic Solutions and Aeroflex Test Solutions. The Aeroflex Microelectronic Solutions segment manufactured specialty microelectronics products for satellite, aerospace, and defense applications and the Aeroflex Test Solutions segment provided specialized test and measurement systems, which are used by wireless service providers and equipment manufacturers to test wireless handsets and base station. The company used to acquire businesses that would help it to sustain and grow its market share in the different markets it served. The company was acquired by Cobham on May 2014.

Developer of stratospheric surveillance platforms designed to bridge the capability gap between aircraft and satellites. The company's product offerings include stratospheric platforms, radar and perception sensors, air surveillance systems and protective wear, enabling clients to avail statistical detection, tracking and classification, as well as multi-sensor correlation of data.

Aetna is a provider of managed healthcare and accessibility services in Hartford, Connecticut. The company offers customized healthcare plans for individuals, employers, healthcare providers and brokers. The firm was founded in 1852 and is based in Hartford, Connecticut.

Operator of a managed healthcare company in the United States. The company operates in three segments: health plan and medical services, specialized managed care, and workers' compensation. It offers a range of risk and fee-based managed care products and services to individuals, employer and government-funded groups, government agencies, and other insurance carriers and administrators.

Aetna Ventures is the corporate venture capital arm of Aetna based in Hartford, Connecticut. The firm prefers to invest in companies that focus on healthcare services, healthcare technology, and medical devices sectors.

Provider of a service management platform. The company provides an application enabled and cloud-based platform that helps IOT users to connect their devices via a centrally accessible network management software.
Affinity Capital Management was a venture capital firm based in Minneapolis, Minnesota. The firm was founded in 1993 and preferred to invest in companies operating in the healthcare sector.

Affymetrix is a provider of life science products and molecular diagnostic products that enable parallel analysis of biological systems at the gene, protein and cell level. The company sells its products to genomic research centers, academic institutions, government and private laboratories, as well as pharmaceutical, diagnostic and biotechnology companies. The company maintains sales and distribution operations across the United States, Europe, Latin America and Asia. It operates in two business segments: Affymetrix Core and eBioscience. Affymetrix Core focuses on the development, manufacture and commercialization of systems for genetic analysis in the life sciences, agricultural biotechnology (AgBio) and diagnostic industries. eBioscience primarily focuses on the development, manufacture, marketing and distribution of research products in the areas of flow cytometry, immunoassays, microscopic imaging and other protein-based analyses. The company seeks to strengthen it's presence in the market through mergers and acquisitions.

Ag Growth International manufactures portable and stationary grain handling, storage, and conditioning equipment, including augers, belt conveyors, grain storage bins, grain handling accessories, grain aeration equipment, and grain drying systems. The company operates mainly in Portable handling, permanent handling, storage and conditioning, livestock, and manufacturing sectors. It has two reportable segments farm and commercial. Some of its brands are Batco, Wheatheart, Westfield, Storm, Rem, Hi Roller, Union Iron, HSI, Tramco, PTM, VIS, and Nuvision. It has manufacturing facilities in Canada, the United States, Italy, Brazil, France, the United Kingdom, and India. Its geographical segments are Canada, the United States, and the International.

AGDATA is a provider of database marketing and information processing services to the agricultural, animal health and human health markets. The company offers point of sale and EDI data collection, database management, marketing program administration, web development, data collection and data analysis services. It also offers database management and transaction processing services that allow physician offices, hospitals and billing services to complete transactions quickly and accurately. It was founded in 1985 and is headquartered in Charlotte, North Carolina. The company seeks opportunities for growth and to expand through organic growth opportunities and strategic acquisitions.
Agilent Ventures was the venture capital arm of Agilent Technologies and was based in Santa Clara, California.

Agnostic Ventures is a venture capital firm based in New York, New York. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage companies operating in enterprise information technology, software as a service, digital consumer products, and digital bio and healthcare sectors.

Agrify is a developer of branded inventive solutions for the cannabis and hemp industries. Its Senorita brand offers consumers hemp-derived tetrahydrocannabinol (THC) beverages that mirror cocktails like a margarita, in three flavors - classic Lime Jalapeno Margarita, Mango Margarita, and Paloma. In addition to beverages, Agrify has also historically been a provider of inventive cultivation and extraction solutions for the cannabis industry. Its comprehensive extraction product line, which includes hydrocarbon, alcohol, solventless, post-processing, and lab equipment, empowers producers to maximize the quantity and quality of extract required for premium concentrates.

AGS is a designer and supplier of gaming products and services for the gaming industry. The company mainly supplies electronic gaming machines (EGM), server-based systems and back-office systems which casinos, and various gaming locations use. Its operating segments are EGM, table products, and Interactive. The EGM segment offers a selection of video slot titles developed for the global marketplace as well as EGM cabinets. Its table product segments include live proprietary table games, side bets, and ancillary table products. The Interactive segment delivers games through mobile apps such as Lucky Play Casino and Vegas Fever. It earns a majority of its revenue from the electronic gaming machines segment and geographically from the United States.

Founded in 2018, AI Venture Labs is an accelerator based in Dubai, United Arab Emirates. The firm focuses on pre-series A or post-seed stage ence startups operating in artificial intelligence, cognitive computing, machine learning, financial technology, the internet of things, cloud platforms, and blockchain sectors.

AIG Global Investment Group provided asset management services. The company also managed equity, fixed income, multi-manager hedge funds, private equity, and real estate investments of businesses. The company was founded in 1996 and was headquartered in New York. It was acquired by PineBridge Investments on September 5, 2009.

Aimia is a holding company with a focus on making long-term investments in public and private companies globally, through controlling or minority stakes. The company through its own operations and subsidiaries operates three reportable and operating segments, namely, Bozzetto, Cortland International and Holdings. The geographic segments are Europe, Asia & Oceania, Americas, Africa/Middle East.

Founded in 1902, Air Liquide is one of the leading industrial gas companies in the world, serving over 3.8 million customers in 78 countries. The company generated approximately EUR 27.6 billion of revenue in 2023, serving a wide range of industries, including chemicals, energy, healthcare, food and beverage and electronics. Air Liquide employs approximately 65,000 people.
Airbag Ventures is a venture capital investment firm based in Las Vegas, Nevada.

Airgain is engaged in providing antenna technologies. These technologies can be used to enable performance wireless networking across devices and markets which include connected homes, enterprises, automotive and the Internet of Things. It also provides solutions to complex radio frequency, engineering challenges and improving wireless service that requires higher throughput, broad coverage footprint and carrier-grade quality. Geographically, it derives maximum revenue from North America and also has a presence in China and the Rest of the World. The company products include antenna plus: fleet, M2M, iot antennas, carrier-class antenna, embedded antennas and external dipole antennas.

Founded in 2000, Aisling Capital is a venture capital firm based in New York, New York. The firm seeks to invest in healthcare and life science sectors based in the Canada Europe & American regions. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Mr. Ajay Agarwal serves as Partner at Bain Capital Ventures. He serves as Board Member at LightSource, Captora, Reprise, Clockwise, Clari, BUILD, Vention, and ShipBob. He served as a Board Member at Voiceops. Earlier, he served as Board Member at Gainsight and Inrix. He leads the Bay Area offices for Bain Capital Ventures, where he focuses on early-stage application software and SaaS investing. Prior to Bain Capital Ventures, he was an early employee at Trilogy, where the head of sales and marketing grew annual revenues to $300 million. He leads the Bay Area offices for Bain Capital Ventures, where he focuses on early-stage application software and SaaS investing. Prior to joining Bain Capital Ventures in 2003, he was head of sales and marketing at Trilogy, where he grew annual revenues to $300 million. Previously, he was a consultant with the Los Angeles office of McKinsey & Company. He has a BS in Electrical Engineering from Stanford University and an MBA from Harvard Business School. He also holds a patent for the "Method and Apparatus of Configuration Solutions." At Bain Capital Ventures, his passion is working with early-stage founders on team-building, culture, iteration of product-market fit, and scaling the early go-to-market operations. His primary investment themes include commerce enablement, the revolution of the sales and marketing functions, and the use of big data and machine learning to transform business applications. In 2012 and 2013, he was named to the Forbes Midas List of Top 100 Venture Capital Investors. Previously he served as Advisor at Symphony Commerce. He serves as Board Member at AutoLeap.

Akamai operates a content delivery network, or CDN, which entails locating servers at the edges of networks so its customers, which store content on Akamai servers, can reach their own customers faster, more securely and with better quality. Akamai has over 325,000 servers distributed over 4,100 points of presence in more than 1,000 cities worldwide. The firm also offers security and cloud computing for its customers and those businesses have grown to be bigger than the legacy CDN.
Akatsuki is engaged in smartphone service and social network application development. It offers mobile social game services.
Founded in 2020, Akilia Partners is a venture capital firm based in Madrid, Spain. The firm seeks to invest in the healthcare and financial technology sectors.

AKS Capital was a venture capital firm which specializes in seed and early-stage venture funding for high growth companies. The firm preferred to invest in the experienced management teams and startups.

Mr. Akshay Kothari is an Investor & serves as Advisor at Scoutible. He is an Angel Investor. He served as Legal Associate at Duane Morris. Akshay practices in the area of corporate law. He has experience with contracts, employment and insurance law.

Netherlands-based AkzoNobel is the world's third-largest paint and coatings producer. Europe is the largest market, with around 46% of sales generated in the Europe, Middle East and Africa, or EMEA, region. Cumulatively, the Asia-Pacific and Latin American divisions have also grown quickly to more than 40% of sales. Construction-related end markets are the most important, but meaningful revenue is also generated from the industrial, consumer goods and transportation markets.

Provider of security solutions that reduce software theft, authenticate network users, and protect against spam and viruses. The company operates in two segments: Software Digital Rights Management (DRM), which allows software publishers to manage licensing and distribution of software; and Enterprise Security, which develops and markets its patented USB-based eToken hardware solution for authentication and digital identity management.

Founded in 1999, Alafi Capital Company was a venture capital firm based in Emeryville, California. The firm used to invest in seed-stage, early-stage, later-stage, and growth-stage companies operating in healthcare and life-sciences sectors based in the United States and Europe.

Mr. Alan Braverman serves as Chairman at Nightingale Security. Mr. Braverman co-founded & served as Co-Chief Executive Officer at Textline. He founded Sobo. He co-founded and served as Partner at The Giant Pixel. He co-founded and served as Chief Technology Officer at Xoom. He also serves on the boards of Geni and Eventbrite. He co-founded and served as Chief Technology Officer at Xoom. He earned a BS in Computer Science from the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. He is an entrepreneur and computer programmer currently serving as CEO and co-founder of Textline, a Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) text messaging platform specializing in customer service. Prior to Textline, Mr. Braverman was a co-founder of several internet software companies, including genealogy social network Geni (acquired by MyHeritage) and its spin-off enterprise social network, Yammer (acquired by Microsoft). Earlier, he co-founded Mollyguard Corporation, a payment-themed software studio that spun-off both Xoom (NASDAQ IPO 2013, acquired by PayPal in 2015) and Eventbrite (NYSE IPO 2018). Earlier in his career, Mr. Braverman programmed web software at Silicon Graphics, eGroups, and Yahoo!. He earned a B.S. in Computer Science from the University of Illinois.
Mr. Alan Schoenbaum serves as Advisor at TrueAbility. Mr. Schoenbaum served as General Counsel at Rev. He was a Co-Founder of BuildGroup. He is also the Board Member at Board Member.
Ms. Alana Goyal is the Founder and serves as Managing Partner at Base Case Capital. Ms. Goyal is an Angel Investor.

Alarm.com Holdings has two reportable segments, Alarm.com & other. The Alarm.com segment represents the cloud-based software platforms for intelligently connected property & related solutions. The other segment is focused on researching, developing & offering residential & commercial automation solutions & energy management products & services in adjacent markets. The majority of revenue is from the Alarm.com segment. The platform allows home & business owners to secure their properties and automate & control an array of connected devices. SaaS & license fees from service providers, who resell these services & pay Alarm.com a monthly subscription, are the sources of revenue for the firm. The majority of revenue is generated in the United States & Canada.
Founded in 1976, Alaska Permanent Fund (APF) is a sovereign wealth fund based in Juneau, Alaska. The firm focuses to invest in equities, fixed income, real estate, and private equity.

Albemarle is one of the world's largest lithium producers. In the lithium industry, the majority of demand comes from batteries, where lithium is used as the energy storage material, particularly in electric vehicles. Albemarle is a fully integrated lithium producer. Its upstream resources include salt brine deposits in Chile and the US and two hard rock mines in Australia, both of which are joint ventures. The company operates lithium refining plants in Chile, the US, Australia and China. Albemarle is a global leader in the production of bromine, used in flame retardants. It is also a major producer of oil refining catalysts.

Dr. Albert Wenger serves as Partner at Union Square Ventures. Dr. Wenger is an Angel Investor. Dr. Wenger serves as Board Member at Shapeways Holdings, Clarifai, Simscale, Human Dx Rise Together and Dwolla. He serves as a Board Member at Wattpad, Foursquare, Shapeways and Shippo. He serves as a Board Member at Viam. He served as a Board Member at Zanskar. He also serves as a Board Member at Shippo, Blockstack, Code Climate, Skillshare and Top Hat. He also serves as a Board Member at Clue. He served as a Board Member at Otis Wealth, Clarifai, Dwolla, The Human Diagnosis Project, and goTenna. He serves as Board Observer at Sift. He is also an Advisor at ChangeX and Remora. As an entrepreneur, he has founded or co-founded five companies, including a management consulting firm (in Germany), a hosted data analytics company, a technology subsidiary for Telebanc (now E*Tradebank), and most recently, DailyLit. Previously, he also served as the President of del.icio.us. He graduated summa cum laude from Harvard College in economics and Computer Science and holds a Ph.D. in Information Technology from MIT.

Alberto Culver was a manufacturer of beauty care, skin care and household products. The company developed, manufactured, distributed and markets beauty care products, hair care products, face care products, hand care products, body lotions and body washes. It was a manufacturer in the multicultural beauty care market with such brands as Soft & Beautiful, Just For Me, Motions and TCB. The company focused on its expansion of product lines through mergers and acquisitions.

Founded in 1996, Albion Capital is a venture capital investment firm headquartered in London, United Kingdom. The firm seeks to invest in the health tech, digital risk, fintech, artificial intelligence, and data stack sectors in the United Kingdom.

Founded in 1996, AlbionVC is a venture capital firm based in London, United Kingdom. The firm seeks to invest in seed-stage, early-stage, and later-stage companies. The firm seeks to invest in artificial intelligence, climate tech, deep tech, digital risk, fintech, health tech, and life science sectors.

Founded in 2014, Album VC is a venture capital investment firm based in Lehi, Utah. The firm prefers to invest in the software, healthcare services, SaaS, life sciences, and oncology sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Alcan Packaging was a manufacturer of plastic products. The company produced flexible packaging and folding carton packaging and many more products. It was founded in 2009 and is headquartered in Illinois, Naperville. The company was acquired by Amcor.

Alcatel-Lucent was a networking company that provided fixed, mobile and converged broadband networking, internet protocol (IP) and optics technologies, applications and services to end-users. The firm offered its services to strategic industries such as defense, energy, healthcare, transportation and governments worldwide. It was founded in 1872 and was headquartered in Paris, France. Alcatel-Lucent followed an acquisition strategy to strengthen its capabilities and increase revenue and earnings growth. It was actively seeking to acquire fast-growing companies, mainly those that are operating in the enterprise networks management, business communications, microelectronics, data networking segments. The company was acquired by Nokia on January 4, 2016.

Alcon is one of the leading vision care companies in the world. Following nine years as a Novartis subsidiary, it was spun off as a public company in April 2019. Alcon operates in two segments: Vision Care and Surgical. Visioncare comprises contact lenses, lenscare solutions, and a suite of ocular health products. With brands like Dailies, Total1, and Air Optix, Alcon controls about one-fourth of the US contact lens market. Surgical comprises intraocular lenses, ophthalmic surgical equipment, and consumables used during surgeries. Its main products include Centurion, a phacoemulsification device used during cataract surgeries, and a portfolio of IOLs, including PanOptix and Vivity. Alcon has one of the largest installed bases of eye surgical equipment in the world.

Founded in 2014, Aldrich Capital Partners is a private equity firm headquartered in McLean, Virginia. The firm seeks to invest in the fintech, healthcare information technology, software and tech-enabled service sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Abbott (Healthcare) was a manufacturer of consumer and professional medical diagnostic products designed for detection of diseases and conditions within its areas of focus. The company's medical diagnostic products produced a range of vitamins and nutritional supplements for cardiology, women's health, oncology, infectious disease and drugs of abuse enabling patients and their healthcare providers to work together to manage patients' conditions over the continuum of care, from the hospital to home.

Distributor of various types of building products. The company offers concrete products which include construction chemicals, decorative concrete and associated equipment, specialized construction chemicals and heavy duty industrial tires.

Mr. Alex Duff serves as Managing Partner at Fortius Ventures. Mr. Duff is an Angel Investor. He served as a Principal at Alexander Advisors. Previously he served as Executive Vice President of PIX System and Chief Financial Officer of Tenzing Communications.

Alex is the Head of Business Development at Behance (Adobe), the leading online platform for creatives to showcase and discover creative work. As a founding member of Behance, Alex served as Vice President until Adobe acquired Behance in 2012.Under Alex's leadership, Behance powers the online galleries for the AIGA, Wacom, Linkedln, Pantone, Cooper-Hewitt/Smithsonian Museum, RISD, and AdWeek - among others. Prior to joining Behance, Alex held business and creative roles at Coach Inc. and 24 Seven Inc.
Mr. Alex Ok is an Angel Investor.

Mr. Alex Stamos serves as Chief Information Security Officer at SentinelOne. He serves as an Advisor & Venture Partner at Felicis. Before joining Stanford, he served as the Chief Security Officer at Facebook. He is a cybersecurity expert, business leader, and entrepreneur working to improve the security and safety of the Internet through his teaching and research at Stanford University. He is an Adjunct Professor at Stanford's Freeman-Spogli Institute and a visiting scholar at the Hoover Institution. Prior to joining Stanford, he served as the Chief Security Officer of Facebook. In this role, he led a team of engineers, researchers, investigators, and analysts charged with understanding and mitigating information security risks to the company and safety risks to the 2.5 billion people on Facebook, Instagram, and WhatsApp. During his time at Facebook, he led the company's investigation into manipulation of the 2016 US election and helped pioneer several successful protections against these new classes of abuse. As a senior executive, he represented Facebook and Silicon Valley to regulators, lawmakers, and civil society on six continents, and has served as a bridge between the interests of the Internet policy community and the complicated reality of platforms operating at a billion-user scale. Before joining Facebook, he was the Chief Information Security Officer at Yahoo, rebuilding a storied security team while dealing with multiple assaults by nation-state actors. While at Yahoo, he led the company's response to the Snowden disclosures by implementing massive cryptographic improvements in his first months. In 2004, he co-founded iSEC Partners, an elite security consultancy known for groundbreaking work in secure software development, and embedded and mobile security. Throughout his career, he has worked toward making security a more representative field and has highlighted the work of diverse technologists as an organizer of the Trustworthy Technology Conference and OURSA. He has been involved with securing the US election system as a contributor to Harvard's Defending Digital Democracy Project and involved in the academic community as an advisor to Stanford's Cybersecurity Policy Program and UC Berkeley's Center for Long-Term Cybersecurity. He is a member of the Aspen Institute's Cyber Security Task Force, the Bay Area CSO Council, and the Council on Foreign Relations. He also serves on the advisory board of NATO's Collective Cybersecurity Center of Excellence in Tallinn, Estonia. He worked under Prof. David Patterson while earning a BS in Electrical Engineering and Computer Science at UC Berkeley.

Founded in 1996, Alexandria Venture Investments is a venture capital firm headquartered in Pasadena, California. The firm seeks to invest in B2C, healthcare, information technology, health technology, agriculture technology, digital health, climate technology & food technology sectors. The firm is a subsidiary of Alexandria Real Estate Equities.

Mr. Alexis Ohanian is the Founder & serves as General Partner at Seven Seven Six. Mr. Ohanian is an Investor of 2 Punks Capital. He served as an Advisor at Summon (Automotive). He serves as Board Member at AdQuick, Ro, Visual.ly, Atoms and ApeCoin. He served as Board Member at Hotshot. He is an Angel Investor. He is a Co-Founder and Serves as Board Member at Angel City FC. He is the Founder of Das Kapital Capital. In 2020, he founded Seven Seven Six, an early-stage venture capital firm. He also serves as Advisor and Limited Partner at Ingressive Capital. At heart, the firm is a technology company that deploys venture capital. Two years later, he launched his family foundation 776.org to combat inequity worldwide through entrepreneurship and announced a $20M commitment to climate action through his new 776 Climate Fellowship. He also wrote a national bestselling book, Without Their Permission, for which he embarked on a 5-month bus tour speaking at 82 universities across America about innovation. He was a partner at Y Combinator and a co-founder of Initialized Capital. Before that, in 2005, he co-founded Reddit. He departed in 2010, only to return as executive chairman in 2014 to help lead the turnaround of what is now one of the largest websites in the U.S. and listed on the NYSE as $RDDT.

Developer of a blockchain-based transactions platform designed to address blockchain's scaling challenges. The company's open-source platform addresses blockchain scalability problems through a permissionless, rapid and efficient user consensus along with permitting small transactions regardless of transaction volume, enabling users to make blockchain transactions within seconds at low transaction costs.

Manufacturer of food service equipment built for commercial food cooking, preparation and processing. The company offers a range of products including cooking, bakery, meal delivery and preparation, refrigeration, washing and waste management, ice cream and beverage dispensing equipment, ice makers and coffee machines and other products to its clients.

Mr. Ali Partovi serves as Chief Executive Officer at Neo (Consulting Services (B2B)). Mr. Partovi is an Angel Investor. He is a Co-Founder & serves as Chief Executive Officer at Code.org. He is also the Founder and Manager of Neo Fund. He served as an Advisor at SignalFire and Remora. He was a co-founder of LinkExchange and iLike, and an investor or advisor to numerous startups including Dropbox, Indiegogo, and Zappos. He helped launch Code.org and the Hour of Code campaign and continues to provide strategic advice to the team. He is also an Angel Investor. He served as an Advisor at Dropbox.

Alibaba is the world's largest online and mobile commerce company as measured by gross merchandise volume. It operates China's online marketplaces, including Taobao (consumer-to-consumer) and Tmall (business-to-consumer). The China commerce retail division is the company's most valuable cash flow-generating business. Additional revenue sources include China commerce wholesale, international commerce retail/wholesale, local consumer services, cloud computing, digital media and entertainment platforms, Cainiao logistics services, and innovation initiatives/other.
Founded in 2011, Aligned Partners is a venture capital firm based in Los Altos, California. The firm invests in early-stage information technology companies.

Manufacturer of semiconductors, memory and non-memory products. The company provides analog and mixed signal products, high-performance memory products and connectivity and networking technologies for the communications, computing, embedded, industrial and consumer markets.

Alkermes is a fully integrated biotechnology company that applies its proprietary technologies to research, develop, and commercialize pharmaceutical products designed for unmet medical needs in therapeutic areas. The company utilizes several to develop and commercialize products and, in so doing, access technological, financial, marketing, manufacturing, and other resources. Alkermes either purchases active drug products from third parties or receives them from its third-party licensees to formulate products using its technologies. It operates in the U.S., which derives maximum revenue, from Ireland and the rest of the world.

Provider of sales lead generation services to insurance companies. The company provides leads that connect financial and insurance agents to consumers who are actively shopping for financial and insurance products.

Allegion is a global security products company with a portfolio of leading brands such as Schlage, Von Duprin and LCN. The Ireland-domiciled company was created via a spinoff transaction from Ingersoll-Rand in December 2013. In fiscal 2022, Allegion generated 73% of sales in the United States. The company mainly competes with Sweden-based Assa Abloy and Switzerland-based Dormakaba.

Allegro Microsystems is a designer, developer, fabless manufacturer, and marketer of sensor ICs and application-specific analog power ICs for automotive and industrial markets. Its Sensor IC allows customers to precisely measure motion, speed, position, and current, and power ICs include high-temperature and high-voltage capable motor drivers, power management, and LED driver ICs. Its products are divided into three categories such as SENSE which includes current sensors, switches and latches, and interface ICs among others; REGULATE which includes regulators, clearpower modules, and LED drivers; and DRIVE which includes BLDC Drivers, brush DC, and others. Key revenue for the company is generated from Greater China and the rest from the United States, Japan, Europe, and other regions.
Founded in 1924, Allen & Company was an investment bank based in New York, New York.

Allergan was one of the largest specialty pharmaceutical manufacturers of eye care, neurosciences, medical dermatology, medical aesthetics, breast enhancement, obesity intervention and urologic. The firm was founded in 1983 and was based in Dublin, Ireland.

Manufacturer and provider of livestock identification equipment. The company offers visual tags, tissue sampling products, electronic tags, syringes, applicators, antennas, and other related products, that use visual, electronic and radio frequency identification technology to provide important livestock information quickly, enabling livestock owners to better manage their animals.

Founded in 1997, Alliance of Angels is an angel group based in Seattle, Washington. The firm seeks to invest in seed to early-stage companies operating in the software-as-a-service, artificial intelligence, life sciences, technology, hardware, consumer, manufacturing, retail, and food industries across the United States and Canada.

Allient, formerly Allied Motion Technologies designs, manufactures, and sells precision and specialty motion control components and systems. The firm primarily caters to the vehicle, medical, aerospace and defense, and electronics and industrial, pumps, and robotics sectors. It mainly operates and sells across the United States, Canada, South America, Europe, and Asia. Its products and solutions include nano precision positioning systems, servo control systems, motion controllers, digital servo amplifiers and drives, brushless servo, torque, and coreless motors, brush motors, integrated motor drives, gear motors, gearing, incremental and absolute optical encoders, active (electronic) and passive (magnetic) filters for power quality and harmonic issues.

Alliqua is a provider of advanced wound care solutions. The company is developing an advanced wound care solutions that will enable surgeons, clinicians and wound care practitioners to address the entire spectrum of challenges presented by chronic and advanced wounds.
Provider of information service on global cinema and entertainment. The company offers a phone-based and online cinema guide in France, Russia, Brazil, Germany and Turkey.

Allot is a provider of network intelligence and security solutions for service providers and enterprises. The company's solutions are deployed globally for network and application analytics, traffic control and shaping, and network-based security services. The firm's multi-service platforms are deployed by mobile, fixed, and cloud service providers and enterprises. It has a customer base in Europe, Asia and Oceania, the Americas, the Middle East, and Africa.

Founded in 1996, Alloy Ventures was a venture capital firm based in Palo Alto, California. The firm preferred to invest in information technology, healthcare, software-as-a-service, manufacturing, life sciences, mobile, technology, media, telecommunications, and cleanTech sectors in the United States.
Founded in 2008, Almaz Capital is a venture capital firm based in Portola Valley, California. The firm seeks to invest in technology sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 1984, Alpha Capital Partners is a private equity firm based in Chicago, Illinois. The firm seeks to invest in the manufacturing, distribution, consumer products, retail, and restaurant chain sectors.

Founded in 2008, AlphaLab is an accelerator based in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. The firm seeks to invest seed capital and mentorship to early-stage technology companies operating in the software, web services, gaming, mobile, and consumer internet sectors.

Founded in 2001, Alpine Investors is a private equity firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm specializes in buyouts, add-ons, carveouts, recapitalization, and growth capital. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the media, software, healthcare, business services, consumer services, and consulting services sectors based in the United States, Canada, Europe, and Australia. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 1987, Alpine Meridian is a venture capital investment firm based in New York, New York. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage companies in the internet, data, software, digital media, financial services, and e-commerce sectors.

Founded in 2006, Alsop Louie Partners is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm seeks to invest in media, gaming, technology, cloud infrastructure, analytics, consumer tech, cyber security, disruptive tech, and mobile sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).
Founded in 2011, Alt-Capital is an angel group investment fund based in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. The firm prefers to invest in early stage companies in Pittsburgh.
Founded in 2018, Alta Global Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Lehi, Utah. The firm prefers to invest in venture-stage and growth-stage companies.

Founded in 2005, Altair Capital is a venture capital investment firm based in San Francisco, California. Dr. Benjamin Ling is the Founder and serves as General Partner at Bling Capital. Dr. Ling serves as an Advisor at Chowbus. He serves as an Advisor at Ignition. There, he led investments in Wattpad, Tapingo, Gitlab, True Accord, and Webflow, among many others. Previously, Ben served in senior operating roles at Google, YouTube, and Facebook. He also is an active angel investor with early stakes in Airtable, Lyft, Square, Palantir, Quora, Gusto, Udemy, and others. While at Google, he served as Senior Director of Search and Local Business Products, which included overseeing Google Images, Videos, Books, News, and Finance. At YouTube, Ben was Senior Director of Partnerships and Platforms, where he was responsible for music, movies, sports, and news, as well as mobile, television, and API partnerships. In his first role at Google, he was the founder and general manager of Google's commerce group, which includes Google Wallet and Google Shopping. At Facebook, Ben was the first director of the Facebook platform and oversaw the development of the company's developer ecosystem. He also led product, marketing, developer operations, and partner solutions. Ben played a crucial role in developing Facebook Connect, which helped grow Facebook across the web. Ben holds a B.S. in Electrical Engineering & Computer Science (EECS) from UC Berkeley and a M.S. and PhD in Computer Science from Stanford University. Ben is a Department of Defense fellow and a recipient of UC Berkeley's Bechtel Achievement Award, given to the top graduating senior from the College of Engineering.

Mr. Benjamin White is a Co-Founder and serves as Chairman at Upp.ai Mr. White co-founded and served as Board Member at Star Technology Services. He serves as an Advisor at Catalyst Investors. He serves as a Board Member at Loop Email. He also is an Angel Investor. He serves as a Partner at Notion Capital. He is one of the best-known technology entrepreneurs in the UK having co-founded three businesses helping to grow them all into market leaders each with revenues in excess of $100M. In 1993, he co-founded RBR Networks, an IT distributor that specialized in Cisco. By 1998 RBR had become Cisco's largest distributor in Europe, with revenues in excess of $160M, and towards the end of that year was acquired by Datatec. At the same time, he co-founded Star Internet in 1995 as one of the UK's first ISPs. He served as Star's CEO from 1995 to 2000 and from 2006 to 2008, establishing the company as one of the UK's largest ISPs. He led a management buy-out of the company in 2007. In 2012 Star was sold to Claranet for £55M. In 2000, he co-founded MessageLabs to scale up the anti-virus technology developed within Star. He served as the CEO of MessageLabs until 2006. In 2008 MessageLabs was acquired by Symantec for approximately $700M. Upon completion of the acquisition he stepped down from the MessageLabs board to devote his time to Notion Capital, a SaaS-focused venture fund where together with his general fund responsibilities, he focused on strategy, product, and technology within portfolio companies. He studied at Stowe School in 1987.
