The company operates through a direct business that makes sales from the company's own inventory and a partner business that sells merchandise from manufacturers, distributors and other suppliers through the company's websites. The company generates the majority of its total revenue from partner businesses in terms of business format and from the U.S. in terms of market.

Founded in 2005, Bezos Expeditions is a family office based in Mercer Island, Washington. The firm makes venture capital investments. The firm prefers to invest in the software, financial services, and online retail sectors.

BGC Group is a brokerage and financial technology company that serves the global financial markets, energy and commodities markets. Its service and product offerings include brokerage for a wide range of financial products including fixed income, equities, commodities, derivatives, and real estate, software solutions for trading platforms, clearing, trade execution, and other back-office services. Its clients mostly include banks, financial institutions and corporate clients. BGC operates in one reportable segment, which is providing brokerage services. Geographically the company generates revenue from Asia, Other Europe/MEA, France, and other Americas with the majority of its revenue coming from the United Kingdom followed by the United States.

Founded in 2011, BGF is a private equity investment firm based in London, United Kingdom. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in advanced tech, artificial intelligence & data, technology, climate & sustainability, healthcare, life sciences, retail & e-commerce, media, infrastructure, construction & property, business services, automotive & aerospace, specialist manufacturing, food & drink, education, energy & resources, waste management, leisure & hospitality sectors.

Provider of offender management and rehabilitation solutions for community correctional agencies and government customers. The company offers GPS, radio frequency, and remote alcohol compliance monitoring, and equipment-free monitoring and reporting products. It also offers solutions for jail overcrowding, budget constraints, multiple DW/DUI offenders, probation problems, parole issues, increased recidivism, and prisoner reentry. In addition, its services include monitoring and community-based treatment services, reentry programs to adult and juvenile offenders on parole, probation, or pretrial release, and supervision services from a national monitoring center and community correctional service centers.

BIA Digital Partners is a Chantilly, Virginia based investment firm with a mezzanine focus. The firm seeks to make both debt and equity investments in middle market companies operating in the media, entertainment, telecommunications, information and business services industries.

Founded in 1997, Big Basin Partners is a venture capital investment firm based in Sammamish, Washington. The firm prefers to invest in computer hardware, cybersecurity, the Internet of Things, semiconductors, internet software services, application software, medical devices, healthcare, alternative energy, and education sectors.

BigBear.ai Holdings is a technology-led solutions organization, that provides software and services to its customers. Its AI-powered decision intelligence solutions are leveraged in three markets; supply chains & logistics, autonomous systems, and cybersecurity. It operates in two segments; the cyber & engineering segment and the analytics segment.

BigCommerce Holdings is engaged in offering a Software-as-a-service (SaaS) e-commerce platform. The company's SaaS platform engages in the creation of online stores by delivering a combination of ease-of-use, enterprise functionality, and flexibility. It powers both the customers' branded e-commerce stores and their cross-channel connections to popular online marketplaces, social networks, and offline point-of-sale systems. The group operates in a single segment covering geographical areas of Americas-U.S., Americas-other, EMEA, and APAC, of which the majority of revenue is generated from Americas-U.S.

Founded in 2012, Bild Alternative Investments is a venture capital firm based in Toronto, Ontario. The firm seeks to invest in the food, waste management, composting, smart mobility, transport, accessibility, e-commerce, data analytics, system learning applications, clean energy, storage, sustainable manufacturing, and product design sector.
Bill Bryant and Associates is a Vero Beach, FL based private company whose line of business is Nonresidential construction

Mr. Bill Lee is an Angel Investor. Mr. Lee co-founded and served as Chief Executive Officer at Remarq. He graduated Beta Gamma Sigma from UC Berkeley with a B.S. in accounting/finance and received a JD/MBA from UCLA.

Mr. Bill Trenchard serves as a Partner at First Round Capital. He served as a Board member at Airbase. He serves as Advisor at Remora. He is also an Angel Investor. He served as an advisory at Naborly. He served as Board Member at Edify and EvolutionIQ. He served as Advisor at Evergrow (Environmental Services (B2B)). He collaborates with founders who look to solve big problems in the world, with investments including Uber, Looker, Flexport, Verkada, Sift, Superhuman, Legion, Airbase, Crossbeam, Pine Park Health, Ossium, Promise, Labelbox, Last Energy, Sprig, Maven, Cocoon, Remora and many others. His Angel Investments include: Ginkgo Bioworks, Finch Therapeutics, Moat, MileIQ, NextRoll, Step, Honor, Everlane, Newfront Insurance, Topsy, LendingClub, Gyft, IronPort, Powerset, Xoopit, Tapulous, Slide, Chegg. Prior to becoming an angel and full-time seed investor he was co-founder and CEO of LiveOps and Jump Networks (acquired by Microsoft). He serves as Board Member at Ossium Health.

Developer of cloud-based AR platform offering order-to-cash solutions intended to digitally transform accounts receivable and B2B payments processes. The company's order-to-cash cycle encompasses the entire process from receiving an order for goods or services to receiving payment for those goods or services, thereby helping clients streamline and accelerate this cycle leading to faster payment processing and improved cash flow for businesses.

BIO-key International is a fingerprint biometric technology company. It develops and markets advanced fingerprint biometric identification and identity verification technologies, as well as related identity management and credentialing hardware and software solutions. Its product portfolio comprises SideSwipe, SidePass, EcoID, WEB-key and others. The company generates its revenue in the form of services, license fees and others.

Based in Minnesota, Bio-Techne is a life sciences manufacturer supplying consumables and instruments for the pharma, biotech, academic and diagnostic markets. It reports in two segments, protein sciences (75% of revenue) and diagnostics and genomics (25%). The protein sciences segment sells reagents and analytical instruments used in life sciences research, including antibodies used in protein analysis. The diagnostics and genomics segment sells diagnostic reagents, molecular diagnostics and spatial biology products. The United States accounts for about 55% of revenue. The firm also has operations in Europe, the Middle East and Africa (20% of sales), the UK (5%) and Asia-Pacific (15%), with the rest of the world accounting for the remaining 5%.
Founded in 2012, Biobrit is a venture capital firm based in La Jolla, California. The firm seeks to invest in the life sciences sector.

BioClinica is a provider of clinical-trial management services. The company is divided into three business segments to deliver focused service supporting multifaceted technologies. The Medical Imaging and Biomarkers segment provides medical imaging and cardiac safety services and includes a molecular marker laboratory. The eHealth Solutions segment comprises an e-clinical technology platform and professional services along with safety and regulatory solutions. Under the Global Clinical Research segment, Bioclinica offers a network of research sites, patient recruitment-retention services, and a post-approval research division. It was founded in 1990 and is headquartered in Doylestown, Pennsylvania. The company continues to grow by making periodic small acquisitions.

Founded in 2002, BioCrossroads is a venture capital investment firm based in Indianapolis, Indiana. The firm prefers to invest in the biotechnology, pharmaceutical, medical device, diagnostic, ag-tech, biotech, and health information technology sectors.

Biogen and Idec merged in 2003, combining forces to market Biogen's multiple sclerosis drug Avonex and Idec's cancer drug Rituxan. Today, Rituxan and next-generation antibody Gazyva (oncology) and Ocrevus (multiple sclerosis) are marketed via a collaboration with Roche. Biogen markets several multiple sclerosis drugs including Plegridy, Tysabri, Tecfidera, and Vumerity. Biogen's newer products include Spinraza (SMA, with partner Ionis), Leqembi (Alzheimer's, with partner Eisai), Skyclarys (Friedreich's Ataxia, Reata), Zurzuvae (postpartum depression, Sage), and Qalsody (ALS, Ionis). Biogen has several drug candidates in phase 3 trials in neurology, immunology, and rare diseases.

BioLife Solutions is active in the healthcare segment. The company is engaged in developing, manufacturing, and marketing a portfolio of biopreservation tools and services for cells, tissues, and organs, including clinical grade cell and tissue hypothermic storage and cryopreservation freeze media and a related cloud, hosted biologistics cold chain management application for shippers. The company's product offerings include hypothermic storage and cryopreservation freeze media products for cells, tissues, and organs.

Operator of women's health company, involved in the early detection and treatment of breast cancer. The company manufactures and markets the MammoPad breast cushion, a radiolucent foam cushion that breast centers use to provide women with a mammogram.

Founded in 2013, Biomark Capital is a private equity firm based in Greenwich, Connecticut. The firm seeks to invest in early, mid, and late-stage life science and healthcare companies operating in the therapeutics and medical devices, molecular diagnostics, and information technology sectors across North America, along with a specific focus in Russia, Taiwan, India, and China. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

BioMed Ventures was a life science venture capital group and an investment arm of BioMed Realty. The firm used to invest in the biotechnology, medical and diagnostics sectors. It was established in 2010 and was based in San Diego, California.

Provider of centralized diagnostic services. The company's clinical trials services and medical devices offer centralized cardiac safety, medical imaging and respiratory services in drug development and also collect analyzes and distributes electronic patient-reported outcomes in multiple modalities across all phases of clinical research helping bio-pharmaceutical and healthcare organizations to manage clinical trials process.

Founded in 1963, BioMerieux designs develops, and manufactures a broad portfolio of in vitro diagnostics products for detecting disease-causing pathogens and contamination and is headquartered in Marcy-l'Etoile, France. The firm operates in four segments: molecular biology (39% of 2023 sales), microbiology (34%), immunoassays (11%) and industrial applications (about 16%). The Americas account for the largest portion of the firm's revenue (49%), followed by Europe, the Middle East and Africa (33%) and Asia-Pacific (18%)

Bionano Genomics is a life sciences instrumentation company in the genome analysis space. It is engaged in the development and marketing of the Saphyr system, a platform for ultra-sensitive and ultra-specific structural variation detection that enables researchers and clinicians to accelerate the search for new diagnostics and therapeutic targets and to streamline the study of changes in chromosomes.

Manufacturer of digital x-ray cameras intended to develop medical imaging technology focused on women's health. The company offers breast specimen radiography devices, x-ray cameras, radiographic X-rays, fluoroscopic X-rays and other related products, thereby proving quality products to its clients.

Founded in 2005, BioStar Capital is a Venture firm headquartered in Michigan, United States. The firm is a uniquely structured venture capital firm focused on transformative medical technologies. A nationally recognized leader in cardiology founded the firm, Dr. Louis A. Cannon, the firm's team composition includes renowned healthcare clinicians and executives, medical thought leaders, and financial professionals, differentiating us within the industry and mitigating risk through our holistic, disciplined investment process. Today, the firm encompasses five venture capital funds, with successful early- and late-stage investments focusing primarily on the fields of cardiology, orthopedics, and robotics. The firm's mission, to make a difference in patients' lives while providing returns for our investors, remains steadfast and is the foundation of everything we do.

BioTelemetry provides monitoring services and digital population health management for healthcare providers, medical device manufacturing and centralized core laboratory services for clinical research. It operates under healthcare, technology, and research segments. The Healthcare segment is focused on the diagnosis and monitoring of cardiac arrhythmias or heart rhythm disorders. The Research segment is engaged in central core laboratory services providing cardiac monitoring, imaging services, scientific consulting and data management services for drug and medical device trials and the Technology segment, focuses on the development, manufacturing, testing, and marketing of cardiovascular and blood glucose monitoring devices to medical companies, clinics and hospitals.

Bioton is a Poland-based company engaged in the principal business activity of manufacturing medicines and pharmaceutical preparations and the production of pharmaceutical substances. The products of the company include recombinant human insulin in pharmaceutical substance form and as preparations for injections; glimepiride, an oral hypoglycemic drug and metformin, an oral hypoglycemic drug. Its product line focuses on diet supplements, products for particular nutritional uses and cosmetics dedicated to patients with certain health problems. The group operates in Poland and internationally, of which the majority of the revenue is derived from Poland.

Biotronic NeuroNetwork was a provider of intraoperative neurophysiological monitoring in the world. The company provided reliable neurophysiologic monitoring services to hospitals across the country and eliminates the troublesome problem that surgeons and hospital staff encounter when trying to arrange for neural monitoring on short notice and often settling for improperly trained or inexperienced monitoring technologists and unsatisfactory service. Biotronic NeuroNetwork was comprised of NeuralWatch, Biotronic Great Lakes, Biotronic National, Biotronic Midwest, Biotronic Southeast, Biotronic West, NeuroMed and Calder Development Associates. The company continually sought opportunities for growth and to expand through organic growth opportunities and strategic acquisitions. The company was acquired by NuVasive (NASDAQ: NUVA) on July 5, 2016.

Bird Construction is a construction company operating from coast to coast and servicing all of Canada's major markets. The group provides a comprehensive range of construction services from new construction for industrial, commercial, institutional, and civil infrastructure markets, to industrial maintenance, repair and operations services, heavy civil construction, and mine support services. It also provides vertical infrastructure including, electrical, mechanical and speciality trades. In addition to its commitment to safety, Bird provides services that offer long-term value to its stakeholders.

Founded in 2001, Bison Capital Asset Management is a private equity firm headquartered in Santa Monica, California. The firm prefers to invest in lower middle-market companies seeking supportive capital to finance growth, acquisition opportunities, and recapitalizations. The firm seeks to invest in the business services, healthcare services, tech enabled services, distribution, and logistics sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Manufacturer of bitcoin mining hardware designed to offer cryptocurrency. Its hardware develops and sells bitcoin miners using ASIC chip technology, enabling users to get high quality and efficient computing chips, high density server equipment and large scale parallel computing software.

Founded in 2010, Black Ocean Group was a venture capital firm based in New York, New York. The firm preferred to invest in the enterprise technology, real estate, media, e-commerce, and social interaction sectors.

Blackbaud provides software solutions designed to serve the social good community, including nonprofits, foundations, corporations, educational institutions, healthcare institutions and individual change agents. Through M&A and organic product development efforts, the company has also moved into related areas outside of core fundraising, notably into K-12 schools. The firm enables more than $100 billion in donations annually across a customer base in excess of 40,000 customers in over 100 countries.

BlackBerry, once known for being the world's largest smartphone manufacturer, is now exclusively a software provider with a stated goal of end-to-end secure communication for enterprises. The firm provides endpoint management and protection to enterprises, specializing in regulated industries like government, as well as embedded software to the automotive, medical and industrial markets.

Blackboard is a provider of education technology services designed to offer a virtual learning environment and course management system. The company's education technology platform works on a web-based system which features course management, customizable open architecture and scalable design that allows integration with student information systems and authentication protocols.

BlackLine is engaged in providing financial accounting close solutions delivered as Software as a Service (SaaS). The Company's solutions enable its customers to address various aspects of their critical processes, including financial close & consolidation, intercompany accounting, and invoice-to-cash. The majority of the revenue of the company is earned in the United States.

Founded in 2016, BlackPines Capital Partners is a multi-family office based in Vancouver, Canada. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the technology sector. The firm is a private holding company that owns a portfolio of companies, manages direct investments, and provides strategic long-term advice to companies.

Founded in 2014, Blackstone Entrepreneurs Network Colorado is an accelerator/incubator based in Denver, Colorado. He firm Operator of a program that supports Colorado scale-up entrepreneurs by providing resources and connections to help them grow their businesses. BEN offers guidance and connections through a board of directors, network advisors, and targeted industries.

Blackstone Innovations Investments is a venture capital firm based in New York, New York. The firm seeks to invest in technology companies operating in the fintech, property technology, cybersecurity, and enterprise sectors.
Founded in 2016, Blacktop Capital is a venture capital firm based in Rocklin, California. The firm seeks to invest in the software sector.

Founded in 1998, Blenheim Chalcot is a venture builder based in London, United Kingdom. The firm prefers to build seed-stage, early-stage, and later-stage companies operating in edtech, fintech, financial services, education, software, sport, media, and technology sectors.

Founded in 2009, BLH Venture Partners is a venture capital firm based in Atlanta, Georgia. The firm prefers to invest in consumer internet, technology-enabled services, digital media, e-commerce, enterprise technology, and software sectors.

Blink Charging is an owner, operator, and provider of electric vehicle (EV) charging services. The company offers both residential and commercial EV charging equipment, enabling EV drivers to easily recharge at various location types. The company's business is the sale and distribution of electric vehicle charging equipment and its associated revenues earned from customers and/or property partners who use equipment connected to its network. It earns the majority of its revenue from the U.S.A.

Founded in 2009, Block provides payment services to merchants, along with related services. The company also launched Cash App, a person-to-person payment network. In 2022, Square's payment volume was a little over $200 million.
Founded in 2011, Bloodhound Partners is a family office firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm specializes in investing in technology companies.
Founded in 2021, Bloom Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Tel Aviv, Israel. The firm targets multifaceted, technology, and diversified investments.
Founded in 2013, Bloomberg Beta is a corporate venture capital arm of Bloomberg based in San Francisco, California. The firm seeks to invest in startups focusing on technology-related sectors.
Founded in 1999, BLS Venture Capital is a venture capital firm based in Berlin, Germany. The firm prefers to invest in companies operating in the technology sector.

Founded in 2007, Blue Lagoon Capital is a venture capital firm based in Sunrise, Florida. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the technology sector. The firm provides advisory services to entrepreneurs, technology venture CEOs, CTOs, and other C-level executives across sales, operations, and finance.
Blue Marlin Holdings is an investment holding company.

Investor Legal Name: Qingdao Blue Peninsula Investment Management Co. Limited

Description: Founded in 2000, Blue Point Capital Partners is a private equity firm based in Cleveland, Ohio. The firm prefers to invest in industrial, business services, consumer and value-added distribution sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Blue Ridge Capital is an Atlanta, Georgia based real estate investment firm targeting value-added properties in the Southeast. The company specializes in retail centers, but also considers other turn-around or opportunistic real estate investments, offering the potential for value enhancement.

Blue Water Capital was a venture capital firm based in McLean, Virginia and was founded in 1995. The firm preferred to invest in the information technology companies emphasizing enabling software, e-commerce, telecommunications, multimedia, content, services and integration technology sectors.

JDA Software Group is a computer software company that specializes in supply chain software, collaborative category management, merchandising, pricing and revenue management and supply chain management. The company was founded in 1985 and is headquartered in Arizona. It tends to acquire those companies which will let it expand its operations and drive growth. It also aims to make those acquisitions which will enable high-performance business process optimization.
Bluegrass Growth Fund Partners was a private equity firm which used to specialize in growth investments founded in 2010

Boston Community Capital is a nonprofit community development financial institution whose mission is to build communities where low-income people live and work. The firm operates a venture fund by the name of Boston Community Venture Fund which provides equity investments in businesses that create a double bottom-line of financial and social returns. In addition, the fund seeks to invest in companies that produce products that enhance the environment or reduce pollution.

Founded in 2014, BluePointe Ventures is the venture capital arm of BluePointe Capital Management and is based in San Mateo, California. The firm prefers to invest in artificial intelligence, augmented reality, virtual reality, big data, and cloud, software as a service sectors.

Blueprint Ventures was a venture capital firm specializing in seed, start up and early stage investments in companies within the mobility, wireless, security, digital home, disruptive software, semiconductor, components, nanoelectronics, cleantech, digital media, infrastructure software and consumer electronics sectors. The firm ceased operations on April 22, 2010.

Founded in 1998, BlueRun Ventures is a venture capital investment firm based in San Mateo, California. The firm seeks to invest in the mobile software, services, and financial technology sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).
BlueStar Ventures was a venture capital firm based in Chicago, Illinois.

Bluestream Ventures was a venture capital firm that was specialized in early, middle and later-stage investments in technology firms. The firm used to invest in communications, enterprise and infrastructure software, storage and wireless sectors. The firm was founded in 2000 and was based in Stillwater, Minnesota.

Founded in 2016, BlueYard Capital is a venture capital investment firm based in Berlin, Germany. The firm prefers to invest in seed-stage, early-stage, and later-stage companies. The firm seeks to invest in business products, business services, consumer products, consumer services, healthcare, information technology, software-as-a-service, life sciences, blockchain, cryptocurrency, and fintech sectors across Europe.

Founded in 2006, Bluff Point Associates is a private equity firm based in Westport, Connecticut. The firm seeks to invest in lower middle-market growth information technology companies serving the financial services and healthcare industries.

Founded in 1975, Blum Capital Partners is a private equity firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm seeks to invest in the technology, manufacturing, business services, and product sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 1991, Blumberg Capital is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm prefers to invest in AI-driven B2B technology companies across fintech, data analytics & infrastructure, cybersecurity, healthtech, supply chain & logistics, and other enterprise technology sectors. The firm was a first investor in industry leaders.

Founded in 2003, bm-t Beteiligungsmanagement Thuringen is a venture capital firm based in Erfurt, Germany. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the ecological, digital, social innovations, automotive, machines, metal, electronics, electrical engineering, greentech, information technology, media, life science, materials science, security, and technology sectors across Germany.

In addition to being one of the world's leading premium light-vehicle manufacturers, BMW Group produces BMW motorcycles and provides financial services. Premium light-vehicle brands include BMW, Mini and ultraluxury brand Rolls-Royce. Operations include 31 production facilities in 15 countries, research and development facilities in 17 countries and a sales network reaching over 140 countries. In 2023, worldwide sales volume was over 2.5 million automobiles and over 209,000 motorcycles.

BNP Paribas Securities Services is a securities services provider and asset service bank that provides its service to various financial institutions. It specializes in fund administration, investment banking, stock-option plans management, collateral management and investment reporting as well. It has a growth strategy of enhancing its global portfolio and also expands its hedge fund administration businesses. The company was founded in 1955 and is headquartered in Pantin, France.

Mr. Bob Pasker is the Founder & serves as Board Member at Tengah. Mr. Pasker is an Angel Investor. He has been building successful technology companies and products for over 25 years. His deep understanding of the software, hardware, and networking industries has led him to design and develop numerous innovative, award winning products, most notably WebLogic, where he was a cofounder, as well as the principal developer and chief architect of the WebLogic Application Server. At Kenamea, Bob was a pioneer in the real-time web and AJAX space when, in 1999, he developed one of the first internet pub/sub and Rich Internet Application systems. At Tribe Computer Works, he led the team which developed the first embedded web-based device management system.Bob has also held technology leadership positions at Azul Systems, BEA Systems (Now Oracle), and Digital Equipment. As a technology advisor, he consults with hardware and software start-ups to develop and implement long-term business strategies and provides direction on product development, fund raising, sales and marketing, and business development. Bob has been an active angel investor for 10 years (including Mint.com, which sold to Intuit for $170MM in September 2009), and is Mentor for Techstars NYC. He also served as the CTO-in-Residence and Venture Advisor at Azure Capital Partners from 2006-2010. Bob graduated magna cum laude and Phi Beta Kappa from San Francisco State University and holds a Masters degree from Brown University.

Mr. Bobby Goodlatte is the Founder & serves as Managing Partner at Form Capital. Mr. Goodlatte is an Angel Investor. He serves as Designer-in-Residence at Greylock Partners. He works with the consumer investing team to find and invest in early-stage companies, then supports those companies on design initiatives ranging from prototyping to design recruiting. He has been an angel investor in more than 20 startups. He started his career as a product designer for Facebook, where he led design for user growth (2008-2010), Facebook Chat (2008), and Facebook Photos (2011-2012). His work on user growth mechanics in 2008 substantially boosted Facebook's registration and retention rates. He has spoken on the topic of growth mechanics at several international design conferences. He co-founded and served as the Chief Executive Officer at Openvote. He graduated from Duke University in 2008, where he majored in Computer Science.

Founded in 2015, Bodhi Capital is a venture capital based in New York, New York. The firm focuses on investing in business products, business services, information technology, TMT, and health tech sectors.

Founded in 2005, Bodley Group is a family office based in Saint Louis, Missouri. The firm seeks to invest in seed and growth opportunities in the information technology sector across the United States.

Founded in 2010, Boehringer Ingelheim Venture Fund is a corporate venture capital arm of Boehringer Ingelheim based in Ingelheim am Rhein, Germany. The seeks prefers to invest in companies operating in digital health, immune-oncology, regenerative medicine, and other technology sectors.

BofA Securities is an investment bank based in Charlotte, North Carolina. The firm offers services to private clients, small businesses, institutions and corporations. The organization is divided into two interrelated business segments: global markets & investment banking and global wealth management. Their global wealth management is comprised of global private client and global investment management. The company continually seeks opportunities for growth and to expand through organic growth opportunities and strategic acquisitions. The firm has been acquired by Bank of America.

Boingo Wireless Inc is a provider of wireless connectivity solutions for smartphones, tablets, laptops, wearables and other wireless-enabled consumer devices. It acquires long-term wireless rights at large venues like airports, transportation hubs, stadiums, arenas, military bases, universities, convention centers, and office campuses; build high-quality wireless networks such as distributed antenna systems ("DAS"), Wi-Fi, and small cells at those venues; and monetize the wireless networks through several products and services. The company operates in one reportable segment. Boingo generates most of its revenue from distributed antenna systems ("DAS").

Bolder Venture Partners was a venture capital firm that used to make investments in early-stage firms in technology, biotech, software and consumer services sectors. The firm was based in Denver, Colorado.

Founded in 2013, Bolt is a venture capital firm based in Boston, Massachusetts. The firm prefers to invest in seed and early-stage companies operating in the technology and data-driven sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Bombardier Pension Plan is a single employer corporate pension fund based in Montreal, Canada. The plan provides retirement, pension, survival and death benefits to the employees of Bombarier, a manufacturer of planes and trains. The objective of the Bombardier pension fund is to provide pension, benefits and perquisites at the median of the comparator group. External consultants are used to benchmark the pension, benefits and perquisites offered by Bombardier to its senior executives.

Founded in 2018, BOND Capital is a venture capital firm headquartered in San Francisco, California. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the information technology and consumer products and services sectors. It is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 2017, Bonfire Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Los Angeles, California. The firm seeks to invest in seed rounds and focuses on companies operating in the B2B software sector across the United States.

Booking is the world's largest online travel agency by sales, offering booking and payment services for hotel and alternative accommodation rooms, airline tickets, rental cars, restaurant reservations, cruises, experiences, and other vacation packages. The company operates several branded travel booking sites, including Booking.com, Agoda, OpenTable, Rentalcars.com, Kayak, and Momondo. Transaction fees for online bookings account for the bulk of revenue and profits.

Dr. Koh Hwee serves as Chairman at Agilent Technologies. Mr Koh Boon Hwee is the Chairman of Sunningdale Tech.He is also the General partner and Chairman of Altara Ventures. He is Chairman (executive) of Credence Partners. He is also currently the Non-Executive Chairman of public-listed Yeo Hiap Seng, Far East Orchard Ltd, AAC Technologies Holdings and Agilent Technologies. He is also the Non-Executive Chairman of FEO Hospitality Asset Management and FEO Hospitality Trust Management which manage listed Far East Hospitality Trust. Mr Koh serves as a director on the board of Bank Pictet & Cie (Asia), and is also the Chairman of the Nanyang Technological University Board of Trustees and Chairman of Rippledot Capital Advisers. Mr Koh was previously Chairman of DBS Group Holdings and DBS Bank (2005-2010), Singapore Airlines (2001-2005), SIA Engineering Company (2003-2005), Singapore Telecommunications Ltd (1986-2001), Omni Industries Ltd (1996-2001), Executive Chairman of the Wuthelam Group of Companies (1991-2000) and, before that, Managing Director of Hewlett-Packard Singapore (1985-1990), where he started his career in 1977. He holds a Bachelor of Science (Mechanical Engineering) First Class Honours Degree from Imperial College, University of London, and a Master of Business Administration (with Distinction) from Harvard Business School.

Founded in 2002, Borealis Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Hanover, New Hampshire. The firm invests in companies operating in the life sciences, digital health, and animal healthcare sectors.

Dr. Boris Wertz is a Founding Partner & serves as General Partner at Version One Ventures. Dr. Wertz serves as Board Member at Outreach. He served as a Board Member at Figure 1. He is a Co-Founder of Kobalt. He is a Board Member of Weddingful and Ada Support. He also served as Board Member at Yapta. He is a Co-Founder of GrowLab. He is also an Angel Investor. He was a Board Member of Indochino. He is a Board Member of Figure 1. He served as an Advisor at Citizen Hex. He serves as Board Member at EnPowered.

Developer and supplier of technology hardware and services intended to offer services for smart homes and connected mobility. The company operates as a multinational engineering and electronics company that provides technology and services worldwide and operates through four segments that are mobility services, industrial technology, consumer goods and energy and building technology segments, providing people with products and services that are designed to spark enthusiasm, improve quality of life and help conserve natural resources.

Founded in 2004, Boston Harbor Angels is an angel group based in Boston, Massachusetts. The firm seeks to invest in information technology, products and services, life sciences, fintech, healthcare, agriculture tech, cleantech, and sustainable clean technologies sectors.

Boston Scientific produces less invasive medical devices that are inserted into the human body through small openings or cuts. It manufactures products for use in angioplasty, blood clot filtration, kidney stone management, cardiac rhythm management, catheter-directed ultrasound imaging, upper gastrointestinal tract diagnostics, interventional oncology, neuromodulation for chronic pain, and treatment of incontinence. The firm markets its devices to healthcare professionals and institutions globally. Foreign sales account for nearly half of the firm's total sales.

Boulevard Acquisition was the operator of a blank-check company. The company was formed for the purpose of effecting a merger, capital stock exchange, asset acquisition, stock purchase, reorganization or similar business combination with one or more businesses. It was incorporated in Delaware on October 24, 2013, and was headquartered in New York, USA. The company (NASDAQ: BLVDU) was acquired by AgroFresh through a reverse merger, resulting in the combined entity trading on the NASDAQ Stock Exchange under the ticker symbol AGFS on July 31, 2015.
Bowman Capital Management was a venture capital firm that invested in internet infrastructure, software and services, networking, enterprise software and communication equipment sectors.

Box is a cloud-based content services platform that provides cloud-based storage and workflow collaboration services for enterprise customers. The firm was founded in 2005 as a file sync and sharing provider. More recently, however, the company has focused on bolstering its product portfolio by adding tools such as governance and e-signature that enhance workflow management and collaboration.

The firm has three specialized teams in the areas of information technology, life sciences, and industrial technologies. The firm invests primarily in equity and promotes joint investment with third parties in Spain and Portugal.

CalAmp provides wireless communications solutions applications to customers. The company's products, software, and application services are sold into a broad array of market verticals, including transportation, government, construction, and automotive to customers in the United States; Latin America; Europe the Middle East, and Africa; Asia-Pacific; and others. Its business activities are organized into its telematics systems and software & subscription services. The telematics systems segment offers a series of mobile resource management ('MRM') telematics products and applications. The software & subscription services segment offers cloud-based application enablement and telematics service platforms.

Founded in 1878, Caledonia Investments is a private equity investment firm based in London, United Kingdom. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the industrial, consumer services, financial services, healthcare, leisure, holding companies, construction engineering, and real estate management sectors. The firm invests in public and private companies and private equity funds.

California Public Employees' Retirement System (CalPERS) is an agency in the California executive branch that manages retirement and health benefits to approximately 1.5 million public employees, retirees, and their families and more than 2,500 employers. It was established by state law in 1932 to provide retirement benefits for state employees. In 1939, public agency and classified school employees were allowed to participate. In 1962, state law authorized CalPERS to provide health benefits to state employees. The health benefits program was expanded in 1967 to include public agency and school employees. In 1995, CalPERS began offering a supplemental deferred compensation retirement savings plan to members of public agencies that contract for it, and long-term care insurance on a not-for-profit basis. Currently, CalPERS provides benefits based on a member's years of service, age, and highest compensation. In addition, benefits are provided for disability and death, with payments in some cases going to survivors or beneficiaries of eligible members. CalPERS derives its income from investments, from member contributions, and from employer contributions. The CalPERS Real Estate Program consists of three portfolios: base, international tactical and domestic tactical. The Real Estate Program makes investments into core assets in traditional product types such as office, multifamily, retain and office with a geographic focus on the U.S. and growth markets.

Founded in 1999, California Technology Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Pasadena, California. The firm seeks to invest in information & communications technology, computer hardware, telecommunications, electronics, semiconductors, software, systems, multi-media, internet, bio-pharmaceuticals, medical devices, and life sciences sectors.

Callidus Software was a developer of a cloud-based performance management platform designed to create a road map of the sales cycle. The company's cloud-based performance management platform identified the right leads, ensured proper territory and quota distribution, enabled sales forces, automate configure price quote, speed up contract negotiations, properly recognized revenue and streamlined sales compensation, enabling sales, marketing, finance, human resource and legal professionals to accelerate and maximize their multi-product strategy and take informed decisions. The company was acquired by SAP.

Founded in 1997, Caltius Structured Capital is a private equity and mezzanine debt provider based in Los Angeles, California. The firm provides junior capital solutions to companies operating in the business and professional services, consumer products and services, healthcare services, specialty manufacturing, specialty staffing, and tech-enabled service sectors.

Calvert is a responsible Investing. Calvert Research and Management traces its roots to Calvert Investments, which was founded in 1976 and was the first to launch a socially responsible mutual fund that avoided investment in companies that did business in apartheid-era South Africa. The firm is one of the diversified families of responsibly invested mutual funds, encompassing actively and passively managed strategies, the United States and international equity strategies, fixed-income strategies and asset allocation funds.

Provider of health services intended to offer solutions to individuals and families in the United States. The company provides caregiver support and senior services, focuses on the health system and engages in creating and deploying tools required for consumers to make informed healthcare decisions based on price, quality and convenience, thereby helping people achieve better health and well-being and make healthcare more available, affordable and accessible.

Operator of an educational technology platform intended to enhance learning outcomes for students. The company provides in-school core reading programs, reading and math intervention programs, personalized learning platforms and professional development programs, thereby enabling K-12 schools to create dynamic and effective learning environments with measurable academic growth.
Founded in 2001, Cambrian Growth Partners is a growth/expansion firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm prefers to invest in healthcare and technologies companies.
Cambrian Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Livermore, California.. The firm focuses on the software and technology sectors.

Founded in 2006, Cambridge Enterprise is a venture capital firm based in Cambridge, United Kingdom. The firm prefers to invest in companies operating in the life science and medical technology sectors.

Founded in 1995, Camden Partners is a growth equity firm based in Owings Mills, Maryland. The firm focuses on lower-middle-market companies operating in the technology, software, business services, and education sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Cameron International was a manufacturer and supplier of flow equipment products to oil, gas, and process industries. The company used to offer a variety of products related to flow control, drilling, subsea, surface, and process systems, reciprocating compression, centrifugal compression, valves, valve automation, measurement, and valve management.

Provider of FIX (Financial Information Exchange) infrastructure and connectivity products. The company's products are specifically developed to address the cross-functional needs of sell and buy side firms, exchanges and ISVs.

Founded in 2012, Camp One Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Palo Alto, California. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in social media, blockchain, mobility, consumer internet, financial technology, payments, cloud computing, and software-as-a-service sectors.

The firm preferred to make investments in the communication, information technology, networking, semiconductor, wireless, software, storage, and security industries sectors.
Founded in 1950, Canaccord Genuity is an investment bank based in Toronto, Ontario. The firm provides financial services.

Canada Cannabis is a producer of psychoactive drugs. The company is the producer and supplier of marijuana for medical use. It intends to offer 15 different strains of dried marijuana, as well as the constituents to produce edible and elixir products for medicinal use. Founded on January 20, 2014 the company's headquarters are in Brampton, Onatrio. The company seeks to expand its business operations through mergers and acquisitions.

Founded in 2009, Canadian Technology Accelerator is an accelerator headquartered in New York, New York. The firm seeks to support companies operating in digital technologies, life science, and cleantech sectors.

Founded in 1980, Candover Investments was a private equity investment firm based in London, United Kingdom. The firm preferred to invest in companies operating in the media, information technology transport, manufacturing, SaaS, and oil and gas sectors.
Founded in 2014, Cane Investment Partners is a growth equity firm based in Skokie, Illinois. The firm prefers to invest in the healthcare, specialty finance, energy, real estate, and service sectors.
Acquirer of data-enabled information and marketing services firms.

Canon designs, manufactures and distributes an extensive range of consumer and electronic products, including copiers, cameras, lenses, and inkjet printers. The company operates four major business segments: printing, imaging, medical, industrial and others. It generates maximum revenue from the printing segment. The printing business unit includes office multifunction devices (MFDs), document solutions, laser multifunction printers (MFPs), laser printers, inkjet printers, image scanners, calculators, digital continuous feed presses, digital sheet-fed presses and large format printers.

Cantel Medical was a New Jersey-based manufacturer of hospital supplies for infection prevention, which included products used in endoscope disinfection, water purification systems for use in dialysis treatment, and dental supplies. The firm reported in four segments: medical (46% of fiscal 2020 sales), dental (32%), life sciences (19%), and dialysis (3%). Geographic exposure was primarily in the U.S., which accounted for about 75% of revenue, with international markets making up the remaining 25%. The company was acquired by Steris on June 2, 2021.

Canterbury Capital is a venture capital firm based in Bluffton, South Carolina. The firm invests in companies operating in cleantech, advertising and marketing, financial technology, health and life sciences.
Founded in 2013, Canvas is an early-stage VC firm investing in AI (Artificial Intelligence) transforming digital health and fintech. The firm is invests in Series A & B companies ready to scale.
Founded in 2011, Canyon Creek Capital is a venture capital firm based in Santa Monica, California. The firm seeks to invest in the technology sector.

Capgemini is a French IT services company with a global presence. The firm has over 450 offices globally, with more than half of its employees based in India. Capgemini provides services related to IT consulting, software applications and technology services, infrastructure management, engineering research and development, and business process outsourcing.
Founded in 1982, Capital A is a growth equity firm based in Amsterdam, Netherlands. The firm seeks to invest in middle-market companies across Netherlands and Belgium.

Founded in 2013, Capital A Partners was a venture capital firm based in New York, New York. The firm preferred to invest in early-stage B2B companies based in the United States and the Nordic region. The firm was merged with Butterfly Ventures in 2016.

Capital Group Private Markets is a private equity firm that also specializing in buyouts and growth capital investments. The firm was founded in 1992 and is based in Chaoyang, China. Capital One is a diversified financial services holding company headquartered in McLean, Virginia. Originally a spinoff of Signet Financial's credit card division in 1988, the company is now primarily involved in credit card lending, auto loans, and commercial lending.

Provider of securities brokerage services. The company mainly engages in securities brokerage, underwriting, self-operation, investment consulting, asset management, margin financing and securities lending, investment banking, direct investment and many other financial businesses.

Founded in 1990, Capital Z Partners is a private equity firm based in New York, New York. The firm prefers to invest in B2B, financial services, healthcare, mortgage technology, insurance technology, SaaS, industrial & cybersecurity sectors based in the United States & United Kingdom regions.
Capital-C Ventures was a Bunnik, Netherlands based venture capital firm. The firm primarily invested in information and communication technology companies.

Founded in 2005, Capital-E is a venture capital firm based in Antwerp, Belgium. The firm provides early-stage capital to companies operating in semiconductors, materials, processing, metrology & instrumentation, consumer electronics & multimedia, and communications & networking sectors.

Founded in 2013, CapitalG is a growth equity firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm prefers to invest in focus on growth-stage companies operating in the technology sector.

Capitalia Sofipa was a Milan, Italy based private equity firm specializing in mid-cap private equity investments, with a focus on companies based in Italy, OECD countries, and Israel. The preferably exited its investments through trade sales, initial public offerings, and secondary buy-outs. As of July 25, 2012 the company was acquired by Synergo.
Founded in 1987, Capricorn Holdings is a growth expansion investment firm headquartered in Greenwich, Connecticut. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage growth and middle-market companies.
Developer of software for the bail bond market. The company develops software for bail bond agents to organize and manage their data and save costs.

Carbonite Inc is a provider of cloud and hybrid business continuity solutions. Its solutions include Carbonite Personal, which offers unlimited cloud backup for individuals, and Carbonite which offers cloud backup for small and midsize businesses, for an annual flat fee based on the amount of storage needed. Both solutions are packaged at three different service levels. The company derives revenues from subscription fees for its software-as-a-service offerings. A large majority of the firm's revenue is generated in the United States. The company continues to grow by making periodic small acquisitions.

Founded in 1996, Cardinal Partners is a venture capital firm based in Princeton, New Jersey. The firm seeks to invest in the healthcare, consumer, machine learning, blockchain, technology, and life sciences sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Cardlytics operates an advertising platform within financial institutions' digital channels, which include online, mobile, email and various real-time notifications. The company operates through segments namely, the Cardlytics platform in the U.S. and U.K. and the Bridg platform. The Cardlytics platform segment which generates key revenue, operates a proprietary native bank advertising channel that enables marketers to reach consumers through their trusted and frequently visited online and mobile banking channels. The Bridg platform generates revenue through the sale of subscriptions to the cloud-based customer-data platform and the delivery of professional services like implementation, onboarding and technical support. The company receives maximum revenue from the United States.

Care.comis a provider of online marketplace for connecting people seeking care services. The company operates as an online marketplace for finding and managing family care and also provides e-commerce service selling curated products designed for families, helping families address their particular lifecycle of care needs and focusing on child care, senior care, special needs care and other non-medical family care needs such as pet care, tutoring, and housekeeping.

CareCloud is a healthcare information technology company. It provides a full suite of proprietary cloud-based solutions and related business services. Its software-as-a-service platforms include practice management (PM), electronic health record (EHR), business intelligence, telehealth, patient experience management (PXM) solutions and robotic processing automation (RPA) bots, along with complementary software tools and business services such as revenue cycle management (RCM), premiere healthcare consulting and implementation services and on-demand workforce staffing capabilities for high-performance medical groups and health systems nationwide. The operating segments of the group are healthcare IT, which is the key revenue-generating segment and practice management.

CareMax is a technology-enabled care platform providing value-based care and chronic disease management to seniors. It operates various owned medical centres that offer a comprehensive suite of healthcare and social services and a proprietary software and services platform that provides data, analytics and rules-based decision tools/workflows for physicians across the United States.

CarGurus is a company that acts as an online automotive marketplace connecting buyers and sellers of new and used cars. The company provides three types of marketplace listing products, restricted listings, and enhanced or featured listings, through which it offers real-time and historical data analysis of the connections and pricing analysis. The listing platforms offer auto manufacturers and others to buy advertising on the company's site and target consumers based on the make, model, and zip code of the cars. The company operates through two segments, namely the U.S. marketplace and digital wholesale. It generates maximum revenue from the U.S. marketplace segment. Geographically, the company derives its key revenue from the United States and the rest from international markets.

Mr. Carl Bass serves as Chairman of the Board and Member of the Compensation Committee at Velo3D. Mr. Bass serves as Chief Technology Officer, Chief Operating Officer and Chief Executive Officer at Autodesk Ventures. He is an Angel Investor. He served as Executive Chairman at Zoox. He served as a Board Member at Built Robotics. He serves as an Advisor at Higharc. He serves as a Chairman at Alpha Ring International. He serves as Chairman of the Board and Member of the Compensation Committee at Velo3D. He served as Board Member at Dyndrite. He served as President & Chief Executive Officer at Alias Systems. He serves as a Board Member at Toric. He serves as a Board Member at Oqton and as Chairman at Ouster. He serves as a Board Member at ARRIS. He served as Chief Executive Officer at Autodesk. He is a Board Member of nTopology, Formlabs, Autodesk, and HP. He served as an Advisor and Board Member at Impact Venture Partners. He co-founded Ithaca Software, which was acquired by Autodesk in 1993. Since joining the company, He has held several executive positions including Chief Technology Officer and Chief Operations Officer. He sits on the board of trustees of the Smithsonian's Cooper-Hewitt National Design Museum, Art Center College of Design, and California College of the Arts; and on the advisory boards of Cornell Computing and Information Science, UC Berkeley School of Information, and UC Berkeley College of Engineering. He holds a bachelor's degree in mathematics from Cornell University. He is a maker and spends his spare time building things from chairs and tables to boats and most recently, an electric go-kart. He serves as a Board Member at Dendrite.

Mr. Carl Icahn is the Founder and serves as Chief Executive Officer at Icahn Capital. Mr. Icahn serves as Chairman at Icahn Enterprises. He served as President, Director & Treasurer at Carl C. Icahn Foundation. He Co-Owned Cloudera. Mr. Icahn serves on the boards of directors of several of Icahn Enterprises L.P.'s subsidiaries. Mr. Icahn has been: chairman of the board of CVR Refining, LP, an independent downstream energy limited partnership, since January 2013; chairman of the board of CVR Energy, Inc., a diversified holding company primarily engaged in the petroleum refining and nitrogen fertilizer manufacturing industries, since June 2012; chairman of the board of Tropicana Entertainment Inc., a company that is primarily engaged in the business of owning and operating casinos and resorts, since March 2010; and a director of Federal Mogul Corporation, a supplier of automotive powertrain and safety components, since December 2007, and the non-executive chairman of the board of Federal-Mogul since January 2008.. Mr. Icahn was previously: chairman of the board and a director of American Railcar Industries, Inc., a railcar manufacturing company, from 1994 to July 2014; a director of American Railcar Leasing LLC, a lessor and seller of specialized railroad tank and covered hopper railcars, from June 2004 to November 2013; a director of WestPoint Home LLC, a home textiles manufacturer, from October 2005 until December 2011. Mr. Icahn has served as chairman of the board and a director of Starfire Holding Corporation, a privately-held holding company, and chairman of the board and a director of various subsidiaries of Starfire, since 1984. Mr. Icahn has also served as President and a member of the executive committee of XO Holdings, a competitive provider of telecom services, since September 2011, and chairman of the board and a director of its predecessors since January 2003; and a director of Cadus Corporation, a company engaged in the acquisition of real estate for renovation or construction and resale, from July 1993 to July 2010. Mr. Icahn received his B.A. from Princeton University. He is also an angel investor.

Carlisle Companies is a holding company. The company manufactures and sells single-ply roofing products and warranted systems and accessories for the commercial building industry. The company is organized into two segments including Carlisle construction materials and Carlisle weatherproofing technologies. The company's product portfolio includes moisture protection products, protective roofing underlayments, integrated air and vapor barriers, spray polyurethane foam and coating systems, and others. The majority of the company's revenue comes from the Carlisle construction materials segment and more than half of the total revenue is earned in the United States.

Carlson (Minnetonka) is an operator of holding company that owns and manages hotels in the United States and internationally. It operates luxury, lifestyle, upscale, midscale, and upper midscale hotels. Its hotels' amenities and facilities include fitness centers, swimming pools, guest rooms and suites, business centers, meeting rooms, whirlpools, and more. The company also provides business travel management services.

Founded in 1993, Carmanah Management Corporation is a venture capital firm based in Victoria, Canada. The firm is also a Venture Builder. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage technology start-ups. The firm also makes social investments in home, nature, and education.
Founded in 1900, Carnegie Mellon University is a university based in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. The firm also seeks to incubate and provide micro-grants to students via the Olympus Incubator Program.

Carnegie Mellon University Endowment is the endowment arm of Carnegie Mellon University. The fund engages in alternative investment strategies including venture capital and international private equity. Carnegie Mellon University Endowment is headquartered in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania.

Carnegie Technologies is a communication company intended to develop applications and software for mobile devices, cellular core network operations and others. The company's network convergence platform delivers ubiquitous access across Wi-Fi and cellular networks and provides the critical factors for success, a smooth user experience with industry leading bandwidth aggregation, connection management and network quality analytics thereby improving connectivity across wireless networks, enabling businesses to eliminate manual work and reduce the effort it takes to conduct business. It was founded in 2010 and is headquartered in Austin, Texas. It seeks to expand its operations by acquiring stakes in companies.
Carreras, Kestner and Co. was an investment firm that preferred to invest in the transportation, business and consumer products and services sectors.
Founded in 2021, Carriage House Rock is a growth and expansion investment firm based in New York, New York. The firm seeks to invest in later-stage private companies and funds.

Cars.com is an online destination for buying and selling new and used vehicles. The company brands include Dealer Inspire, DealerRater, FUEL, Accu-Trade, PickupTrucks.com, CreditIQ and NewCars.com. websites directed towards different consumer segments.

Casa Systems is engaged in providing a suite of software-centric infrastructure solutions that allow cable service providers to deliver voice, video and data services over a single platform at multi-gigabit speeds. In addition, the company offers solutions for next-generation distributed and virtualized architectures in cable operator, fixed telecom and wireless networks. The company focuses on creating a software-centric, multi-service portfolio that enables a broad range of core and access network functions for fixed and wireless networks. The company's product line includes cable networks, IP networks, mobile networks, optical networks, professional and managed services and others. Substantial revenue is generated from North American operations.
Cascade Investment is the private investment fund of Bill Gates. The fund invests in several alternative strategies along with making venture capital investments.

Founded in 1998, Castile Ventures is a venture capital firm based in San Diego, California. The firm seeks to invest in the communications, software, information technology, and infrastructure sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

A. M. Castle is a distributor of specialty metals and plastics. The company products include nickel alloys, aluminum, stainless steel and carbon in various forms such as plate, bars, tubing and coil. It operates throughout North America, Europe and Asia. The company continues to grow by making periodic small acquisitions. It was established in 1890 and is based in Oak Brook, Illinois.
CastleHill Ventures was a venture capital firm that was based in Toronto, Ontario. The firm was founded in 1997 and used to to invest in companies operating in the information technology sector.

Catalent is a contract development and manufacturing organization, or CDMO. It operates under four segments: biologics, soft gel and oral technologies, oral and specialty delivery and clinical supply services. Catalent derives its revenues primarily from long-term supply agreements with pharmaceutical customers. The company provides a range of development and manufacturing solutions for drugs, protein-based biologics, cell and gene therapies, and consumer health products throughout the entire life cycle of a product from the drug development process to commercial supply. Catalent has over 50 facilities across four continents.

Founded in 2010, Catalina Ventures was a venture capital firm based in Laguna Hills, California. The firm specialized in seed and early-stage investments. The firm seeked to invest in companies operating in the technology and life science sectors.
Catalyst Centre was an incubator that used to invest in the information technology sectors. The firm was based in Southampton, England.
Founded in 1999, Catalyst Investments is a private equity firm based in Tel Aviv, Israel. The firm seeks to invest in Israeli and Israeli-related companies operating in the technology sectors.

Founded in 2000, Catalyst Investors is a growth equity firm based in New York City that invests in lower middle market, high-growth B2B technology (software / SaaS, tech-enabled services, and digital infrastructure) businesses.

Catamaran engages in providing pharmacy benefits management and also healthcare information technology solutions to the healthcare benefits management industry. They connect pharmacists, doctors and caregivers with prescription data to improve health outcomes, offering the clinical intelligence, technology and scale to lower payer costs while improving member health. The two segments that the company operates in are Pharmacy Benefits Management (provides electronic point-of-sale pharmacy claims management, mail and specialty pharmacy claims management, Medicare Part D services benefit design consultation, preferred drug management programs, drug review and analysis, consulting services, data access and reporting and information analysis) and Healthcare Information Technology (offers software products for managing prescription drug programs and for drug prescribing and dispensing). The company was established in 1981 with its headquarters in Schaumburg, Illinois. The company plans to grow through its accretive acquisition strategy of focusing on identifying acquisition opportunities that expand its core footprint in the PBM market, add new products and services in potential high growth areas and provide additional scale in areas such as specialty pharmacy management, oncology or public sector pharmacy (including state Medicaid). It believes that its management team's proven ability to successfully identify acquisition opportunities that are complementary and synergistic to its business and to integrate them into its existing operations with minimal disruption has played, and will continue to play, an important role in the expansion of its business. On March 30th 2015 UnitedHealth Group has announced that it will acquire Catamaran for $12.8 billion.

Founded in 2000, Catamount Ventures is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm focuses on investing in companies operating in the consumer goods, healthy living, sustainability, technology, and education sectors.

Founded in 2016, Catapult VC is a venture capital investment firm headquartered in Palo Alto, California. The firm prefers to invest in seed-stage, early-stage, and later-stage companies. The firm prefers to invest in the software sector in North America, Western Europe, and Eastern Europe.

Founded in 2003, Cathay Investments is a private equity investment firm based in Croydon, United Kingdom. The firm prefers to invest in businesses carrying out a range of distribution activities, including composite materials and chemical distribution companies, logistical providers, stationary and toy suppliers, and the healthcare sector.

Cavium is a designer, developer and marketer of semiconductor processors. The company's products are used for intelligent networking, communications, storage, video and security applications. It sells its products to providers of networking, wireless, storage, and consumer electronic equipment directly or through contract manufacturing organizations and distributors. The company continues to grow by making periodic small acquisitions. It was established in 2000 and is headquartered in San Jose, California. It seeks to expand its core operations through mergers and acquisitions.
CB Health Ventures was a venture capital firm that focused on investing in companies operating in the healthcare services, medical information technology, biotechnology and genomics sectors.

Founded in 1973, CCB International is an investment services firm owned by China Construction Bank Corporation ("CCB") and is based in Hong Kong, Hong Kong. The firm offers underwriting, financial advisory, corporate mergers and acquisitions, restructuring, additional issuance and placement of shares, refinancing for listed companies, direct investment, asset management, securities brokerage, market research, investment consultancy and commodity trading services. The firm also provides different investment and services through its different subsidiaries which are CCB International Capital, CCB International Asset Management, CCB International Securities and CCB International China.

Founded in 1984, CCMP Capital Advisors is a private equity firm based in New York, New York. Provider of enterprise software solutions and services to medium and large enterprises. The company's solutions include enterprise resource planning (ERP) supply chain management, manufacturing operations management (MOM), customer relationship management (CRM), business performance management (BPM), human resource management (HRM).

CDC Entreprises was a portfolio management company and a wholly-owned subsidiary of the French Caisse des Dépôts. The firm made private equity and venture capital investments primarily in the biotechnology, games and manufacturing sectors. The firm has been acquired by Qualium Investissement.
Founded in 1995, CDP Innovation-Sofinov was a venture capital firm based in Montreal, Canada. The firm invested in technology companies. The firm ceased its operations as of February 23, 2023.

Founded in 2017, CE-Ventures is a corporate venture capital arm of Cresent Enterprises based in Sharjah, United Arab Emirates. The firm prefers to invest in technologies, energy tech, enterprise SaaS, fintech, medical tech, supply chain management technologies, education tech, agriculture tech, and food tech sectors across the MENA region.

Founded in 1999, CEA Investissement is a corporate venture arm of Commissariat à l'Energie Atomique and is headquartered in Paris, France. The firm seeks to invest in the education, life science, energy, microelectronics, materials, and equipment, nanotechnologies, security, medical technologies, and clean technologies sectors.

Founded in 1998, Cedar Fund is a venture capital firm based in Waltham, Massachusetts. The firm prefers to invest in seed and early-stage startups across the United States and Israel. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).
Founded in 2015, Cedar Springs Capital is a private equity firm based in Dallas, Texas. The firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).
Provider of medical diagnostic services. The company caters to the healthcare industry and offers diagnostic testing and information services.

Founded in 2013, Celesta Capital is a venture capital firm based in San Mateo, California. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in digital biology, industry transformers, artificial intelligence, machine learning, cloud computing, self-driving cars, semiconductors, software, cybersecurity, big data, robotics, and mobile sectors.

Celgene is a biopharmaceutical firm that discovers, develops, and markets therapeutics for the treatment of cancer and immunological diseases. Celgene markets Thalomid and Pomalyst to treat multiple myeloma and Revlimid, a less toxic thalidomide derivative, to treat myelodysplastic syndromes, multiple myeloma, and mantle cell lymphoma. Acquisitions have brought MDS drug Vidaza, T-cell lymphoma drug Istodax, and cancer drug Abraxane. The firm's first immunology drug, Otezla, was approved in the U.S. in 2014. Recent acquisitions of Juno and Impact bring additional drugs for Celgene's blood cancer pipeline.

Founded in 1994, Celtic House Venture Partners is a venture capital firm based in Ottawa, Canada. The firm prefers to invest in the software, digital media, communication, wireless, networking, application, and information technology sectors.

Cencora is one of three domestic leading pharmaceutical wholesalers. It sources and distributes branded, generic, and specialty pharmaceutical products to pharmacies (retail chains, independent, and mail orders), hospital networks, and healthcare providers. It and McKesson and Cardinal Health constitute over 90% of the us pharmaceutical wholesale industry. Cencora also provides commercialization services for manufacturers of pharmaceuticals and medical devices, global specialty drug logistics (World Courier), and animal health product distribution (MWI Animal Health). Cencora expanded its international presence in 2021 by purchasing Alliance Healthcare, one of the leading drug wholesalers in Europe.
Founded in 2010, Cendana Capital is a fund of funds based in San Francisco, California. The firm prefers to invest in early-stage venture capital funds globally.
Founded in 2001, Centennial Ventures was a venture capital firm headquartered in Littleton, Colorado. The firm invested in network firms and related enabling software and technology enterprises.

Investors: Center for the Advancement of Science in Space
Investor Legal Name: Center for the Advancement of Science in Space, Inc.

In the innovative role, CASIS is charged with promoting and brokering a diverse range of research in life science, physical science, remote sensing, technology development and education. It was founded in 2011 and is headquartered in Melbourne, Florida.

Founded in 1996, CenterPoint Ventures was an early-stage venture capital firm based in Dallas, Texas. The firm preferred to invest in companies operating in information technology, and communication infrastructure including wireless, enterprise software and business applications, semiconductors, hardware, and Internet-enabled business sectors across the Southwest region. The firm ceased its operations on August 20, 2021.

Founded in 2006, Centerview Capital is an operationally-driven investment platform focused on the U.S. consumer sector and based in Naples, FL.
