Citigroup is a provider of a wide range of financial advisory services in the areas of commercial and investment banking, wealth management, private equity, fixed income research, cash management, transaction services, brokerage, asset management and consumer lending. It operates as a global investment bank. It also specializes in capital markets, fixed income research, fixed income analytics, consumer lending and cash management as well. The company was founded in 1811 and is headquartered in New York, New York. It seeks to acquire other regional banks and other companies that provide commercial banking products and services. It follows a growth strategy of strengthening its market position by mergers and acquisitions. Another central element in the strategy of this company has been to position itself at the head of each of the markets, segments and lines of business in which it competes.

Provider of web-based remote access, remote support and web conferencing solutions for consumers and businesses. The company offers GoTo cloud services that enable people to work from anywhere with anyone by providing cloud-based collaboration, remote access and IT support solutions for every type of business.

Citrix Startup Accelerator was an enterprise accelerator and was based in Santa Clara, California. The firm used to invest in companies operating in the cloud services, enterprise mobility and collaboration technology sectors.

City View Green Holdings is a vertically integrated cannabis company. The company intends to produce medicinal products and recreational cannabis products for the adult-use market. Its facility is located in Brantford Ontario which offers cultivation and extraction space.
CIV was a venture capital firm based in Corning, New York. The firm specialized in seed, early stage and later stage investments.

Investors: CL Alaska L.P. and JT Line Partners

Description: Founded in 1956, Clal Industries is a private equity firm based in Tel Aviv, Israel. The firm seeks to invest in ecommerce, biotechnology, hi-tech, real estate, retail services, and energy companies.
Founded in 2005, Claremont Creek Ventures is a venture capital investment firm based in Oakland, California. The firm prefers to invest in the energy, technology, and healthcare sectors.

Clariant AG is a Switzerland-based specialty chemicals company with worldwide operations. The company reports in three business areas: care chemicals, absorbents and additives and catalysts. The company's chemicals mainly target consumer end markets such as personal care and home care, but it also has an industrial component. Absorbents and additives encompass the company's coatings, absorbents, and plastics segments. Catalyst manufacturers process catalysts, mainly for petrochemical and syngas plants.
Clariden Investment was a venture capital firm that preferred to invest in the biotechnology sector.

Founded in 1987, Claridge is a private equity firm based in Montreal, Canada. The firm represents the interests of the Stephen Bronfman family, with a focus on long-term capital appreciation. The firm prefers to invest in small and medium-sized businesses in industry sectors, including holdings in food, technology, entertainment, renewable energy, and real estate.

Provider of anatomic pathology and molecular testing services. The company offers various cancer diagnostic, consultative services and commercial services to bio pharmaceutical companies and other research organizations. It also offers hematopathology testing for leukemia and lymphoma.

Clarivate is a data, information and software workflow solutions company serving customers primarily in academia, government, law, life sciences and healthcare. The company was formerly part of Thomson Reuters before being sold to private equity as an independent company in 2016. In 2019, Clarivate went public on the New York Stock Exchange. Around half of the company's revenue is generated in the Americas while Europe, the Middle East and Africa account for around a quarter.

Mr. Clark Landry serves as Managing Partner at Hawke Ventures. He is an Angel Investor, He co-founded and served as an Advisor at Inspective. He also served as a Venture Advisor at Watertower Ventures. He served as Advisory Board Member at Assignmint. He co-founded and served as the Chief Operating Officer at Maple Media. He served as a Board Member at Assignment & Crexi. He also served as Corporate Development & IR at Obsesh. He also serves as a Special Advisor of Social Media and Ad Platforms at Madison Alley Global Ventures. He was a Co-Founder of Minds + Machines. He also served as a Member of the Advisory Board at Blue Cloud Ventures. He also serves as a Board Member at Brand Networks. He also serves as a Special Advisor of Social Media and Ad Platforms at Madison Alley. He also served as a Senior Associate at Arrowroot Capital. He also serves as a Fund Advisor at Double M Partners. He is an entrepreneur and investor with several successful exits in the online advertising, enterprise software, and consumer Internet sectors.

Mr. Clark Valberg serves as Managing Partner at Tiferes Ventures. Mr. Valberg is a Co-Founder and serves as Board Member at InVision. Previously he co-founded Epicenter. He served as an adviser at Lev. He served as Chief Executive Officer at inVision.

Clarus is a designer, developer, manufacturer, and distributor of outdoor equipment and lifestyle products focused on the climb, ski, mountain, sport, and skincare markets. The company operates through the outdoor segment, which includes Black Diamond Equipment and PIEPS, and is a global leader in designing, manufacturing, and marketing innovative outdoor engineered equipment and apparel for climbing, mountaineering, trail running, backpacking skiing, and a wide range of other year-round outdoor recreation activities. The Adventure segment, which includes Rhino-Rack, MAXTRAX, and TRED, is a manufacturer of highly engineered automotive roof racks, trays, mounting systems, luggage boxes, carriers, recovery boards, and accessories in Australia, New Zealand, and the United States.

Provider of social platform for high school classmates. The company provides a platform for members of high school classes to find, communicate and organize activities with each other. The company also is an online source of scanned yearbooks, as well as a channel for advertisers.

Clean Energy Fuels is a natural gas marketer and retailer operating in the United States and Canada. The company supplies compressed natural gas, liquefied natural gas and renewable natural gas as an alternative fuel for vehicles. The majority of revenue is generated within the U.S. and mostly consists of compressed natural gas. The company operates by purchasing natural gas from local utilities; compressing, cooling, or liquefying it at company-owned plants and selling natural gas products through company-owned or customer-owned fueling stations. The company also builds, operates and maintains natural gas fueling stations for customers. The company's target markets include heavy-duty trucking, airports, public transit, institutional energy users and government fleets.
Founded in 1998, Clear Fir Partners is a venture capital firm based in Seattle, Washington. The firm prefers to invest in the telecom, SaaS, healthcare, life sciences, and technology sectors.

Founded in 2000, ClearLight Partners is a private equity firm based in Newport Beach, California. The firm prefers to invest through means of buyouts, add-ons, junior debt, mezzanine, and growth capital. the firm prefers to invest in specialty manufacturing, industrial technology, consumer products and services, healthcare services, business services, and education and training sectors based in the United States and Canada. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

ClearOne is a communications solutions company, which is engaged in designing, developing, and selling conferencing, collaboration, streaming, and digital signage solutions for audio, video, and visual communication. It sells its commercial products to end-users predominantly through a network of independent distributors, who in turn sell its products to dealers, systems integrators, and other resellers. Its products include DSP mixers, amplifiers, video walls, professional cameras, and professional microphones among others. Geographically the firm has its business presence across the United States and international markets.
Founded in 2005 , Clearspring Capital Group was a private equity firm based in Houston, Texas.

Founded in 1998, Clearstone Venture Partners is a venture capital firm based in Santa Monica, California. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage technology companies operating in the fintech and payments, enterprise technologies, and data-driven marketplaces sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Provider of automated mobile workforce management and optimization services. The company provides organizations with end-to-end visibility and control of the service management chain by optimizing forecasting, planning, shift and task scheduling, mobility and real-time management of resource and customer communication.

Developer of a sales, marketing, and customer management platform intended to offer a connected cloud commerce ecosystem. The company's platform provides IoT management services and optimizes cloud infrastructure and services to increase business development opportunities, enabling businesses to easily manage contacts, customer deals, and channels.

Mr. Clifford Holekamp is a Co-Founder and serves as Managing Director & General Partner at Cultivation Capital. He serves as a Board Member at Resilia. He serves as a Board Member at ScopeStack and Benchmark. He serves as an Advisor at Ecobot. He serves as a Board Member at Element451 and Clever Real Estate. He also served as a Board Member and Advisor at Venture for America. He serves as an executive at Holekamp Ventures. He served as a Board Member at Avail and PolicyEngage. He served as an Advisor at Sparo. He serves as a Board Member at Finlocker. He also serves as an Advisor and Board Member at Rentalutions. He also serves as a Board Member at SC Launch. He also served as an Advisor and Board Member at Hatchbuck. In addition, he serves as the Senior Lecturer in Entrepreneurship and Director of the Entrepreneurship Platform for the Olin Business School at Washington University in St. Louis. He is the founder of Foot Healers and Back Experts and has served on the boards of LockerDome, Hatchbuck, TrackBill, Arch Frame & Design, Rothman Furniture, The Danube Fund, and City Academy. He enjoys judging startup competitions, including GlobalHack, the SEIC, and the Olin Cup, and serves on the board of directors for Arch Grants. He is also active in the Entrepreneurs' Organization (EO). He worked as an account executive for IBM before beginning his entrepreneurial career. He served as a Board Member at TopOPPS. He also serves as a Board Member at LockerDome. He is also an Angel Investor. Also, he serves as a Board Member at PlanGap. He holds a BA from Washington and Lee University and an MBA from Washington University in St. Louis.

Provider of healthcare staffing and outsourcing services created to match the top talent with the top companies and make a better future and life for the global population. The company's staffing services include building relationships between companies and talented professionals that perform high-quality work in a timely manner in the fields of pre-clinical trials and scientific research, enabling pharmaceutical, biotechnology, medical device and related clinical trials industries to help them achieve their objectives of completing projects efficiently and getting efficacious products to market faster by delivering experienced professionals.

Clinical Data was an operator of a global biotechnology company developing early and late stage targeted therapeutics, as well as genetic and pharmacogenomic tests that detect serious diseases and help predict drug safety, tolerability, and efficacy, Clinical Data, Inc. offers various products. The company's late-stage compounds included Vilazodone, a potential drug candidate for the treatment of depression, and Stedivaze, a potential cardiac stress agent. The company employed biomarker strategies and technologies to develop targeted therapeutics with advantages over existing treatments to help patients, healthcare professionals, and payers. Its PGxHealth division was leveraging its biomarker discovery expertise and intellectual property to develop and commercialize pharmacogenomic tests to detect serious diseases and help predict drug safety, tolerability, and efficacy. PGxHealth built the commercial, managed care, and CLIA-certified laboratory infrastructure and capabilities to support its marketed tests, including the FAMILION family of genetic tests for inherited heart diseases and PGxPredict tests for predicting drug response. As of April 4, 2011, Clinical Data has been acquired by Forest Laboratories.

Founded in 2006, CloudBreak Capital is a private equity firm based in Fort Lauderdale, Florida. The firm prefers to invest in management buyouts, leveraged buyouts, and divestiture transactions. The firm prefers to invest in the manufacturing, distribution, and service sectors.

Provider of a SaaS fitness and gym management platform designed to help fitness club operators to manage all aspects of their business. The company's club management platform provides a web based client facing club management software to manage the base operations of a club including things like check-in, POS, billing, member management and payroll, enabling fitness facilities to increase staff productivity levels, without spending more on training, by giving every employee just what they need to be efficient.
Mr. Clyde Fessler is an Angel Investor. He is the retired H-D marketing Vice President.

Founded in 1999, CM Acquisitions is a private equity firm based in Evanston, Illinois. The firm prefers to invest in manufacturing and distribution companies with a focus on engineered plastics and materials, industrial outsourcing services, capital goods manufacturers, metal fabrication, electrical components, specialty chemicals and coatings, contract manufacturing, precast concrete, and packaging and container sectors across the United States.

Founded in 1992, CM Equity Partners is a private equity firm based in New York, New York. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the federal services, aerospace & defense sectors across the United States.
Cobalt Investments was a venture capital firm based in Lexington, Kentucky.

Cocrystal Pharma is a biotechnology company discovering and developing novel antiviral therapeutics that target the replication machinery of influenza viruses, hepatitis C viruses, and noroviruses. It employs structure-based technologies and Nobel Prize-winning expertise to create first- and best-in-class antiviral drugs. It is developing CC-31244, an investigational, oral, broad-spectrum replication inhibitor called a non-nucleoside inhibitor (NNI).

Founded in 2009, Code For America is an accelerator based in Oakland, California. The firm is a technology nonprofit that believes the government can work for the people, by the people, in the digital age.
COFA Invest is a limited partner based in Paris, France. The firm was established in 2006.
Founded in 2007, Coffin Capital & Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Park City, Utah. The firm seeks to invest in the internet and digital media sectors.

Coghill Capital Management was an investment management and advisory firm catering to endowments, foundations, family offices, high net worth individuals, pension plans and institutional investors. The firm was based in Chicago, Illinois.

Cognex provides machine vision products that help automate manufacturing processes. The firm's products include vision software, vision systems, vision sensors, and ID products. The vision software combines vision tools with a customer's own cameras and peripheral equipment and can help with several vision tasks, including part location, identification, measurement, and robotic guidance. The vision systems combine a camera, processor, and vision software into a single package. The vision sensors deliver simple, low-cost solutions for common vision applications, such as checking the size of parts. ID products read codes that have been applied to items during the manufacturing process. Cognex generates the maximum proportion of its sales in the United States and Europe.

Cohu is a supplier of semiconductor test and inspection handlers, micro-electro-mechanical system (MEMS) test modules, test contactors and thermal sub-systems used by semiconductor manufacturers and test subcontractors. The company's products include Semiconductor ATE (Automated Test Equipment), semiconductor handlers, interface products such as test contactors, probe heads and probe pins, spares and kits, Bare Board PCB Test Systems and services. It has one reportable segment, semiconductor test and inspection equipment (semiconductor test & inspection).

Founded in 2000, COI Partners is a DACH-focused growth investor based in Zurich, Switzerland. The firm focuses on deal-by-deal investments. The firm seeks to make investments in growth companies that have a proven business model and positive unit economics. The firm focuses on sectors such as IT and software, consumer and retail, life sciences, technology, and industrials and continues to pursue an industry agnostic approach.

Operator of a chain of self-service coin-cashing kiosks in North America, Europe and Japan. The company offers conversion of loose change into paper currency, donations and gift cards at supermarkets, mass merchants, drug stores and financial institution kiosk locations, enabling lead generation on the interactive kiosk screen and a flexible digital advertising platform that sits atop kiosks.
Mr. Cok Mudde is a Co-Founder of Linden-IT. He is an Angel Investor. Mr. Mudde Co-Founded and served as Partner at Linden Mobile Ventures.

Colabor Group is a wholesaler and distributor of food and related products in Canada. The company operates in two segments distribution and wholesale segment. Its distribution segment operations include the distribution of food products and related products in hotels, restaurants and institutions (HRI) and the retail market. Its products such as meat, fish and seafood (speciality distribution), as well as general food-related products (broadline distribution) and the wholesale segment's operations, include the sale of general food-related products to distributors from its distribution centre in Boucherville. The company generates maximum revenue from the distribution segment.

Coleman Cable is a manufacturer and innovator of wire, cable and other electrical products, serving a multitude of channels and industries. Its products are used by the security, sound, telecommunications, electrical, industrial, HVAC and automotive markets. The company was founded in 1970 and is headquartered in Waukegan, Illinois. It has an acquisition strategy of expanding its product offerings, enhancing market presence and exceeding the expectations of its diverse and growing customer base through acquisitions.

Ms. Colette Ballou is a Co-Founder & serves as a Chairman at Ballou PR. She is also an Angel Investor. She is the Founder and serves as Investor and Chairwoman at Ballou Capital. She is both the founder of Ballou, a European communications advisory that works with high-growth technology and technology-enabled companies, as well as a technology investor and an LP in VC and PE funds, including Cavalry Ventures, Connect Ventures, and Asia Partners. Her focus is high-level counsel and CEO advisory. Clients she has worked with include Klaus Hommels, Jan Koum, and Mark Zuckerberg. Prior to founding Ballou PR, she was a Vice President at Edelman PR's Enterprise Software and Services group. She is an active part of the European start-up community, speaking at industry events and mentoring start-up organizations such as Seedcamp. She holds a master's degree in Ethics/Philosophy from Union Theological Seminary and a bachelor's degree in psychology and religious studies from the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.

Developer of semantic software systems. The company develops and distributes high definition search and discovery software and offers research history for institutions with conceptual fingerprints and unique relationships.
Collier Investments was a venture capital firm based in Naples, Florida. The firm use to invested in early stage and later stage companies in the field of technology based education system.

Founded in 2006, Collina Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Carmel, Indiana. The firm seeks to make minority investments in seed-stage, early-stage, and later-stage companies. The firm prefers to invest in the software and technology sectors in Central Indiana.

Collins Aerospace is a manufacturer of aerospace components and systems catering to commercial, regional, business aviation and military sectors. The company specializes in the design of aerostructures, avionics and interiors as well as the mechanical, mission and power control systems, thereby helping clients in tackling safety challenges related to aircraft and modern aerial warfare.

Investors: Colorado Office of Economic Development & International Trade
Description: Founded in 2000, Colorado Office of Economic Development & International Trade is a government firm based in Denver, Colorado. This firm seeks to invest in B2B, aerospace, electronics, logistics, infrastructure, food products, media, retail, transportation, energy, healthcare, information technology, advanced manufacturing, agriculture technology, financial technology, food technology, health technology, infrastructure, life sciences, Saas & technological sectors based in the Colorado region.
Founded in 2004, Columbia Partners Private Capital is a fund of funds based in Bethesda, Maryland. The firm also specializes in growth capital investments.

Founded in 2019, Columbia River Partners is a private equity firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm seeks to invest in tech-enabled services, information technology, and software support services, technology distributors and resellers, integrators, manufacturers, and technology consulting sectors. The firm's investment types include corporate divestitures, recapitalizations, carve-outs, and other complex situations in the lower middle market.

Founded in 2000, Columbus Nova was a multi-strategy investment firm based in New York, New York. The firm managed assets through its own funds and affiliated portfolio companies. The firm invested in lower middle-market segment companies operating in the consumer product, service, education, entertainment, leisure, infrastructure and media sectors.
Columbus Nova Technology Partners was a multi stage, technology focused investment firm. The firm was founded in 2012 and was based in Menlo Park, California.

Manufacturer of space communications products and systems. The company is engaged in the production of instruments and microwave products for space satellites such as microwave multiplexers and filters, couplers, circulators, coaxial switches and micro-satellite spacecraft products.
Provider of combustion engineering services based in Norwalk, Connecticut.

Comcast is made up of three parts. The core cable business owns networks capable of providing television, internet access, and phone services to 64 million US homes and businesses, or nearly half of the country. About 50% of the locations in this territory subscribe to at least one Comcast service. Comcast acquired NBCUniversal from General Electric in 2011. NBCU owns several cable networks, including CNBC, MSNBC, and USA, as well as the NBC network, the Peacock streaming platform, several local NBC affiliates, Universal Studios, and several theme parks. The firm plans to spin off most of its cable networks later in 2025. Finally, Sky, acquired in 2018, is a large television provider in the UK and Italy, and it also has a presence in Germany and Austria.
Founded in 2017, Comcast NBCUniversal LIFT Labs is an accelerator based in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. The firm focuses on enterprise artificial intelligence startups.

Founded in 1999, Comcast Ventures is a corporate venture capital arm of Comcast based in New York, New York. The firm seeks to invest in B2B, B2C, energy, financial service, healthcare, information technology, digital health, financial technology, mortgage technology, real estate technology, artificial intelligence & big data sectors based in the United States region.

Comdisco Ventures was a Rosemont, Illinois based venture capital firm specializing in early stage investments. The firm primarily seeked to invest in technology companies. It also invested in software and computer services, communications and networking, hardware, semiconductors, biotechnology and medical devices.

Comerica is a financial services company headquartered in Dallas. It is primarily focused on relationship-based commercial banking. In addition to Texas, Comerica's other primary geographies are California and Michigan, with locations also in Arizona and Florida and select businesses operating in several other states as well as Canada and Mexico.

Commerce.Innovated was an accelerator jointly run by Silicon Valley Bank and First Data. It was designed to help commerce, payments and fintech startups grow their businesses. The four-month virtual program provided participants with operational mentorship from Silicon Valley Bank, First Data and their respective networks.
Common Metal is a venture capital firm based in the San Francisco Bay Area.

Founded in 2001, Commons Capital is a venture capital firm based in Brookline, Massachusetts. The firm focuses on investing in companies whose products, and services promote a sustainable economy and deliver market solutions to major social and environmental problems. The firm primarily invests in the healthcare, energy, environment, and education sectors.

Founded in 1995, Commonwealth Capital Ventures is a venture capital investment firm based in Woburn, Massachusetts. The firm specializes in early and growth-stage investment companies. The firm invests in the information technology, healthcare, retail, mobile, software, service, internet, digital media, communication, wireless, instrument, system, and manufacturing sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

CommVault Systems provides data and information management software applications and services. The firm sells software licenses and services to large global enterprises, small- and midsize businesses and government agencies through both its salesforce and its network of reseller partners. Its software solutions include Commvault Complete Backup and Recovery, HyperScale, Hedvig and metallic. The company operates in the United States and exports to many other countries.
Founded in 1998, CommVest was a venture capital firm based in West Newport, Massachusetts. The firm is no longer active.
Conduit Ltd. provides a platform for building online communities via community toolbars to Web site owners and bloggers

Compal Electronics is a Taiwan-based original design manufacturer that produces notebook computers, monitors and televisions for equipment manufacturers. The firm's operations are organized into two reportable segments, information technology products and strategy-integrated product segments. The majority of the firm's revenue is generated in the United States, with the rest coming from China, the Netherlands, the United Kingdom and others.

Compaq Computer was a developer and manufacturer of personal computers, PC systems and related products for sale primarily to business, home, government and education customers. Its products were marketed in more than 100 countries worldwide. The company offered a wide range of personal computing products, including desktop personal computers, battery-powered notebook computers, AC-powered portable computers and tower PC systems that store and manage data in network environments. The company was founded in 1982 and was headquartered in Palo Alto, California. Compaq Computer aimed for strategic investments through acquisitions that helped the business expand across the country and worldwide.

Founded in 1998, Compass Diversified is a private equity firm based in Westport, Connecticut. The firm prefers to invest in North American companies in the industrial and consumer sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).
Founded in 1988, Compass Technology Partners is a venture capital firm based in Menlo Park, California. The firm seeks to invest in emerging companies with innovative products or services.

Funded in 2006, Compound is a venture capital firm based in New York, New York. The firm prefers to invest in companies operating in automation, healthcare & biology, cryptocurrency, and other sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Computer Sciences was a provider of information technology (IT) services and solutions. The company offered application services, business and technology consulting, infrastructure services, cloud computing, health IT, cyber-security, big data and analytics, systems integration, industry software and solutions, outsourcing and IT transformation. It served businesses, government and communities. The company grew by making periodic small acquisitions. It was established in 1959 and is based in Tysons Corner, Virginia. As of April 2017, the company merged with HP Enterprise Services to form DXC Technology.

Developer of cloud-based cyber-security systems. The company offers application and security managed security tools that include the provision of cloud infrastructure, professional services and support services, enabling clients to secure their systems and data.

Computer Task Group is engaged in providing information technology services to its clients. The company divides its services into information technology solutions and information technology & other staffing. Its segments include North America IT Solutions and Services, Europe IT Solutions and Services and Non-Strategic Technology Services. The firm derives most of its revenues from information technology & other staffing services. It mainly caters its services to technology service providers, financial services, healthcare, manufacturing and energy industries. The geographical segments are the United States, Luxembourg, Belgium and other countries.

Developer of a suite of mainframe development and testing tools software products. The company provides end-to-end application performance management, IT portfolio management and mainframe innovation, enabling its clients to fully leverage their high-value mainframe investments with agility. The company was acquired by BMC Software, via its financial sponsors Kohlberg Kravis Roberts and Bain Capital Ventures, through a $2 billion LBO on June 1, 2020.

Comscore is a United States-based information and analytics company that measures advertising, content, and the consumer audiences of each, across media platforms. The platforms measured include televisions, mobile devices, computers, tablets, CTV devices and movie theaters. The company generates almost all its revenue from the United States, followed by Europe, Latin America, Canada and others. It provides solutions for automotive, digital media, financial services, FMCG, pharmaceutical, retail, technology and travel.

ComSovereign Holding is a provider of technologically advanced telecom solutions to network operators, mobile device carriers, governmental units and other enterprises worldwide. The company offers telecom and network products and solutions, intelligent batteries & back-up power solutions and tethered drones and aerostats.

Comstock is engaged in technologies that efficiently use wasted and under-utilized natural resources to produce renewable energy and other products that contribute to balancing uses and emissions of carbon and enhance mineral and material discoveries. It has three operating segments; the renewable energy segment consists of technology and engineering services sales, licenses, royalties, demonstration plants and equipment, and research and development expenses, The mining segment consists of mining, mine development, metal processing, and environmental and reclamation operations and the strategic and other investments segment includes all other activities, including investments in non-mining real estate and its equity method investments.

Comtech Telecommunications is a provider of modern communications solutions. The company is engaged in designing, developing, producing and marketing products, systems, and services for communications solutions. It is engaged in two business segments, Satellite and Space Communications and Terrestrial and Wireless Networks. The majority of sales are generated from the satellite and space communications segment.

Founded in 2018, Conan Capital is a venture capital firm based in London, United Kingdom. The firm seeks to invest in the environmental technology, and health technology sectors. The firm also invests in projects which have a positive impact on society.

Concentrix is a technology-enabled company specializing in customer engagement and customer management. The company provides end-to-end capabilities, including CX process optimization, technology innovation and design engineering, front- and back-office automation, analytics and business transformation services to clients in five primary industry verticals. The company's verticals are technology and consumer electronics, retail, travel and e-commerce, communications and media, banking, financial services and insurance and healthcare. Geographically, the company operates in the Philippines, United States, India, Canada, Germany, Great Britain and others.

ServiceSource International was the provider of customer and revenue lifecycle management solutions. The firm operated in a single segment that was focused on service offerings that integrated data, processes, and cloud technologies. The company generated revenue through a pay-for-performance model, where clients paid a commission based on renewal sales generated. Most of the firm's revenue was generated in North America and Latin America, and the rest from Europe, the Middle East, Africa, and Asia-Pacific. The company was acquired by Concentrix on July 20, 2022.

Concept Ventures was a venture capital firm based in Santa Clara, California and was founded in 2005. The firm specialized in seed, startup and early stage investments. The firm used to invest in digital media, communication, semiconductor, software and healthcare sectors.

Founded in 2012, Conconi Growth Partners is a family investment office based in Vancouver, British Columbia. The firm seeks to invest in information technology, FinTech, space technology, and artificial intelligence.

Concord Ventures was a Herzelia, Israel based venture capital investment firm. The firm used to focus on investing in companies based in Israel within the semiconductors, healthcare, software and telecommunications sectors.
Operator of an advertising firm intended to provide services for digital journalism and print media in the United States. The company produces media content for print, digital and video brands.
Founded in 2001, Conduit Ventures is an impact investment firm based in London, United Kingdom. The firm seeks to invest in the manufacturing and energy services sectors.

Conmed is a Utica, New York-based medical equipment company that focuses on sports medicine procedures and general surgeries. The firm currently reports through two reporting units, orthopedic surgery, and general surgery. From a geographic perspective, the firm is U.S.-centric, with maximum domestic sales accounting for revenue, EMEA accounting for second place, APAC at third, and the non-U.S. Americas region driving the remaining revenue.

Connect Springboard San Diego is an accelerator/incubator headquartered in San Diego, California. The firm seeks to provide different services and access to funding to startups operating in the technology and life science sector.

Founded in 1989, Connecticut Innovations is a venture capital investment firm based in New Haven, Connecticut. The firm seeks to invest in seed-stage, early-stage, and later-stage companies. The firm seeks to invest in SaaS, manufacturing, life sciences, clean tech, oncology, cybersecurity, infrastructure, big data, e-commerce, and technology-based sectors in Connecticut, United States.

Conrad N. Hilton Foundation is a non-profit independent family foundation located in Agoura Hills, California. Established in 1944, its mission is to partner with non-profit organizations, government and other funders to address critical societal need in the United States and around the world with a mandate to help the world's disadvantaged and vulnerable people. The plan is managed and administered by foundation board consisting of thirteen members.

Consolidated Water is a water utility company. It develops and operates seawater desalination plants and water distribution systems. The company's business segments are; The retail segment operates the water utility for the Seven Mile Beach and West Bay areas of Grand Cayman Island, The bulk segment supplies potable water to government utilities in Grand Cayman and the Bahamas under long-term contracts, The services segment designs, constructs and sells water infrastructure and provides management and operating services to third parties and the manufacturing segment manufactures and services a wide range of custom and specialized water-related products applicable to commercial, municipal and industrial water production, supply and treatment.
Founded in 2003, Consor Capital is a venture capital firm based in Sausalito, California. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage companies operating in the consumer sector.
Constantin Partners was a seed and early stage venture capital firm based in San Anselmo, California. It invested in seed stage software and internet infrastructure companies.

Constellation Web Solutions is a provider of Software as a service (SaaS) products in the real estate industry. The company manages and builds vertical market software businesses that provide software solutions for the real estate industry. The company was founded in 1995 and is headquartered in Milwaukee, Wisconsin.
Contango Capital Management was a venture capital firm that was based in Houston, Texas. The firm invested in companies that operated in the energy and information technology sector.
ContiFinancial was a lender in the United States. The firm was declared bankrupt on December 20, 2000.

Continental is a global auto supplier and tiremaker. Operating segments include the automotive group (electrical architecture and networking, autonomous mobility, safety and motion, smart mobility, and user experience), tires, and ContiTech which uses rubber in industrial and automotive components and systems. Last year, automotive group revenue was around 49% of the total, tire was 34%, ContiTech was 16%, and contract manufacturing for Vitesco was 1%. The top five customers include Ford, Mercedes-Benz, the Renault-Nissan-Mitsubishi alliance, Stellantis, and Volkswagen, representing about 34% of total revenue. Europe, at 49% of total revenue, is the company's largest market, followed by North America at 27%, Asia (mostly China) at 21%, and 4% in other regions.

Founded in 2006, Continental Investors was a private equity firm based in Chicago, Illinois. The firm preferred investments in companies operating in the financial service industry, IoT, mobile, eCommerce, and consumer businesses.
Convergence Partners was a financing solutions provider based in Palo Alto, California.

Founded in 2013, Denny Hill Capital was a venture capital firm based in Seattle, Washington. The firm sought to invest in early and growth-stage companies. The firm preferred to invest in the building product, e-commerce, retail, clean technology, mobile, biotechnology, business software, entertainment software, social software, and oncology sectors.

Dentsply Sirona is one of the world's largest manufacturers of dental equipment and supplies. It is a result of a merger of equals in 2016 between Dentsply International (manufactured dental consumables and lab products) and Sirona Dental Systems (manufactured technologically-advanced dental equipment). The firm's wide portfolio consists of dental consumables, lab products, CAD/CAM and imaging technology, medical devices, and specialty products in orthodontics, endodontics, and implant dentistry. It distributes two-thirds of its dental consumables, technology and equipment through third-party distributors and the remaining portfolio is either sold to labs and offices through the firm's salesforce or directly to consumers (such as Byte clear aligner).

Dentsu Group is a Japanese international advertising and public relations company that provides communication-related solutions and services such as management and business consulting. Dentsu is one of the world's largest advertising agencies. The company operates through its nine global network brands--Carat, Dentsu, Dentsu media, iProspect, Isobar, mcgarrybowen, MKTG, Posterscope and Vizeum--as well as through its specialist/multi-market brands. It is also active in the production and marketing of sports and entertainment content on a global scale. The company earns a majority of its revenue in Japan, followed by Europe and the Americas while operating in over 100 countries around the world.

Provider of expertise and capabilities in brand, media, digital and specialist communications intended to offer a holistic and integrated approach. The company's communication services include digital creative execution, content creation, media planning, sports and entertainment marketing, SEO strategy, near-field communications (NFC) and marketing analytics and enables clients to communicate and build relationships with consumers around their products and brands.

Department for International Trade is the government organization helping United Kingdom based companies to sell their products and services overseas and bringing high quality foreign direct investment to the UK. It also provides specialist help for entrepreneurs and ongoing support to help companies grow their business after setting up in the United Kingdom.

Descartes Systems Group provides a software solution that allows users in the shipping industry to communicate with one another. Its core product is the global logistics network, which is best understood as transaction-driven. Descartes charges clients to send/receive messages, data, and documents on the GLN. Customers typically contract for a monthly minimum over a multiyear period. The GLN platform allows Descartes to upsell additional software modules as well, typically provided via a software-as-a-service model.

Founded in 1995, Desjardins Capital is a private equity arm of Desjardins Group based in Montreal, Canada. The firm has 50 years of experience with a mission to contribute to the prosperity of individuals and communities by investing in the growth of Quebec businesses. The firm assets under management of $3 billion as of December 31, 2023, also contribute to the longevity of nearly 760 companies, cooperatives, and funds in various sectors of activity from all regions of the province. In addition to contributing to socio-economic growth, productivity, and the adoption of sustainable practices, this subsidiary of Desjardins Group offers entrepreneurs access to a broad business network, enabling them to be accompanied and supported in their projects.

Desktop Metal manufactures 3D printing to make metal and carbon fiber 3D printing accessible to all engineers, designers, and manufacturers. 3D metal printing helps in the design and development of automotive parts, consumer goods, manufacture of industrial equipment, and design of mechanical systems. The company ships its product to markets in the Americas, Europe Middle East and Africa (EMEA), and Asia Pacific (APAC). It derives maximum revenue from the Americas.
Founded in 1872, Deutsche Effecten- und Wechsel- Beteiligungsges is a private equity firm based in Jena, Germany. The firm prefers to invest in the digital finance and technology sectors.
DEVK Private Equity was a private equity firm based in Cologne, Germany. The firm used to seek investment in professional, scientific and technical sectors.

DEVK Rückversicherungs- und Beteiligungs is an insurance company based in Cologne, Germany. The company provides reinsurance for the insurance operations undertaken in various segments and types of non-life, accident, health and life insurance. The management board is responsible for the administration of the firm.

Dexcom designs and commercializes continuous glucose monitoring systems for diabetic patients. CGM systems serve as an alternative to the traditional blood glucose meter process, and the company is evolving its CGM systems to provide integration with insulin pumps from Insulet and Tandem for automatic insulin delivery.

DFJ Tamir Fishman was an Israeli venture capital firm for early stage investments. The firm used to focus on investing in companies within the media, retail, manufacturing and information technology sectors.

Founded in 1983, DFW Capital Partners is a private equity investment firm based in New York, New York. The firm seeks to invest in lower middle market firms operating in the healthcare, business, and industrial services sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Digital Generation was a provider of satellite technology for advertising content distribution. The company offered end-to-end digital advertising delivery network. It also offered media asset management services for order entry and process management. It was founded in 1991 and was headquartered in Irving, Texas. Digital Generation aimed for strategic investments through acquisitions that helped the business expand across the country and worldwide. It seeked to buy digital ad serving technologies.

Founded in 2009, DG VENTURES is the corporate venture arm of Digital Garage based in Tokyo, Japan. The firm seeks to invest in the United States, Japan, India, Canada, and Asia-based companies operating in the fintech, martech, artificial intelligence, blockchain, software-as-a-service, e-commerce, proptech, tech, fintech, urban mobility, health, insurance, virtual reality, artificial intelligence, healthcare, internet of things, and marketplace sectors.

Founded in 1999, DHG Communications Network is a venture capital firm based in Hoogkarspel, Netherlands. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the e-commerce, SaaS, and technology sectors based in India, the United States, Israel, the Netherlands & Singapore regions.

Based in Germany, DHL Group ranks among the largest parcel shipping and third-party logistics providers globally. Its DHL divisions (international express shipping, air and ocean freight forwarding, contract logistics and e-commerce solutions) generate roughly 80% of revenue. Roughly 20% of revenue comes from the post and parcel Germany division, which includes the legacy postal business and the German small-package delivery business.

Founded in 2016, Diagram Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Montreal, Canada. The firm prefers to invest in early-stage companies in the fintech, Web3, artificial intelligence, and climate tech sectors in the United States and Canada.

Founded in 2004, Diamond Castle Holdings is a private equity firm based in New York, New York. The firm seeks to invest in energy, healthcare, financial technology & health technology sectors based in the United States & Canada regions.

Founded in 1999, Diamond State Ventures was a private equity firm based in Little Rock, Arkansas. The firm sought to invest in small and lower middle-market companies. The firm preferred to invest in companies operating in the manufacturing, business services, consumer products and services, and healthcare sectors.

Didi Chuxing Technology is a developer of a mobile ride-hailing application designed to match customers with local drivers in China. The company's application provides vehicles and taxis for hire and also offers chauffeur services, minibus and ride-sharing services in China, enabling users to request rides through smartphone applications.

Diebold Nixdorf is engaged in providing software and hardware services for the financial and retail industries. The customer segments of the company are banking which offers integrated solutions for financial institutions and retail which offers solutions, software, and services that improve the checkout process for retailers.

Mr. Diego Berdakin is an Angel Investor. Mr. Berdakin co-founded and served as President at Lucky Group. Previously, Mr. Berdakin also served as Chief Executive Officer at City Storage Systems. Prior to that, he was the Executive Vice President of Strategy and Product at Slingshot Labs. Slingshot Labs, a division of News Corporation, is a web incubator dedicated to building new Internet companies. In this role, he was responsible for Product Strategy, Corporate Strategy, Business Development, Corporate Development and Marketing. He is a serial entrepreneur who specializes in building businesses from the ground up. He has taken an innovative approach to many established business ideas, adapting them to shifting technological paradigms. Most recently, he co-founded a pioneering online escrow service, iEscrow.com, where he served as President. Concurrently, he served as a principal adviser to online marketing company, Bzzing, Inc. He also co-founded a Los Angeles-based internet incubator, MD Capital, where he helped incubate successful start-ups. He holds a Bachelor of Science from Northwestern University in Political Science with a specific interest in campaigning on the social web. He also serves as an Advisor at Troy Capital Partners.

Digi International is a Minnesota corporation. The company provides business and mission-critical and Internet of Things (IoT) connectivity products and services. It has two segments: IoT Products and Services and IoT Solutions. The IoT Products and Services segment consists of distinct communications products and communication product development services. The IoT Solutions segment offers wireless temperature and other environmental condition monitoring services as well as employee task management services. The company generates the majority of its revenue from the IoT Products & Services segment. Geographically, the company generates the majority of its revenue from its business in the United States and also has its presence in Europe, the Middle East Africa and the rest of the world.
Founded in 2013, Digital Fuel Capital is a private equity firm based in Boston, Massachusetts. The firm seeks to invest in middle-market companies in e-commerce, retail, and TMT sectors.

Digital Garage integrates three technologies--information technology, marketing technology, and financial technology--into one solution it provides to its business customers. The company operates three primary business segments. The incubation segment invests in and develops startups and new businesses. The marketing segment includes advertising and promotion solutions that reach consumers. The financial segment offers payment solutions to monetize Internet businesses. The marketing and financial segments provide most of the company's revenue. Digital Garage operates primarily in Japan.

Developer of micro-optics and optical integration solutions. The company has developed wafer-based micro-optics technology using the processes developed for manufacturing semiconductor IC's, with which one can produce precision micro-optics and optical assemblies. These technologies can be applied to consumer electronic products.

Founded in 2016, DigitalHealth.London Accelerator is an accelerator/incubator firm based in London, United Kingdom. The firm provides bespoke advice, mentoring, education, peer networking, brand awareness and partnership opportunities

Provider of information technology infrastructure services catering to Middle East and African companies. The company offers technology modernization, digital acceleration, cloud, network enterprise and consulting and transformation services, thereby helping clients optimize the performance and availability of the unified communications and collaboration tools that run on desktop and contact center technologies.

Mr. Dipchand Nishar is an Angel Investor. Mr. Nishar serves as Managing Director, Investment Team at General Catalyst. Mr. Nishar serves as a Board Member at Kandji. He serves as a Board Member of Georgiamune. He served as an Advisor at FetchRev. He serves as an Advisor at Upside. He serves as a Board Member at Automation Anywhere, Fungible & Kandji. He served as an Advisor at SignalFire. He served as a Board Member at SambaNova Systems and Pear Therapeutics. He served as Senior Managing Partner at SoftBank Group. He serves as Senior Managing Partner at SoftBank Group. He served as a Board Member at Formlabs and Encoded Therapeutics. He served as a Board Member at TripAdvisor, Improbable. He served as a Senior Managing Partner, in the Americas at SoftBank Investment Advisers and as a Senior Managing Director at Softbank. He served as a Board Member at ElevateBio, Relay Therapeutics, and Automation Anywhere. He is a Co-Founder and serves as VP of Products & Strategy at Patkai Networks. He is a Board Member of Opower. He served as a Senior Vice President of Products and User Experience at LinkedIn, as a Board Member, and as an Advisor at Post Intelligence. He received a B.Tech from the Indian Institute of Technology (Kharagpur), an MSEE from the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign, and an MBA from Harvard Business School.

Diplomat Pharmacy was active in the United States healthcare sector. It provided specialty pharmacy and infusion services, including pharmacy solutions for chronic diseases. The company had two main segments: specialty pharmacy and pharmacy benefit management. Its specialty pharmacy segment offered solutions to dispense, deliver, and dose prescription drugs. The pharmacy benefit management segment offered services to help control pharmacy benefit dollars and maximize quality of care. It derived most of its revenue through prescription drug sales in the United States. The company (NYS: DPLO) was acquired by Optum, a subsidiary of UnitedHealth Group (NYS: UNH), for $300 million on February 7, 2020.

While Direct Line is one of the more focused personal lines insurers that we cover in Europe, it is still quite diversified. The business sells insurance under four divisions: personal lines motor, personal lines home, rescue and other personal lines, and commercial. Rescue and other personal lines include rescue, travel and pet insurance. Commercial insurance is sold to small businesses. Direct Line only sells insurance in the United Kingdom. Its motor insurance division typically accounts for around 60% of the total group gross written premium and the personal home insurance unit typically sells around 20%. Rescue and other personal lines account for around 10% and commercial insurance accounts for around 10%.
Mr. Dirk Vermunicht is a Co-Founder & serves as Investor and Board Member at Azumuta.

Mr. Dirk Wakeham serves as Managing Director at Vista Equity Partners. Mr. Wakeham is an Angel Investor. He serves as a Board Member at StarRez. He serves as a Board Member at Leonardo247. He serves as a Board Member at Critical Start. He served as Chief Executive Officer at Zego (Financial Software). He served as Chief Executive Officer at Paylease. He serves as a managing director for the Private Equity Foundation at Vista Equity Partners. He joins PayLease from a leadership position at Kibo, where he has been responsible for driving the transformation, best practices, and customer experience. He also served as Managing Director at Westlake Venture Partners. He served as President and Chief Operating Officer at Lanyon. He served as President and Chief Operating Officer at Kibo Software. Additionally, he is responsible for several key strategic products, including Cloud Technologies and procurement, as well as sales and marketing. Prior to joining RealPage, he served as president and CEO of LeasingDesk, which was acquired by RealPage in April 2007, where he developed the flagship renters' insurance product. LeasingDesk pioneered the offering of point-of-lease insurance programs for multi-family portfolios. He's also served as senior vice president at Western National Group, where he was responsible for the management and deployment of enterprise systems focused on the management and operation of a diverse multifamily portfolio. He served as an Advisor at Anyone Home. He also served as an Advisor at Rentlytics.

Founded in 1986, Discovery Capital was a venture capital firm based in Port Coquitlam, Canada. The firm preferred to invest in British Columbia-based companies operating in the information technology, communications, health, life sciences, environmental, and energy technologies sectors.
Founded in 2021, DisruptAD is a corporate venture capital arm of ADQ based in Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage technology companies.

Ditech Holding is a provider of mortgage banking services intended to provide mortgage financing. The company is a diversified mortgage banking firm. It serves a wide array of loans across the credit spectrum for its own portfolio and for GSEs, government agencies, third-party securitization trusts and other credit owners. The company's segment includes Servicing and Originations. Servicing segment performs servicing for its own mortgage loan portfolio. It also operates complementary businesses including asset receivables management that performs collections of post-charge-off deficiency balances for third parties, and Originations segment originates and purchases mortgage loans. The company generates a majority of its revenue from the Servicing Segment.

Divine was actively engaged in business-to-business or B2B, e-commerce through its Internet Zaibatsu, a community of partner companies. These companies collaborated to provide cross-selling and marketing opportunities and support entrepreneurial initiatives, business growth and the sharing of information and business expertise. The company managed, financed, operated and provided services to its partner companies, offering a turn-key solution for building successful B2B e-commerce business. The company went out of business in 2003. The company focused on its expansion through mergers and acquisition.

Developer and distributor of digital video technologies. The company offers video compression-decompression software library more popularly known as codec, as well as consumer software application. The company's technologies enable users to compress, secure, and distribute digital video and participate in its digital media ecosystem. The company also offers various consumer software product bundles for different operating systems. They also sell a mobile player that allows users to playback company's videos on their handsets from various sources. The company also provides technology licensing for independent software vendors, consumer hardware device manufacturers, content creators and consumers. The company offers certification programs to integrated circuit manufacturers, original design manufacturers, original equipment manufacturers and software vendors.

DJO Global is a manufacturer of orthopedic devices designed to get and keep people moving. The company offers hot and cold therapy products, bone growth stimulators, vascular therapy systems, compression garments, electrical stimulators, and physical therapy products, enabling healthcare professionals, spine surgeons, primary care physicians, pain management specialists to experience a diverse range of orthopedic rehabilitation products to treat their patients. It was founded in 1978 and headquartered in Lewisville, Texas.

DKA Capital was a sector focused Danish private equity fund which used to invest in knowledge-intensive and technology companies with game changing business models and international potential with the aim of creating long term sustainable value. The firm focused its investments in companies within manufacturing, healthcare, information technology sectors.

Founded in 1922, DMG Information is a private equity firm based in London, United Kingdom. The firm is a subsidiary of the British media company - Daily Mail and General Trust. The firm focuses on investing in late seed and Series A rounds of companies with disruptive consumer propositions.

dMY Technology Group II was the operator of a blank check company intended to perform business combinations with one or more businesses. The company was formed for the purpose of entering into a merger, stock exchange, asset acquisition, stock purchase, recapitalization, reorganization, or other similar business combinations with one or more target businesses. The company was founded on June 18, 2020 and was headquartered in Las Vegas, Nevada. The company was acquired by Genius Sports Group through a reverse merger, resulting in the combined entity trading on the New York Stock Exchange under the ticker symbol GENI on April 20, 2021.

Founded in 2010, The DMZ is an accelerator/incubator based in Toronto, Canada. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the technology, edtech, proptech, housing, and impact sectors across Canada and North American regions.

Founded in 2011, Docomo Innovations is an accelerator firm based in Palo Alto, California. The firm seeks to incubate and invest in mobile network technology, video codec standardization, network service innovation, and android product innovation sectors.
Provider of financial reporting tools and services. The company offers financial reporting, print fulfillment and shareholder communication tools to public companies, funds and pre-public companies.

Document Security Systems Inc operates in the security and commercial printing, packaging and plastic ID markets. The company develops, markets, manufactures and sells paper and plastic products designed to protect valuable information from unauthorized scanning, copying, and digital imaging. It is organized into the operating segments of Packaging and Printing; Plastics; Digital; Technology management; and Corporate. The Packaging and Printing, and Plastics segments, which are the key revenue-generating segments, are engaged in the printing and production of paper, cardboard and plastic documents with a wide range of features designed for the protection of documents against unauthorized duplication and altering.

DocuSign offers Agreement Cloud, a broad cloud-based software suite that enables users to automate the agreement process and provide legally binding e-signatures from nearly any device. The company was founded in 2003 and completed its initial public offering in May 2018.

Provider of outsourced services for life science applications. The company's outsourced services for life science applications include supply chain, customer and patient support, technology, financial, consulting, and quality and regulatory services, enabling startup, mid-tier and Fortune 500 avail efficient, effective and easy to use health experience. The company was founded on 1858 and is headquartered in Milwaukee, Wisconsin.

Dolphin Equity Partners ceased operations at the end of 2012. The remaining assets held by Dolphin Equity Partners have been purchased by Second Alpha Partners I. Dolphin Equity Partners is a venture capital firm that invests in growth stage, technology services companies that have management teams committed to building transformational companies. As an advisor and partner, Dolphin Equity Partners combines industry experience with a sense of partnership with their portfolio companies' management teams. The firm's focus is building companies in sectors such as Software as a Service (SaaS) and Cloud Computing, Mobile-Enabled Technology, Digital and Social Media, and Communications Services.
Founded in 1985, Domain Associates is a venture capital firm based in Princeton, New Jersey. The firm prefers to invest in pharmaceuticals, diagnostics, and medical devices sectors.

Founded in 1985, Dominion Ventures was a venture capital firm based in Walnut Creek, California. The firm provided capital and strategic guidance to emerging technology companies operating in the communications, software, and technology sectors. The firm ceased its operations as of April 19, 2023.
Mr. Donald Lucas is an Angel Investor.

Founded in 1959, Donaldson, Lufkin & Jenrette was an investment bank based in New York, New York. The firm used to provide investment banking services which include securities underwriting, sales and trading, investment and merchant banking, financial advisory services, investment research, venture capital, correspondent brokerage services, interactive brokerage services, and asset management. On November 2000, the firm was acquired by Credit Suisse
Mr. Donn Harvey is an Angel Investor.

Dot Edu began as a small core group of entrepreneurial friends at Stanford and UC Berkeley. Dot Edu was a university based network of friends, spanning computer science and engineering faculty, students, and alumni at various US universities. Dot Edu consisted of three components: a modest fund to allow seed stage investment in cutting edge ideas and technologies built around doctoral and post-doctoral research, a network of pro-active limited partners and regular workshops for exchange and promotion of ideas for future research.
Provider of data protection and recovery software for Microsoft Windows applications. The company also offers server backup software applications.

Provider of digital marketing technology and services to advertisers, publishers and agencies. The company operated through two segments, TechSolutions and Data. It's TechSolutions segment includes Ad Management products, including DART for Publishers Service; Marketing Automation, including email products based on DARTmail Service and enterprise marketing solutions and Performics, comprising search engine marketing and affiliate marketing solution. Its Data segment offered direct marketers solutions for building and managing customer marketing databases; tools to plan, execute and measure multichannel marketing campaigns and list processing and data hygiene products and services. The company was acquired by Google on March 11, 2008.

DoubleVerify Holdings is a digital media measurement and analytics software platform. The Authentic Ad ensures that a digital ad was delivered in a brand-safe setting, completely viewable, by a real individual, and in the expected geography, is one of its solutions. It generates revenues from its advertisement customers by charging a Measured Transaction Fee on the volume of Media Transactions Measured on the software platform.

Mr. Douglas Atkin serves as a Board Member at Miles Howland & Co. Mr. Atkin is a Co-Founder & serves as Managing Partner at Communitas Capital Partners. He also serves as a Board member at Miles Howland & Co, Selerity, Entrio. He also served as a Board member at Red Deer. He served as Chief Executive Officer at Island ECN. He is a Co-Owner of Vivex Biologics. He serves as an Advisor at Lightkeeper. He has been an investor, founder, and senior executive in the financial technology industry for over 25 years. He began his career at Instinet, the world's first electronic stock exchange, where he rose to become the company's CEO and led its $464 million IPO in 2001. He was a co-founder of Efficient Frontiers, a consulting and research firm specializing in trading technology, regulation, and market structure. He was also the CEO of Majestic Research, a data-driven research firm catering to large global fund managers. Majestic was acquired by ITG (NYSE: ITG). Most recently, He ran Guggenheim Partners' venture capital business. Throughout his career, he has been an active investor, with a particular emphasis on financial technology, crowdfunding, "marketplaces" and data-driven companies. New York Magazine selected him as one of the Top New Yorkers for his leading role in redefining the financial marketplace and Institutional Investor profiled him as one of the top 30 individuals making the greatest impact on e-finance. Mr. Atkin received a BA in Economics from Tufts University.

Mr. Douglas Pepper serves as General Partner at ICONIQ Capital. Mr. Pepper is an Angel Investor. He serves as a General Partner at ICONIQ Growth. He serves as a Board Member at Reprise, BetterUp, Sanity and Braze. He serves as a Board Member at Aurora Solar. He served as Board Member at CyberGRX. He serves as an Advisor & Board Member at Writer. He served as Managing Director at Shasta Ventures. Mr. Pepper served as a General Partner at InterWest Partners. He was a Board Member of Lattice (Performance Management) and Beautiful.ai. He had been with InterWest since 2000, investing in SaaS, Mobile, and Consumer Internet companies. He was on the boards of Badgeville, INVIDI, Marketo (Nasdaq: MKTO), NewsCred, Skilljar, and Spredfast. He led InterWest's investment in Flurry, Mobee, Optimizely, and Totango. He is also a personal investor in leading seed funds, Homebrew and Freestyle Capital. Prior to joining InterWest, he worked in business development at Amazon.com. Before Amazon.com, he was a financial analyst at Goldman Sachs in New York, where he worked globally with technology clients. He received his B.A. from Dartmouth College and his M.B.A. from Stanford University. He was a Board Member of Totango and Varolii. He also serves as an Advisor at Camera IQ. He served as a Board Member at Sanity. He serves as an Advisor & Board Member at Writer.

Dow Chemical is a diversified global chemicals producer, formed in 2019 as a result of the DowDuPont merger and subsequent separations. The firm is a leading producer of several chemicals, including polyethylene, ethylene oxide, and silicone rubber. Its products have numerous applications in both consumer and industrial end markets.

Founded in 1994, Dow Venture Capital is a corporate venture capital arm of Dow based in Midland, Michigan. The firm prefers to invest in seed-stage, early-stage, and later-stage companies. The firm seeks to invest in business products, business services, information technology, healthcare, and TMT sectors across the United States, Canada, Europe, and Japan.

Developer of customer communications management software designed to create, manage and deliver business-critical customer communications. The company's suite includes client onboarding, statement composition, archiving, and content management that are used by banks, credit unions, wealth management, and investment brokerage firms, enabling them to transform their customer experience, improve operational efficiency and grow wallet share, using a set of integrated, omnichannel applications and services that digitize key customer touchpoints.
Founded in 1999, DragonVenture is a venture capital firm based in Menlo Park, California. The firm also provides advisory services.

Founded in 1985, Draper Associates is an early-stage venture capital firm backing visionary founders building the future. The firm invest from pre-seed to Series A and remain industry-agnostic and opportunistic, while gravitating toward transformative ideas in AI, robotics, biotech, robotics, defense, crypto, space, and deep tech. We're especially excited by the wild, the weird, and the world-changing ideas that seem impossible today but will be inevitable tomorrow and with a vision of fund the people crazy enough to change the world. The firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 2017, Draper Cygnus is a venture capital firm based in Buenos Aires, Argentina. The firm is focused on backing early-stage, high-impact companies with global potential. The firm specializes in deep tech, including artificial intelligence, biotechnology, materials, space, and cybersecurity, while also targeting opportunities in fintech and decentralization. The firm partners with visionary founders, particularly those from Latin America or US Latinos, to drive transformative innovation and scale on the international stage.

Founded in 1985, Draper Fisher Jurvetson Management was a venture capital firm based in Menlo Park, California. The firm was specialized in seed, early and growth stage investments. The firm primarily sought investments in commercial space exploration, robotics and sustainable transportation.
Draper Richards was a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm was founded in 1996 and seeks to invest in companies operating in the information technology sector.

Founded in 1997, Draper Triangle Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. The firm has additional offices in Ann Arbor and Columbus. The firm seeks to invest in software, robotics, medical devices, mobile applications, SaaS, big data, the Internet of things, and connected devices sectors.

Founded in 1990, Draper Venture Network is an alliance of independent venture capital firms based in San Mateo, California. The firm cooperates on investment diligence, marketing intelligence, corporate relationships, and co-investments.

Founded in 2008, Dreamit Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. The firm prefers to invest in seed-stage, early-stage, and later-stage companies operating in business products, business services, consumer products, consumer services, healthcare, cybersecurity, and real estate technology sectors across the United States.
Mr. Drew Bernard serves as a Partner at Oregon Venture Fund. He is an Angel Investor. He co-founded and served as Co-Chief Executive Officer at ActionSprout.

Dr. Dries Buytaert is the Co-founder and serves as Chief Technology Officer, Chief Strategy Officer & Executive Chairman at Acquia. He is the Founder and serves as Project Lead, President, and Board Member at Drupal. He also serves as a Board Observer of Seaters. He serves as an advisor at Reaction Commerce. He is an open-source developer and technology executive. He is the founder of Buytaert. He is the original creator and project lead for Drupal, an open-source platform for building websites and digital experiences. He is also co-founder and chief technology officer of Acquia, a venture-backed technology company. Acquia provides an open cloud platform to many large organizations, which helps them build, deliver, and optimize digital experiences. A Young Global Leader at the World Economic Forum, he holds a Ph.D. in computer science and engineering from Ghent University and a Licentiate Computer Science (MSc) from the University of Antwerp. He was named CTO of the Year by the Massachusetts Technology Leadership Council, New England Entrepreneur of the Year by Ernst & Young, and a Young Innovator by MIT Technology Review. He blogs frequently on Drupal, open source, startups, business, and the future at buytaert.net. He has a Ph.D. (Doctor of Philosophy) in Computer Science & Engineering from Ghent University. He served as an advisor in recreation commerce

Founded in 2012, Driscoll Holdings is a growth equity firm based in West Conshohocken, Pennsylvania. The firm prefers to invest in growth-stage companies through buyouts. The firm seeks to invest in consumer products, consumer services, and manufacturing sectors in Mid Atlantic.
Founded in 2014, DRW Venture Capital is a corporate venture capital arm of DRW Holding based in Chicago, Illinois. The firm focuses on finance and enterprise technology sectors.

Founded in 2020, Dry Line Partners is a private equity firm based in San Antonio, Texas. The firm seeks to invest in North American, United States, Canada, Australia, New Zealand, and Europe-based companies operating in the b2b, and technology sectors.

DryShips was engaged in the shipping industry in the United States. The company used to operate as a provider of dry bulk commodities transportation services for the steel, electric utility, construction and agri-food industries. It used to operate through the dry bulk carrier and offshore support services divisions. Through this division, it used to operate as a provider of offshore support services to the offshore energy industry. The company used to own a fleet of Panamax dry bulk vessels, Newcastlemax dry bulk vessels, Aframax tankers and gas carriers.
Developer of a semantics web technology. The company offers a range of products in order to facilitate collaborative semantics database and sharing the data on application design.

DSM-Firmenich is a global science-based company formed in 2023 through the merger of DSM, a Dutch nutrition, health and sustainable living player and Switzerland-based Firmenich, the third-largest player in the flavor and fragrance market. The company serves a wide range of end-consumer markets providing nutrition solutions ranging from animal feed to medical and early-life nutrition, fragrances for personal, home and laundry-care brands, prestige perfumes, and other ingredients for food and beverage, home and personal care. DSM-Firmenich has nearly 30,000 employees, with more than 2,000 scientists and engineers spread across 15 research and development facilities.

Founded in 2001, dsm-firmenich Venturing is the corporate venture capital arm of DSM-Firmenich. The firm invests in early stage health, nutrition, personal care, food and beverage ingredients in North America, Europe and Israel.
Founded in 2009, DST Global is a venture capital firm based in Grand Cayman, Cayman Islands. The firm seeks to invest in information technology, mobile, internet of things & e-commerce sectors.

Founded in 2015, DTCP Growth is a growth equity investment arm of DTCP based in Hamburg, Germany. The firm focuses on investing in B2B SaaS and artificial intelligence infrastructure sectors across Europe, Israel, and the United States.

Provider of audio technology solutions intended to make the world sound better. The company offers high-definition multi-channel audio solutions for a variety of devices in digital surround sound formats used for both individual, commercial and theatrical applications, and they are also engaged in providing transcoding, encoding, blue-ray authoring, and other related solutions to mobile, home, and industrial markets.

The Company commercializes materials, products and production processes for the alternative energy generation, energy storage and information technology markets.

Developer of environmental-treatment systems for groundwater and air.
