Innovation Capital Advisors was a venture capital firm that seeks to invest the SaaS information technologies, e-commerce platforms, human resource and education software, healthcare IT, media, business information services, advanced chemicals and material sectors. The firm was based in Wilmington, Delaware.

Founded in 2011, Innovation Factory is a non-profit business accelerator based in Hamilton, Canada. The firm is funded by the Government of Ontario to accelerate Ontario-based companies. The firm caters to the advanced manufacturing, clean tech, information technology, life sciences, healthcare, and social innovation sectors in Ontario.

Founded in 2014, Innovation Martlesham is an accelerator based in Ipswich, United Kingdom. The firm aims to nurture technology companies in their early stages, providing rent-free office space and Comms for at least six months as well as expert commercial advice from mentors who can provide support to help develop their businesses. The firm offers a 6-month structured program of activities focused on growth.

Founded in 2018, the Innovation Network Corporation of Japan is a growth equity firm based in Tokyo, Japan. The firm invests in the materials & chemicals, electronic devices, industrial machinery, energy, transportation & automotive, consumer goods & retail, health, medicine, information technology, business services, content, infrastructure, and intellectual property sectors.

Founded in 2002, Innovation Partnerships is a venture capital firm based in Ann Arbor, Michigan. The firm seeks to support University of Michigan (U-M) licensed startups operating in the technology sector. The firm also is an incubator and provides mentorship and office spaces. The firm also seeks to invest in those early-stage startups via the Accelerate Blue Fund.

A development stage biopharmaceutical company engaged in pre-clinical testing of one of its product candidates and out-source clinical trials, pre-clinical testing and the manufacture of clinical materials to third parties.

Founded in 2005, Innovative Capital Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Menlo Park, California. The firm prefers to invest in the information technology, software-as-a-service (SaaS), analytics, and life sciences sectors across California.

Manufacturer of structural composite panels. The company manufactures and sells lightweight structural composite products utilizing fiber reinforced thermoplastics. Its products are applied in various industries, including affordable housing and transportation.

Founded in 1996, InnoVentures was a venture capital firm based in Salt Lake City, Utah. The firm preferred to invest in early-stage information technology and service companies seeking growth capital to fund marketing activities.
Founded in 2008, InnoVentures Lab is an accelerator/incubator firm based in Beverly, Massachusetts. The firm seeks to invest in the clean technology and biotech sectors.

Innovus Pharmaceuticals Inc is engaged in the healthcare industry. It is a specialty pharmaceutical company engaged in the commercialization, licensing and development of safe and effective non-prescription medicine and consumer care products to improve men's and women's health and vitality and respiratory diseases. Innovus distributes OTC medicines and consumer and health products directly, through commercial partners to primary care physicians, urologists, gynecologists and therapists, and directly to consumers through its on-line channels, retailers, and wholesalers.

Inocap Gestion is an asset manager and venture capital firm based in Paris, France and specializes in investment in the small and medium-sized companies. The firm was founded in 2007 and it seeks to invest in the biotechnology, medical, electronic, energy, information technology, telecommunication, industrial good and service sectors.

Inovalon Holdings provides cloud-based analytics and platforms for healthcare providers and pharmaceutical firms. Its platform can be used to identify gaps in care, quality, data integrity, and financial performance. The primary capabilities of Inovalon's big data platform are data integration, advanced analytics, intervention platforms, and business processing. It maintains a registry of data compiled from several sources, including electronic health records, claims, and pharmacies. Analytics run on this data can determine the presence of a disease, gaps in clinical outcomes, or medical compliance.

Inphi is a provider of high-speed analog and mixed-signal semiconductor solutions for the communications, data center, and computing markets. The company's semiconductor solutions are designed to address bandwidth bottlenecks in networks, maximize throughput, and minimize latency in computing environments. For peak performance, Inphi works with system vendors to develop proprietary component, channel, and system simulation, models. These models are used to predict system performance prior to fabricating the semiconductor.

Inpixon is an Indoor Intelligence company. Its solutions secure, digitize and optimize their indoor spaces with positioning, mapping and analytics products. The company's segment includes Indoor Intelligence, Saves and Shoom. It generates maximum revenue from the Indoor Intelligence segment. Geographically, it derives a majority of its revenue from the United States.

Inseego is into the design and development of fixed and mobile wireless solutions (4G and 5G NR), industrial Internet of things and cloud solutions for enterprises, service providers, small and medium-sized businesses, governments, and consumers around the globe. Its products and services include intelligent mobile hotspots, wireless routers for IoT applications, USB modems, integrated telematics and mobile tracking devices, which are supported by applications software and cloud services designed to enable customers to easily analyze data insights and configure and manage their hardware. It generates maximum revenue from the United States and Canada. The company also has a presence in Australia and Europe (including the United Kingdom).

Founded in 2011, Inspovation Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Los Altos, California. The firm focuses on start-ups and early-stage investments across the healthcare, information technology, and internet services sectors located in the San Francisco Bay Area.

Investors: Institute for Commercialization of Florida Technology
Description: Founded in 2007, Florida Institute for the Commercialization of Public Research is a not-for-profit venture capital firm based in Clearwater, Florida. The firm seeks to make venture capital, seed-stage, debt or equity and angel investments. The firm prefers investment in the technology and healthcare sectors.

Integra Lifesciences Holdings is a New Jersey-based medical equipment company focused on developing products for regenerative therapy, extremity orthopedics, and neurosurgical applications. The firm is organized into two primary segments: Codman specialty surgical and tissue technologies. Codman specialty surgical generates maximum revenue from its segmental operations. Integra serves Europe, Asia Pacific, and the rest of the world whilst it derives key revenue from domestic sales.

Integrated DNA Technologies is a manufacturer and supplier of custom nucleic acid products for the life sciences industry. The company's primary business is the production of custom oligonucleotides for molecular biology applications and has developed proprietary technologies for genomics applications such as next-generation sequencing, CRISPR genome editing, qPCR, and RNA interference. Its products used in diagnostic tests for many forms of cancer and most inherited and infectious diseases.

Intel is a leading digital chipmaker, focused on the design and manufacturing of microprocessors for the global personal computer and data center markets. Intel pioneered the x86 architecture for microprocessors and was the prime proponent of Moore's law for advances in semiconductor manufacturing. Intel remains the market share leader in central processing units in both the PC and server end markets. Intel has also been expanding into new adjacencies, such as communications infrastructure, automotive, and the Internet of Things. Further, Intel expects to leverage its chip manufacturing capabilities into an outsourced foundry model where it constructs chips for others.

Founded in 1991, Intel Capital is a venture capital arm of Intel based in Santa Clara, California. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the cloud, silicon, devices, and frontier sectors.

Intellicheck is a trusted industry leader in technology solutions that stop identity theft and fraud with real-time identification authentication and age verification. The company makes it possible for its clients to increase revenues, improve customer service and increase operational efficiencies. Under the new direction, the company is focused on partnering with banks credit card issuers and retailers to prevent fraud. It derives revenue through sales of systems, subscription fees, sale of software upgrades and extended maintenance programs.

Intelligent Venture Capital Management was a venture capital firm based in Aachen, Germany. The firm preferred to invest in the pharmaceuticals, biotechnology, medical products, bioinformatics, information, and communication technology, information technology, and software sectors.

Intellisync was the provider of mobile software and platforms to large enterprises, mobile operators, software providers and device manufacturers. The company provided seamless synchronisation, secure wireless email, device control and mobility management software that connects nearly every device, data source and application available on the market. The company sought to expand its business operations through mergers and acquisitions. The company was acquired by Nokia on February 10, 2006.

Provider of financial market data and analytics services. The company provides portfolio management and valuation, research and analysis, trading, wealth management, sales and marketing and client service activities.

Interactive Intelligence Group is a computer software company that specializes in workforce management, business process automation, cloud communications, unified communications, outbound dialer, enterprise collaboration and media servers. The company was founded in 1994 and is headquartered in Indianapolis, Indiana. It seeks to acquire other companies that develop software for financial institutions or provide cloud-based services and interactive intelligence purecloud communication services.

InterCall is a provider of telephony, messaging, conferencing and collaboration tools to various businesses. Its products help in scheduling meetings, starting conference calls, sharing screens, streaming video for live camera, webcasting and unified communication among others. The company was founded in 1991 and is headquartered in Chicago, Illinois. It seeks to acquire other companies that provide software and related services to the media industry and collaboration services.

InterCloud Systems Inc is a provider of networking orchestration and automation for the Internet of things (IOT), software-defined networking (SDN) and network function virtualization (NFV) environments. The company operates in three operating segments - as an application and infrastructure provider, and professional services provider.The applications and infrastructure segment provides engineering and professional consulting services and voice, data and optical solutions. The professional services segment provides outsourced services to the wireless and wireline industry and information technology industry. The company continues to grow by making periodic small acquisitions.

Intercontinental Exchange is a vertically integrated operator of financial exchanges and provides ancillary data products. Though the company is probably best known for its ownership of the New York Stock Exchange, which it acquired in 2013, ICE operates a large derivatives exchange, too. The company's largest commodity futures product is the ICE Brent crude futures contract. In addition to the exchanges business, which is about 54% of net revenue, Intercontinental Exchange has used a series of acquisitions to create its mortgage technology business (22% of net revenue) and fixed-income and data services segment (24% of net revenue).

InterKnowlogy is a global technology leader specializing in the design, implementation, and delivery of innovative solutions leveraging both current and emerging Microsoft technologies. The InterKnowlogy reputation is built upon the ability to enable clients to capitalize on their strategic investments, maximize efficiency, and focus on their core business competencies.For the past 10 years, InterKnowlogy has focused on remaining ahead of the curve in technology and process. For the past 4 years, we have delivered dozens of large WPF, Silverlight, Surface, and Windows 7 Touch applications to clients across the country. It is our goal to remain the leader in application development around these technologies. Technology is driving forward at a breakneck pace. The same can be said for our InterKnowlogy engineers who are capable of moving at that same speed. With InterKnowlogy, clients can take advantage of InterKnowlogy's ability to live and move with the innovation edge, without taking on the risk, training, and time required to develop their own teams internally.InterKnowlogy is a team of modern technology architects in all aspects of the term. They understand the business need, the user mindset, the physical space, the data structure, and transfer it all into a cohesive, well-executed and visualized solution. Being capable of that end result-an engaging visual transformation of provided data-is the InterKnowlogy difference. InterKnowlogy unlocks groundbreaking barriers that have existed between people and technology by allowing users the ability to manipulate objects in touch screens with a single swipe of a finger. More so, InterKnowlogy thoughtfully has the end user in mind in building human and sometimes emotional experiences that leave lasting and longing impressions on our clients end user. InterKnowlogy currently sits on the eBusiness, .NET, and the US Sales PACs, providing great contacts and access into some of Microsoft's most exciting and dynamic business and technology teams. Being a leader in both the technologies and business thought arena propels InterKnowlogy into the highly sought after position of being visionaries in our field.Based in Carlsbad, CA, InterKnowlogy works with customers around the globe, facilitated by an agile methodology and clear client management strategy that keeps everyone on the same page throughout the engagement.

Provider of automobile security services. The company's automobile security services include vehicle lock, accident protection and related services, enabling the automobile manufacturing industry to access a wide range of services for their operation and product building.

Founded in 2012, Intermountain Ventures is the corporate venture arm of Intermountain Healthcare based in Salt Lake City, Utah. The firm prefers to invest in early and growth-stage innovative companies operating in the healthcare sector.

Founded in 1994, International Biotechnology Trust is a venture capital firm based in Wales, United Kingdom. The firm seeks to make early-stage investments and has a preference for the biotechnology sector.

IBM looks to be a part of every aspect of an enterprise's IT needs. The company primarily sells software, IT services, consulting, and hardware. IBM operates in 175 countries and employs approximately 350,000 people. The company has a robust roster of 80,000 business partners to service 5,200 clients, which includes 95% of all Fortune 500. While IBM is a B2B company, IBM's outward impact is substantial. For example, IBM manages 90% of all credit card transactions globally and is responsible for 50% of all wireless connections in the world.

International Flavors & Fragrances is the largest specialty ingredients producer globally. The company sells ingredients for the food, beverage, health, household goods, personal care, and pharmaceutical industries. The company makes proprietary formulations, partnering with customers to deliver custom solutions. The nourish segment, which generates roughly half of its revenue, is a leading flavor producer and also sells texturants, plant-based proteins, and other ingredients. The health and biosciences business, which generates around one-fourth of revenue, is a global leader in probiotics and enzymes. IFF is also one of the leading fragrance producers in the world.

International Paper manufactures packaging products and cellulose fibers. It accounts for roughly one-third of the North American corrugated packaging market. Though it has operations in Brazil, India, and China, more than three-fourths of its sales come from North America. International Paper serves a variety of end markets, including industrial, consumer products, and manufacturing.
Provider of surf resorts, camps, and guided surf tours based in Henderson, Nevada.

Provider of venture capital funds for internet and e- health holding start- up companies in healthcare sectors. The company focuses on healthcare insurance products, web based business-to-business transactions and customer support and procurement. The company provides ways for small businesses to buy health insurance over the internet.

Interpump Group is an Italy-based company that manufactures and markets high-pressure piston pumps and hydraulic products. The company operates through two segments. Its water jetting segment manufactures high- and ultra-high-pressure pumps. Its hydraulic segment manufactures power take-offs, cylinders, componentry engineering, hydraulic distributors, valves, and hoses and fittings. The company owns production facilities in Italy, the U.S., Germany, China, India, Brazil, Bulgaria, Romania, and South Korea. The company has a global presence, with the domestic Italian market accounting for a fraction of its revenue.

Intersections is a provider of identity risk management, privacy protection and other subscription based services for consumers. It specializes in identity theft protection services, credit monitoring, identity validation, breach remediation, health monitoring platforms, internet data risks and credit reports among others. The company was founded in 1996 and is headquartered in Chantilly, Virginia. It seeks to acquire other companies whose businesses will complement its existing operations.

Founded in 1985, Intersouth Partners is a venture capital firm based in Durham, North Carolina. The firm prefers to invest in companies operating in the communication, internet, digital media, semiconductor, software, biotechnology, medical technology, and pharmaceutical sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Intertainment Media is a provider of technology and marketing services. The company operates as a technology incubators and is focused on developing, nurturing and investing in both North American and global technologies and companies whose platform's provide distinct services for brands and consumers. It also owns and operates a number of key properties and divisions. The company was founded in 2006 and is headquartered in Richmond Hill, Canada. Intertainment Media implements an aggressive acquisition and expansion strategy across all its business segments.

InterWest Healthcare Partners was a venture capital arm of InterWest Partners based in San Francisco, California. The firm prefers to invest in the healthcare, biotechnology, pharmaceutical, healthcare IT, personalized medicines, and medical device sectors.

Founded in 1979, InterWest Partners is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm seeks to invest in information technology and healthcare sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

inTest is a supplier of innovative test and process solutions for use in manufacturing and testing across a wide range of markets including automotive, defense/aerospace, industrial, medical, semiconductor and telecommunications. It manages the business as two operating segments, thermal products and electromechanical semiconductor products. The thermal segment designs, manufactures and sells thermal test and thermal process products while; ems segment designs, manufactures and sells semiconductor test products. It sells its products worldwide.

Intuit is a provider of small-business accounting software (QuickBooks), personal tax solutions (TurboTax), and professional tax offerings (Lacerte). Founded in the mid-1980s, Intuit controls the majority of US market share for small-business accounting and do-it-yourself tax-filing software.

Founded in 2007, Invati Capital was a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm preferred to invest in information technology hardware, medical products (non-invasive), sensor and sensor equipment for various industries, and industrial products with an emphasis on materials technology sectors based in the Bay Area, Massachusetts, and California regions.

Inventure Capital A/S was an early stage venture capital firm that seeked to make investments in the information and communication technology, life sciences and clean technology sectors. The firm was headquartered in Denmark.
Founded in 1998, Inventures Group is a venture capital firm based in Palo Alto, California. The firm seeks to invest in the information technology, SaaS, and technology sectors.
Provider of women's healthcare products. The company manufactures health maintenance and home self-test diagnostic products for the diabetes, women's health and nutritional supplement markets.

Founded in 1998, Invest Equity Management Consulting is a private equity firm based in Vienna, Austria. The firm focuses on companies operating in the consumer product, manufacturing, food, beverage, building material, industrial equipment, business service, chemical, communication, electronic, industrial technology, healthcare, information technology, and retail sectors.

Invest NI is a business development and venture capital firm based in Belfast, Ireland. The firm caters to the financial services, energy, software, clean energy, connected health, meat and poultry, transport and travel, textile and clothing, materials handling, construction, electronics, food, print and packaging, furniture, fish and seafood and bakery sectors.
Invest Northern Ireland has contributed £2.6m to establish a seed accelerator.
Founded in 2011, Investa is a venture capital firm based in Reykjavik, Iceland. The firm seeks to invest in the B2B & information technology sector based in the Iceland region.
InveStar Capital was a venture capital firm that was based in San Jose, California. InveStar preferred to invest in semiconductors, communications and networking and internet infrastructure sectors.

Investcorp Technology Partners is the private equity arm of alternative investment manager Investcorp headquartered in London, United Kingdom. The firm seeks to invest in technology companies based in Europe.

Provider of online investment-analysis services. The company is an independent provider of investment-performance analytics, manager research, and reporting technology. The company serves investment consultants and advisors, institutional investors and asset managers.

Founded in 2008, InvestMichigan! Program is a mezzanine firm based in Farmington Hills, Michigan. The firm provides mezzanine and growth capital investments. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the industrial manufacturing, business services, healthcare, technology, and consumer products sectors.

Founded in 1916, Investor is a private equity firm based in Stockholm, Sweden. The firm seeks to make a strong and sustainable business. The firm aims to invest in companies operating in advanced manufacturing, infrastructure, the internet of things, SaaS, manufacturing, clean technology & climate technology based in the Northern European region.

Investview operates a financial technology services company, offering several different lines of business, provides research, education and investment tools designed to assist the self-directed investor in successfully navigating the financial markets. The services include research, trade alerts and live trading rooms that consist of instruction in equities, options, FOREX, ETFs, binary options, crowdfunding and cryptocurrency mining services and sector education. The firm also provides education and software applications to assist the individual in debt reduction, increased savings, budgeting and proper tax management.

Founded in 2019, Invictus Growth Partners is a private equity firm based in San Mateo, California. The firm prefers to invest in cloud software, financial technology, cybersecurity, SaaS, artificial intelligence & information technology sectors based in the United States & Israel region. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 1997, Invision is a private equity investment firm based in Zug, Switzerland. The firm seeks to invest in healthcare, medical technology, information technology, software, education, consumer & luxury goods, e-commerce, industry, and other service sectors.

Invitae operates as a genetic information company in the diagnostic and research industry. The company's tests include multiple genes associated with hereditary cancer, neurological disorders, cardiovascular disorders, pediatric disorders, metabolic disorders and other hereditary conditions.

Provider of fixed-line telecom services. The company provides telecommunications services like entertainment and multimedia services from digital and high definition television to internet and telephony services.

Life Technologies Corporation was a global biotechnology tools company dedicated to improving the human condition. The company worked across biological spectrum, working to advance personalized medicine, regenerative science, molecular diagnostics, agricultural and environmental research. The company was acquired by Thermo Fisher Scientific on 2/4/2014.

Founded in 2008, Invus Opportunities is an investment firm based in New York, New York. The firm focuses on non-control, private company investments and typically makes equity investments of $10-50M in a range of industries including fintech, marketplace/eCommerce, healthcare, SaaS, and other tech-enabled sectors.

Ion Beam Applications develops and manufactures medical devices and software solutions. The firm operates in two segments, proton therapy and other accelerators and dosimetry. Proton therapy and other accelerators business contribute to the majority of sales. It offers solutions for precision cancer treatment through the use of proton beams, as well as cyclotrons used for the production of radioisotopes and industrial accelerators for sterilization and ionization. The dosimetry business sells measurement and quality assurance instruments for radiotherapy and medical imaging. The firm operates in three geographical areas, Belgium, the United States and the rest of the world.
Founded in 2016, IOVC is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm prefers to invest in startups operating in the software sector.
Founded in 2013, Iowa City Capital Partners is a family office based in Iowa City, Iowa.

Founded in 2001, IP Group is a venture capital investment firm based in London, United Kingdom. The firm seeks to invest in the clean technology, life sciences, and deep technology sectors. IP Group has been backing and growing science and technology-based businesses for over 20 years, supporting visionary companies with access to capital as well as the essential expertise and insight that help accelerate the impact of science for a better future.

Provider of enterprises and telecommunications carriers with cloud-based mobility management and networks connectivity services. The company offers enterprises cross-device, cross-network internet connectivity services, along with connection policy enforcement, real time reporting and analysis of all mobile network activity.
Founded in 1986, IPGL is a family office firm based in London, United Kingdom.
Founded in 2000, IPV Capital is a venture capital firm and is based in Beijing, China. The firm invests in startups operating in the semiconductor industry.

iQIYI is an online entertainment service provider in China. It is primarily engaged in providing a variety of services encompassing internet video, live broadcasting, online games, online literature, animations, e-commerce and social media platform. The company produces original video content and distributes appealing professionally-produced content, partner-generated content, and user-generated content. It also offers a diverse collection of internet video content that appeals to users from broad demographics. The company's revenue is generated from membership services and online advertising services. The company earns the majority of its revenue from China

IQVIA is the result of the 2016 merger of Quintiles, a leading global contract research organization, and IMS Health, a leading healthcare data and analytics provider. The research & development segment focuses primarily on providing outsourced late-stage clinical trials for pharmaceutical, device and diagnostic firms. The technology and analytics segment provides aggregated information and technology services to clients in the healthcare industry, including pharmaceutical companies, providers, payers and policymakers, as well as data and analytics capabilities for clinical trials, including virtual trials. The company also has a small contract sales business.

IRIDEX is involved in the development, manufacturing and marketing of laser-based medical systems, delivery devices and consumable instrumentation for ophthalmology. Its products include lasers, laser delivery devices, glaucoma devices, retinal surgical instruments and veterinary and ENT products. The firm also powers its products with its proprietary Micropulse technology. The company operates in only one reportable segment, ophthalmology. It derives revenues from the sale of consoles, delivery devices, consumables, services and support activities. The geographical segments of the company include the United States, which drives maximum revenue, Europe and the Americas, excluding the U.S. and Asia/Pacific Rim.
Founded in 2012, IrishAngels is an angel group based in Chicago, Illinois. The firm seeks to invest in software, consumer products, and medical devices.

iRobot Ventures is the corporate venture capital arm of iRobot based in Bedford, Massachusetts. The firm prefers to invest in seed-stage, early-stage, and later-stage companies operating in consumer technology, service-based business models, recurring revenue streams, cloud services & infrastructure, computer vision, localization & mapping, artificial intelligence, robotics, mobility & manipulation sectors.

Founded in 2009, Iron Creek Partners is a private equity investment firm based in Santa Fe, New Mexico. The firm seeks to invest in software and technology-enabled services sectors such as SaaS, education, data, media, communications, managed service providers, business process outsourcing, HR outsourcing services, Healthcare IT, and related payments and litigation.

Founded in 1986, Ironwood Capital is a private equity firm based in Avon, Connecticut. The firm prefers to invest in waste & environmental services, aerospace & defense, transportation & logistics, facilities services, business services, manufacturing, and healthcare sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Iroquois Capital Group (Iroquois) is a merchant banking and investment banking firm led by business executives who have been chief executive officers, owners and operators of businesses, with extensive finance and mergers and acquisitions experience. The firm works primarily with companies in the healthcare and financial services industries, and often invest their own capital and the capital of it's investors in these companies. Within the investment banking division, Iroquois offers services in the areas of private capital raising, acquisition capital, owner liquidity, refinancing, and senior and subordinated debt.

iSherpa Capital was a venture capital firm that specializes in investments in start-ups and early-stage companies nationwide. The firm seeked to invest in the wireless, media and entertainment industries, and supporting technologies. It was founded in 1999 and is based in Greenwood Village, Colorado.
Operator of an investment management firm based in Henderson, Nevada.
Operator of a holding company. The company manufactures and distributes agricultural products such as fertilizers, potash, phosphate fertilizers, phosphoric acid and flame retardants.

Founded in 1965, Israel Innovation Authority is an investment arm of the Israeli Government based in Jerusalem, Israel. The firm prefers to create an infrastructure to support diverse industries, develop tools and programs that suit the needs of the industry, and budget and finance high-risk projects and products. The firm offers various programs, grants and investments to early-stage companies.

Founded in 1857, ITOCHU Corp is a group of businesses that engage in importing, exporting, and trading various products. The traded goods include textiles, machinery, metals, minerals, energy, chemicals, food, general products, realty, and information and communications technology. The largest segments by net profit to the group are food; energy and chemicals. The food segment pursues efficiency-oriented operations from production and distribution to retail in all areas of food from raw materials to finished products both in Japan and overseas. The energy and chemicals segment trades crude oil and oil derivatives and chemicals.

Founded in 2000, ITOCHU Technology Ventures is a venture capital investment firm based in Tokyo, Japan. The firm seeks to invest in companies operated in internet services in the b2b and b2 sectors based in Japan and the United States.

Itron provides solutions that measure, manage and analyze energy and water use. It operates under the Itron brand and manages and reports under three operating segments: device solutions, networked solutions, and outcomes. The device solutions segment includes hardware products used for measurement, control or sense that do not have communications capability embedded for use with broader Itron systems. The networked Solutions segment includes a combination of communicating devices, network infrastructure and associated application software designed and sold as a complete solution. The outcome segment includes their value-added, enhanced software and services which manage, organize, analyze and interpret data to improve decision-making and maximize operational profitability.

ITT is a diversified manufacturer of engineered critical components and customized technology solutions predominantly for the transportation, industrial and energy markets. The company's products include brake pads, shock absorbers, pumps, valves, connectors, switches and others. Its operating segments are, Motion Technologies (MT), Industrial Process (IP) and Connect & Control Technologies (CCT). The majority of the revenue is generated from the Motion Technologies segment which is a manufacturer of brake pads, shims, shock absorbers, energy absorption components and sealing technologies. Geographically, the company generates the majority of its revenue from North America and also has its presence in South America, Europe, Asia, the Middle East and Africa.

Founded in 2000, iVisionary Ventures is a private equity firm based in Lexington, Kentucky. The firm specializes in focused industries including retail, business service, technology, real estate, hospitality, health, and wellness sectors.

Founded in 1980, IVP is a venture capital investment firm based in Menlo Park, California. The firm seeks to invest in artificial intelligence, consumer, digital health, enterprise infrastructure, fintech, cryptocurrency, gaming, and go-to-market sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 2002, Ivy Capital Partners is a private equity firm based in Montvale, New Jersey. The firm seeks to invest in healthcare companies including sports medicine, rehabilitation products, musculoskeletal, and trauma sectors.

Provider of equipment and applications for computer network maintenance. The company's products and services include test applications, test hardware, security and visibility products, training services, testing as a service and test consulting service by enhancing security resilience for various enterprises, service providers, and nanoelectromechanical systems (NEMS). The company seeks to expand its business operations through mergers and acquisitions.

Ixys is a manufacturer of power semiconductors. The Company is engaged in the development, manufacture and marketing of power semiconductors, mixed-signal integrated circuits, application specific integrated circuits, microcontrollers, systems and radio frequency power semiconductors.

IZEA Worldwide is a create economy, specializing in providing software solutions and professional services that connect brands with a broad spectrum of social influencers and content creators. It's a pioneering marketing technology company that offers cutting-edge software and professional services, empowering brands to engage and transact with a diverse range of social influencers and content creators. Its brands are The Creator Marketplace, IZEA Flex, and Full-Service Influencer Marketing. Its geographic areas are North America, APAC, and other.

J&J Snack Foods manufactures, markets, and distributes snack foods and beverages to food service and retail supermarket outlets. The company's products include frozen beverages, juice, fruit bars, sorbet, cakes, and cookies that are distributed to various consumers, including restaurants, supermarkets, convenience stores, universities, theaters, and theme parks. The company operates in three business segments: food service, which sells snacks, desserts, and baked goods at the point-of-sale; retail supermarkets, which sells frozen and prepackaged products to supermarkets; and frozen beverages, which sells frozen beverages under brands Icee, Slush puppie, and Parrot ice in the United States, Mexico, and Canada.
J. & W. Seligman & Company was an investment bank based in New York, New York. The firm was acquired by Ameriprise Financial in November 2008.

J.B. Hunt Transport Services ranks among the top surface transportation companies in North America by revenue. Its primary operating segments are intermodal delivery, which uses the Class I rail carriers for the underlying line-haul movement of its owned containers (48% of sales in 2023), dedicated trucking services that provide customer-specific fleet needs (28%), for-hire truckload (6%), heavy goods final-mile delivery (7%) and asset-light truck brokerage (11%).
Mr. J.D. Fagan is an Angel Investor. Mr. Fagan is a Data Scientist at Sqor Sports. Prior to this he was a Software Engineer at FCI Communications.

Founded in 1946, J.H. Whitney Capital Partners is a private equity investment firm based in New Canaan, Connecticut. The firm prefers to invest through means of buyouts, debt, recapitalization, and growth capital. The firm prefers to invest in consumer, healthcare, and specialty manufacturing sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

J.P. Morgan Chase (Global Special Opportunities Group) was an investment arm of JPMorgan Chase Bank, National Association. It specialized in investments in junior capital including subordinated debt and mezzanine debt. It was founded in 2005 and was headquartered in New York, New York. It used to expand its business through investment, mergers and acquisitions.
J20 Ventures was an early-stage & later-stage venture capital firm based in New York, New York.

Mr. Jack Abraham is a Co-Founder and serves as Chief Executive Officer and Managing Partner at Atomic Labs. He is a Co-Founder of Replicant. He also served as an Advisor at Felicis. He is a Co-Founder of Sauron. He is a Co-Founder and serves as Chairman at Indomo. He is also the Founder and serves as Investor at Found. He is an Angel Investor. He is a Co-Founder and serves as a Board Member at Villa. He is a Co-Founder and co-owner and serves as a Board Member at Raydiant. He serves as an Advisor at Nue Life. He is a Co-Founder and serves as an Executive Chairman at Homebound. He is a Co-Founder and investor at Hims & Hers Health. He founded Atomic in 2012, inventing the studio fund model, to develop a better way to build companies, and now is founding companies out of a $150M second fund. Atomic and its companies have raised over $600M from some of Silicon Valley's most respected investors and as of 2019, two out of ten of the fastest-growing companies in San Francisco are Atomic companies. Before Atomic, he was the founder and CEO of Milo.com, which was acquired by eBay in December 2010 when he was 24 years old. He is also an angel investor in Pinterest, Postmates, Uber, Flatiron Health, and Doctor on Demand, among others. He is an advisor to Felicis Ventures and has previously advised John Donahoe, the former CEO of eBay, who now leads ServiceNow. He has been named one of the "100 Most Creative People in Business" by Fast Company and has made Forbes' "30 under 30" list two times. He attended The Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania, studying Technological Entrepreneurship.

Jack Henry is a leading provider of core processing and complementary services, such as electronic funds transfer, payment processing, and loan processing for us banks and credit unions, with a focus on small and midsize banks. Jack Henry serves almost 1,000 banks and over 700 credit unions.
Mr. Jack Larson is an Angel Investor.

Jack Nathan Medical is a healthcare company that is improving access for millions of patients by co-locating physician and ancillary medical services, conveniently inside Walmart stores. The company generates the majority of its revenues from license fees, which are charged in exchange for the right to use its brand name and the licensed premises. Its geographical segments are Canada, which accounts for the vast majority of revenue; Mexico and China.
Founded in 2004, JAL Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Herzliya, Israel. The firm seeks to invest in software, e-commerce, internet, and communication companies.

Jalia Ventures was a venture capital firm which was involved in impact investing and provided expansion capital to companies owned by entrepreneurs who had a social and sustainable mission to make a positive impact on underserved US communities. It invested in revenue generating companies across all industries and applied a hands-on approach to assist the entrepreneurs. The firm was headquartered in New York, New York.

Mr. James Altucher is a Co-Founder of BitZumi. Mr. Altucher is an Angel Investor. He was the Founder and Chief Executive Officer of Reset. He was also the C.E.O. of Stockpickr.com, Managing Director of Formula Capital, Partner of 212 Ventures, and Founder and C.E.O. of Vaultus Mobile. Altucher graduated from Cornell University with a bachelor's degree in computer science in 1989. He later attended Carnegie Mellon University as a doctoral student in computer science. He also served asan Advisor at DoubleRock.

Mr. James Breyer is the Founder and serves as Chief Executive Officer at Breyer Capital. Mr. Breyer serves as a Board Member at MSD Acquisition. He serves as Board Member at Blackstone. He served as a Board Member at Atropos Health. He serves as Board Member at Blackstone. He is a Co-Owner of the Boston Celtics. He serves as an Investment Advisory Board Member at Xfund. He serves as an Advisor at Vida. He is a Co-Founder and Board Member of EDO and a Board Member of GNL Québec. He served as a Board Member at UM and Wickr. He previously served as Co-Chairman at IDG Capital. He has been an investor in over 40 consumer internet/technology companies that have completed successful public offerings or mergers, including Facebook, Etsy, Legendary, Datalogix, and Marvel Entertainment.
