It generates a majority of its revenue from the Europe segment which consists of its activities to develop secure solutions for networked machines using a combined portfolio of hardware, software, and loT services in Europe. The business segment focuses on the company's proprietary technologies and solutions, in particular for industrial automation, 5G connectivity, and communication solutions as well as medical technology and smart energy markets. Key revenue is derived from Germany.

Founded in 2017, Konvoy Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Cambridge, Massachusetts. The firm invests in e-sports, infrastructure technology, tools, platforms, and video gaming sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 1977, Konza Valley Capital is a private equity investment firm headquartered in Overland Park, Kansas. The firm prefers to invest in lower middle-market companies operating in the manufacturing, service, distribution, retail, and technology-related sectors in Midwestern-based companies. The firm provides primarily later-stage expansion financing, acquisitions, ownership transitions, management buyouts, turnarounds, and recapitalization opportunities.

Investor of companies in agrochemicals, finance, telecommunications and asset management sectors. The company actively invests in agrochemicals through Makhteshim Agan Industries, in finance through Credit Suisse, in telecommunications and technology through its holdings in Microwave Networks, in asset management through Epsilon Investment House and in venture capital through Koor Corporate Venture Capital.

Founded in 1986, Korea Investment Partners is a venture capital firm based in Seoul, South Korea. The firm seeks to invest in B2B, media, healthcare, information technology, manufacturing, life science, oncology, mobile, infrastructure, augmented reality, industrials, beauty, real estate technology, mortgage technology, advertisement technology, advanced manufacturing, electronic sports, gaming, the internet of things, micro mobility & mobility technology sectors.

Kornit Digital develops, designs and markets digital printing solutions for the global printed textile industry. The company focuses on its DTG and DTF segments of the printed textile industry. Its solutions include digital printing systems, ink and other consumables, associated software and value-added services that allow for large-scale printing of short runs of complex images and designs directly on finished garments and fabrics. It has developed and offers a broad portfolio of differentiated digital printing solutions for the DTG market that provide answers to challenges faced by participants in the global printed textile industry. It generates revenue from sales of systems, ink and other consumables and service including software subscriptions.

Founded in 2010, Kortschak Investments is a venture capital firm based in Aspen, Colorado. The firm seeks to invest in information technology, financial technology, SaaS, artificial intelligence, cloud technology, the internet of things & legal technology sectors based in the United States & European regions.
Mr. Kow Mensah serves as Managing Director at Morgan Stanley. Mr. Mensah is an Angel Investor.
Founded in 2006, KPG Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Lafayette, California. The firm prefers to invest in the technology sector.

Krafton is a South Korean video game holding company based in Seongnam, known for playerunknown's Battlegrounds. Some of its games are PUBG: Battlegrounds, PUBG: New State, Tera, Elyon, and Mistover among others.

Founded in 1998, Kreos Capital is a venture capital firm based in England, London. The firm seeks to invest in the clean technology, communication, consumer, life sciences, semiconductor, hardware and software sectors.

Mr. Kris Gale is an Angel Investor. Mr. Gale co-founded and served as Board Member at Clover Health. Previously at Clover Health, he served as Chief Technology Officer. He also is an Angel Investor. He is a recognized leader in building and scaling engineering teams and was part of the founding engineering team at Yammer. During his six years there as vice president of engineering, he helped grow Yammer's engineering organization from three people to over 200. He also spearheaded the platform's direction and ensured its ability to scale, culminating in its acquisition by Microsoft in 2012. He has been a software developer since 1998 and held positions at companies such as Oversee.net and American Express. He is active in the healthcare space and is an advisor to Flatiron Health.

Mr. Krishna Yarlagadda is a Co-Founder and serves as Chief Executive Officer at Huddl.ai. Mr. Yarlagadda is a Co-Founder & Investor and serves as Board Member at FalconX (Financial Services). He is a Co-Owner and serves as Strategic Advisor at Smartron India. He is a Co-Founder and serves as an Advisor at Fungible. He also served as President at Imagination Technologies. He served as Chairman at IntelliVision. He has over 20 years of experience in Microprocessor, DSP, and system architecture/design and was CEO of Hellosoft before it was acquired by Imagination Technologies in 2010. He worked/was involved in several successful companies including Sun, ZSP, vEngines, SiliconSpice, Intoto, Chiplogic, and eSilicon in Silicon Valley. He has been recognized as a "Technology Pioneer" by the World Economic Forum in Davos. He also serves as an Advisor at Innovium. He holds a BS in Electronics from the University of Pune.

Kroger is one of the largest grocery retailers in the United States with more than 2,700 stores across a portfolio of over 20 supermarket banners. The company boasts an ingrained presence in US communities, citing that it is a top-two grocer in most of its major market areas. Over one fourth of Kroger's roughly $110 billion in nonperishable and fresh food sales (about 75% of revenue) stems from its private-label portfolio, of which the company manufactures about 30% of units via its 33 food production plants. The firm also operates fuel stations and pharmacies at 60% and 80% of its locations, respectively.

Manufacturer and seller of global sports motorcycles and racing vehicles based in Mattighofen, Austria. The company's global sports motorcycles and racing vehicles include motorized leisure bikes and lightweight vehicles for racing, in addition, it offers suspension elements and damping systems, frames, radiators, and exhaust systems, thereby enabling customers to enjoy comfortable riding and participate in racing events worldwide.

Founded in 1953, Kuwait Investment Authority is a sovereign wealth fund based in Kuwait City, Kuwait. The firm invests in private equity, public equity, real estate, fixed income, and alternative investments across the Americas, Europe, Asia-Pacific, and Emerging Markets.
Mr. Kyle Talcott is an Angel Investor.

Kyocera is a Japanese conglomerate whose original business consisted of manufacturing fine ceramic components; the firm has since expanded into manufacturing handsets, printers, solar cells and industrial tools. As a result of the reorganization, the firm now consists of three major business segments, which are the core components business (29% of 2022 revenue), electronic components business (19% of revenue) and solutions business (53% of revenue).

Manufacturer and supplier of electronic components based in Fountain Inn, South Carolina. The company specializes in offering a range of equipment, including ceramic and tantalum capacitors, antennas, diodes, thermistors and inductors as well as filters, resistors, couplers, diodes and circuit protection devices, thereby allowing it to fulfill the unique application requirements of clients in the communications, networking and industrial sectors.

KYOCERA Document Solutions Deutschland develops software-based printing management services. The company manufactures and sells printers, multifunctional products (MFPs), wide-format systems, parts and supplies. It offers monochrome and colour printers, black and white copiers, colour MFPs with colour copy, print and scan options. It also provides a managed document, customization and security, optimization and IT infrastructure services. The company seeks to acquire other companies whose businesses can be integrated into its existing operations.

Founded in 2015, L Capital is a private equity firm headquartered in San Francisco, California. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in technology, business services, industrial and consumer sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).
L Capital Partners was a venture capital firm based in New York, New York. Established in 2001, the assets of the firm were managed by the executive management team.
Founded in 2014, L Marks is an accelerator firm based in London, United Kingdom. The firm prefers to invest in the technology sector.

Founded in 2014, L-Spark is an accelerator firm based in Ottawa, Canada. The firm prefers to acquire minority stakes in companies involved in the software as a service, internet of things, and autonomous vehicles sectors based in Canada.

L.B. Foster is a US-based firm engaged in the manufacturing, fabrication and distribution of products and services, especially for the rail, construction, energy and utility industries. The company operates its business through three segments: rail technologies and services; precast concrete products and steel products and measurement. Its principal business activity involves providing new and used rail, trackwork and accessories, producing concrete railroad ties, insulated rail joints, power rail, track fasteners, cover boards and sales of sells and rents steel sheet piling, H-bearing pile and other piling products for foundation and earth retention requirements. It generates the majority of its revenues from the rail technologies and services segment.

L3Harris Technologies provides products for the command, control, communications, computers, intelligence, surveillance and reconnaissance, or C4ISR, market. The firm produces uncrewed aerial vehicles, sensors and avionics, provides military and commercial training services and maintains the us Federal Aviation Administration's communications infrastructure. In July 2023, the company acquired Aerojet Rocketdyne, a key supplier of rocket motors to the space and defense industry.

Founded in 1917, La Banque Privee Saint-Germain is an asset manager based in Paris, France. The firm provides mandate management, advisory, life insurance, family office, real estate, and banking services.

Laboratory Corporation of America is one of the nation's two largest independent clinical laboratories, with roughly 20% of the independent lab market. The company operates approximately 2,000 patient-service centers, offering a broad range of 5,000 clinical lab tests, ranging from routine blood and urine screens to complex oncology and genomic testing.

Founded in 1989, Labrador Ventures is a venture capital investment firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm seeks to invest in the software, media, mobile, and SaaS sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Mr. Lachy Groom is a Co-Founder & serves as Co-Chief Executive Officer at Physical Intelligence. Mr. Groom is an Angel Investor. Previously, he ran Stripe Issuing and led payments product and partnership teams, where he oversaw payment operations, strategic initiatives and partnerships with Stripe's financial partners including Visa, Mastercard, and American Express. Originally from Australia, Lachy now lives and works in San Francisco.

Ladenburg Thalmann & Co. is the investment banking arm of Ladenburg Thalmann, offering a full suite of investment banking and capital markets products and services, including proprietary equity research and a fixed-income trading desk. The investment banking team offers services in the areas of initial public offerings, follow-on offerings/secondary offerings, confidentially marketed public offerings, registered directs, at-the-market offerings, private investment in public equities (PIPE), private placements, fixed income offerings, mergers and acquisitions, leveraged buyouts, management buyouts, going private transactions, balance sheet and corporate restructuring, fairness and solvency opinions, and valuations. Ladenburg Thalmann was founded in 1876 and is based in Miami, Florida.

Founded in 2007, Lagoon Capital is a venture capital investment firm based in Helsinki, Finland. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the SaaS, fintech, adtech, e-commerce, artificial intelligence, IoT, VR/AR, content, market places and game sectors.

Founded in 2003, Lake Street Capital is a secondary buyer based in Detroit, Michigan. The firm seeks to invest in small private companies operating in the technology, healthcare, and business services sectors. The firm prefers to acquire investments in the secondary direct market, acquiring venture capital investments in private companies from existing investors.
Provider of chassis-manufacturing and contract-manufacturing services. The company manufactured a line of chassis for commercial printers, military, medical and telecommunications applications.

Lam Research is one of the largest semiconductor wafer fabrication equipment or WFE, manufacturers in the world. It specializes in the market segments of deposition and etch, which entail the buildup of layers on a semiconductor and the subsequent selective removal of patterns from each layer. Lam holds the top market share in etch and holds the clear-cut second share in deposition. It is more exposed to memory chipmakers for DRAM and NAND chips. It counts as a top customer of the largest chipmakers in the world, including TSMC, Samsung, Intel, and Micron.
Mr. Lance White serves as Managing Director & Wealth Advisor at Morgan Stanley. He s an Angel Investor.

Lantronix is a networking company. It provides secure data access and management solutions for the Internet of Things (IoT) and information technology assets. It organizes its products and solutions into three product lines: IoT solutions, IoT system solutions, and software & services. Embedded IoT solution segment is the key revenue driver for the company. The company serves a diverse range of markets including healthcare, industrial, security, energy, transportation, and government networking. Its primary geographic markets are the Americas, Europe, the Middle East and Africa, and Asia Pacific Japan. The Americas contribute the vast majority of total revenue.

Mr. Larry Marcus is a Co-Founder and serves as Managing Director at MarcyPen Capital Partners. Mr. Marcus serves as Managing Director at Walden Venture Capital. He serves as a Board Member at Our Place, Savage X Fenty, Wyze, Partake Foods, Pela (Accessories), AndieSwim, and SoundHound. Previously, he served as a Board Member at, Factor 75, Aark, RobustWealth, BandPage, and MeUndies, and Board Observer at Hungry Marketplace, and TouchBistro. Previously, he also served as a Board Member & Founding Investor at Pandora Media. He holds a Degree in Economics and History from the University of Birmingham, an MBA, and a BA in Economics & Political Science from the University of California, Berkeley. He served as a Board Member at Savage X Fenty.

Mr. Lars Albright serves as a General Partner at Unusual Ventures. He also serves as an Advisor at Data Point Capital. He co-founded and served as Chief Executive Officer and Board Member at SessionM. Before co-founding SessionM, he was at Apple, Inc., where he was a member of the executive team and, Apple's mobile advertising business unit. While at iAd, he worked on a variety of initiatives including running partnerships and alliances in the U.S., Europe, and Asia. Before Apple, he was a Co-Founder and Senior Vice President of Business Development at Quattro Wireless, a leading mobile advertising platform that was acquired by Apple in 2010. Before Quattro, he was Vice President of Business Development at m-Qube, North America's dominant mobile aggregator that was acquired by VeriSign in 2006. He started his career in investment banking and finance on the West Coast, working for Montgomery Securities, and later for an affiliate fund of a private equity firm, Texas Pacific Group. He received an MBA from the Tuck School of Business at Dartmouth and his AB with honors from Harvard University.

Lassonde Industries is a food and beverages industry in North America. It develops, manufactures and markets a wide range of private-label and national-brand products, including ready-to-drink beverages, fruit-based snacks as well as frozen juice concentrates. It is also a producer of cranberry sauces and specialty food products such as pasta sauces, soups and fondue broths and sauces. The company operates through a single segment. Its single operating segment generates revenues from the sale of products including ready-to-drink beverages, fruit-based snacks, frozen juice concentrates and specialty food products as well as from rendering services related to the sale of these products. It earns the majority of the revenue in the United States.

Founded in 2011, Late Stage Management is a secondary buyer investment firm based in Saint Montclair, New Jersey. The firm seeks to invest in pre-IPO, early-stage, and high-growth companies operating in cloud computing, software-as-a-service, social media, banking, and biotechnology sectors.

Latham Group is a designer, manufacturer and marketer of in-ground residential swimming pools, liners, and covers in North America, Australia, and New Zealand. It derives a majority of its revenue from the United States.

Lattice Semiconductor is a developer of semiconductor technology that it distributes through products, solutions and licenses. The company reaches its customers through consumer, communications, and industrial markets. The company has one operating segment namely the core lattice business that includes silicon-based and silicon-enabling products, evaluation boards, development hardware and related intellectual property licensing, services, and sales. The products of the company are offered globally; and, the majority of sales are derived from customers in Asia.

Founded in 2000, Lauder Partners is a venture capital firm headquartered in Atherton, California. The firm seeks to invest in the technology sector across the United States and Canada. The firm seeks to invest both directly in companies as well as in funds.
Founded in 2024, Launch Point Partners is a private equity investment firm based in New York, New York. The firm is focused on the aerospace & defense sector markets.

Founded in 2008, LaunchCapital is a venture capital investment firm based in New Haven, Connecticut. The firm prefers to invest in commerce, marketplace, consumer, media, entertainment, enterprise software and services, emerging tech, data, finance, healthcare, and medical technology sectors.
Founded in 2014, LaunchKC is an accelerator and incubator based in Kansas City, Missouri. The firm prefers to invest in technology startups based in Missouri.

Launchpad Venture Group is a Boston, Massachusetts based angel investment group and venture capital firm which provides funding to early-stage technology and life science companies. The firm primarily focuses on the software, information technology, web, e-commerce, media and social media, mobile and wireless, medical devices, diagnostics, healthcare IT, networking and telecom, clean-tech, renewable energy and green-tech sectors located in the United States.

Ms. Lauren Flanagan served as the Board of Advisors at Dell Technologies. She is a Co-Founder and serves as Chairman, Chief Executive Officer, and Head of Strategy at Sesame Solar. She serves as Managing Director at Belle Capital. She served as a Liaison at Shyft. She also serves on Dell's EIR advisory board, on the Angel Capital Association's collaboration committee, and is an active member of AngelList. As SCIO Corp's chief executive officer, she has more than 25 years of experience in founding and operating technology companies. She was the Co-Founder and Managing Director at Phenomenelle Angels Fund. Before founding SCIO Corp, she co-founded WebWare Corp, a pioneer in creating the digital asset management market. She served as WebWare's chairman and chief executive officer for seven years, where she raised approximately $20 million in equity capital. WebWare, one of the first Software as a Service (SaaS) companies, was acquired in 2003. Before WebWare, she co-founded four technology companies and consulted for high-technology leaders including Apple, Atari, HP, IBM, Microsoft, NeXT, Texas Instruments, and Xerox. She is executive chairman at Current Motor Company, Chairman of the Board at HarQen, and a Board Member at Nopsec and Springboard Enterprises.
Founded in 2004, Laurence Capital is a private equity firm based in Waterloo, Canada. The firm invests in technology, growth & innovation, financial services, and real estate sector.

Ms. Laurene Powell Jobs is the Founder and serves as President at Emerson Collective. Mr. Powell Jobs served as a Board Member at Ozy. She also serves as a Board Member at Anonymous Content and The Rise Fund. In addition to her work with the Emerson Collective and College Track, she serves on the boards of directors of the NewSchools Venture Fund, New America Foundation, and Conservation International. She also serves as a member of the Council on Foreign Relations. Earlier in her career, she spent several years working in investment banking and later co-founded a natural foods company in California. She is also an Angel Investor. She holds a BA and a BSE from the University of Pennsylvania and an MBA from the Stanford Graduate School of Business.

Operates as a principal investment firm specializing in investments in various stages of a company's development. It seeks to invest in companies with novel products and services in information technology, healthcare, and biotechnology. Within these categories, the firm looks for companies with the potential to become a platform company.
Lawrence Capital Partners was a private equity firm based in New York, New York.

Mr. Lawson DeVries serves as Managing General Partner at Grotech Ventures. e serves as a Board Member at Apkudo, Ceros, CrowdStreet, UrbanBound, Optoro, Sunstone Credit, RedPoint Global, and SturdyAI. He served as a Board Member at Tethr. He served as a Board Member at TaskEasy. He serves as a Board Member and Advisor at DirectScale. He focuses primarily on investment opportunities in enterprise software and tech-enabled services. He currently serves on the boards of BetterWorld, Cloverly, Parallax, and Yardstik and is responsible for the firm's investments in Cerebro, Datasembly, EcoMap Technologies, FOUNT Global, and ShipMonk. He has also worked closely with several other prior Grotech portfolio companies including TaskEasy (acquired by WorkWave), DirectScale (acquired by Exigo), Perishable Shipping Solutions (acquired by Lineage Logistics), NexGen Storage (acquired by Fusion-io), LogRhythm (acquired by Thoma Bravo), Clarabridge (acquired by Qualtrics), Logi Analytics (acquired by Marlin Equity) BroadSoft (NASDAQ: BSFT; acquired by Cisco), Collective Intellect (acquired by Oracle) and Aztek Networks (acquired by GenBand). Before joining Grotech Ventures, he was in the Institutional Equity Sales division of the Buckingham Research Group, a boutique independent research firm. Previously he was in the Equity Research division at Deutsche Bank where he rolled out coverage on a new division of the Industrials sector that included Caterpillar, Deere and Co., and AGCO. Before this, he was in Deutsche Bank's Health Care group covering Managed Care stocks. He has a BA in English Literature from Harvard University and an MBA from Duke University's Fuqua School of Business.

Lawson Software was a computer software company that provided enterprise software and service solutions to the manufacturing, distribution, maintenance and service industries. It specialized in ERP, business intelligence, HCM and customer relationship management. The company was founded in 1975 and was headquartered in St. Paul, Minnesota. It acquired companies in the same line of business and also those that provided planning and forecasting solutions, business management software and workforce communications solutions.

Lazard Technology Partners was a venture capital firm based in New York, New York. The firm preferred to invest in the telecommunications, enterprise and infrastructure software, financial services, business process applications and services and information technology sectors.

Founded in 1996, LB Investment is a venture capital firm based in Seoul, South Korea. The firm seeks to invest in Korea and China-based companies operating in the technology, information and communication technology, media, consumer, education, biology, healthcare, clean technology, and manufacturing sectors.

Founded in 1998, LBBW Venture Capital is the venture arm of Landesbank Baden-Württemberg based in Stuttgart, Germany. The firm focuses on software, life science, healthcare technology and technology sectors.

LCI Industries supplies domestically and internationally components for the original equipment manufacturers of recreational vehicles and adjacent industries including buses; and trailers used to haul boats, livestock, equipment, and other cargo. It has two reportable segments; the original equipment manufacturers segment and the aftermarket segment. The OEM segment manufactures or distributes components for the OEMs of RVs and adjacent industries, including buses; trailers used to haul boats, livestock, equipment, and other cargo; trucks; pontoon boats; trains; manufactured homes; and modular housing. Its products are sold primarily to major manufacturers of RVs such as Thor Industries, Forest River, Winnebago, and other RV OEMs, and to manufacturers in adjacent industries.
Founded in 2002, LEAD Incubator is an incubator firm based in Linkoping, Sweden. The firm is a not-for-profit company and runs programs focusing on technology startups across Östergötland, Sweden.

Founded in 2018, Leadout Capital is a venture capital investment firm based in Portola Valley, California. The firm prefers to make investments in early-stage companies. The firm prefers to invest in cloud infrastructure, developer tools, SaaS, financial services, crypto, infrastructure, community & social, consumer, business-to-business marketplace, gov tech, internet of things, hospitality, property technology, automation, climate, geospatial data, health tech, advertisement, tech, and transportation.

Operator of a consumer internet company engaged in building brands that enable communities of creators to reach audiences in large and growing lifestyle categories. The company operates creator-driven brands that reach passionate audiences in categories, including fitness and wellness, home, art, and design, helping advertisers find innovative ways to engage with their customers.

Founded in 1999, Leapfrog Ventures was a venture capital firm based in Menlo Park, California. The firm preferred to invest in information technology, software, communication, wireless and technology-heavy consumer start-ups.

Lear designs, develops and manufactures automotive seating and electrical systems and components. Seating components include frames and mechanisms, covers (leather and woven fabric), seat heating and cooling, foam, and headrests. Automotive electrical distribution and connection systems and electronic systems include wiring harnesses, terminals and connectors, on-board battery chargers, high-voltage battery management systems, high-voltage power distribution systems, domain controllers, telematics control units, gateway modules, vehicle positioning for automated and autonomous driving, embedded control software, cloud and mobile device software and services, and cybersecurity. Lear's largest customer and regional market is GM and North America at 20% and 44% of 2022 revenue, respectively.

Ledstiernan was an Ekenässjön, Sweden based private equity firm that used to invest in the growth firms operating in the manufacturing, retail, energy, information technology and communication technology with a focus on mobile communication and wireless technology sectors. The firm was founded in 1994.

Mr. Lee Berger serves as Chief Executive Officer at Octacom. He served as Vice President at Vendian Investment Management. He served as Advisor at Ripple Ventures. He also is an Angel Investor. He served as Vice President, Investments at Langara Group. Previously he served as Associate, Global Equity Finance at Scotia Capital. Currently, he is Director & Co-Owner at True North Sports Camps.

Founded in 2006, Lee Equity Partners is a private equity firm based in New York, New York. The firm prefers to invest in business service, financial service, and healthcare service sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Mr. Lee Linden is a Co-Founder and serves as Managing Partner at Quiet Capital. He served as Board Member at Reinvent Technology Partners Z. He serves as a Board Member at Reinvent Technology Partners. He serves as an Advisory Board Member at Preface Ventures. He serves as an Industry Advisor at DN Capital. He serves as a Board Member at Spruce Health. He serves as an Advisor at Infinitus, Homebrew, and Taskade. He served as a Board Member at Industrious. He served as Head of eCommerce at Facebook. He is a Strategic Advisor of Lumia Capital. Before Facebook, He was the Co-Founder and served as Chief Executive Officer at Karma. He Co-Founded Crystalroot and Tapjoy. He also serves as a Board Director or in a formal advisory role for several companies. As a proven investor and well-recognized serial founder and CEO for a diverse set of businesses, he is often called upon by a wide range of entrepreneurs looking for strategic and tactical advice. He received his BA from the University of Michigan and his MBA from Stanford University.

LegalZoom.com is an online provider of services that meet the legal needs of small businesses and consumers in the United States. The company also offers services that include ongoing compliance and tax advice and filings, business licenses, accounting, virtual mailbox and e-signature solutions, trademark filings and estate plans.
Legend Ventures was a venture capital firm based in Bethesda, Maryland. The firm used to invest in the new media, telecommunications and information technology firms.

Provider of outsourced legal services to in-house legal departments and law firms. The company provides managed services, or teams of attorneys on voluminous work that needs process and expert management, one attorney at a time for specific assignments or durations who act in a consultative role, collaborating with clients to determine how best to handle and execute legal work.
Founded in 2017, Legion Capital Partners is a venture capital and incubator firm based in Cheyenne, Wyoming. The firm seeks to invest in early stage companies.

Leidos Holdings is a technology, engineering, and science company that provides services and solutions in the defense, intelligence, civil, and health markets, both domestically and internationally. Company customer includes the U.S. Department of Defense ("DoD"), the U.S. Intelligence Community, the U.S. Department of Homeland Security ("DHS"), the Federal Aviation Administration ("FAA"), the Department of Veterans Affairs ("VA"), and many other U.S. civilian, state and local government agencies, etc. The company is engaged in three reportable segments; Defense Solutions, Civil, and Health. Defense Solutions provides the latest technological services, solutions, and products to a broad customer base. It generates key revenue from Defense Solutions.

LeMaitre Vascular manufactures and distributes medical devices for the treatment of peripheral vascular disease. Its products are primarily used during open vascular surgery and address several anatomical areas, such as the carotid, lower extremities, upper extremities and aorta. The firm's lower extremities product line contributes the largest proportion of revenue, followed by the carotid product line. Its surgical devices include angioscopes, balloon catheters, carotid shunts, phlebectomy devices, vascular grafts, vascular patches and vessel closure systems. The company generates the majority of its revenue in the United States.

LendingTree is a United States-based company that is principally engaged in operating an online loan marketplace. The company provides online tools and resources that can help consumers find loans or other credit-based offerings They need, including mortgage loans, reverse mortgages, home equity, personal loans, auto loans, credit cards, student loans, small business loans, and other related offerings. The company offers consumers direct access to a broad range of lenders. They have three reportable segments which are home, consumer, and insurance. The company generates match fees by matching consumers with lenders, and closing fees from lenders on loans when a transaction is closed. The company operates business solely in the United States.

Lenovo is a global technology hardware company with a leading market share in personal computers. Its operations are divided into three main business segments: PC and smart devices, mobile, and data center, which we expect to account for 60%, 13%, and 17% of sales in the midterm, respectively. The firm has been actively growing its data center business, which primarily sells network servers to enterprise and hyperscale customers, as well as storage equipment through its mainland China joint venture with NetApp. Server-related revenue contribution has jumped to 16% of overall sales in fiscal 2022, from 6% in 2015.
Leo Capital Holdings was a venture capital firm and was based in Northbrook, Illinois. The firm used to make investments across the United States.
Founded in 2017, Leonard is an accelerator/incubator firm based in Paris, France. The firm seeks to support and invest in construction, mobility, energy, infrastructure, and real estate sectors.

Founded in 2010, Lerer Hippeau is a venture capital firm based in New York, New York. The firm prefers to invest in pre-seed to seed-stage companies. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).
Founded in 2001, Leslie Ventures is a venture capital investment firm based in Portola Valley, California. The firm seeks to invest in the information technology sectors.

Lettuce Entertain You Enterprises is an operator of restaurants and bars. The company offers a wide range of dining experiences from casual to fine dining, gift cards and parties for private and corporate events. The company was founded on June 10, 1971 and is headquartered in Chicago, Illinois.

Provider of integrated communications services intended to provide end-to-end security and connectivity. The company offers data center connectivity, cloud computing, contact centers, data networks, content and video delivery, managed services, unified communications and collaboration, and security solutions for the financial, government, healthcare, entertainment, and educational industries.

Founded in 1996, Levensohn Venture Partners w a venture capital firm based in Salzburg, Austria. The firm seeks to invest in information technology, digital media, healthcare, and biotechnology sectors.

Mr. Lew Moorman is an Angel Investor. He serves as Board Member at Rackspace US. He served as the Board Member at Lew Moorman. He is a senior consultant to the top executives of Rackspace, focusing on strategy and product issues. Lew joined Rackspace in April of 2000 and has served in a variety of roles, including as President and Chief Strategy Officer, while the company grew to $1.3 billion in annual sales.

Founded in 2001, Lewis and Clark Capital is a private equity firm based in Saint Louis, Missouri. The firm prefers to invest in companies operating in sectors such as industrial products and services, business and financial services, food and beverage sector, health and wellness products, niche manufacturing sector, commercial services, healthcare devices, healthcare technology, distribution, communications, networking, software, software-as-a-service, food tech, and health technology.

Provider of data and advanced analytics solutions and services intended to provide decision tools that combine public and industry-specific content with advanced technology and analytics to assist in evaluating and predicting risk and enhancing operational efficiency. The company provides customers with innovative technologies, information-based analytics, decision tools, and data management services, enabling clients to make better decisions, stay compliant, reduce risk, and improve operations.

Provider of printers, supplies and accessories. The company's printers and accessories combine innovative technologies with deep industry expertise, enabling retail, financial services, healthcare, manufacturing, education and government sectors to print, secure and manage information with ease, efficiency and unmatched value. The company seeks to acquire businesses through mergers, acquisitions and investments which would help the firm expand and consolidate its presence in the imaging and output solutions sector.
Mr. Lhoucine Aderdor is an Angel Investor.

Liberty Associated Partners was an investment arm of Liberty Media Group, specializing in private equity and venture capital investments. The firm made investments in the internet, telecommunications, media and other technology-related sectors.
Founded in 2015, Liberty Growth is a corporate venture arm of Liberty Global based in London, United Kingdom. The firm seeks to invest in technology, content and infrastructure sectors.

Formula One Group controls the exclusive commercial and promotional rights to the FIA Formula One World Championship series, and the monetization of those rights is the primary business of the group. Mr. Marc Benioff is a Co-Founder and serves as Co-Chief Executive Officer & Chairman at Salesforce. Mr. Benioff is an Angel Investor. He served as an Advisor at Forward. He is the Founder of TIME Ventures. He serves as a Board Member at SilviaTerra and Artera. He serves as a Member of, the Breakthrough Energy Coalition at Breakthrough Energy. He serves as an Executive at The Marc R. Benioff Revocable Trust. He was the Owner of Efficient Capacity. He served as an Advisor at Brandcast. He co-founded Salesforce in 1999. He has been widely recognized for his visionary leadership and pioneering innovations. He is also a member of the World Economic Forum Board of Trustees. He also serves as a Board Member and Advisor at BirdEye. He created the 1-1-1 model of philanthropy, which leverages the resources of Salesforce to improve communities around the world. Before launching Salesforce, he spent 13 years at Oracle Corporation. He founded his first company, Liberty Software, which created video games, at the age of 15. He also worked as an assembly language programmer in Apple Computer's Macintosh Division. He is the author of three books, including the national bestseller, Behind the Cloud. He is also an Angel Investor. He served as an Advisor at DoubleRock. Building a different kind of company, he created Salesforce to not only develop great products but also to have a positive impact on the world. On day one, he created the 1-1-1 model of philanthropy, which leverages the resources of Salesforce to improve communities around the world. Today, more than 12,000 companies have adopted the 1-1-1 model through the Pledge 1% movement, and his wife, Lynne, has focused their philanthropy on healthcare, the environment, public education, and homelessness. He has given more than $250 million to the University of California, San Francisco, to build UCSF Benioff Children's Hospitals in San Francisco and Oakland. The Benioffs have also established the Benioff Ocean Initiative at the University of California, Santa Barbara, the UCSF Benioff Homelessness and Housing Initiative, the UCSF Benioff Initiative for Prostate Cancer Research, and the UCSF Benioff Center for Microbiome Medicine, and they have provided the initial funding for the Stanford Microbiome Therapies Initiative. A member of the World Economic Forum (WEF) board of trustees, he co-founded 1t.org - the global movement to conserve, restore, and grow 1 trillion trees - and the WEF Friends of Ocean Action. He also serves as the inaugural chair of WEF's Centre for the Fourth Industrial Revolution in San Francisco. He received a B.S. in Business Administration in 1986 and an honorary degree of Doctor of Humane Letters in 2014 from the University of Southern California.

Zynga merger with Take-Two Interactive in 2022. Before Zynga, Mark founded tribe.net, one of the earliest online social networks whose technology was acquired by Cisco Systems. MASSEY BURCH CAPITAL CORP. was formed in January 1994 as the continuation of the investing activities of Jack C. Massey and Lucius E. Burch, III. "Massey Burch" was formed to continue the venture capital activities originated by Messrs. Massey and Burch.

Founded in 1978, MassVentures is a venture capital firm based in Worcester, Massachusetts. The firm prefers to invest in information technology, healthcare, cybersecurity, e-commerce, mobile, manufacturing, and robotics sector firms in Massachusetts. The firm offers various accelerator programs.

MasterCraft Boat Holdings designs, manufactures, and markets performance sport boats and outboard boats. The company is based in the United States and operates in three brand-specific segments. The MasterCraft segment generates the majority of the company's revenue and includes inboard boats for water skiing, wakeboarding, and wake surfing. The Pontoon segment produces pontoon boats at its Owosso, Michigan facility. Pontoon boats are used for general recreational boating. The Aviara segment produces luxury day boats at its Merritt Island, Florida facility. Aviara boats are used for general recreational boating.

Founded in 1997, Masthead Venture Partners was a venture capital firm headquartered in Danvers, Massachusetts. The firm preferred to invest in the information technology sector. The firm ceased its operations on June 30th, 2017.

Match Group is a provider of online dating products. The firm became public in 2015 and was more than 80% owned by IAC/InterActiveCorp until IAC spun it off in 2020. The company has a vast portfolio of different online dating service providers, including Tinder, Hinge, BLK, Chispa, Match.com, OkCupid, PlentyOfFish, and Meetic. Match Group has more than 45 brands of online dating sites and/or apps, from which it generates user fee revenue (95%) and advertising revenue (5%).

Founded in 2019, Material V is a venture capital investment firm based in Monaco City, Monaco. The firm prefers to invest in seed-stage, early-stage, and later-stage companies. The firm seeks to invest in information technology, financial services, cybersecurity, e-commerce, and technology-based sectors.

Materion is a producer of engineered materials based in the United States. The company produces materials used in electrical, electronic, thermal, and structural applications. The company operates in four reportable segments: Performance Materials, Electronic Materials, Precision Optics, and others. The majority of revenue is derived from Electronic Materials which produces chemicals, microelectronics packaging, precious metal, non-precious metal, and specialty metal products, including vapor deposition targets, frame lid assemblies, clad and precious metal pre-forms, high-temperature braze materials, and ultra-pure wire.
Founded in 1996, Matignon Investissement et Gestion is a venture capital investment firm based in Paris, France.

Mativ Holdings is a diversified producer of premium specialty papers and resin-based products. It manufactures and sells paper and reconstituted tobacco products to the tobacco industry as well as specialized paper products. The company operates in two segments namely advanced materials and structures, which manufactures resin-based products used in specialty applications in the filtration, infrastructure and construction, transportation, industrial and medical end-markets and engineered papers, which produces cigarette papers and reconstituted tobacco products for cigarette and cigar manufacturers, as well as various other non-tobacco paper products.

Founded in 2002, MatlinPatterson Global Advisers was a private equity firm based in New York, New York. The firm used to invest in distressed companies in the form of senior and subordinated, secured and unsecured debt and equity, in both public and private companies. The firm geared up for a bankruptcy showdown on July 9, 2021.

Founded in 1977, Matrix is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage companies operating in the artificial intelligence, B2B, consumer, fintech, frontier, health tech, infrastructure, and semiconductor sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 1988, Matrix Capital Markets Group is a Richmond, Virginia based independent, privately-held investment bank serving privately-held, private-equity owned and publicly traded companies. The firm offers services in the areas of mergers and acquisitions, company sales, recapitalizations, asset divestitures, corporate recovery, management buyouts, debt and equity capital raising, corporate valuations, and fairness opinions.

MatrixCare is a developer of a cloud-based long-term post-acute care software for senior citizens. The company offers electronic health record (EHR) applications which help skilled nursing and senior living providers, life plan communities (CCRCs) and home health organizations to maximize reimbursements, reduce readmission and maintain high occupancy.

Mr. Matt Cohen is the Founder and serves as Managing Partner at Ripple Ventures. He serves as a Board member at OnCall Health. He served as Board Observer at Cognota. He also serves as Board Member at Rose Rocket. He served as Board Member at Apteo. He also serves as Board Observer at Voiceflow. He serves as a Board Observer at ZenHub. He has extensive experience and knowledge in building and growing SaaS and FinTech startups. Founding investor and BoD of Turnstyle Solutions, BoD Nanogenecs Diagnostics. He served as Director, Institutional Equities Sales, and Trading at the National Bank of Canada. He was a Board Member at Turnstyle Solutions. He served as Board Member at Cybeats. He currently serves as Board Observer at Synapse.

Mr. Matt Cutts is an Angel Investor. Mr. Cutts joined Google as a Software Engineer in January 2000. Before Google, he was working on his Ph.D. in computer graphics at the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill. He has an M.S. from UNC-Chapel Hill, and B.S. degrees in both mathematics and computer science from the University of Kentucky. Matt wrote SafeSearch, which is Google's family filter. In addition to his experience at Google, Matt held a top-secret clearance while working for the Department of Defense and he's also worked at a game engine company.

Mr. Matthew Coffin is the Founder of Coffin Capital & Ventures. He founded and served as Board Member at Digital Funding Group. He is a Co-Founder of Monc XIII. He also serves as Chairman at Goji. He served as Board Member at Tubular. He He also serves as a Board Member at Talent Inc. He is also a Co-Founder and serves as Chairman at Brighter. He also serves as an Advisor at HSCM Ventures. He was the Founder and served as the Chief Executive Officer of LowerMyBills.com, which sold to Experian and an investor in companies including Demand Media, Buscape, Rubicon Project, Mahalo, Machinima, Hautelook, ShoeDazzle and EcoMom. He serves as an Executive at Coffin Capital & Ventures. At Experian, he was also president of online customer acquisition services and president of the incubator-like Experian Interactive Innovation Center, a division of the company that focused on new online ideas to leverage Experian data and analytics resources. He also serves as the Executive Chairman. He served as Board Member at Tastemade.

Mr. Matthew Davey served as Chief Executive Officer & Chairman at Tekkorp Digital Acquisition II. He is the Founder and serves as Chairman of Tekkorp Capital. He served as a Board Member at Till Payments. He served as Chief Executive Officer at OpenBet Technologies. He served as Group Chief Executive Officer at Scientific Games. He is also the Chief Executive Officer of SG Digital, the newly created division of Scientific Games.

Mr. Matthew Gorniak serves as Chief Executive Officer and Board Member at Threekit. He Co-Founded and served as Senior Advisor at G2. He served as Chief Revenue Officer at G2. He is a seasoned high-tech executive that has worked in leadership roles for global leaders GE, CAT, and EMC, as well as software start-ups such as OctetString (sold to Oracle). Most recently he led alliances and sales at BigMachines and grew revenue from $2 to $50 million making BigMachines one of Inc. 5000's Fastest Growing companies for five years in a row. When not spending time with his new bride, he can be found glued to his iPad managing his stock portfolio. He was born in Poland, raised in Germany, and studied in the US.

Mr. Matthew Huang is a Co-Founder & serves as Managing Partner at Paradigm (Crypto Fund). Mr. Huang serves as Chairman at Ithaca. He serves as a Board Member at Privy. He serves as Board Member at Stripe. He also served as a Board Member at Amber Group. Previously, he was a partner at Sequoia Capital, focusing on early-stage venture investments, including leading the firm's cryptocurrency efforts. He was the founder and CEO of Hotspots, a Y Combinator company acquired by Twitter in 2012. He purchased his first Bitcoin from MtGox in 2012. He holds a B.S. in Mathematics from MIT.
Mr. Matt Maloney is a high net worth investor based in New York. The assets of the firm are managed by the executive management team.

Mr. Matthew Ocko is a Co-Founder and serves as Managing Partner at DCVC. Mr. Ocko serves as a Board Member at Tradeshift. He also serves as an Independent Investment Committee Member at Elevate NZ Venture Fund. He serves as Board Member at Capella Space. He served as a Board Member at Nervana Systems. He serves as a Board Member at Kentik, Agility Robotics, Primer, Atomwise, and Reach Labs. He served as a Board Member at Jupiter Intelligence. He was also the Managing Director at Archimedes Capital. He also sits on the Board of Fortem Technologies, Rocket Lab, and Pierson Labs. He also served as an Advisor of Blockchain Capital. He also served as a Board Member at Cofactor Genomics. He also serves as Managing Director at Archimedes Capital, as an Advisor at Instart Logic & Signifyd, and as a Partner at Sevin Rosen Funds a sourcing partner in SRB Partners Fund, and has worked with Sevin Rosen since 2002. For SRB Partners Fund, he will focus on deals in the data center, enterprise, big data (including analytics, machine learning, sensor platforms, and deep vertical applications), and Web 2.0 (large-scale software platforms). He has been active in helping develop China's venture capital and technology regulatory framework for two decades and his 1996 lecture to the Central Committee Party School on Venture Capital with a Chinese Face has been widely distributed at all levels of government in China. He also serves as an Advisor at Instart Logic. He holds a BA in physics from Yale University. He is also an Angel Investor. He also served as a Venture Partner at Sevin Rosen Funds. He served as a Board member at Vium. He is also an Angel Investor. He served as an Advisor at BranchOut. He serves as an Advisor at the Store.

Mavenir PLC through its subsidiaries is engaged in providing software to drive the digital transformation of mobile networks. The software applications provide critical network functionality that allows Wireless Service Providers to meet the needs of their enterprise and consumer customers. Mavenir offers the mobile communications software stack that runs on cloud infrastructure and connects devices and people to the Internet and Apps. Its products and services are Multimedia Messaging, 5G Core Solution, Software for Mobile Access & Edge, and Private Networks among others. Geographically, the firm operates in the Americas, Europe, the Middle East and Africa, and Asia-Pacific.

Founded in 1998, Maveron is a venture capital firm based in Seattle, Washington. The firm has additional offices in San Francisco and New York. The firm prefers to invest in early-stage companies operating in the housing, consumer, education, health, fitness and wellness, communication and social, ridesharing, travel, and hobbies, entertainment, media and games, autonomous vehicles, fuel, fashion, personal care and beauty, food, technology, and innovation sectors based in the United States region. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA). The firm investment focus is in early-stage consumer technology companies.

Mr. Max Levchin is the Founder & serves as Chief Executive Officer at Affirm. Mr. Levchin served as Board Member at Unity. He is a Co-Founder and serves as a Partner at SciFi VC. He founded & served as Chief Technology Officer PayPal Holdings. He serves as a Board Member at Polywork, Unity Technologies, MixPanel, and Quid. He serves as the Executive Chairman at Upwards Labs Holdings. He is an Advisor of Anchorage. He was an Advisor of Crunchyroll. Before Affirm, he co-founded and was the Chairman of Glow.
