In 2004, he founded Slide, a personal media-sharing service for social networking sites such as MySpace and Facebook, which he sold to Google in August 2010. Also in 2004, he helped start Yelp, where he was the first investor and Chairman of the Board from 2004 until 2015. He served as a Board member at Emerald Cloud Lab, Yahoo!, Yelp, and Evernote. In 2002, he was named to the Technology Review TR100 as one of the top 100 innovators in the world as well as Innovator of the Year. He earned his Bachelor of Science from the University of Illinois in Urbana-Champagne. He serves as a Limited Partner Advisor at Nyca Partners. He served as an Advisor at SignalFire. He is an Angel Investor.
Mr. Max Rayner is an Angel Investor.

Founded in 2013, Maxfield Capital is a venture capital investment firm based in New York, New York. The firm prefers to invest in information technology companies in Europe, Israel, and the United States.

MaxLinear is a provider of radio frequency and mixed-signal integrated circuits for cable and satellite broadband communications, the connected home, and for data center, metro, and long-haul fiber networks. The company's radio frequency receiver products capture and process digital and analog broadband signals to be decoded for various applications. MaxLinear's product options include both radio frequency receivers and radio frequency receiver systems-on-chips. The company's products enable the distribution and display of broadband video and data content in a wide range of electronic devices. Customers for MaxLinear include original equipment manufacturers, module makers, and original design manufacturers.

The Company develops, manufactures and markets energy storage and power delivery products for transportation, industrial telecommunications and other applications and microelectronic products for space and satellite applications.

MAYA Heat Transfer Technologies is an integrator and developer of software products. It specialized software solutions in a wide range of fields, including engineering, design, manufacturing, aerospace, military and defense, datacenter operation and others. The company was founded in May 1982 and is based in Montreal, Canada.

Mayflower was an engineering company that designed, engineered and manufactured bodies for cars, light trucks and sports utility vehicles. It also specialized in making coach bodies, chassis and fire engines as well. It was founded in 1964 and was headquartered in the United Kingdom. It made those acquisitions that would enable it to expand and grow by using the acquired companies expertise and innovative technologies.

Founded in 2019, Mayhaw Capital is a family office investment firm based in the United States. The firm also employs a real estate investment strategy and invests across the software, hardware, developer tools, fintech, internet of things, artificial intelligence/machine learning, e-commerce, and vertical SaaS sectors.

Founded in 1985, Mayo Clinic Ventures is the corporate venture capital arm of Mayo Clinic headquartered in Rochester, Minnesota. The firm seeks to invest in healthcare, life science, big data, oncology & internet of things sectors across the United States.

Mr. Mazen Aljubeir is a Co-Founder and serves as a Co-Chief Investment Officer at Isometry Capital. He serves as a Board Member at Jada (Riyadh). He served as Board Member at Saudi Arabian Military Industries. He serves as a Board Member at Nusaned Investment. He served as an Executive Vice President at Amwal Alkhaleej and also served as Engagement Manager at McKinsey and Company. He also serves on the boards of several major government-owned and private companies. He graduated from the Harvard Business School where he received an M.B.A. with highest distinction and from Harvard College where he received his B.A. in Economics with honors. He serves as a Board Member and Chairman at Jada. He serves as a Board Member at Seera Group, Maxis, Mohammed I. Alsubeaei & Sons Investment Company MASIC and Sulaiman Bin AbdulAziz Al Rajhi Holding Co. He served as a Board Member at Careem, Raidah Investment Company, Public Pension Agency of Saudi Arabia and National Agricultural Development Company (NADEC).

Founded in 2001, MB Venture Partners is a venture capital investment firm based in Memphis, Tennessee. The firm seeks to make seed, early-stage, and later-stage investments in companies operating in the medical devices and biotechnology sectors across the Southeast and Midwest of the United States.

MBF Capital was a private investment firm based in New York, New York. The firm specialized in making private equity investments in technology-driven companies. The firm invested in early-stage information technology and medical technology companies.
mc3 ventures was a California based venture capital investment firm which used to make venture capital investments.

McCoy Global is a provider of equipment and technologies to support tubular running operations, enhance wellbore integrity and assist with collecting critical data for the global energy industry. It is engaged in the design, production and distribution of capital equipment to support tubular running operations, enhance wellbore integrity and support capital equipment sales through aftermarket products and services such as technical support, consumables and replacement parts. Some of its products are specialized hydraulic power tongs, dies, and inserts, make or break torque equipment, and computerized torque turn monitoring systems.

McDermott International provides integrated engineering, procurement, construction and installation, and module fabrication services for oil and gas field developments worldwide. The company delivers fixed and floating production facilities, pipeline installations, and subsea systems for complex offshore and subsea oil and gas projects. Revenue is derived internationally, and customers include national, major integrated, and other oil and gas companies. Contracts are executed through a series of different methods, principally fixed-price, but also include fixed reimbursable, cost-plus, day-rate, and unit-rate basis.

Founded in 1999, MCI Capital is a private equity firm based in Warsaw, Poland. The firm seeks to invest in the technology sector with a focus on digital climate technology, digital disruption, digital infrastructure, and digital transformation in Poland, CEE, Greece, and Austria.

McKesson is one of three leading pharmaceutical wholesalers in the us engaged in sourcing and distributing branded, generic, and specialty pharmaceutical products to pharmacies (retail chains, independent, and mail order), hospital networks, and healthcare providers. Along with Cencora and Cardinal Health, the three account for over 90% of the us pharmaceutical wholesale industry. Outside the us market, McKesson engages in pharmaceutical wholesale and distribution in Canada. Additionally, the company supplies medical-surgical products and equipment to healthcare facilities and provides a variety of technology solutions for pharmacies.
Founded in 1994, McLean Watson Capital is a venture capital firm based in Toronto, Canada. The firm prefers to invest in companies operating in the hardware, software, and energy technology sectors.

MCNC Enterprise Fund is a technology non-profit company. It builds, owns and operates a broadband infrastructure and leverages it to create opportunity for North Carolina's research, education, non-profit healthcare and other community institutions. The services of the company include connectivity, data center services, video conferencing, engineering, security, software licensing and webcasting. MCNC was founded in 1985 and is headquartered in Research Triangle Park, North Carolina.
MD Holdings is a private equity firm based in Richardson, Texas.
Dr. MD Pham is an Angel Investor.

MDB Capital Group is an intellectual property (IP) investment bank. The firm understands that the primary source of asset creation in emerging technology companies is IP and they provide merchant and investment banking services exclusively to companies that possess disruptive and market-changing IP. The firm offers expertise in a range of areas beyond traditional investment banking transactions, including IPOs, private placements, merchant banking advisory services, and merger and acquisition services.
Founded in 2010, MDC Ventures was the corporate venture arm of MDC Partners based in New York, New York. The firm was investing in early-stage and marketing technology companies.
MDS Capital was a Canada based venture capital firm

MDY Healthcare was an operator of an investment holding company. The company was engaged in investing in public and private businesses of healthcare, medical, diagnostics, pharmaceutical industries. It used to invest in companies based in the United Kingdom, Europe, Scandinavia, North America, Far East, and Asia.

Meakem Becker Venture Capital was a venture capital firm that invested in early and later-stage companies. The firm focused on investing in companies operating in the software, mobile, business and consumer services, new media and energy sectors.

Developer of a data management platform intended to provide informed analysis about sustainability performance. The company's cloud-based platform collects data, creates investment-grade sustainability reports, and offers alerts regarding improvement opportunities about environmental, social, governance programs, enabling clients to collect sustainability data, analyze and accurately report on performance and identify efficiency opportunities.

Medacta Group is a Switzerland-based company involved in developing, manufacturing and distributing orthopedic and neurosurgical medical devices. The company offers solutions for hip, knee, shoulder and spine. The majority of the company's revenue is generated from Europe, the Middle East and Africa (EMEA) and the rest is from other regions.
Media Technology Ventures was a private equity and venture capital firm based in Dallas, Texas.

MediaCorp is a provider of broadcast media services. The company operates digital, television, radio, print, and out-of-home media brands in Singapore. The company also produces content for studios, offers marketing consulting services, and manages talent development academies. Moreover, it operates a one-year incubator program for seed-stage media start-ups. MediaCorp was founded in June 1936 and is headquartered in Singapore, Singapore. The company continually seeks to expand its business portfolio through mergers and acquisitions. It was acquired by Temasek Holdings.
MediaOne Ventures was the corporate venture arm of MediaOne Group. On June 2000, the firm was acquired by Venture Management Services.

MediaTek Ventures is a strategic investment arm of MediaTek that invests in startups in Greater China, Europe, Japan and North America. The firm seeks to invest in early stage companies operating in the semiconductor, system and device, internet infrastructure and information technology sectors.

Founded in 2018, Medici Capital Partners is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the digital consumer, technology, sports, internet, gaming, and media sectors.

Founded in 2014, Medici Ventures is a corporate venture capital arm of Overstock.com based in Salt Lake City, Utah. The firm prefers investing in seed-stage, early-stage, and later-stage companies. The firm seeks to invest in information technology, blockchain, cybersecurity, SaaS, and fintech sectors.

Medidata Solutions Inc provides cloud-based solutions for the clinical development programs of life sciences companies. Its customers include biopharmaceutical companies, device makers, contract research organizations, and academic institutions. The majority of the company's business comes from subscriptions to the Medidata Clinical Cloud, with the remainder of revenue coming from services. The Medidata Clinical Cloud provides solutions for study design and planning, data capture, patient activity measurement, risk-based monitoring, and payments. The services segment includes technology and support services and professional consulting services. The majority of the firm's revenue is generated within the United States.
Developer of cardiovascular drugs. The company researches, develops, manufactures and markets therapeutic drugs for liver and cancer diseases operating in Taiwan.

Provider of pharmacy benefits management (PBM) services intended to serve employers, and commercial and government healthcare organizations. The company's services include claims processing, manufacturer contract management, retail and mail network management as well as cost, quality and outcomes management, helping clients to manage medications, order refills and deliver door-to-door medication.

Founded in 2012, Medina Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Miami, Florida. The firm primarily invests in seed and series A companies. The Firm prefers to invest in cybersecurity, big data analytics, fintech, proptech, climate tech, health tech, and cloud computing sectors.

Founded in 2013, MedTech Innovator is an accelerator firm based in Los Angeles, California. The firm supports medical devices, digital health, consumer healthcare, imaging, remote patient monitoring & clinical studies, workflow optimization, and diagnostic companies.

One of the largest medical-device companies, Medtronic develops and manufactures therapeutic medical devices for chronic diseases. Its portfolio includes pacemakers, defibrillators, heart valves, stents, insulin pumps, spinal fixation devices, neurovascular products, advanced energy, and surgical tools. The company markets its products to healthcare institutions and physicians in the United States and overseas. Foreign sales account for roughly 50% of the company's total sales.
Medtronic Ventures was the corporate venture arm of Medtronic. The firm focused on investing in companies operating in the medical devices, diagnostics and pharmaceuticals sectors.

Founded in 1986, MedVenture Associates was a venture capital firm based in Lincoln, California. The firm sought to invest in companies operating in the medical device, medical information technology, pharmaceutical, and biotechnology sectors. The firm closed all of its funds on December 31st, 2017.
Megunticook Management was a venture capital firm that invested in companies in the media, communications and technology sectors. The firm ceased its operations.

Mr. Mehdi Maghsoodnia is a Co-Founder and serves as Chief Executive Officer, President & Board Member at 1health. Mr. Maghsoodnia is also a Venture Partner at Candou Ventures. Previously, he served as Chief Executive Officer and Board Member at Vitagene, and as Executive Chairman at Livara Health (SpineZone). In addition, he acts as an angel investor at Combustion Ventures and served as a Board Member at Dokkio. He has held several other notable positions, including Chief Executive Officer and Board Member at Rafter, and Executive Vice President of Online Business at CafePress. He has been an Entrepreneur in Residence (EIR) at Trinity Ventures and Mohr Davidow Ventures. As the founder and COO at FaceTime Communication and SVP of Products at Intellisync (PumaTech), he played a key role in the company's acquisition by Nokia in 2003 for $450 million. He has held various executive positions at other Silicon Valley companies and currently sits on the boards of D3, 1Health, and big-brain.ai. He completed his undergraduate studies at the University of California, Berkeley, and his graduate studies at Stanford University.

Mr. Mehrdad Piroozram is the Founder and serves as General Partner at InsurTech.v. He is a Co-Founder and serves as Advisor at Soonami.io. He is a Co-Founder and serves Advisor & Board Member at Widgetlabs. He served as Managing Director at Widgetlabs. He is an entrepreneur and investor with a global network specializing in mentoring companies from start-up to IPO, company acquisitions, and integration.
Operator of a investment firm headquartered in Herzliya, Israel. The company specialized in investment services.

Mellanox Technologies Ltd is engaged in the development, manufacturing, marketing and sales of end-to-end Ethernet and InfiniBand intelligent interconnect solutions and services for servers, storage, and hyper-converged infrastructure. The company offers integrated circuits, adapter cards, switch systems, cables, modules, software, services, and accessories. The company supplies its products mainly to the storage and communications infrastructure equipment vendors. The company operates its business mainly in the United States, Europe, China, Japan, India, Taiwan and Australia.

Mellon Ventures is the former name of Navigation Capital Partners. As none of the deals executed by Mellon Ventures are listed on the Navigation Capital Partners website, Mellon Ventures is no longer actively tracked by PitchBook.

Developer of virtual reality technology systems. The company has developed a proprietary post-production workflow that enables the aforementioned recorded material to be processed into MelodyVR 360 degree panoramic video content.

Memorial Sloan Kettering Cancer Center is a cancer care hospital, that engages in cancer prevention, treatment, research and education activities. It offers a range of programs to help patients and families throughout various phases of treatment, including genetic counseling, rehabilitation, integrative medicine, counseling, pain and palliative care, cancer screening and assistance in navigating life after treatment. The company provides childhood cancer treatments, including blood and marrow transplantation, pediatric surgery and subspecialty services and treatment. It was founded in 1884 and is headquartered in New York, New York. It seeks to acquire other companies whose businesses can be integrated into its existing operations.

MemorialCare Innovation Fund is a corporate venture capital arm of MemorialCare Health System based in Long Beach, California. The firm prefers to invest in seed-stage, early-stage, and later-stage companies in healthcare, information technology, life sciences, the internet of things, SaaS, TMT, and technology-based sectors in the United States.
Menire was an investment company which specialized in fast-growing enterprises in the online and wireless communications field. Its investment used to focus on Finland and the Nordic countries.

Founded in 1976, Menlo Ventures is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm prefers to invest in seed-stage, early-stage, later-stage, and growth-stage companies operating in the computer hardware, software, big data, fintech, and healthcare sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Mentor Graphics was the provider of electronic design automation software and hardware services. The company developed software technology to automate the design, analysis & testing of electronic hardware and embedded systems software in electronic systems & components. The company was acquired by Siemens for EUR 4.06 billion on March 31, 2017.

Mentor Venture Partners was a venture capital firm headquartered in Palo Alto, California. They firm specialized in seed, early stage and later stage investments. It used to seek investments in internet and technology sectors.

Founded in 2005, MentorTech Ventures was a venture capital investment firm based in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. The firm preferred investments in seed and early-stage rounds. The firm preferred to invest in companies based in Philadelphia and New York City, The firm invested in the information technology, marketing technology and physical sciences industries.

MER Telemanagement Solutions is a US-based provider of solutions for telecommunications expense management (TEM), CA and contact center software. Its TEM suite helps organizations reduce operational expenses, improve productivity and optimize networks and services associated with communications networks and information technology.

MercadoLibre runs the largest e-commerce marketplace in Latin America, with more than 218 million active users and 1 million active sellers across 18 countries, stitching into its commerce network or fintech solutions when last reported. The company operates a host of complementary businesses to its core online shop, with shipping solutions (Mercado Envios), a payment and financing operation (Mercado Pago and Mercado Credito), advertisements (Mercado Clics), classifieds, and a turnkey e-commerce solution (Mercado Shops) rounding out its arsenal. MercadoLibre generates revenue from final value fees, advertising royalties, payment processing, insertion fees, subscription fees, and interest income from consumer and small-business lending.

Based in Stuttgart, Germany, Mercedes-Benz Group makes premium and luxury passenger vehicles and commercial vans. Brands include Mercedes-Benz, AMG, and Maybach. Mercedes-Benz Mobility provides the company's dealers and its customers with vehicle financing as well as mobility services in ride hailing, car sharing, and charging. Mercedes owns 9.74% of Aston Martin and 9.55% of Beijing Automotive Group. Through Tenaciou3 Prospect Investment, Li Shufu, chair of Chinese automaker Geely, owns 9.69% of Mercedes-Benz. Other major shareholders include Beijing Automotive Group at 9.98% and Kuwait Investment Authority at 4.9% (6.8% before the sale of a 1.9% stake in March 2023).
Merchant Venture Investment was a venture capital firm.

Founded in 2000, Merck Capital Ventures was a subsidiary of Merck & Co Inc. based in Woodcliff Lake, New Jersey. The firm preferred to invest capital in commercialization, distribution and delivery of pharmaceuticals and related health care services.

Founded in 2010, Merck Global Health Innovation Fund is the corporate venture capital arm of Merck & Co. based in Rahway, New Jersey. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the digital health, drug discovery, manufacturing, supply chain, information technology, medicine, and technology sectors.

Merck Millipore is a provider of life science products and services. The company provides innovative products and services that help academic, biotechnology and pharmaceutical customers advance their research, development and production.

Founded in 2004, Mercuria Energy Trading is an asset manager based in Geneva, Switzerland. The firm prefers to invest and trade in oil and gas, energy, petrochemicals, biofuels, environmental products, natural gas and liquefied natural gas, power, dry bulk commodities, soft commodities, base metals, agricultural, and commodities sectors.

Founded in 2004, Mercury Fund is a venture capital investment firm headquartered in Houston, Texas. The firm prefers to invest in the software-as-a-service, cloud, data, and artificial intelligence sectors.

Merge Healthcare was a provider of enterprise imaging and interoperability services. The company used to provide medical imaging and information software and delivered related services. It also offered clinical trials software, health data and analytic services that engage consumers in their personal health. It was founded in 1987 and is Chicago, Illinois. It used to aim for strategic investments through acquisitions to helps its business expand across the country and worldwide. The company was acquired by International Business Machines on October 13, 2015.

Meridian Bioscience is an integrated life science company. It develops and distributes diagnostic tests and reagents, as well as biologic substances used by pharmaceutical and biotechnology companies. Its Diagnostics segment manufactures tests primarily for gastrointestinal, viral, respiratory, & parasitic infectious diseases. Its testing platforms include isothermal DNA amplification, rapid immunoassays, and enzyme-linked immunoassays. The Life sciences segment sells b-antigens, antibodies, and reagents in bulk to other diagnostic manufacturers, the agriculture industry, and researchers. It also manufactures proteins that biopharmaceutical companies use in new drugs and vaccines. The entity has a business presence in the US and other countries.

MeridianLink is a cloud-based software solution for financial institutions, including banks, credit unions, mortgage lenders, specialty lending providers, and consumer reporting agencies. It generates maximum revenue from Lending Software Solutions.
Founded in 1980, Merifin Capital is a venture capital firm based in Brussels, Belgium. The firm provides early and late-stage, buy-outs, and turn-around investments.

Founded in 1993, Merit Capital Partners is a private equity investment firm based in Chicago, Illinois. The firm prefers to invest in companies operating in the manufacturing, distribution, logistics, and services sectors. The firm seeks to invest in both control/non-control equity and subordinated debt. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Merit Medical Systems is a medical equipment company that develops and manufactures products for use in interventional cardiology, radiology, and endoscopy procedures. The firm reports two segments which are cardiovascular and endoscopy. The majority of its revenue is earned from the cardiovascular segment. The United States generates the majority of the revenue.
Merlin BioMed Group was venture capital firm which used to invest in the biotechnology, pharmaceuticals, medical devices and healthcare care sectors.

Founded in 2007, Merrick Ventures is a private equity firm based in West Palm Beach, Florida. The firm seeks to invest in the business products and services, consumer products and services, software, technology, networking, and equipment sectors.

Investor Legal Name: Merrill Lynch Global Private Equity, Inc.
Description: Merrill Lynch Global Private Equity was a private equity arm of Merrill Lynch based in New York, New York. The firm got merged with Bank of America Capital Investors, the private equity arm of Bank of America and was known as BAML Capital Partners.
Founded in 2012, Mesa Ventures was a venture capital firm based in New York, New York. The firm preferred to invest in early-stage internet and enterprise sector.

Meta Materials delivers previously unachievable performance, across a range of applications, by inventing, designing, developing and manufacturing sustainable, highly functional materials. Its extensive technology platform enables global brands to deliver breakthrough products to their customers in consumer electronics, 5G communications, health and wellness, aerospace, automotive and clean energy. Its products include NANOWEB, which is a transparent conductive film; holoOPTIX; ARfusion; metaAIR; and glucoWISE.
Founded in 2015, Method Capital is a venture capital investment firm based in Chicago, Illinois. The firm seeks to invest in growth-stage companies focused on the technology sector.

Metro is the third-largest grocery retailer in Canada (behind Loblaw and Sobeys) and also owns the top pharmacy chain in Quebec, Jean Coutu, following the 2018 acquisition. Its grocery banners include supermarket chain Metro, discounters Super C and Food Basics, and ethnic food grocer Adonis, while its pharmacies primarily operate under the Jean Coutu and Brunet trademarks. Metro operates both as a food retailer and a franchisor, licensing its trademarks and supplying merchandise to registered pharmacists. The firm also acts as a wholesaler and distributor to serve smaller, neighborhood grocery stores. Unlike peers Loblaw and Sobeys which operate chain stores across Canada, Metro's operations are concentrated in Quebec and Ontario, with no presence in western Canada.

Founded in 2000, Metropolis Ventures is a corporate venture capital arm of Metropolis Partners based in San Francisco, California. The firm prefers to invest in the energy, food, software, and consumer sectors.
Founded in 2021, MEXC Pioneer is a venture capital firm based in Victoria, Seychelles. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the blockchain, and cryptocurrency sectors.
Mezzanine Capital Partners was a financial services company which provided debt and equity related services to venture capital backed start-up companies.

MGT Capital Investments Inc ranks as one of the largest U.S. based Bitcoin miners. It has operating facilities in northern Sweden and Washington State. The company will own and operate approximately 7,000 Bitmain S9 mining rigs, and 50 GPU-based Ethereum mining machines. Further, the Company continues to execute on an expansion model to secure low cost power and grow its crypto assets materially.

Founded in 2006, MHS Capital is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm invests in early-stage companies. The firm seeks to invest in consumer products, consumer services, digital, software, e-commerce, mobile, healthcare, and information technology sectors across the United States, Europe, and South America.
Founded in 2009, MI Ventures is a venture capital firm based in New York, New York. The firm seeks to make seed and early-stage investments in the technology sector.

Mi-jack Products is a provider of container-handling equipment. The company offers translift and travelift rubber-tired gantry cranes to automation solutions for ports, intermodal terminals, and industrial applications. The company was founded in 1954 and is headquartered in Hazel Crest, Illinois.
Mr. Michael Adler serves as Advisor at Atunwa Digital. He is an Angel Investor.

Mr. Michael Barrett serves as Chief Executive Officer at Magnite. Mr. Barrett is an Angel Investor. He also held at ad exchange pioneer Rubicon Project before its 2020 merger with CTV leader Telaria. Before joining Rubicon Project, he was President and Chief Executive Officer at Millennial Media, an independent mobile ad technology company. In October 2015, AOL/Verizon acquired Millennial Media. Previously, he served as President and Founder of Ichabod Farm Ventures, a private investment firm he established after working as Executive Vice President and Chief Revenue Officer of Yahoo. Earlier, he worked at Google, where he led integration efforts following the acquisition of Admeld, where he also served as Chief Executive Officer. He has served as Executive Vice President and Chief Revenue Officer at Fox Interactive Media, Executive Vice President of Sales and Partnerships at AOL Media Networks, and in senior sales positions at GeoCities and Disney Online. He was an economics major at The College of the Holy Cross, and currently serves as a Trustee of the College.

Mr. Michael Boodaei is a Co-Founder & serves as Chief Executive Officer at Transmit Security. He is a Co-Founder and serves as Partner at Picture Capital. He served as Board Member at Fireglass. Mr. Boodaei also serves as an Advisor at Island. He serves as Board Member at WireX. He co-founded and served as Chief Executive Officer at Trusteer. He is an Investor at Hyperwise Ventures.

Mr. Michael Carpenter is the Founder & serves as Executive Chairman at XFactor.io. Mr. Carpenter is an Angel Investor. He serves as a Venture Partner at Lightspeed Venture Partners. He served as President of global Sales and Field Operations at CrowdStrike. He also served as a Board Member at Armis. He served as an Advisor at Sapho. He is responsible for expanding CrowdStrike's global sales footprint, customer acquisition, sales enablement, and the company's partner program. His major focus on building a best-in-class sales team is generating historic growth in revenue for the company across the globe. He also oversees CrowdStrike's successful expansion in the public sector and healthcare market. With 20 years of experience in the security industry, he brings deep expertise in building global, high-growth sales organizations spanning both the private and public sectors. He brings a combination of strategic planning, out-of-the-box thinking, risk-taking, and teamwork to the sales process. His mantra of "treat others as you want to be treated" resonates throughout CrowdStrike's sales organization, building exceptional levels of collaboration and alignment across his global team. Described as entrepreneurial, strategic, and determined, he ably guides his team in generating both record revenues and outstanding customer retention rates in a highly competitive market and public safety market.

Mr. Michael Chasen is a Co-Founder of SocialRadar. He served as Chief Executive Officer and Board Member at PrecisionHawk. He is also a Co-Founder and Chief Executive Officer at Class. Mr. Chasen serves as Board Member at Symplicity. Before PrecisionHawk, he was the co-founder and CEO of Blackboard (NASDAQ: BBBB), a leader in the global eLearning space. He grew Blackboard to serve over 30,000 institutions worldwide and had 3,000 employees and 20 offices around the world. He took Blackboard public in 2004 and ran it as a public company for 7 years before selling it to Providence Equity Partners for $1.7B. Mr. Chasen then started SocialRadar, a company specializing in improving location accuracy on SmartPhones, which he sold to Verizon in 2016. He has his undergraduate degree in Computer Science and got his MBA from Georgetown.

Mr. Michael Cheung is the Founder and serves as a General Partner & Managing Principal at Caerus Investment Advisors. Mr. Cheung is an Angel Investor. He is the Founder and serves as Managing Principal at Caerus Investment Advisors. He served as an Operating Advisor at Dugan Katragadda. With a background in private banking and wealth management, he excels in investments and succession planning, serving high net worth individuals and providing financial advisory services. Prior to founding his own firm, he gained experience at Credit Suisse and Barclays Wealth, showcasing a strong foundation in asset management and financial modeling.

Mr. Michael Dell is the Founder and serves as Chief Executive Officer and Chairman at Dell Technologies. Mr. Dell is an Angel Investor. He co-founded and served as Chairman & Chief Executive Officerat at Dell-VMWare Tracking He is also the Founder of DFO Management. He builds the essential infrastructure for organizations to build their digital future, transform IT, and protect their most important information. In 1992, he became the youngest Chief Executive Officer ever to earn a ranking on the Fortune 500. He took Dell Technologies private in 2013, setting the stage to architect the largest technology deal in history with the combination of Dell, EMC, and VMware in 2016 and the subsequent relisting of Dell Technologies on the public markets in 2018. In 1998, he formed MSD Capital, now DFO Management, a private investment firm that exclusively manages the capital for the Dell family. In 1999, he and Susan Dell, established the Michael & Susan Dell Foundation to accelerate opportunities for children growing up in urban poverty in the U.S., India, and South Africa. is an honorary member of the Foundation Board of the World Economic Forum and is an executive committee member of the International Business Council. He is also a member of the Technology Chief Executive Officer Council and the Business Roundtable. He serves on the advisory board of Tsinghua University's School of Economics and Management in Beijing, China, and the governing board of the Indian School of Business in Hyderabad, India. He is a board member of Catalyst and also served as the United Nations Foundation's first Global Advocate for Entrepreneurship. He has a Degree from the University of Texas, Austin.

Mr. Michael Hirshland is a Co-Founder and serves as Partner at Resolute Ventures. Mr. Hirshland served as Board Member at Greats. He also serves as a Board Member at Hopscotch, Fancy Hands and and Later. Farmstead, He serves as a Board Member and Advisor at Signifyd. He served as a Board Member at Pact, Later and CARD.com. He has been an investor and contributor to the early-stage ecosystem for 23 years. He launched Resolute Ventures in 2011, where he has led seed investments in Companies including BarkBox (NYSE BARK), Opendoor (NYSE OPEN), Sunrise (acquired by Microsoft), Bitium (acquired by Google), Orbitera (acquired by Google), WHOOP, Greenhouse and Signifyd, among many others. He previously led the seed round for Automattic (WordPress). Before Resolute, he was a partner at Polaris Ventures from 1999-2011, where he created Dogpatch Labs, the founder community that helped launch over 350 companies including Instagram, TaskRabbit, and Twilio.

Mr. Michael Lazerow is a Co-Founder and serves as Managing Director and Investment Committee Member at Velvet Sea Ventures. He is the Founder and Investor at Lazerow Ventures. He was the Founder of the L3 investment fund. He also serves as an Executive Chairman at Olympia Media Group. He serves as a Board Member at Elementus, Pixel Vault, KarmaCheck, and Mercato. He co-founded & served as a Board Member at SuperF3st. He co-founded and served as Chief Executive Officer and Board Member at Shape Matrix. He also served as a Special Advisor at Greycroft Partners. He is an Angel Investor. He was a Board Member of Odyssey and MapAnything. He is a serial entrepreneur, investor, writer, and painter best known as the founder of Buddy Media, a social marketing software company that was purchased by Salesforce.com (NYSE: CRM) in 2012 for $800 million. He most recently served as Salesforce's chief strategy officer. During his three years at the company, Salesforce grew its annual revenue run rate to $6 billion from $2 billion and was named the most innovative company in the world by Forbes Magazine for three consecutive years. Before Salesforce and Buddy Media, he founded GOLF.com, purchased by Time Warner's Time division in January 2006. And as an undergraduate at Northwestern University, he started UWIRE, an Associated Press-like network of more than 850 student-run newspapers, purchased by CBS. With 65 early-stage investments, including Buzzfeed, Domo, Mashable, and Dash Radio, he is one of the most prolific tech investors in New York City, where he spends much of his time cheerleading, providing therapy to and coaching entrepreneurs. Additional honors include Fortune Magazine's 40 Under 40, Crain's New York 40 Under 40, Number 1 on the Silicon Alley 100, and the Ad Age Digital A-List. He earned a bachelor's and master's degree in journalism from Northwestern. His writing about technology, advertising, startups, investing, and life has appeared in Ad Age, Forbes, Fortune, Fast Company, and more than a dozen newspapers, including Roll Call, the newspaper of Capitol Hill, and the Fort Lauderdale Sun-Sentinel, and the Miami Herald.

Mr. Michael Levit is a Co-Founder & serves as Chief Executive Officer at Tempest (Ireland). Mr. Levit serves as Strategic Advisor at Catapult Capital. Mr. Levit served as Managing Partner at Founders Den. He also served as Board Member at August Home. In 2017, he co-founded the company to embed private search into our everyday lives after observing a gap in the market for a mainstream private-focused search engine. Michael is an experienced and passionate entrepreneur, previously co-founding Spigot - one of the world's leading multi-platform application developers. Michael has held advisory and executive positions at top tech companies, including Alibaba, Softonic, DeleteMe, Docker, Say Media and Revel Systems. He has also consulted the world's largest corporations during his time at Accenture. Michael holds a B.A. in Business Economics, a B.S. in Mechanical and Environmental Engineering and a Master of Business Economics from the University of California, Santa Barbara. He serves as Board Member at Softonic International.

Dr. Michael Münnix serves as Board Member at Quobyte. He is a Co-Founder and serves as Partner & Managing Director at Backtrace Capital. He serves as a Venture Partner at Planet A. Dr. Münnix served as a Venture Partner & Investment Committee Member at Spacewalk VC. He served as a Partner at Target Partners. He brings 12 years of venture capital, software development, and R&D experience to the partnership. He joined Target Partners in 2011 and became a Partner in 2016. He has been active in the IT industry since 1997. From 2003 to 2008 he led various development projects in financial technology at ORIMOS Financial Analytics, Berlin. ORIMOS was sold to ION Trading Group in 2008. In 1999 he founded a software development firm that focused on projects for mid-sized companies and universities. His experience included the development of complex software architectures and the management of larger IT projects. In 2008 he received his Diploma in physics from the Technical University of Berlin and in 2011 he was awarded a Ph.D. in theoretical physics from the University of Duisberg-Essen. He was a Fellow of the German National Academic Foundation and a Fulbright Scholar at Boston University during his Ph.D. studies. He served on the advisory board at Adsquare GmbH as well as an observer on the board of directors at Swarm64 AS. He served as a Board Member at Datapath.io. He served as a Board Observer at Senic and Swarm64. He served as a Board Observer at Corrux. He holds a Ph.D. in Theoretical Physics from the University of Duisburg-Essen, Ph.D. in Physics from Boston University, and MS in Physics from Technische Universität Berlin.

Mr. Michael Skok served as Founding Partner at Underscore VC. Mr. Skok started his first software business as a teenager, spent 21 years as an entrepreneur and then the past 18 years as a venture investor. During this time, he has founded, worked with and invested in startups, and created thousands of jobs and billions of dollars of value. Along the way, he also mentored and taught for 4 years at Harvard University, and created the Startup Secrets series. As an entrepreneur and an investor, Mr. Skok has focused on breakthrough technologies and disruptive business models including Open Source, Cloud, IoT, and emerging domains such as Blockchain, Virtual/Augmented Reality, and Artificial Intelligence/Machine Learning. He has served on or is active on many private and public boards such as Acquia, Demandware (now a Salesforce company), Mautic (acquired by Acquia in 2019), Salsify and Zaius. He has also participated in leadership roles in many industry groups such as the Software Publishers Association where he was Chairman for many years in Europe. In 2015, Mr. Skok co-founded Underscore VC first and foremost to empower entrepreneurs to realize their vision in building impactful businesses. He has a passion for helping the next generation of entrepreneurs succeed by not only investing but bringing the resources, talent and commitment of an aligned community around them to assure their success. He served as Board Member at Cazena.

Mr. Michael Tanne is an Angel Investor. Mr. Tanne served as Managing Partner at Endeavor Partners. He is a successful, serial entrepreneur who has started several companies, including AdForce (IPO), XDegrees (acquired by Microsoft), and Wink (acquired by Reunion) and invested in over 30 companies, including LinkedIn, ICON Aircraft, Wikia, BrightRoll and Fundly. He previously led a product at Verity (IPO), led a technology accelerator in Poland and worked at Apple. He earned an EE from the University of Alberta and an MBA from Stanford. He is also an Angel Investor.

Mr. Michael Yavonditte is a Co-Founder and serves as Chief Executive Officer and Board Member at Yieldmo. Mr. Yavonditte is an Angel Investor. He founded and served as Chief Executive Officer at Hashable. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Quigo Technologies, Inc. since 2002. He served as Vice President Of Sales at USA Networks Electronic Commerce Solutions Group in New York. In that position, he was responsible for negotiating complex 'outsourced' e-commerce alliances with leading U.S. retailers. His group managed the e-commerce operations at CBS Sportsline, Nascar.com and the National Hockey League. In 2000, he joined AltaVista, a CMGI-owned company, where he quickly negotiated and closed several large, multi-year, multi-million dollar agreements for AltaVista. He also took an interest in figuring out new ways to monetize relevancy-based search results and was instrumental in the formation of the Trusted Feed program. Mr. Yavonditte served as Managing Director of the Strategic Alliances Group, where he was responsible for the day-to-day operations of AV's business development activities and one of their largest revenue streams. In 1997, Mr. Yavonditte joined Juno Online Services, Inc. as a Director in their business development group. In 1998, he was promoted to Vice President and continued to focus on negotiating large advertising and e-commerce agreements. He started his career at Ziff-Davis Publishing in New York where he held various sales and management roles.He served as Director of Quigo Technologies, Inc. In 1996, he was named one of only three ZD employees to win the coveted Chairman's Club Award two consecutive years. Mr. Yavonditte has a degree in Business and Political Science from Pace University in New York.

Michelman is a corporation based at Cincinnati, Ohio. The company is a global developer and manufacturer of environmentally friendly materials for industry, offering solutions for the coatings, printing & packaging and industrial manufacturing markets. The management board is responsible for the administration of the firm.

Micrel was a global manufacturer of IC power and mixed-signal integrated circuits. It specialized in power management IC's, linear IC's, RF wireless IC's, LAN solutions and physical layer transceiver IC's. The company was founded in 1978 and was headquartered in San Jose, California. It acquired other companies in the same line of business to expand its operations and build a broader customer base.

Microchip Technology became an independent company in 1989 when it was spun off from General Instrument. More than half of revenue comes from MCUs, which are used in a wide array of electronic devices from remote controls to garage door openers to power windows in autos. The company's strength lies in lower-end 8-bit MCUs that are suitable for a wider range of less technologically advanced devices, but the firm has expanded its presence in higher-end MCUs and analog chips as well.

Provider of semiconductor products and services for the defense, aerospace and industrial markets. The company's range of products include radiation-hardened, analog mixed-signal integrated circuits, power-management products, timing and synchronization devices, security technologies and enterprise storage systems.

The company conducts its business through three principal business segments namely the commercial foodservice equipment group, the food processing equipment group and the residential kitchen equipment group. The firm derives the majority of its revenue from the commercial foodservice equipment group segment.

The firm seeks to acquire or invest in privately held companies and divisions or subsidiaries of large corporations.
Mr. Mike Egan is an Angel Investor.
Mr. Mike Kearns is an Angel Investor.

Mr. Mikhail Fridman serves as Member of the Board of Directors at Alfa Bank. He was a Co-Founder and served as Chairman at LetterOne. Mr. Fridman graduated from school in Lvov in 1980, where he won school Olympiads in physics and mathematics. After graduating from university with a first-class degree, he started to work as an entrepreneur. He has built private businesses with several partners, from the bottom up, in retail banking; telecoms; insurance, and water. He is co-founder of the ABHH group based in Luxembourg, which invests in banking groups, that provide retail banking services - for more than five million people and has about 40,000 corporate customers. In 1995 he and his partners entered the food retail market. They started with a handful of retail stores. The company they created - is today "X5 Retail Group", which is listed in London - is the No.1 food retailer in Russia - with 15700 stores. In 2003 he completed a deal with BP to form the 50/50 TNK-BP joint venture, which was sold for $56 billion in 2012. Mr. Fridman is the founder of the International Jazz Festival in Lvov, which is now one of Europe's top 10 Jazz festivals. He is an active supporter of Jewish initiatives worldwide - including co-founding the Genesis Prize, which is awarded annually in Jerusalem and has been dubbed the Jewish Nobel by Time magazine. He also co-founded the Genesis Philanthropy Group, which develops and enhances a sense of Jewish identity among Russian-speaking Jews worldwide.

Founded in 1995, Milestone Partners is a private equity firm based in Villanova, Pennsylvania. The firm prefers to invest in the technology and financial solution sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Millennial Media is an independent mobile marketplace that provides digital advertising services to its clients. The unique data and technology assets enable its advertising clients to connect with their target audiences at scale. The company is a part of the marketing and advertising industry and specializes in mobile advertising and marketing, mobile monetization and mobile data. It offers advertisers a suite of solutions that allow them to reach and connect with the target audiences across screens, from smartphones, tablets and other mobile devices to PCs. It aims to acquire those companies that will enable it to accelerate its leading position in mobile advertising. The company was founded in 2006 and is based in the United States.

Millennium Global Holdings is engaged in the seafood business. Its business activity is the processing and export of several quality and high valued seafood products such as Black Tiger Shrimps, Kisu (asohos) fillet, frozen lobsters, among others. It derives its revenue primarily from the export sale of aquatic and marine products.

MiMedx Group develops and markets regenerative biomaterial products and bioimplants made from the human amniotic membrane, birth tissues, and human skin & bone. Its products are primarily targeted towards the wound-care, burn, surgical, sports medicine, and orthopedics markets. MiMedx's key products are allografts processed from amniotic tissue, which include EpiFix for external use and AmnioFix for internal use. AmnioCord, AmnioFill, EpiBurn, and EpiCord are some of its other products. Also, it sells allografts for ophthalmic surgery and dental applications through licenses to third parties.

Operator and provider of mobile messaging and payment services. The company offers mobile marketing and messaging services in Germany, Brazil, China, Great Britain, Indonesia, Romania, Spain and the United State America.
Developer, manufacturer and marketer of medical devices. Its business is segmented into three - patient monitoring and life support products, in-vitro diagnostic products and medical imaging systems.

This firm invests in private start-ups operating in intelligent technologies, robotics, and technologies that promote a hydrogen economy, electrification, new materials, and carbon neutrality sectors.

Founded in 2001, Miramar Digital Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Corona del Mar, California. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the internet of things, big data, and artificial intelligence sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

The firm seeks to invest in Southern California-based companies operating in the communication, mobile, enterprise applications, infrastructure, and information technology sectors. The company's three operating segments are North America, international and products & systems, of which key revenue is derived from the North America segment. Services segment provides asset protection solutions predominantly in North America, with a large amount of concentration in the United States, followed by Canada, consisting of non-destructive testing, and inspection. The asset protection solutions include field inspections, consulting, maintenance, data management, access, monitoring and laboratory quality assurance.
Founded in 2019, MIT Delta V is an educational accelerator firm based in Cambridge, Massachusetts. The firm provides a capstone educational opportunity for MIT students.

Founded in 2015, Mitchell Family Office is a family office firm based in Birmingham, Michigan. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the healthcare, automotive, commercial & industrial, business services, and digital commerce sectors.

Mavenir Systems provided software-based networking services that enable mobile service providers to deliver next generation services over 4G LTE networks. The company had a fully virtualized end to end portfolio of voice nad video, messaging and mobile core products that include IP Multimedia Subsystem (IMS), Evolved Packet Core (EPC) and Session Border Controller (SBC). The company sought to expand its business operations through mergers and acquisitions. The company (NYSE: MVNR) was acquired by Mitel Networks on April 29, 2015.

Founded in 2012, Mithril Capital Management is a venture capital investment firm based in Austin, Texas. The firm seeks to invest in businesses that focus on technology. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Mitsubishi is a conglomerate that operates businesses in various industries. Its operating segments include natural gas, industrial materials, petroleum & chemicals, mineral resource, industrial infrastructure, automotive, food & consumer industry, power solutions and urban development.

Mitsubishi International is an operator of a trading company. The company engages in the trading of industrial materials, crude oil and petroleum products, commodity chemicals and non-ferrous and ferrous raw materials. The company was founded in 1954 and is headquartered in New York.

Manufacturer of pharmaceuticals focuses centered on ethical and over-the-counter drugs. The company offers products that are used for diabetic nephropathy, chronic kidney diseases, hyperphosphatemia and depression.

Founded in 1971, Mittelstandische Beteiligungsgesellschaft Hessen is a venture capital firm based in Wiesbaden, Germany. Mizrahi Tefahot Bank offers commercial and personal banking services. The company reports seven core segments: household, consisting of individuals with assets less than ILS 3 million in assets; private banking, consisting of individuals with financial assets greater than ILS 3 million; micro and small business; medium business; large business; institutional investor, servicing asset managers, fund managers, and insurance companies; and financial management, including trade operations, asset, and liability management, and miscellaneous investments. Approximately half of the company's total revenue comes from the household segment. The company operates through a branch network spanning Israel, Europe, and the Americas.

MKS Instruments is engaged in providing instruments, subsystems and process control systems used to measure, monitor, deliver and control parameters of manufacturing processes. The company's product portfolio includes instruments, components and systems required in manufacturing products such as flat panel displays, medical devices and electronic materials, among others used in industrial technologies, semiconductors, life and health sciences and research and defense markets. The company organizes itself into three reportable business segments: Vacuum Solutions, Photonics Solutions and Materials Solutions. The Vacuum Solutions segment contributes the majority of the company's revenue and the majority of its revenue is earned in the United States.

Founded in 2000, MMC Ventures is a venture capital investment firm headquartered in London, United Kingdom. The firm focuses on early stage transformative technology companies that utilise AI and data science across sectors including enterprise AI, cloud & data infrastructure, fintech and data-driven health.

Mobile Heights Business Center was a business accelerator for startups based in Lund, Sweden. The firm invested in the start-up businesses operating in the software, mobile and information technology sectors.

MobileIron provides a purpose-built mobile IT platform. The company's platform enables enterprises to manage and secure mobile applications, content, and devices while providing their employees with device choice, privacy, and native user experience.It serves to midsize and large enterprises across industries like financial services, government, healthcare, legal, manufacturing, professional services, retail, technology, and telecommunications. Geographically, it operates in California North America, Europe, the Middle East, Asia, and Australia.

Dean Witter Reynolds was an American stock brokerage and securities firm catering to retail clients. Prior to its acquisition, it was among the largest retail firms in the securities industry with over 9,000 account executives (ranking third in the US in 1996) and was among the largest members of the New York Stock Exchange. The company served over 3.2 million clients primarily in the U.S. Dean Witter provided debt and equity underwriting and brokerage as well as mutual funds and other saving and investment products for individual investors. The company's asset management arm, Dean Witter InterCapital, with total assets of $90.0 billion prior to acquisition, was one of the largest asset management operations in the U.S.In 1997, Dean Witter's parent company Dean Witter, Discover, Inc., which also owned Discover Card, merged with investment banking house Morgan Stanley to form Morgan Stanley Dean Witter. The combined firm later dropped the Dean Witter name. In 2009, the Dean Witter retail operations were transferred to Morgan Stanley Smith Barney, a joint venture with Citigroup.For many years, the company used the corporate slogan, "We measure success one investor at a time," which was later adopted by Morgan Stanley.

Developer of healthcare management software. The company offers credentialing software that helps health systems and hospitals streamline the entire credentialing process from onboarding through reappointment, by eliminating paper-based and manual administrative tasks.

Provider of mobile content solutions and services to the wireless industry. Mr. Nathaniel Turner serves as Chairman & Chief Executive Officer at Collectors (Santa Ana). Mr. Turner co-founded & served as Chairman at Flatiron. He is a Co-Founder of Conductor Capital. He oversees all initiatives across provider solutions, clinical oncology, business development, sales operations, legal, and other corporate functions. Before co-founding Flatiron Health, he was co-founder and CEO of Invite Media, an advertising technology company based in NYC. Invite Media was acquired by Google in 2010. Before Invite Media, he started numerous internet companies and also worked at Say Media and First Round Capital. An active angel investor, he has invested in over 30 technology startups throughout the country, including Bell Biosystems, Clover Health, Color Genomics, Doctor Evidence, Gravie, Notable Labs, Oscar, and Quarter Health. He also serves as an Advisor at Great Oaks Venture Capital. He served as an Advisory Board Member at Integrated CBD. Oracle provides database technology and enterprise resource planning, or ERP, software to enterprises around the world. Founded in 1977, Oracle pioneered the first commercial SQL-based relational database management system. Today, Oracle has 430,000 customers in 175 countries, supported by its base of 136,000 employees.

Oracle Cerner is a leading supplier of healthcare information technology solutions and tech-enabled services. The company is a long-standing market leader in the electronic health record industry and along with rival Epic Systems corners a majority of the market for acute care EHR within health systems. The company is guided by the mission of its founding partners to provide seamless medical records across all healthcare providers to improve outcomes. Beyond medical records, the company offers a wide range of technology that supports the clinical, financial and operational needs of healthcare facilities.

Developer of cloud business software suite intended for enterprise resource planning and to keep track of financials. The company's cloud business software suite offers enterprise resource management, accounting, business management, customer relationship management, business intelligence, order management, production management, supply chain management and warehouse management, enabling companies to manage all key business processes in a single system. Netsuite Oracle seeks to acquire other companies whose businesses will complement its existing operations and also those that develop business management software, and enterprise billing software. It was acquired by Oracle on November 07, 2016.

OraSure Technologies is a medical devices company that develops, manufactures and distributes oral fluid diagnostic and collection devices. Its reportable segments are diagnostics and molecular solutions. The diagnostics segment produces rapid oral diagnostic tests and specimen collection devices for infectious diseases such as HIV and HCV. The molecular solutions segment specializes in kits used to collect, stabilize and transport genetic material samples for molecular testing of both hereditary diseases and infectious diseases, such as COVID-19. The company gets the majority of its sales from the molecular solutions business, derived mainly from customers in the United States.

ORBCOMM is a satellite communications company that primarily provides machine-to-machine communication, which is designed to track, monitor, and control fixed and mobile assets. The company operates in such markets as transportation and distribution, heavy equipment, industrial fixed assets, oil and gas, maritime, mining, and government. The company earns revenue across the United States, South America, Japan, and Europe, with the majority from the U.S. The company owns telecommunications infrastructure, specifically low Earth orbit satellites and accompanying ground infrastructure.

Orbital Infrastructure Group was a diversified infrastructure services platform that provided engineering, design, construction and maintenance services to customers in three operating segments namely electric power, telecommunications and renewables. The company was founded on April 21, 1984 and was headquartered in Houston, Texas. The company was liquidated and ceased operations on March 5, 2024.

Orbotech is an Israel-based manufacturer of scientific instruments, although China is its biggest market. It manufactures products which can be used to test other products in development in terms of efficiency. Orbotech functions within three operating segments Production Solutions for the Electronics Industry, Solar Energy and Recognition Software. The company secures a major share of its revenue from the sale of products to suit the needs of the electronics industry. It develops capital equipment for inspection and deposition for manufacturers of printed circuit boards and semiconductors devices. The Solar Energy segment manufactures photovoltaic energy systems and the recognition software segment develops check processing and healthcare payments automation solutions to banks.
Founded in 2003, ONAMI is funded by Business Oregon and Oregon Tax Lottery Funds. The University is based in Corvallis,Oregon.

Mr. Oren Zeev is a Founding Partner of Zeev Ventures. Mr. Zeev serves as a Board Member at SmartShopper. Orgenesis is a biotech company working to unlock the potential of cell and gene therapies. The company's business includes two reporting segments: octomera and therapies.
Provider of market intelligence services headquartered in Sydney, Australia. The company offers a suite of services that enable its clients to maximize the opportunity of public ownership.

Over the three decades, OUCC has constantly improved its core ethylene oxide processing technology and has become a major supplier of ethylene glycol and ethylene oxide derivatives in Taiwan and throughout the Asia-Pacific Region.

Mr. Orion Henry serves as an Advisor at Infusion 51a. He served as Advisor at Heavybit. He is a Founder at Heroku. He co-founded TrustCommerce. He holds a BS (Bachelor of Science) in Computer Science from University of San Diego.

Orthofix Medical is a medical device company delivering orthopedic and spine solutions to healthcare providers. The majority of the company's sales come from the global spine segment in the United States. Orthofix distributes its products throughout North America, Europe, and several countries globally. The company provides solutions to hospitals, physicians, other healthcare providers, and patients.

OrthoPediatrics is a medical device company. The company is engaged in providing products to the pediatric orthopedic market. The firm designs develop and commercialize implants and instruments to meet the needs of surgeons and patients. Its products, include PediLoc, PediPlates, Cannulated Screws, PediFlexTM nail, PediNailTM, PediLoc Tibia and ACL reconstruction system among others.

Provider of biopharmaceutical services intended to aid in scientific discoveries and new treatments. The solutions combine proprietary software, physical intellectual property (or IP) for integrated circuit (or IC) designs, electrical measurement hardware tools, various methodologies, and professional services. The company's products and services are sold to integrated device manufacturers (or IDMs), fabless semiconductor companies, foundries, outsourced semiconductor assembly and test (or OSATs), and system houses.

Mr. Pejman Nozad is a Co-Founder and serves as Managing Partner at Pear. Over the past two decades, he has been a seed investor in some of the most iconic tech companies including Doordash, Dropbox, Applovin, Gusto, Guardant Health, Branch, Aurora Solar, Soundhound, CourseHero, and others. As an immigrant from Iran, he did not take the typical path towards becoming a VC. In fact, he is tech's most unlikely venture capitalist. After arriving in the U.S., he lived in an attic above a yogurt shop and then worked at a rug store in downtown Palo Alto. He immersed himself in the vanguard of technology and slowly, with a few small investments, developed a reputation for both identifying talent and taking promising ideas to the next level. He received the Ellis Island Medal of Honor in 2014 for his contribution to America as an immigrant.

Developer of novel drug therapies intended for the treatment and management of adolescent lifestyle conditions. Pfizer is one of the world's largest pharmaceutical firms, with annual sales close to $50 billion (excluding COVID-19 product sales). While it historically sold many types of healthcare products and chemicals, now prescription drugs and vaccines account for the majority of sales. Top sellers include the pneumococcal vaccine Prevnar 13, the cancer drug Ibrance and cardiovascular treatment Eliquis. Pfizer sells these products globally, with international sales representing close to 50% of total sales. Within international sales, emerging markets are a major contributor.

PFSweb is a commerce services company. The company's operating segments include PFS-oOperations. It offers services on an a la carte basis or as a complete end-to-end solution.

PG&E is a holding company whose main subsidiary is Pacific Gas and Electric, a regulated utility operating in Central and Northern California that serves 5.3 million electricity customers and 4.6 million gas customers in 47 of the state's 58 counties. PG&E operated under bankruptcy court supervision between January 2019 and June 2020. In 2004, PG&E sold its unregulated assets as part of an earlier postbankruptcy reorganization.

PGT Innovations is a leading manufacturer of impact-resistant aluminum and vinyl-framed windows and doors and offers a broad range of fully customizable window and door products. The company distributes products through multiple channels, including window distributors, building supply distributors, window replacement dealers and enclosure contractors. The products are sold through authorized dealers and distributor networks in the states of the Caribbean, Florida, Canada and South and Central America but the majority of its revenue is generated from Florida.

Operator of a contract research organization intended to offer integrated drug development, laboratory and lifecycle management services to client enterprises. The Company is an outsource provider of mortgage and fleet management services. It conducts its business through three operating segments: Mortgage Production, Mortgage Servicing and Fleet Management Services.

Nearly 50% of the company's revenue comes from the diagnosis and treatment segment, which features imaging systems, ultrasound equipment, and image-guided therapy solutions. The connected care segment (around 30% of revenue) encompasses monitoring and analytics systems for hospitals, informatics business, and also houses the sleep and respiratory care segment. Personal health business (remainder of revenue) is mainly oral health and personal care product lines, which include electric toothbrushes and men's grooming and personal care products.

Its activities include the aggregation of video content, media management, traditional and online advertising, hosting, and content delivery. It operates a global network of individual destination portals under the brand ROO TV that enables end users to view video content over the Internet. Piper Sandler is an investment bank that offers financial advisory services in the areas of mergers and acquisitions, public offerings, public finance, capital markets, institutional brokerage, investment management, research, follow-on and secondary offerings, initial public offerings, and convertible securities. Piramal Enterprises is a diversified holdings company that functions through two segments: financial services and pharma. Its financial-services business focuses on lending, primarily to real estate developers. Alternative asset management and retail financing operations fall into this segment, as well. Pharma is divided into three businesses: contract development and manufacturing, providing solutions across drug lifecycle; complex hospital Generics provides anesthesia and antibiotic products; and consumer healthcare, providing self-care products. The pharma segment focuses on the manufacture, development, and supply of pharmaceuticals for hospitals worldwide.

Pitney Bowes is a global technology company that offers e-commerce solutions to its clients. The company provides various products and services such as domestic delivery, return and fulfillment, cross-border shipping solutions, sorting services for large volumes of postal mail, and technological solutions to enable digital mailing, shipping, and other services. The company operates through three business segments: global e-commerce, presort services, and sendtech solutions. The company generates the majority of its revenue from the United States.

Pittco Management is the single-family office for Joseph R. Pitt Hyde III, founder of AutoZone, and his wife Barbara. The firm was established over 30 years ago and provides investment, accounting, tax, and financial services from its headquarters in Memphis, Tennessee. The firm's investment approach is threefold. First, it invests in best-in-class investment managers across all investment classes including equities, bonds, and energy and natural resources. Second, through its wholly owned entity, Pittco Direct Investments, the firm makes investments directly into companies. Types of investments include venture, buyout, and PIPE transactions. Finally, through a captive relationship with Meta Real Estate Partners, the firm invests in multi-family, hotel, office and retail, primarily in the Southeastern United States.
Pittsburgh Equity Partners is a venture capital investment firm based in Bridgeville, Pennsylvania. The firm seeks to invest in the technology and information technology sector.

Founded in 2002, Pittsburgh Life Sciences Greenhouse is a venture capital firm based in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. The firm invests in companies operating in biotechnology tools, diagnostics, medical devices, healthcare information technology, and therapeutics sectors.

Pivotal Asset Management was a San Francisco, California based private equity firm. The firm primarily used to invest in emerging growth technology companies. It also invested in late stage private and post-IPO technology enterprises that focused on IP based economy, with a specific focus on communications, software and service entities.

Founded in 2013, Pivotal Capital Partners is a Growth/Expansion firm based in Menlo Park, California. The firm provides venture debt financing for equipment purchasing, growth capital, and acquisitions. The firm seeks to make investments in United States venture-backed companies in the technology, life sciences, and sustainable energy sectors.
Founded in 2001, PJC is a venture capital firm based in Boston, Massachusetts. The firm invests across all industries in North America. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Planet Broadband is a venture capital firm based in Boston, Massachusetts and was founded in 1997. The firm specializes in the consulting, investments, and research of companies operating in the broadband, consumer electronic product, system solution and telecommunication sectors

Operator of a multi-currency payment and data processor. The company enables processors, acquiring banks and merchants to accept, process and reconcile credit card transactions in multiple currencies and allows cardholders to view prices and settle transactions in their home currency.

Playmaker Capital is a digital sports media company that sits at the nexus of sports, media, gambling and technology. The company is building a collection of sports media brands and curated engaged audiences of sports fans to sports betting companies, leagues, teams and advertisers. Its segment includes digital media, technology services, affiliate marketing and corporate. Geographic locations are Canada, the United States, the United Kingdom, Uruguay and the rest of the World, the company's majority of the revenue comes from the United States.

PLBY Group connects consumers around the world with products, services, and experiences to help them look good, feel good, and have fun. PLBY Group serves consumers in four categories: style and apparel, digital entertainment and lifestyle, sexual wellness, and beauty and grooming. It operates through three segments direct-to-consumer, licensing, and digital subscriptions and content. It generates revenue through the sales of products and content services to consumers.

Plenus was a venture capital firm that specialized in the early stage investments. It preferred to invest in the agribusiness, education and financial services sectors. The firm was based in San Pedro Garza Garcia. Mexico.

Investor Legal Name: The PNC Financial Services Group, Inc.
Description: Founded in 1851, PNC Financial Services Group is a diversified financial services company offering retail banking, corporate and institutional banking, asset management and residential mortgage banking across the United States.

Established in 1979, PNC Erieview Capital is a minority equity and mezzanine investment firm based in Cleveland, Ohio. The firm prefers to invest in the distribution, manufacturing, healthcare, and service sectors.

Provider of digital photography and media services. The company provides platform metrics, online photo services, mobile platforms, kiosk software services, printing services and personalized cards and invitations.

Since filing our first patent in 1987, PNI has been at the forefront of innovation in the design, development, and application of sensor technology. Our patented Magneto-Inductive (MI) reference sensors, systems and sensor suites provide accurate and reliable information for a wide range of applications, including robotics, surveying, navigation, and oceanography and consumer products.Our ready-to-integrate sensors and sensor systems enable companies to design sensors into their products without making a large investment in in-house sensor expertise. By combining best-in-class sensors with advanced software engines (including auto-calibration and measurement algorithms that can be adapted to the specific needs of an application), PNI's products eliminate the time-consumingand often unexpectedalgorithm development and calibration work that significantly increase development costs and time to market.

A real estate investment trust, whose businesses are organized into three operating segments: Resource, Real Estate and Wood Products.

Power Integrations designs, develops and markets analog and mixed-signal integrated circuits (ICs) and other electronic components and circuitry used in high-voltage power conversion. Products are used in power converters that convert electricity from a high-voltage source to the type of power required for a specified downstream use. Products are used in electronic products including mobile phones, computing and networking equipment, appliances, electronic utility meters, battery-powered tools, industrial controls, and home automation, or internet of things applications such as networked thermostats, power strips and security devices. Provider of energy and smart grid services. The company offers light emitting diode, lighting fixtures, power systems and lamps.

Operator of a contract research organization (CRO) intended to support the pharmaceutical, biotechnology and medical device industries in the form of research services outsourced on a contract basis. Precigen is a biotechnology company that develops synthetic biology solutions. The company designs builds and regulates gene programs. Intrexon's business model is to commercialize its technologies through exclusive channel collaborations with collaborators that have specific industry expertise, development resources, and sales and marketing capabilities, in order to bring new and improved products and processes to market. Its reportable segments are biopharmaceuticals and exemplar. The company's collaborators provide compensation through technology access fees, royalties, milestones, and reimbursement of certain costs.

Predictive Oncology functions in the healthcare domain. It also creates proprietary 3D culture models used in drug development; the Birmingham segment that provides contract services and research focused on solubility improvements, stability studies and protein production; and the Eagan segment that produces the FDA-cleared STREAMWAY System and associated products for automated medical fluid waste management and patient-to-drain medical fluid disposal. It derives maximum revenue from the Eagan Segment.
Founded in 2010, Prehype is a venture capital firm based in New York, New York. The firm prefers to invest in early-stage companies operating in B2C and technology sectors.

Premier Asset Management Group is focused on delivering good investment outcomes for investors through relevant products and active management.
