The company's revenue consists of net warehouse club sales from merchandise sales, membership income from annual membership fees, export sales, and other income, with net warehouse club sales accounting for the majority of the company's total revenue.

Founded in 2004, Prides Capital Partners was a private equity firm based in Boston, Massachusetts that used to invest in the electronic distribution and payments services sectors. The firm also specialized in strategic block, active investing in small and micro-cap public and private companies.

Prim is engaged in the provision of hospital supplies. Supplier of plants and facilities for the metals industry. The company supplies plants, facilities, products and services for the iron, steel and aluminum industries.

Developer of constructive biology technologies designed to accelerate the evolution of highly efficient enzymes and microbes. Priority Technology Holdings is a provider of merchant acquiring and commercial payment solutions to small and medium business enterprises in the United States. The company has three reportable segments which are SMB payments, B2B payments and enterprise payments. The SMB payments segment which generates the majority of revenue provides full-service acquiring and payment-enabled solutions for B2C transactions, leveraging Priority's proprietary software platform, distributed through ISO: The B2B Payments segment provides AP automation solutions to corporations, software partners and industry FIs: and enterprise payments segment provides embedded payment and treasury solutions to enterprise customers to modernize legacy platforms and accelerate software partners' strategies to monetize payments.

Provider of battery energy storage systems for utility, industrial and commercial markets. The software products are hosted on its cloud-based SaaS construction management platform. Subscriptions are sold for a fixed fee and revenue is recognized ratably over the term of the subscription.

Since its founding in 1837, Procter & Gamble has become one of the world's largest consumer product manufacturers, generating more than $80 billion in annual sales. It operates with a lineup of leading brands, including more than 20 that generate north of $1 billion each in annual global sales, such as Tide laundry detergent, Charmin toilet paper, Pantene shampoo, and Pampers diapers. Professional Diversity Network is engaged in providing access to networking, training, educational and employment services to its registered users. Progenics Pharmaceuticals is a developer of medicine for oncological treatment located in New York, United States. Its portfolio includes AZEDRA (to treat malignant and recurrent pheochromocytoma and paraganglioma); 1404 and PyL (imaging agents for prostate cancer); 1404 Index and PyL (analytical tools for analysis and indexing of images for prostate cancer); 1095 (treatment of metastatic prostate cancer); PSMA ADC (treatment of metastatic castration-resistant prostate cancer); and EXINI boneBSI (an analytical Bone Scan Index tool from bone scintigraphy images, currently sold in Europe and Japan). Its partnered products are RELISTOR (sold in the U.S., EU, Australia, and Canada) to treat opioid-induced constipation, and the PRO 140 HIV treatment.

Retailer of fitness apparel and accessories. The company offers clothing, footwear, accessories and other related services.

The consumer products segment is engaged in the research, development, manufacture, distribution, marketing and sale of OTC consumer healthcare products and dietary supplements in the United States and also provide personal genomics products and services.

Developer of databases comprising of periodicals, newspapers, dissertations, out-of-print books and other scholarly information. The company's solutions enable buyers to move fluidly across its customers' direct sales, partner, online, mobile, and emerging channels with personalized experiences. Provider of software-as-a-service (SaaS) web design and marketing tools designed for CPA firms and dental practices. Designer and manufacturer of research, teaching, educational and commercial greenhouses. The company builds custom greenhouses and conservatories that help commercial growers, retail garden centers, research facilities, universities and schools.

Proterial is a Japan-based company that operates through four segments. The high-grade metal products and materials segment produce specialty steel, rolls, amorphous metals and cutting tools. The high-grade functional components and equipment segment produce casting components, piping components and construction components. The wires, cables and related products segment produces electric wires and cables, automotive products and information systems. Infrastructure, automobiles and electronics are the target sectors of the company's products. Japan, Europe, Asia and North America are the biggest markets for Proterial.

Proto Labs is an on-demand manufacturer of custom parts for prototyping and short-run production. The company services clients' needs for prototype solutions, parts for testing procedures, bridge production capabilities during disruptions in manufacturing processes, limited-quantity requests and end-of-life production support. Proton Holdings is a manufacturer of automotives and related parts. The company's products include automobiles, sports cars, automobile parts, accessories and OEM parts enabling customers to get automobiles at suitable prices.

Manufacturer of electronic components. The company manufactures antennas, mobile device antennas, LAN and power magnetic products.

Founded in 2002, Quaker Partners was a venture capital firm based in Bala Cynwyd, Pennsylvania. The firm preferred to invest in seed-stage, early-stage, and later-stage companies. The firm preferred to invest in the healthcare, life sciences, and oncology sectors.

Qualcomm develops and licenses wireless technology and designs chips for smartphones. The company's key patents revolve around CDMA and OFDMA technologies, which are standards in wireless communications that are the backbone of all 3G, 4G, and 5G networks. The company's IP is licensed by virtually all wireless device makers. The firm is also the world's largest wireless chip vendor, supplying nearly every premier handset maker with leading-edge processors. The company also sells RF-front-end modules into smartphones, as well as chips for automotive and Internet of Things markets.

Founded in 2000, Qualcomm Ventures is the corporate venture capital arm of Qualcomm headquartered in San Diego, California. The firm seeks to invest in B2C, B2B, media, healthcare, information technology, SaaS, mobile, cybersecurity, the internet of things, health technology, virtual reality, infrastructure, artificial intelligence, cloud technology, augmented reality, robotics & drones sectors.

Qualcomm Ventures China is a corporate venture capital arm of Qualcomm based in Beijing, China. The firm prefers to invest in seed-stage, early-stage, and later-stage companies operating in artificial intelligence, autonomous cars, cloud tech, the Internet of Things, and mobile sectors.

Qualtrics International is a software technology company based in the United States. It develops software for organizations. Its XM platform is purpose-built to help organizations collect feedback and data across the four vital signs of a business: customers, employees, brand, and product. The firm derives revenue from sales of subscriptions to access its XM platform; research services and professional services.

Quarterhill is focused on the acquisition, management and growth of companies in the intelligent transportation systems (ITS) and innovation and licensing industries. It operates in two segments, licensing, which includes companies that count licensing as their principal business activity and intelligent transportation systems, which include companies that provide integrated systems and solutions to the ITS industry and its adjacent markets. Its geographical segments are the United States, Canada, Chile, China, Korea, Singapore, Taiwan, Thailand, Ukraine and the rest of the world. The majority of the revenue comes from the United States.
Quercus Trust was a greentech venture capital firm headed by David Gelbaum. The firm preferred to make investments in clean-tech companies with a primary interest in solar.
Founded in 2012, Quesnay is an accelerator based in New York, New York. The firm seeks to invest in information technology, fintech, insurtech, mobility and TMT sectors.

Quest Diagnostics is a leading independent provider of diagnostic testing, information, and services in the U.S. The company generates over 95% of its revenue through clinical testing, anatomic pathology, esoteric testing, and substance abuse testing with specimens collected at its national network of roughly 2,300 patient service centers, as well as multiple doctors' offices and hospitals. The firm also runs a much smaller diagnostic solutions segment that provides clinical trial testing, risk assessment services, and information technology solutions.
Founded in 2008, Quest Venture Partners is a venture capital firm based in Palo Alto, California. The firm seeks to make early-stage investments. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 1998, QuestMark Partners is a venture capital firm based in Baltimore, Maryland. The firm prefers to invest in companies operating in enterprise software, vertically-focused cloud software, mobile software, tech-enabled business services, security, financial technology, consumer internet, and healthcare technology sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Operator of an online brokerage and stock trading services intended to offer financial independence to investors. The company's services offer tools for market analysis, charting capabilities, trading webinars, research and real-time market news, enabling clients to get information on stock trading and earn high returns on their investments.

Quetzal/JPMorgan Partners was a private equity firm based in New York. The firm invested in growth equity capital in communications companies with an ethnic individual and/or a woman in the senior management or a significant shareholder position. Quetzal/JPMorgan Partners invested in sectors such as radio and TV broadcasting, broadband and cable, IT, telecommunications, services and equipment, wireless, services and equipment and internet.

Quicksilver Ventures was a venture capital firm based in Saratoga, California that seeks to invest in computing and consumer technology. The firm used to invest in video and imaging, networking and mobility, data management, services and security, storage components and systems and enterprise applications.

QuidelOrtho is engaged in the development, manufacturing, and marketing of rapid diagnostic testing solutions. The company is engaged in immunoassay and molecular testing, clinical chemistry and transfusion medicine which helps clinicians and patients to make decisions across the globe. Geographically the company has a presence in North America, EMEA, China and Other countries. It generates the majority of the revenue from North America.

QuinStreet focuses on marketplaces and technologies for the financial services and home services industries. It delivers measurable and cost-effective marketing results to its clients, in the form of qualified inquiries such as clicks, leads, calls, applications, or customers. It generates revenue by delivering measurable online marketing results to the clients. Its products and services are customer acquisition, QuinStreet rating platform (QRP), and CloudControlMedia.

Founded in 2010, Quotidian Ventures is a venture capital firm based in New York, New York. The firm prefers to invest in early-stage companies operating in the information technology, technology, media, telecommunications, advanced manufacturing, big data, e-commerce, the internet of things, micro-mobility, mobile, and adtech sectors across New York.

Quotient Technology is a promotions and media technology company that delivers targeted digital promotions and media for advertisers and retailers to reach consumers and drive action. Using the company's platforms and suite of omnichannel solutions, advertisers can plan, target, deliver and measure performance marketing and brand marketing to impact sales. The Company's network includes the digital properties of retail partners, non-retail publisher partners and CPG customers, social media platforms, its consumer brand, shopmium and its digital out-of-home properties. This network provides the company with proprietary and licensed data, including retailers' in-store point-of-sale shopper data, first-party consumer behavior and purchase intent data and location intelligence.

Qurate Retail through its subsidiaries, is engaged in the video and online commerce industries. Its segments include QxH, which includes QVC U.S. and HSN market and sell a wide variety of consumer products in the United States, primarily using their televised shopping programs and via the Internet through their websites and mobile applications; QVC International segment markets and sells a wide variety of consumer products in several foreign countries, primarily using its televised shopping programs and via the Internet through its international websites and mobile applications; and Zulily markets and sells a wide variety of consumer products in the United States and several foreign countries. Its geographical segments include the U.S., Japan, Germany and other countries.
R&R Ventures is an angel investor based in Annapolis, Maryland. It seeks to invest in the media and information technology industries.

R.B. Webber and Company is a venture capital firm. The firm primarily invests in early-stage startups, pre-IPO companies and mid-size public companies. It operates as a management consulting firm providing strategic advisory services to technology companies.

Manufacturer of construction materials. The company produces and supplies supply bulk aggregates, industrial minerals, ready-mix concrete, masonry block products, structural and architectural precast components, and building supplies along with transportation of these materials.

Founded in 2004, R42 Group is a venture capital firm based in Palo Alto, California. The firm seeks to invest in information technology, healthcare, life sciences, big data, the internet of things, artificial intelligence, machine learning, and technology-based sectors.

Founded in 2005, RAA Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Las Vegas, Nevada. This firm seeks to invest in companies operating in internet marketing, technology, e-commerce, consumer products and services, lifestyle, media, entertainment, social media, energy production, infrastructure, mobile gaming, and app sectors.
Provider of a communication platform for auto racing industry. The company allows users to log the settings and adjustments, and event and race details through their computer and tablet.
Founded in 2016, Radest Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Peachtree City, Georgia. The firm prefers to invest in the fintech sector.

Provider of an embedded wireless infrastructure for telecom, aerospace, defense and public safety applications. Its products include its market-leading ATCA and IP media server platforms as well as application software for new IP based communications services.

RAE Systems is a developer and manufacturer of rapidly deployable chemical and radiation detection monitors and multi-sensor networks for homeland security and industrial applications. It specializes in portable gas detection, wireless communication, radiation detection and dosimeter, CWA Detection, real-time decision software solutions and fixed gas detection.

Founded in 1993, Rafael Development Corporation was a corporate venture capital arm of Rafael Advanced Defense Systems based in Tel Aviv, Israel. The firm preferred to invest in companies operating in the communications, agriculture, information technology, industry and manufacturing, medical devices, and environment sectors.

Mr. Rafael Pinedo is the Founder and serves as Partner at Crescent Hill Capital. He also serves as a Managing Partner at E-One Globalinvest Capital. He built his career as a business consultant for Booz Allen Hamilton, Cap Gemini America, Ernst & Young, and was Senior Vice President of Oracle Corporation and Computer Associates International. He has been a director and member of finance committees of public companies in the USA, Canada, and Europe. Currently, he serves as President at Alpha Petroleum Resources, Technomeca Defense, Inc, CAM Group, Inc, AD Capital, Inc among others. He served as Advisor and Board Member at Technorides.
Founded in 2013, Raine Ventures is a corporate venture arm of The Raine Group based in San Francisco, California.

Rainmaker Systems doing business as ViewCentral is an enterprise solutions company. Rainmaker Systems and its subsidiaries are focused on serving business enterprises to help increase sales to small and medium sized businesses. The company's services include lead generation services, SMB sales and contract renewals and training. The company has developed the Rainmaker Revenue Delivery Platform which combines sales and marketing services coupled with renewals software and business analytics. The company's services include marketing strategy development, personalized renewals and subscription e-commerce and microsite creation and hosting, inbound and outbound e-mail, direct mail, chat, and call center services across the world. The company's ViewCentral SaaS platform provides an end-to-end solution for the management and delivery of training programs for corporations. The ViewCentral Learning Management System platform is a SaaS, cloud based, on-demand, training management system. The company seeks to expand its business operations through mergers and acquisitions.

Raizen SA is an integrated energy company. Its operating model involves the production and sale of renewable energy and sugar from sugarcane to the delivery of this energy to different parts of the world. The Company's main activities are the distribution and sale of fossil and renewable fuels, the production and sale of automotive and industrial lubricants, oil refining, and operations related to convenience stores. The company operates in three reportable segments Mobility, Sugar and Renewables. The Marketing and Services segment refers to the trading and sale activities of fossil and renewable fuels and lubricants, through a franchised network of service stations under the Shell brand in all the national territory and Latin America, operating in Argentina and Paraguay.
Mr. Raj Yavatkar is an Angel Investor. He served as an Advisor at Innovium.

Mr. Rajeev Madhavan is a Co-Founder & serves as Partner at Clear Ventures. Mr. Madhavan also serves as Chief Executive Officer and Chairman at Moscape. He serves as Board Member at Atmosic, WaterGuru, Kognitos, and Cato Digital. He serves as Advisor at Intrinsic ID. He is an Angel Investor. He served as the Chairman of Robin. He focuses on early-stage technology investments. His operational specialties are recruiting, software-oriented technology, product definition, sales acceleration, and scaling. He has been a venture investor in over 35 companies. Before founding Clear in 2014, he founded three successful startups. The most recent, Magma Design Automation, became the 4th largest Electronic Design Automation company in the world under his leadership. He served as Magma's Chairman and CEO from when he co-founded the company in 1997 through its acquisition by Synopsys in February 2012 for $580 million. Magma was listed on Nasdaq in 2001 and was ranked as the 2nd fastest-growing Technology Company in 2005 by Forbes. Magma provided core infrastructure software to mobile pioneers such as Apple, Qualcomm, and Samsung, which was used to design the core processors at the heart of the smartphone era. Before founding Magma, he co-founded and served as President and CEO of Ambit Design Systems, which was acquired by Cadence in 1998 for $280 million. He also co-founded and served as Director of Engineering of LogicVision, Inc. (IPO under LGVN, then acquired by Mentor). He is a recipient of the Red Herring Top Innovator award, the Lifetime Achievement Award at NITK, India, and various other awards. He earned a bachelor's degree in electronics and communication from KREC, Surathkal, India, and an M.S.E.E from Queen's University, Ontario, Canada. He serves as a Board Member at Virtual Power Systems. He also serves as an Advisor at Innovium. He served as Chairman at Reflektion and as Board Member at Falcon Computing.

Dr. Rajeev Motwani is an Angel Investor. Dr. Motwani also served as an Advisor at Dot Edu Ventures. He was a Professor of Computer Science at Stanford University, where he also served as the director of graduate studies. He had been at Stanford since 1988, after obtaining a PhD in Computer Science from Berkeley and a bachelor's degree in Computer Science from IIT Kanpur in 1983. Motwani was well-known for his research in several areas of computer science, including databases and data mining, web search and information retrieval, robotics, computational drug design, and theoretical computer science. He had written two books used at universities all over the world -- Randomized Algorithms published by Cambridge University Press in 1995, and an undergraduate textbook published by Addison-Wesley in 2001. Many startups in Silicon Valley are founded or staffed by people who were Motwani's students at Stanford. He was an avid angel and seed investor, advisor to several venture funds, a charter member of TIE (The IndUS Entrepreneurs), and on the board of BASES (Business Association of Stanford Engineering Students). He served as a board member or advisor to several companies, including Agitar, Asempra, Centrata, Chutney, Coral8, Flarion, Flexlogics, Google, GreenBorder, Jumpstart Ventures, Meru Networks, Mimosa, Neopath Networks, Revenue Science, Sinett, and Xambala.

Founded in 2014, Rakuten Capital is a corporate venture capital arm of Rakuten Group based in Tokyo, Japan. The firm prefers to invest in companies operating in e-commerce, mobile services, travel, digital content, and fintech services including credit cards, banking, securities, e-money, cashless payments, and professional sports sectors.
Founded in 2004, Rally Capital was a venture capital firm based in Kirkland, Washington.

Founded in 2012, Rally Ventures is a venture capital investment firm based in Menlo Park, California. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage startup companies operating in artificial intelligence & machine learning, cybersecurity, fintech, HRtech, developer tools, health tech, market tech, infrastructure, productivity & collaboration, SaaS, and extended reality sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 2006, Ransomshire Associates was an venture capital firm based in Rolesville, North Carolina. The firm was suporting venture capital investment and early-stage companies to achive business growth and successful exits. The firm ceased operations on April 18, 2020.
Mr. Rany Raviv serves as Venture Partner at Oregon Venture Fund. He is an angel investor. He serves as Board Observer at Green Zebra Grocery.

Founded in 2000, Rapid7 is a cybersecurity company that began providing vulnerability management solutions. It has, however, expanded its portfolio to provide extended detection and response; security information and event management; cloud security, threat intelligence and application security and security orchestration, automation and response. The Boston-based company went public in 2015.

Founded in 2009, Raptor Group is a venture capital firm based in Boston, Massachusetts. The firm seeks to invest in financial technology, digital assets, gaming, media, sports, technology, fintech, sports, consumer, media, entertainment, and healthcare sectors.

Founded in 1999, Rare Ventures was a venture capital investment firm based in New York. The firm preferred to invest in financial services, information technology, healthcare, media, communications, mobile, and manufacturing sectors.
Rational Equity was a private equity firm specialized in investments in the middle market companies. It is based in Saint Paul, Minnesota.

Founded in 1865, Ratos is a family office based in Stockholm, Sweden. The firm seeks to invest in Nordic-based companies operating in the industry, technology, infrastructure, consumer, construction, and services sectors.

Founded in 2013, Raven Ventures was a venture capital firm based in Sydney, Australia. The firm preferred to make investments in consumer internet, mobile, security, infrastructure, software, and service sectors. The firm ceased its operations on August 25, 2019.

Raycom Media was a provider of television broadcasting services in Montgomery, United States. The company's television channels provided information about sports, lifestyle, car and civil rights, enabling a viewer to gather knowledge about various things.

Mr. Raymond Tonsing is the Founder & serves as Managing Partner at Caffeinated Capital. Mr. Tonsing serves as a Board Observer at Basetwo AI. He also serves as Investor for Virta Health, TrueAccord, Opendoor.com, Color Genomics and many other companies. He also serves as Board Member at Saronic Technologies, Polywork, Onebrief and ShoppingGives. Previously, he worked as Partner at Akkadian Ventures. Mr. Tonsing gained Bachelor of Arts from University of Colorado Boulder. He serves as Board Observer at TrueML Products.

Raytheon was a U.S. defense contractor that posted just over $27 billion in sales in 2018. It operated through five segments: integrated defense systems, intelligence and information, missile systems, space and airborne systems, and a cybersecurity business branded Forcepoint. Sales to the U.S. government accounted for about 70% of consolidated revenue. Based in Waltham, Massachusetts, Raytheon employed more than 60,000 people. It was founded on July 7 ,1922 and was headquartered in Waltham, Massachusetts. It was acquired by Raytheon Technologies on 3 April 2020 for $33166 million.
Raza Venture Management was a venture capital firm which used to invest in the broadband communications and e-business companies. It was founded in 1999 and was based in Wilmington, Delaware.

RB Global operates the world's largest auction for heavy equipment. The company started as a live auctioneer of industrial equipment; since then it has greatly expanded its operations to include the sale of construction, agricultural, oilfield and transportation equipment. RB Global operates over 40 live auction sites in more than 12 countries, along with online marketplaces, including IronPlanet, Marketplace-E and GovPlanet. Its agricultural auctions are frequently much smaller venues and can include liquidations of single farms. The company holds over 300 auctions yearly and sells $6 billion worth of equipment.
Founded in 1868, RBC Capital Markets is an investment bank based in Toronto, Canada. The firm seeks to invest in the energy, communication, healthcare, banking, real estate, and technology sectors.

RBC Capital Partners is an investment arm of RBC Capital Markets and is based in Toronto, Ontario. It focuses on business growth, acquisitions management buyouts, shareholder transition and dividend recapitalization investments.

Founded in 1994, RC Capital is a growth and expansion firm based in Cincinnati, Ohio. The firm seeks to invest in medical technology companies operating in the healthcare services, medical devices, and healthcare information technology sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

The Real Brokerage is a technology-powered real estate brokerage firm. It has developed, integrated, and adopted various mobile and desktop-focused technologies to create a comprehensive offering to its agents and to assist Real with its brokerage operations. The group delivers a cloud-based platform to improve efficiencies and empower real estate agents to provide a seamless end-to-end experience for homebuyers and sellers. The company generates its maximum revenue from the United States.
Founded in 2007, Real Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Montreal, Canada. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage Canadian tech startups.

Founded in 2019, Realization Capital Partners is a private equity investment firm based in Menlo Park, California. The firm deals in secondary and primary investments. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

RealNetworks creates a new generation of products that employ artificial intelligence and machine learning to enhance and secure daily lives. Real's portfolio includes SAFR, the computer vision platform for live video; KONTXT, an NLP (Natural Language Processing) platform for text and multi-media analysis; and leveraging its digital media expertise, a mobile games business focused on the large free-to-play segment.

Realtime Electronic Payments is engaged in providing integrated payment processing solutions to verticals that have transaction processing needs. It allows customers to pay through a mobile app, text, interactive voice response, virtual terminal, hosted payment page and online customer portal among others. It operates in two segments, consumer payment and business payments.

Founded in 2015, Red Badge Management is a venture capital firm based in New York, New York. The firm seeks to invest in the technology, consumer healthcare, energy, agriculture, financial technology, real estate, and hospitality sectors
Founded in 2006, Red Dawn Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Akersberga, Sweden. The firm prefers to invest in technology and gaming companies.

Red Hat provides services for its version of the open-source (free from licensing costs) Linux software operating systems, middleware, storage, virtualization, and management tools. The company reports revenue through two categories: subscriptions, and training and services. The Americas contributed approximately 64% of total revenue in fiscal 2018; Europe, the Middle East, and Africa contributed 23%; and Asia-Pacific contributed 14%.
Founded in 2011, Red Swan Ventures is a venture capital firm based in New York, New York. The firm prefers to invest in pre-seed to seed-stage companies.

Operator of a portfolio of digital media companies intended to bring consumers and brands together across a range of sectors such as financial services, health, travel, and others. The company specializes in online marketing, telephone sales, and technology infrastructure that provides lead generation, sales conversion, performance tracking, and marketing channel optimization services.

Founded in 2011, RedHouse Associates is an accelerator firm based in Houston, Texas. The firm seeks to invest in information technology, SaaS, advanced manufacturing, the internet of things & technology sectors based in Texas of the United States region.

Founded in 1995, Redrock Investments is an asset management firm based in Bethesda, Maryland. The firm makes venture capital and private equity investments. The firm seeks to invest in the internet technology sector. The firm also makes value-add real estate investments with a focus on land developments, multi-family rental apartments, condominium conversion, office, warehouse, industrial, commercial lofts, retail shopping centers and malls.

Founded in 2016, Refactor Capital is a venture capital firm based in Burlingame, California. The firm prefers to invest in seed-stage companies operating in the hard technology, biotechnology, and health sectors.

Founded in 2006, Reference Capital Management is a venture capital firm based in Portland, Oregon. The firm seeks to invest in B2B, B2C, media, retail, information technology, manufacturing, e-commerce, agriculture technology, big data, clean technology, industrials, internet of things & SaaS sectors based in the Northwest of the United States & Western Canada regions.

Founded in 2016, Regah Ventures is a venture capital firm based in New York, New York. The firm seeks to invest in artificial intelligence & machine learning, data analytics, cybersecurity, cloud and edge computing, enterprise software platforms, biotechnology, and esports sectors.

Founded in 2013, Regent is a private equity firm based in Beverly Hills, California. The firm specializes in acquiring businesses, corporate divestitures, carveouts, and private sales. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the technology, consumer products, retail, industrial, media, and entertainment sectors across The Americas, Europe, and Asia.
Founded in 2007, Reichmann Hauer Capital Partners is a private equity investment firm based in Toronto, Canada. The firm prefers to acquire control over target businesses.

Mr. Reid Hoffman serves as Board Member at Entrepreneurs First. Mr. Hoffman serves as President, Treasurer, and Director at Aphorism Foundation. Mr. Hoffman is a Co-Founder and serves as Board Member at Manas AI. He served as Co-Founding Member, Co-Lead Director & Board Member at Reinvent Technology Partners Z. He is an Angel Investor. He serves as a Board Member & Member of the Environmental, Social, and Public Policy Committee at Microsoft. He serves as a Board Member at the Arc Institute. He serves as a Board Member at Kiva Capital Management. He serves as a Global Board Member at Endeavor Global. He serves as Chairman at Village Global. He served as a Board Observer at Airbnb. He served as a Board Member at Coda. He serves as Co-Lead Director at Reinvent Technology Partners. He served as Chairman of the Investment Committee at Endeavor Catalyst. He serves as a Partner at Greylock. He serves as a Board Member at Coda. He is a Co-Founder and serves as a Board Member at Inflection AI. He is a Co-Founding Member and serves as an Advisor at Reinvent Capital. He serves as an Advisor at Aureila Foundry. He is an accomplished entrepreneur, executive, and investor, and has played an integral role in building many of today's leading consumer technology businesses. He served as a Board Member at NeeEndeavor, Globalva, OpenAI, and Convoy. In 2003, He co-founded LinkedIn, the world's largest professional networking service. In 2009, He joined Greylock Partners, where he focuses on building products that can reach hundreds of millions of participants and businesses that have network effects. In 2019, He joined Reinvent Capital and serves as an Advisory Partner. He serves on the board of directors for Joby Aviation. He also serves on the boards of several private companies and not-for-profits. He holds a master's degree in philosophy from Oxford University, where he was a Marshall Scholar, a bachelor's degree with distinction in symbolic systems, and a Bachelor of Science from Stanford University. He joined the Microsoft board as an independent director in March 2017.

Founded in 2016, Reimagined Ventures is a family office based in Winnetka, Illinois. The firm specializes in investing in, growing, and operating highly innovative companies across a variety of asset classes and industry sectors, including venture capital such as healthcare, green energy, agriculture, crypto, fintech, further real estate sectors such as development, commercial, residential, hotels, F&B operations, restaurants, design.

Rekor Systems is a United States-based company. The company is engaged in providing real-time roadway intelligence through AI-driven decisions. The firm uses artificial intelligence to analyze video streams and transform them into AI-driven decisions. The company's technology and machine learning models power all solutions, including Rekor Command for transportation management, Rekor Discover for urban mobility, and Rekor Scout for public safety, and commercial use. Its geographical segments are the United States and others, of which the majority of its revenue comes from the United States.

Founded in 2008, Relay Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Toronto, Canada. The firm prefers to invest in pre-seed to seed-stage startups operating in the urban tech, proptech, fintech and sports tech sectors across North America.

Founded in 2006, Reliance Venture Asset Management was the corporate venture arm of Reliance ADA Group based in Mumbai, India. The firm preferred to invest in promising technology, media and entertainment, telecom, infrastructure (logistics and defense), clean technology, and mass consumption-driven sectors.

RELX Group is a owner and operator of a data-analytics company. The company offers analytical services in scientific, technical, medical, risk and business and legal sectors. It provides its services by combining content and data with analytics and technology in global platforms. It serves customers in more than 180 countries.

Remark Holdings delivers an integrated suite of AI solutions that enable businesses and organizations to solve problems, reduce risk and deliver positive outcomes. The company's easy-to-install AI products are being rolled out in a range of applications within the retail, financial, public safety and workplace arenas. The company also owns and operates digital media properties that deliver relevant content and e-commerce solutions.

RE/MAX Holdings operates as a franchisor of real estate brokerage services. It recruits and retains agents and sells franchises. The company's operating segments include real estate, mortgage, marketing funds, and others. It generates maximum revenue from the real estate segment.

Founded in 2004, Rembrandt Venture Partners is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm prefers to invest in seed-stage, early-stage, growth-stage, and later-stage companies. The firm seeks to invest in information technology, SaaS, big data, and technology, media, and telecommunications sectors in the United States.

Remeditex Ventures was a venture capital firm based in Dallas, Texas. The firm prefers to invest in entrepreneurial ecosystems and early-stage companies operating in the life sciences, biomedical sciences and biotechnology sectors.

Rendex was a European venture capital firm based in Antwerp, Belgium. The firm focused on first round to pre-IPO private equity investments in the information and communication technology (ICT) and in life sciences sectors, but also manages a historical portfolio of diversified investments.

Integrated Device Technology is a designer, developer and manufacturer of low power, mixed signal semiconductors for the advanced communications, computing and consumer industries. Its computing products are designed specifically for desktops, notebooks, sub-notebooks, storage and server applications while its consumer products are optimized for gaming consoles, set-top boxes, digital TV and smart phones. In addition to its products, the company offers semiconductors targeting communication infrastructure, both wired and wireless for high-performance computing and power management. It was founded in 1980 and is headquartered in San Jose, California. The company seeks to acquire businesses through mergers, acquisitions and investments which would help the firm expand and help it to strive towards its goal of continuously improving digital media experiences.

Renishaw is a United Kingdom-based company that operates in the measurement and healthcare markets. Its products include precision measurement and process control equipment such as machine tool probes, calibration and optimization equipment, and gauging systems; position and motion control equipment such as optical, laser, and magnetic encoders; healthcare equipment for spectroscopy and interferometry; and 3D printing and rapid prototyping equipment. Its products also serve automotive, aerospace, agriculture, and construction markets.
RENN Global Entrepreneurs Fund, Inc. invests in equity securities and convertible issues of small and medium size companies.

Repligen is a global life sciences company. It develops and commercializes innovative bioprocessing technologies and systems that increase efficiencies and flexibility in the process of manufacturing biological drugs. The company's customers include life science companies, global biopharmaceutical companies, and contract manufacturers worldwide. Repligen markets its products globally through a direct commercial organization in the U.S., Europe, and Asia, as well as through strategic partners in select markets. The majority of the company's revenue is generated in North America.

Founded in 2013, Reppert Capital Partners is a private equity firm based in Houston, Texas. The firm prefers to invest in the services, manufacturing, technology, healthcare, and distribution sector firms based in the United States.

Manufacturer of brick and specialty refractory products for metals processing, general industry, and minerals applications. The company serves major industries such as steel, copper, nickel, aluminum, hydrocarbon processing, and cement. Its product line offered includes brick, magnesite-chrome brick, magnesite-carbon brick, alumina-magnesite-carbon brick, alumina brick, clay-alumina specialties (gunning mixes, castables, plastics, ram mixes, and mortars), pre-cast shapes, basic specialties, extruded car top shapes, and minerals.

Provider of integrated clinical development solutions. The company's solutions include clinical trial project management, site management and study monitoring, patient enrollment, data collection and management, statistical analysis and report writing, quality assurance, and regulatory and medical affairs services.

Research Triangle Ventures was a venture capital firm based in Raleigh, North Carolina. The firm invested in emerging, high growth companies located in Research Triangle, North Carolina and surrounding areas.

Founded in 2015, Reshape Ventures is a venture capital investment firm based in New York, New York. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage companies in prop-technology, fintech, retail and e-commerce, and healthcare sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

CafePress is an online retailer that offer products include clothing, accessories, art, photography, posters, custom cases, stickers, home accents, and stationary. The company focuses in print-on-demand products, allowing individual sellers to set up free "shops" within their domain. It serves its customers and content owners and overall the customizable retail products industry through its portfolio of e-commerce websites.
The Corporate Development team company has acquired a number of businesses to expand its categories and technology offerings. The team is specifically interested in companies that have a strong growth rate and strong record of profitability. Over the past years, the company has grown both internally and through acquisitions by acquiring niche tuck-in situations.

Founded in 2001, Resilience Capital Partners is a private equity firm based in Cleveland, Ohio. The firm seeks to invest in aerospace, building products, logistics, industrial supplies, commercial transportation, retail, transportation, and financial services, manufacturing, big data, SaaS, the internet of things & industrial sectors based in the North American region. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 2015, Responder Ventures is a venture capital firm based in West Palm Beach, Florida. The firm prefers to invest in the mobile, big data, software, big data, artificial intelligence, and hardware sectors.

Venus Concept Inc is a medical technology company. It develops, commercializes and delivers minimally invasive and non-invasive medical aesthetic technologies and related practice enhancement services. The company provides devices such as Venus Viva and Venus Fiore. Also, the company's treatments include skin resurfacing, and feminine health.

Founded in 2017, Resurgens Technology Partners is a private equity firm based in Atlanta, Georgia. The firm prefers to invest through means of buyouts, recapitalization, carveouts, and growth capital. The firm prefers to invest in information technology, SaaS, infrastructure, TMT, and big data sectors based in North America. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 2015, Rethink Impact is a venture capital firm based in White Plains, New York. The firm has additional offices in San Francisco, California, and Washington, District of Columbia. The company has rapidly gained market share in recent years and is now the largest mortgage originator in the U.S. as well as the servicer for more than 2 million loans.

Provider of artificial-intelligence advertising services for digital marketers. The company provides advertising services that allow marketers to power their advertising across display, video, mobile and social media platforms.

Rocket Lab's Electron launch vehicle has delivered multiple satellites to orbit for private and public sector organizations, enabling operations in national security, scientific research, space debris mitigation, Earth observation, climate monitoring, and communications. The business operates in two segments launch services and space systems. Geographically it serves Japan, Germany, rest of the world and earns key revenue from the United States.

Provider of mortgage lending services. The company offers house mortgages, refinancing and loans, as well as adjustable and fixed-rate mortgages. The firm generates revenue in the United States, China and Germany, but has a presence around the world.

Rogers Communications is the largest wireless service provider in Canada, with more than 11 million subscribers equating to one-third of the total Canadian market. Its wireless business accounted for more than half of total revenue and has increasingly been providing a bigger portion of total company sales over the last several years. Rogers' cable segment, which provides about 35% of total revenue after acquiring Shaw, offers home internet, television, and landline phone service to consumers and businesses. The remaining sales come from Rogers' media unit, which owns and operates various television and radio stations and the Toronto Blue Jays. Rogers' significant exposure to sports also includes ownership stakes in the Toronto Maple Leafs, Raptors, FC, and Argonauts.

Roku enables consumers to stream television programming. It has more than 80 million streaming households and provided well over 100 billion streaming hours in 2023. Roku is the top streaming operating system in the US, reaching more than half of broadband households, according to the company. Roku's OS is built into streaming devices and televisions that Roku sells and on connected televisions from other manufacturers that license Roku's name and software. Roku also operates the Roku Channel, a free, ad-supported streaming television platform that offers a mix of on-demand and live television programming. Roku generates revenue primarily from selling devices, licensing and advertising and it receives fees from subscription streaming platforms that sell subscriptions through Roku.

Mr. Ronald Conway is the Founder & serves as Managing Partner at SV Angel. Mr. Conway is the Founder of Smart Tech Foundation. He serves as Advisor at A.Capital Ventures, NewCo, and Elation Health. He was awarded Best Angel at The 2009 TechCrunch Crunchies Awards. He was an early investor in Google, Ask Jeeves, Loudcloud, Napster, and PayPal. As a result of the success of these investments, he was included in the Forbes Midas list of top venture investors. In 2009, he raised outside capital for his personal investment vehicle, SV Angel, and subsequently deployed six funds through the firm. (NYSE: OMF), a provider of consumer finance and credit insurance products and services, since 2013, and True Capital Management, a wealth management firm designed for professional athletes, entertainers, and high net worth individuals, since 2006. Barton Asset Management, LLC since 2009. He serves on the Advisory Board for the following companies: Chegg, SportsBubble, Thoughtspot, Uptake, and Zenefits. He holds Bachelor's degree in Public Administration from University of Southern California (USC).

Professor has a Ph.D from Cambridge, an M.S from Massachusetts Institute of Technology and a B.Sc. from Birmingham in the UK. Dr. Sachin Katti serves as Chief Technology Officer at Intel. He is an Angel Investor. Dr. Katti co-founded Kumu Networks. Dr. Katti serves as Advisor at ThirdAI. He founded Uhana. He is an Assistant Professor of Electrical Engineering and Computer Science at the Stanford University since 2010. He has also been the CEO & Co-Founder of Kumu Networks from 2012 to 2014. Prof. Katti's has made groundbreaking research along with his graduate students which shows that it is practically possible to design and implement in-band full duplex radios (i.e. radios that can transmit and receive at the same time on the same frequency). The research has been published in ACM SIGCOMM 2013. The team has designed new algorithms and circuits and demonstrated working prototype implementations of Wi-Fi and LTE in-band full duplex radios, a feat that was hitherto considered impossible. This invention has the potential to revolutionize wireless network design and spectrum allocation. At the simplest level, it cuts the amount of spectrum needed by half. The worldwide value of cellular spectrum used to operate broadband 4G networks is estimated at several trillion dollars. With full duplex, the amount of spectrum needed is cut by half, potentially creating value worth trillions of dollars for society. Prof. Katti has made significant progress in commercializing this technology and bringing it to practice. Along with his students, he has started a company, Kumu Networks that is building the world's first commercial full duplex radios. Kumu has raised $25 million in venture capital investment and is in advanced commercial trials with major operators around the world to bring full duplex technology to practice. Prof. Katti obtained his B. Tech. From the Department of Electrical Engineering, IIT Bombay in 2009. He later obtained his M.S. and Ph.D. degrees in Electrical Engineering and Computer Sciences from MIT in 2005 and 2009 respectively.

The companies he founded have collectively reached an aggregate of 100 million users. Notable companies include Webs.com (sold to Vistaprint for $117.5 million), Social Gaming Network (SGN, merged with Mindjolt), and Hyperoffice, raising over $50 million for these ventures. As an angel investor, he has supported over 40 companies, including Taskrabbit, Cherry, Postmates, Klout, Voxer, Aardvark (sold to Google), Blackjet, Dollar Shave Club, Talent House, Gowalla (sold to Facebook), Milo.com (sold to eBay), Milk (sold to Google), Rapportive (sold to LinkedIn), Likealittle (LAL), Qwiki, Votizen, Yobongo (sold to Mixbook), SpruceMedia, Medialets, and SolveMedia. His achievements extend beyond the business world. He was honored by the U.S. Government as an Outstanding American by Choice, one of only 100 naturalized Americans to receive this distinction. He serves on the advisory board of Comscore (NASDAQ: SCOR), is one of 10 members of the UN Foundation's Global Entrepreneurs Council, and serves as an Entrepreneurial Ambassador on several State Department delegations to the Middle East and Russia. Mr. Steve Anderson is the Founder of Baseline Ventures. Mr. Anderson served as a Board Member at SoFi (Consumer Finance) & Stitch Fix. He serves as an Advisor and Board Member at Figure Technologies. At Baseline, he focuses on helping founders build and grow their early-stage companies into change-affecting enterprises. Among his successes are his investments in OMGPOP, Instagram, Taskrabbit, Stumbleupon, Heroku and Path. Before founding Baseline, he was a Senior Director at Microsoft. Mr. Steve Blank is a Co-Founder of GLIDR. Mr. Blank is a Co-Founder of Epiphany Biosciences. He is also a Co-Founder of M34 Capital. He served as Board Member at Together Labs. He serves as Mentor at Engineering Capital. He has had a 36-year career as a successful entrepreneur and educator. He was an Advisor of Engineering Capital and Gamalon. He also serves as Advisory Board Member at Synapse Partners. He has been a founder or participant in eight Silicon Valley startups. His last startup, E.piphany, was in enterprise software. His other startups include two semiconductor companies (Zilog and MIPS Computers), a workstation company (Convergent Technologies), a supercomputer firm (Ardent), a computer peripheral supplier (SuperMac), a military intelligence systems supplier (ESL) and a video game company (Rocket Science Games). His book about building early-stage companies: Four Steps to the Epiphany launched the Lean Startup movement. His next book, The Startup Owners Manual became the standard handbook for how to start a company. Since 2000, he has been part of the entrepreneurship faculty at U.C. Berkeley, Stanford, Columbia University, and UCSF. His Lean LaunchPad class, modified for the NSF Innovation Corps and the National Institute of Health, has become the standard for experiential entrepreneurial education. He has served as Board Member at Udacity. He holds a degree from Stanford University & University of California, Berkeley.

Mr. Steve Bornstein serves as Board Member at Hudl. He serves as Board Member at Don't Quit. He served as Advisor at Constantin Partners. He served as President and Chief Executive Officer at NFL Network since January 2003. Prior to taking over the helm of NFL Television, Mr. Bornstein served as president of ABC Television. During his 22 years with ESPN, he played a pivotal role in the creation of several programs and affiliates, including SportsCenter, ESPN2 and ESPN Classic, as well as ESPN.com. As Executive Vice President of Media for the NFL, Mr. Bornstein launched NFL Network, NFL RedZone and NFL Sunday Ticket. He oversaw all negotiations with the nation's largest television providers, ultimately reaching more than 72 million homes.

Mr. Steve Coast is an Angel Investor. He is a Co-Founder and serves as Head of OSM at Telenav. He also served as an Advisor at what3words. He co-founded CloudMade. He holds a degree from University of London.

Mr. Steve Loughlin serves as Partner at Accel. Mr. Loughlin served as Board Member at Airkit. He serves as a Board Member at Clockwise, Ironclad, Stairwell, Assembly, Vivun and Monte Carlo. He serves as Board Member at Productiv. He was formerly the Chief Executive Officer and Co-Founder of SalesforceIQ, which was called RelateIQ until Salesforce acquired the company in 2014. He was also the President and Chief Executive Officer of Affinity Circles. He serves as Advisor at Productiv. He served as Board Member at Nines. He holds a Bachelor of Arts Degree in Public Policy and a Master of Business Administration Degree from Stanford University.
Mr. Steve Pagliuca is an Angel Investor.

Mr. Steven Ballmer was a Co-Owner and served as Chief Executive Officer at Los Angeles Clippers. Mr. Steven Ballmer is an Angel Investor. Mr. Steven Ballmer served as Chief Executive Officer at Microsoft Pension Plan.

Mr. Steven Baloff serves as General Partner at Advanced Technology Ventures. He is the Founder of Twin Lakes Ventures. He is a Board Member of EndPlay, Cenzic, Cedexis, Host Analytics, Modria and QuickPay. He was a Board Member of WildTangent. He has over 20 years of entrepreneurial, operating and venture experience. He founded and served as CEO of Worldview Systems, a successful venture-backed startup. Through a joint venture with Sabre Interactive, Worldview Systems created and launched Travelocity.com, the award-winning travel site. Steve also held executive positions in sales, marketing and general management with Covalent Systems, a venture-backed computer systems vendor focused on the graphic arts industry. His career originated in Booz, Allen & Hamilton's San Francisco and London offices, where he focused on strategy engagements for a variety of technology companies in the U.S. and Europe. Steve holds an M.B.A. from Stanford Graduate School of Business and a B.A. from Harvard College. He is also an angel investor.

Mr. Steven Welch is the Founder & serves as Chief Executive Officer at Restore Hyper Wellness. Mr. Welch is a Co-Founder and serves as Board Member at DreamIt Ventures. He is also a Co-Founder and serves as Chairman at Restore Hyper Wellness. He was a Co-Founder and served as Chairman at KinderTown. He started his first big entrepreneurial success, Mitos, in 2001 with hardly a cent to his name. Without ever raising outside money Steve built Mitos into a global company in the biotech manufacturing field prior to selling it in 2007 at the age of 29 to a Fortune 500 company. Under his guidance, Mitos developed several critical innovations and patents which transformed the manufacturing process of biological drugs and vaccines and allowed Mitos to develop a global sales and distribution network. Following the sale of Mitos, He co-founded DreamIt Ventures, a new business accelerator model. As a 2009 Eisenhower Fellow, he spent time around the world studying all aspects of economic development. Throughout Asia, Europe, and North America he has examined how economic development is impacted through 1) government policy 2) technology transfer institutions 3) funding sources, and 4) culture. In 2010 Steve published "We are all Born Entrepreneurs" in which he uses his story and those of over a dozen other entrepreneurs to explain what drives entrepreneurs, while at the same time sharing lessons learned from the success -- and failures -- of entrepreneurs. In 2011 he started KinderTown as an educational app store for parents with children ages 3-8. KinderTown helps parents become their child's best teacher by utilizing game based learning on the tablet with learning in the physical world. In 2013 with almost 400,000 users he sold KinderTown to Demme Learning.

Stevens Ventures was a venture capital investment firm that was focused on early-stage and private companies. It was founded in 2009 and sought to invest in the consumer internet, business service and advertising market sectors. It was based in Boston, Massachusetts.

Mr. Stewart Alsop is a Founding Partner of Alsop Louie Partners. Mr. Alsop serves as a Board Member at Fullpower-AI, Meow Wolf and HOVER. He was a general partner with New Enterprise Associates through 2004 and he led that firm's investments in companies such as TiVo (TIVO), Portola Communications (sold to Netscape), Glu Mobile (GLUU), and Xfire (sold to Viacom). During that time, he also wrote a column for Fortune. Before NEA, he was editor-in-chief of InfoWorld, a weekly newspaper for information technology professionals. He also published PC Letter, a fortnightly newsletter for computer industry insiders, and produced the Agenda and Demo conferences for executives of companies in the computer industry. Before 1985, he served in several executive editorial positions at business and trade magazines, including magazines. He is an Angel Investor.

The firm seeks to invest in information technology, clean technology, energy and resource technology, advanced materials, and technological innovations in traditional industries and life sciences sectors.
Tang Capital Partners is a PE-Backed company and the company has been wound down. It seeks to acquire other companies whose businesses can be integrated into its existing operations.
Founded in 1998, Tango Partners was a venture capital firm based in Boulder, Colorado.

Operator of technology lifecycle management platform intended to manage telecommunications network costs. The company provides information technology and telecom expense management software and related services including expense management, procurement, logistics and activation, usage management, enterprise mobility, mobile support, financial management, enabling a range of global enterprises and service providers to drive both bottom-line improvements and top-line growth through digital transformation initiatives. The company seeks to strengthen and expand its core business through acquisitions. It was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in Orange, Connecticut.

Tantalum is a developer of advanced telematics and informatics technology to the automotive sector. The company develops driver-analysis and driver identification technologies utilized by OEM automotive manufacturers, fleet operators and insurance companies. The company is the creator of the Eco-Log, a plug-and-play device designed to reduce vehicle-fleet running costs by providing data of fuel consumption and wastage. It was founded in 1997 and is based in London, United Kingdom.

Founded in 2013, Tao Capital Partners is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm prefers to invest in technology, alternative energy, transportation, healthcare, education, sustainable food, agriculture, consumer, real estate, and hospitality sectors.

TAO Venture Capital Partners was an investment firm that used to provide capital and advisory services to entrepreneurs that pursued global market opportunities in the SaaS, media, content, consumer service, analytics and security sectors. The firm was based in San Diego, California.
Founded in 1999, Target Partners is a venture capital firm based in Munich, Germany. The firm seeks to invest in seed and early-stage technology companies.

Tarrant Venture Partners was a Texas based venture capital firm which was sponsored by The Texas Pacific Group. The firm was founded in 1993 and primarily used to invest in businesses operating in the information technology sector.

Founded in 1997, Tech Coast Angels is an angel group based in Irvine, California. The firm seeks to invest in business products, consumer products, finance, hardware, internet, life sciences, software, cleantech, and industrial sectors based in the United States and Canada.

Founded in 1995, TCV is a venture capital firm based in Menlo Park, California. The firm prefers to invest in companies operating in business products, business services, consumer products, consumer services, financial services, healthcare, information technology, big data, cybersecurity, e-commerce, infrastructure, the internet of things, wellness, and technology-based sectors.
