Founded in 1918, TD Cowen was an investment bank based in New York, New York. The firm focused on healthcare, energy, telecommunications, media and software sectors. The firm was acquired by TD Bank Group in March 2023.

TD Synnex is a distributor and solutions aggregator for the IT ecosystem. The company aggregates and distributes IT hardware, software, and systems including personal computing devices and peripherals, mobile phones and accessories, printers, server and datacenter infrastructure, hybrid cloud, security, networking, communications and storage solutions, and system components. Its geographical segments include, the Americas, Europe, and APJ.

TDF is a developer of a multi-format and multi-support terrestrial platform for managing and distributing audio, video and data content to all types of receivers. The company was founded in 1975 and is headquartered in Montrouge, France.

Founded in 2004, TDF Ventures is a venture capital investment firm headquartered in Chevy Chase, Maryland. The firm prefers to invest in early-stage companies operating in the infrastructure, software, services, IaaS, SaaS, cybersecurity, artificial intelligence, e-commerce, and XaaS sectors This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

TDK-Micronas is a manufacturer of a sensor-based services for automotive and industrial applications. The company offers hall sensors and embedded controllers for smart actuators for automotive and industrial applications such as drive trains, chassis frames, engine management and convenience functions. Micronas was founded in 1989 and is headquartered in Freiburg, Germany. The company seeks to expand its business portfolio through mergers and acquisitions. It was acquired by TDK in 2016.

Founded in 2008, TDM Growth Partners is a growth equity firm based in Sydney, Australia. The firm seeks to make long-term minority growth capital investments. The firm is industry agnostic with a focus on software, consumer, and healthcare companies.
Founded in 1937, Teacher Retirement System of Texas is a government firm based in Austin, Texas.

Founded in 2013, Team in Residence was an incubator based in San Francisco, California. The firm worked as a group of entrepreneurs and venture capitalists that partnered with innovators to create sustainable enterprises. It provided talented innovators with a well-rounded team that brings expertise, relationships, and access to capital, so entrepreneurs could both realize their vision and be rewarded in the process.

Team is a provider of specialty industrial services, including inspection, engineering assessment and mechanical repair and remediation required in maintaining high-temperature and high-pressure piping systems and vessels that are utilized in refining, petrochemicals, and others. The company operates in two segments namely the inspection and heat treating group and the mechanical services group. Inspection and heat treating group provides non-destructive testing services for the process, pipeline and power sectors and others. The mechanical services group provides call-out and turnaround services under both on-stream and shut-down circumstances.

Founded in 2012, Tech Launch Arizona is an incubator based in Tucson, Arizona. The firm focuses on technology startups. The firm provides mentorship, consulting, and access to funding facilities to startups.
Founded in 2013, Digital Sandbox KC is a venture studio based in Kansas City, Missouri. The firm seeks to invest in the information technology sector.

Founded in 2005, Tech.Co is an investment firm based in London, United Kingdom. The firm is privioulsy is an incubator that provides web publishing and networking events for startups, entrepreneurs and technology enthusiasts. The firm supports emerging technology hubs through event organizing and provides relevant news and information for entrepreneurs on its website.

Founded in 1996, TechAcq Ventures is a private equity firm based in Portland, Oregon. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the biotechnology, clean-tech, food, agriculture, healthcare, life sciences, diagnostics, pharmaceuticals, nanotechnology, software, and data sectors.
Founded in 2014, TechFounders is an accelerator firm based in Munich, Germany. The firm provides funding and programs and focuses on climate, carbon, clean energy and food sectors.

TechGROWTH Ohio is a venture capital investment firm that specializes in seed, startup and early-stage investments. The firm prefers to invest in the technology, agriculture, alternative energy, media and bio-science sectors. It was founded in 2008 and is headquartered in Athens, Ohio.

Founded in 2014, Technicolor Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Los Angeles, California. The firm seeks to make investments in the media, video, over-the-top, artificial intelligence, virtual reality, business applications, transactions, logistics, data, software, technology, marketing, and data analytics sectors.

Alliance Technology Ventures was an early venture capital firm based in Sarasota, Florida. The firm focused on private company investments in the semiconductor, communication components, and life science industries. The firm also focused on novel biopharmaceuticals, diagnostics and devices, and applications for communication components in the semiconductor sector.

Technology Integration Group is an information technology systems integrator. It offers cloud computing, big data strategy and virtualization services, information technology security services that include assessment, end-point security, intrusion management, wireless, managed security, secure content management, network management, engineering, field, help desk and managed print. The company also provides contract manufacturing services, custom development, eCommerce solutions, web design and development services, hardware and software and software licensing services. It was established in 1981 and is based in San Diego, California.

Founded in 1980, Technology Partners was a venture capital firm headquartered in Novato, California. The firm preferred to invest in companies operating in the clean technology and life science sectors.

TPI was an independent data and sourcing advisory firm offering services in the areas of operational assessments, insourcing, outsourcing, applications development and maintenance, corporate real estate, customer relationship management, human resources, information technology infrastructure, financial analysis, mergers, acquisitions and divestitures, healthcare, service management and governance. The company was acquired by Information Services Group on November 16, 2007.
Founded in 1997, TechnoPlus Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Tel Aviv, Israel.

Founded in 1988, Technopôle Brest Iroise is a not-for-profit venture capital firm based in Brest, France. The firm provides supportive programs, and access to a network of experts in the field of marketing, legal, financial, and R&D to the startups.

Tecsys is engaged in the development and sale of enterprise supply chain management software for distribution, warehousing, transportation logistics, point-of-use, and order management. It also provides related consulting, education and support services. The company serves healthcare systems, services parts, third-party logistics, retail and general wholesale distribution industries. Geographically, it derives a majority of its revenue from the United States and also has a presence in Canada, Europe, and other regions.

Founded in 2009, TECTERRA is an accelerator based in Calgary, Canada. The firm focuses on Canadian startups and small and medium-sized enterprises by providing crucial financial backing and resources to commercialize geospatial technology.
Founded in 2017, Tectonic Capital is a venture capital investment firm based in New York, New York. The firm seeks to invest in technology companies.

Founded in 1998, TEDCO is a venture capital investment firm based in Columbia, Maryland. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage companies operating in software, technology, energy equipment, life sciences, and oncology sectors based in Maryland.

Founded in 2019, Tekkorp Capital is a venture capital investment firm based in Las Vegas, Nevada. The firm invests in and provides advisory services for digital wagering and gaming, and related services.
Founded in 1986, Tekla Capital Management is an asset manager based in Boston, Massachusetts. The firm was acquired by Abrdn on October 27, 2023.

Teknoinvest was a Scandinavian venture capital firm which used to invest in the information technology, communications, and healthcare sectors. The firm mainly invested through equity, equity derivatives, convertible debt and bridge loans. It was founded in 1984 and was headquartered at Oslo, Norway.

Teladoc Health is a virtual health provider with a telehealth platform delivering on-demand healthcare via mobile devices, the internet, video and phone. It also offers remote patient monitoring programs for chronic care management. It operates in Teladoc two segments, health integrated care and betterhelp segments. The majority of its revenue generated from access fees on a subscription basis (per member, per month). The balance comes from visit fees and equipment rental and sales to hospital systems. Since inception, Teladoc has partnered with employers, health plans and health systems to offer network access to their members, it has also started to market directly to consumers while expanding its service portfolio.
Founded in 1999, Telecom Paristech is an incubator based in Paris, France. The incubation program offers workshops, mentoring and networking to the start-ups.

TeleCommunication Systems was a developer and provider of wireless communication technology. The company operated through two segments: commercial and government. It operated in the United States, Europe, Latin America, Africa and Asia. It served wireless network operators, VoIP, wireless device manufacturers, automotive industry suppliers, and state and local governments. The company grew by making periodic small acquisitions. It was established in 1987 and was based in Annapolis, Maryland.

FLIR Systems designs, develops, markets, and distributes technologies that detect people, objects, and substances. The company's two business units are industrial technologies and defense technologies segment. The industrial technologies segment develops components used to create thermal, industrial, and other imaging systems. The defense technologies unit develops imaging and recognition solutions for military, law enforcement, and other government customers. The company operates around the world, with a significant portion of revenue coming from the United States.

Teleflex is a Wayne, Pennsylvania-based manufacturer of hospital supplies and medical devices primarily in the bloodstream/vascular and surgical areas. The firm reports results across seven segments: vascular access (24% of 2023 sales), interventional (17%), anesthesia (13%), surgical (14%), interventional urology (11%), original-equipment manufacturing (11%) and other (10%). Geographic exposure for the business is primarily in the US, which accounts for 60% of revenue, with international markets making up the remainder.

Founded in 2014, Telefonica Open Future is an accelerator arm of Telefónica based in Madrid, Spain. The firm focuses on companies operating in the telecommunications, information, and communication sectors.

Incorporated in 2016, Telegraph Hill Advisors is a boutique investment banking firm based in San Francisco that provides investment banking services to emerging growth technology companies. The firm provides financial advisory services for buy-side and sell-side mergers and acquisitions, debt and equity capital placements, restructurings and recapitalizations, and management buyouts. The firm has a core focus on Enterprise Software, Data Analytics, AI/ML, Communications Technology, IoT, Digital Media and Marketing Technology.

Founded in 2007, Telegraph Hill Capital is a venture capital firm based in Barcelona, Spain. The firm prefers to invest in seed-stage, and early-stage companies. The firm seeks to invest in B2B software and digital platforms in the United States, Canada and Europe.

Founded in 2001, Telegraph Hill Partners is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm prefers to invest in life science, medical devices, discovery tools & automation, diagnostics, healthcare information technology, and other healthcare sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 2018, TELEO Capital is a private equity firm based in Boise, Idaho. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the software, technology, healthcare information technology, business services, and industrial sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 1996, Telesoft Partners is a venture capital firm based in Aspen, Colorado. The firm specializes in early-stage, mid-stage, later investments. The firm seeks to invest in technology and energy sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Telia is the incumbent telecommunications operator in Sweden but is also present in Norway, Finland, Denmark and the Baltic countries. In the past five years, Telia has been narrowing its business focus, divesting businesses in Asia and focusing on its core markets. In 2022 Telia had revenue of more than SEK 90 billion, with the majority of it coming from the Nordic markets.

Teligent is a specialty generic pharmaceutical company. Teligent develops, manufactures, and sells (under its own label) topical, injectable, complex, and ophthalmic pharmaceutical products in the U.S. and Canada. The product portfolio consists of hospital-based sterile injectable products and topical products (creams like Synalar and Spectazole; lotions like Kenalog; ointments like Topicort and Kenalog; and topical solutions like Pennsaid and Xylocaine). The company also offers services to the pharmaceutical, over-the-counter, and cosmetic markets.

Developer of collaboration software for online communities and social networks. The company offered a community server, an enterprise social computing platform that includes blogging, web discussions, videos, syndication, wiki and rich user profiles and community server evolution, which allowed users to generate content, share knowledge and resurface communication in real-time and across boundaries. The company was acquired by Verint Systems (NASDAQ: VRNT) for an undisclosed amount on August 17, 2015.

Telos Venture Partners was a venture capital Firm that generally invested in companies seeking funds in their seed round and early- stage ventures. The firm was a major investor of software, internet, semiconductor and communication industries. The Telos team generally aimed at providing guidance, mentoring and capital to those companies which needed in order to establish themselves on a strong foundation.

Telstra Group is Australia's biggest telecommunications company, with dominant market shares in voice, mobile, enterprise telecom, legacy voice and fixed-line broadband resale. The former government monopoly, privatized in 1997, provides its services via its infrastructure assets such as a fixed-line network (data centers, exchanges, poles, ducts, pits and pipes, fiber network), a mobile network, and mobile towers. Its customers span retail, corporate, government, wholesale, and overseas segments. Telstra also provides the government-owned, last-mile fixed-line National Broadband Network with long-term access to its infrastructure, in return for recurring payments. The company also operates a leading telecom business in Papua New Guinea and surrounding South-Pacific countries.

Telus is one of the Big Three wireless service providers in Canada, with over 10 million mobile phone subscribers nationwide constituting about 30% of the total market. It is the incumbent local exchange carrier in the western Canadian provinces of British Columbia and Alberta, where it provides internet, television and landline phone services. It also has a small wireline presence in eastern Quebec. Mostly because of recent acquisitions, more than 20% of Telus' sales now come from non-telecom businesses, most notably in the international business services, health, security and agriculture industries. The firm has a 55% economic stake in Telus International.

Founded in 2001, TELUS Global Ventures is a corporate venture capital arm of TELUS Communications based in Vancouver, Canada. The firm seeks to invest in digital health, ag-tech, business products, business services, consumer products, consumer services, energy, information technology, materials, resources, healthcare, SaaS, cybersecurity, wellness, big data, internet of things, b2b (business-to-business) payments, impact investing, robotics, artificial intelligence, machine learning, and technology-based sectors in United States, Asia, Europe, Middle East, Oceania, and Canada. The firm leverages deep insights from its global business, offering investment partners a pathway to real-world traction and growth, while shaping a friendlier future.

Provider of bill processing and cost & financial management of telecommunications services expenses. The company offers Power Suite that includes two ASP services and its flagship business process outsourcing service.

Founded in 1974, Temasek Holdings is a sovereign wealth fund based in Singapore. The firm prefers to invest in financial services, telecommunications, media, technology, consumer, real estate, transportation, industrials, life sciences, agri-food, energy, and resources sectors across Singapore, China, America, Europe, Middle East, Africa, and Asia regions.

Founded in 2016, Temerity Capital Partners is a family office based in Washington, District of Columbia. The firm seeks to invest in minor league baseball, fintech, real estate, financial services, and information technology sectors. The firm also makes impact investments in civic health, financial inclusion, mental well-being, and climate sectors.
Manufacturer of packaging and forest products. The company manufactures and sells corrugated packaging, building products and medium density fiberboard.

Founded in 2002, Tenable is a cybersecurity company that began providing vulnerability management solutions under its Nessus software. In recent years, Tenable has expanded its portfolio to provide a broader range of exposure management modules. Solutions include cloud security and compliance, active directory management, operational technology security and advanced vulnerability analytics. The Maryland-based company went public in 2018.

Investor Legal Name: Tenacity Venture Capital Fund I Management LLC
Description: Founded in 2021, Tenacity Venture Capital is a venture capital firm based in Palo Alto, California. The firm prefers to invest in all tech companies except the medtech, security, and crypto sectors.

Founded in 1995, Tenaya Capital is a venture capital firm based in Palo Alto, California. The firm prefers to invest in companies operating in the information technology and consumer sectors across the United States. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Tencent holds a prominent position in China's internet sector, with a diverse portfolio of products and services used daily by a significant portion of the population. The company is the world's largest video game publisher and owns Honor of Kings, a top-grossing mobile game globally. Tencent also operates WeChat, China's largest social media super app, which has become deeply integrated into the daily lives of Chinese people for communication, entertainment, shopping, and more. Beyond its offerings, Tencent is a significant player in global venture capital and investment. The company holds substantial stakes in leading tech companies, including PDD, Kuaishou, and Epic Games.

Tencent Investment is the corporate venture arm of Tencent Holdings. The firm prefers to invest in the wireless internet, new media, online games, social games and e-commerce sectors. It was founded in 2011 and is headquartered in Shenzhen, China.

Tenet Healthcare is a Dallas-based healthcare services organization. It operates a collection of hospitals (about 50 as of July 2024) and over 500 ambulatory surgery centers and other outpatient facilities across the U.S., primarily in the South. Through its Conifer segment, Tenet also provides revenue cycle management solutions.

Founded in 1999, Tenex Capital Management is a private equity investment firm based in New York, New York. The firm prefers to invest in companies operating in the diversified industrials, business and tech-enabled services and healthcare sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 2009, TEV Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Essen, Germany. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage companies operating in the consumer-internet, digital services, and emerging technology sectors.

Tennant is a manufacturer of floor cleaning equipment, wood flooring, and wood products. It operates in four geographic business units including North America; Latin America; Europe, Middle East, Africa; and Asia Pacific. The company offers products and solutions consisting of mechanized cleaning equipment, detergent-free, and other sustainable cleaning technologies, aftermarket parts and consumables, equipment maintenance and repair service, specialty surface coatings, and business solutions such as financing, rental and leasing programs, and machine-to-machine asset management solutions.

Tenneco's emissions-control products meet strict air-quality legislation, optimize engine performance, improve fuel economy, and acoustically tune engine sound to fit a vehicle's profile. Ride-control products enhance safety by enabling improved steering, braking, and acceleration as well as ride comfort. Champion, Fel-Pro, Moog, Monroe, and Walker are some of Tenneco's well-known aftermarket brands. In 2020, 40% of revenue came from North America, 37% from Europe, 18% from China, and 5% other regions.
Founded in 2009, Tennessee Community Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Nashville, Tennessee. The firm seeks to make seed and early-stage investments across Tennessee.

Founded in 2016, Tensility Venture Partners is a venture capital firm based in Chicago, Illinois. The firm prefers to invest in artificial intelligence, digital health, infrastructure, cybersecurity, industrial, and technology sectors.

Teradata provides analytic data products and related services. The company operates in data and analytics, which captures, integrates, stores, manages, and analyzes data of all types to answer business questions and deliver insight; and marketing applications, which offer marketing management products to help businesses win customer loyalty. Its solutions include components such as data warehousing, asset optimization, fraud prevention, product innovation, and risk mitigation. A majority of the firm's revenue is generated in the United States.

Founded in 2002 Teramips Technologies is a venture capital firm based in Ramat Gan, Israel. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage companies operating in the deep technology hardware and software sectors.

Terex is a top manufacturer of aerial work platforms, materials processing equipment, and specialty equipment, such as material handlers, cranes, and concrete mixer trucks. Its current composition is a result of numerous acquisitions over several decades and a recent shift to focus on its two core segments after divesting a handful of underperforming businesses. Terex's remaining segments see heavy demand in non-residential construction as well as in maintenance, manufacturing, energy and materials management.

Founded in 1994, Terra Firma Capital Partners is a private equity firm based in London, United Kingdom. The firm prefers to invest in growth-stage companies through buyouts. The firm prefers to invest in business products, business services, consumer products, consumer services, energy, and information technology sectors in the United Kingdom, and Germany.

Provider of managed information technology infrastructure solutions worldwide. The company offers managed services, including device management; operating system and application platform management; patch management; monitoring services; problem and incident management; data storage; backup and restoration; security services, including managed firewalls, intrusion detection, anti-virus services and DDos protection and mitigation; database administration; application performance tuning; software installation and configuration and application testing and deployment. The company also offers managed hosting services that comprise technology and operations support, managed storage and tape backup services; collocation services; disaster recovery services; cloud computing services and network and connectivity services, including massive connectivity, peering and cross-connect services.

Founded in 1995, Tesi is a government investment firm headquartered in Helsinki, Finland. The firm is a state-owned investment company with an industrial policy mission focused on driving economic growth, renewal, and investments. The firm invests on market terms in venture capital and private equity funds, as well as directly in startups, scale-ups, and industrial companies. The firm investments are direct investments, and half are fund investments, but the allocation may vary depending on market conditions.

Tesla is a vertically integrated battery electric vehicle automaker and developer of autonomous driving software. The company has multiple vehicles in its fleet, which include luxury and midsize sedans, crossover SUVs, a light truck, and a semi-truck. Tesla also plans to begin selling more affordable vehicles and sports car and offer a robotaxi service. Global deliveries in 2024 were a little below 1.8 million vehicles. The company sells batteries for stationary storage for residential and commercial properties including utilities and solar panels and solar roofs for energy generation. Tesla also owns a fast-charging network.
Texaco is a distributor of petroleum products. The company's petroleum and gasoline products are offered through the gas stations enabling customers to refuel their cars.

Investor Legal Name: Texas Atlantic Capital GmbH & CO KG
Description: Founded in 2010, Texas Atlantic Capital is a venture capital firm based in Houston, Texas. The firm specializes in seed, early-stage, later-stage, and growth investments. The firm prefers to invest in the e-commerce, Internet, digital life, and software sectors.

Established in 2005, the Texas Emerging Technology Fund was created to provide investments to technology start-ups. It was based in Dallas, Texas and preferred to make venture capital investments in technology and economic development sectors. Governor Greg Abbott signed a law ending the fund on June 4, 2015.

Founded in 2012, Texas Halo Fund is a venture capital firm based in Houston, Texas. The firm specializes in investing in early-stage firms, particularly in the healthcare and information technology sectors.

Dallas-based Texas Instruments generates over 95% of its revenue from semiconductors and the remainder from its well-known calculators. Texas Instruments is the world's largest maker of analog chips, which process real-world signals such as sound and power. Texas Instruments also has a leading market share position in processors and microcontrollers used in various electronics applications.

Textron is a conglomerate that designs, manufactures, and services a range of specialty aircraft including small jets, propeller-driven airplanes, helicopters, and tilt-rotor aircraft. The firm's aviation segment manufactures and services Cessna and Beechcraft planes. Bell is a helicopter and tilt-rotor manufacturer and servicer for both commercial and military customers. Textron Systems produces uncrewed aircraft and armored vehicles for the military market as well as aircraft simulators and training for the commercial and military markets. Textron Industrial contains the Kautex business that manufactures plastic fuel tanks for conventional and hybrid motor vehicles and other subsidiaries that produce specialized vehicles such as golf carts, snowmobiles, and all-terrain vehicles.

TFI International is a transportation and logistics company domiciled in Canada. The company organizes itself into four segments: package and courier, less-than-truckload, truckload and logistics. The package and courier segment picks up, transports and delivers items across North America. The less-than-truckload segment transports smaller loads. The truckload segment transports goods by flatbed trucks, containers, or a more specialized service. The company provides general logistics services through the logistics segment. TFI International derives the majority of its revenue domestically, followed by the United States.

Founded in 2002, TGap Ventures is a venture capital investment firm based in Kalamazoo, Michigan. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the software, business products and services, medical devices, healthcare services, life sciences, plastics, communication telecommunication, internet, and manufacturing sectors.

Founded in 1992, TGF Management was a private equity firm based in Austin, Texas. The firm used to invest in the manufacturing, distribution, industrial services, construction, outsourced business, food and consumer products sectors.

TH Lee Putnam Ventures was a technology-focused private equity firm. The firm targeted private transactions in later-stage venture companies whose success depended on the deployment and use of information technologies. In addition to later-stage venture companies, the company also considererd public entities, middle market buyouts, recapitalization and spinouts of corporate divisions.

Mr. Thanos Triant is an Angel Investor. Mr. Triant served as Managing Partner at The Woodside Financial Group. He served as Advisor at Artemis Ventures. He also serves as Managing Partner at The Woodside Financial Group. Mr. Thanos Triant serves as Senior Advisor at Artemis Ventures. He had a successful career building financial data products in Wall Street (Standard & Poors) and managing large IT organizations (Sun Microsystems, Times Mirror, McGraw-Hill). In 2000 he co-founded and managed a Venture Capital fund in Silicon Valley. He now invests as an angel in early-stage software companies. He has been investing as a VC or Angel investor for 15+ years. Past Angel/VC investments include: Siebel Systems, ClearStation, Seagate, Securify, Rightworks, Valicert, Sendmail, and Postini. Current investments include: BrightEdge, Clairmail, ConnectAndSell, DoubleDutch, Materna, riskIQ, Rodo Medical, Practice Fusion, SendMail, Serious Materials, Symplified, Taulia, Uptake Networks, Xactly. He is a Board Member of Virtual Synaptics.

The Abraaj Group was an Operator of an investment company operating in the growth markets of Africa, Asia, Latin America, Middle East and Turkey. The company engaged in finding, growing and monetizing investments across several sectors through partnerships, enabling businesses and communities to become sustainable and profitable.
Founded in 2006, The Accelerator Centre is an accelerator firm based in Waterloo, Canada. The firm seeks to provide funding, mentorship, sales training, and other services to startups.

The Advisory Board Company provides technology and consulting services intended to hardwire best practices and make health care better, education smarter and communities are stronger. The company's services include best practice research and insight, performance technology software, data- and tech-enabled services and consulting and management services, which are all provided through the company's subscription-based membership programs, enabling health care organizations around to improve their performance.
Founded in 1998, The Alfred E. Mann Institute was an accelerator firm based in Los Angeles, California.

Andersons is a diversified company with its main focus in the agriculture sector. Its operations are segmented into Trade, Renewables, and Nutrient & Industrial. The Trade segment which generates the majority of the revenue is engaged in the movement of physical commodities such as; whole grains, grain products, feed ingredients and domestic fuel products among other agricultural commodities. Geographically, the company generates the majority of its revenue from the United States and the rest from Canada, Mexico, Egypt, Switzerland and other markets.
Founded in 1997, The Angels' Forum is an angel group based in Mountain View, California. The firm prefers to make early-stage investments across Silicon Valley.

Founded in 2009, The ArcView Group is an angel group based in Oakland, California. The firm prefers investment in agtech, biology and pharmaceuticals, software media and analytics, cultivation & retail, infused products and extracts, and ancillary products and services.

The Baldwin Insurance Group is a United States-based insurance distribution firm. Its products include business insurance, benefits consulting, reinsurance, specialty MGA, embedded insurance and personal insurance.

The Bower Foundation is a non-profit foundation located in Ridgeland, Mississippi. Established in 1972, the foundation supports innovative strategies to improve the health of Mississippians. It concentrates primarily on improving access to health care, developing healthy lifestyles among children and promoting innovative health policy. The assets and investments of the foundation are managed by the executive team.

Founded in 2010, The Brandery is an accelerator based in Cincinnati, Ohio. The firm seeks to invest in retail, information technology, e-commerce, marketing technology, advertisement technology, big data, internet of things, mobile & SaaS sectors.

The Broe Group is a private investment firm focusing on real estate, infrastructure, transportation and energy. It owns and/or manage commercial real estate and other businesses across North America. The firm is based in Denver, Colorado and was founded in 1972.

Founded in 1996, The Cambria Group is a private equity firm based in Dallas, Texas. The firm prefers investing through means of buyouts, management buyouts, add-ons, recapitalization, and growth capital. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in business services, consumer products, consumer services, healthcare, independent sponsors, industrial products, manufacturing, processing, distribution, transportation, resource, service businesses, multi-location healthcare, retail, search funds, software as a service, and technology-based sectors in the United States.

Founded in 1990, The CapStreet Group is a private equity firm based in Houston, Texas. The firm prefers to invest in lower middle market software, tech-enabled services, and industrial business services companies. With over 50 platform investments and over 200 add-on acquisitions since inception, The firm's investment strategy is focused on utilizing its Capvalue Framework to help accelerate growth and profitability and help create long-term sustainable businesses. The majority of firm investments have been with founder- or entrepreneur-owned businesses. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 2001, Carbon Trust is a venture capital investment firm based in London, United Kingdom. The firm partner with businesses, organizations, and governments to help them with strategic direction, footprinting, target setting, carbon reduction plans & transitioning, and energy systems & climate action plans for a sustainable, low-carbon future. The firm focuses on corporate sustainability, green finance, assurance & labelling, future energy systems, offshore wind, and net-zero, and supports cities, states, and regions in addressing the climate emergency.

Initially set up to provide pension services to professors, the company's services are now available to the general public. The firm is a subsidiary of Teachers Insurance and Annuity Association of America.

Mr. Tianxiang Zhuo serves as Board Member at SubBase. Mr. Zhuo is an Angel Investor. He is the Managing Partner of Karlin Ventures. He serves as Board Member at SubBase. He has been involved in the startup space since his college days. He started an online textbook retail company while in college, served as the CFO for an electric vehicle startup, Lit Motors, and worked for Innovation Endeavors, a seed stage venture fund backed by Eric Schmidt. Prior to Innovation Endeavors, TX worked for McKinsey & Co in their London office where he was part of their financial institutions and consumer goods practices. TX received a M.B.A. from the Stanford Graduate School of Business and a B.A. in Economics and Mathematics (summa cum laude) from Wesleyan University. Zhuo is also an Associate of Chartered Accountants (U.K.) affiliate.
Tidal Ventures is a California based venture capital firm. It primarily invests in the mobile and internet sector with geographic focus on the Silicon Valley.

Founded in 2007, TiE Oregon is an accelerator firm based in Portland, Oregon. The firm prefers to invest in seed-stage and early-stage companies. The firm seeks to invest in information technology, SaaS, TMT, artificial intelligence, and machine learning sectors in Oregon.

Developer of software infrastructure. Its products include ChunkIt!, an Internet browser-based search application; and XDMS, an enterprise native XML database management server with data- and document-centric capabilities. The company also offers multidimensional database management systems. It serves corporate information technology departments, commercial application developers, system integrators, independent software vendors, value added resellers, and independent consultants. The company is based in San Jose, CA.

Founded in 2012, Tigris Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Houston, Texas. The firm seeks to invest in the Southern California region-based companies operating in the healthcare and environment sectors. The firm also provides incubation support to some of its ventures.

Mr. Tikhon Bernstam serves as Managing Partner at Uncommon Capital. Mr. Bernstam is an Angel Investor. He serves as Advisor at BalkanID. He was a Co-Founder and served as Co-Chief Operating Officer at Scribd. He is a Co-Founder of Rye. He is also an Angel Investor. He is an engineer and physicist by background, graduating at the top of his class at Dartmouth CS before dropping out of his physics Ph.D. to start Scribd. He helps portfolio companies with engineering hiring, engineering culture, fundraising strategy, and more.

Tilray is a Canadian producer that cultivates and sells medical and recreational cannabis. In 2021, legacy Aphria acquired legacy Tilray in a reverse merger and renamed itself Tilray. The bulk of its sales are in Canada and in the international medical cannabis export market. US exposure consists of CBD products and alcohol.
Timeline Ventures was a venture capital firm based in San Diego, California.

Mr. Timothy Draper is the Founder & serves as Managing Partner, Investment at Draper Associates. He is an Angel Investor. He serves as an Advisor at Logic. He is the Founder & serves as Headmaster at Draper University. He is the Founder of VenturesLab. He serves as Managing Director at DFJ DragonFund China. He serves as an Advisor at Zelgor Games. He served as an Advisor at Jur. He serves as a Board Observer at Checkbook.io. He serves as an Advisor at EtherMail. He serves as an Advisor at Good AI Capital. He also serves as President & Board Member of the Draper Foundation. He serves as a Board Member at Blue Social & Sense. Chat. He serves as a Board Observer at DigiBuild. He serves as a Board Member at Mat3ra. He previously served as a Board Member at Kubos and Wheels of Zeus. He also serves as a Board Member at Draper Venture Network. He is an Advisor at Halogen Ventures, Republic, and Aragon One. He is the founder and serves as a special limited partner and board member for Draper Goren Holm. He serves as an Advisor at Move3. He received a Bachelor of Science from Stanford University with a major in electrical engineering and a Master of Business Administration from the Harvard Business School.

Mr. Timothy McCarthy is an Angel Investor. He served as an Advisor at Green Visor Capital. He also served as Chairman and Chief Executive Officer at Nikko Asset Management. From 1998 to 2002, he served as Chairman of Korea's Good Morning Securities, where a reorganization of operations led to the firm increasing its market capitalization almost sixfold. Mr. McCarthy also served as President of Charles Schwab & Company, where he launched Schwab's online brokerage strategy and designed its successful OneSource fund platform. Previously, he was CEO of Hong Kong-based Jardine Fleming Unit Trust. He has also worked with Fidelity, where he launched a multifund platform for banks and independent brokers, and Merrill Lynch. Mr. McCarthy earned his B.A. with majors in international relations and economics at the University of California, Davis, and his MBA from Harvard University, where he was a Baker Scholar.
Founded in 2019, TIN Fonder is an impact investment firm based in Stockholm, Sweden. The firm seeks to invest in the information technology sector.

Tiptree is a United States-based company that provides specialty insurance products and related services. It has two reportable segments: insurance and mortgage. The company has nonreportable segments such as tiptree capital - other and corporate. It generates maximum revenue from the insurance segment. The insurance segment provides specialty insurance, warranty products and related administration services and the mortgage segment originates, sells and services conventional, conforming agency and government-insured residential mortgage loans. tiptree capital - other is the remainder of the company's operations aggregated from mortgage and insurance. Corporate activities include holding company interest expense, corporate employee compensation and benefits and other expenses.

Titan is engaged in the manufacturing and sale of watches, jewelry, eyewear and other accessories and products. Its operating segments are watches and wearables, jewelry, eyewear and others. The firm generates a majority of its revenue from jewelry. The company sells its products under various brands such as Fastrack, Skinn, Sonata, Zoop, Nebula, Zoya, Skinn, Tanishq and others.

Tekelec was a telecommunications company that provided broadband solutions to its customers that enabled them to manage and monetize mobile data traffic and evolve to LTE/IMS. It specialized in diameter routing, sigtran, computer networking, session management and subscriber data management. The company was founded in 1971 and was headquartered in Morrisville, North Carolina. It acquired those companies that could be integrated into its existing operations. It also took over companies that made mobile network equipment and developed application assurance technology.

Titanium Investment was a venture capital firm that preferred to invest in the application software, ad-tech, fin-tech, artificial intelligence, virtual reality, internet of things, SaaS sectors. The firm was established in 2013 and was headquartered in Vancouver, Washington.

Founded in 2011, Titanium Ventures is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm prefers to invest in companies operating in the technology, fintech, education technology, climate tech, cybersecurity, cloud infrastructure, and artificial intelligence sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

TiVo Corp is engaged in media and entertainment products. It provides a broad set of cloud-based services, embedded software solutions and intellectual property that enable people to find and enjoy online video, television programming, movies and music entertainment. In addition, it also offers advanced media and advertising solutions, including viewership data, audience insights and advertising and programming promotion optimization, which enable advanced audience targeting in linear television advertising. The group solutions are sold globally to cable, satellite, and telecommunications pay-TV service providers, virtual service providers, content and new media companies and advertisers. Geographically its presence is seen in US and other international markets.
Founded in 1997, Tivona Capital is a private equity firm based in Toronto, Canada. The firm prefers to invest in the real estate, technology, and biotechnology sectors.

Founded in 1988, TL Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Wayne, Pennsylvania. The firm preferred to invest in companies operating in the software, information technology, and business services sectors.
Founded in 2015, TMD Ventures is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the information technology sector.

Founded in 2002, TMT Ventures is a venture capital investment firm based in Karachi, Pakistan. The firm prefers to invest in cutting-edge technologies, disruptive business models, and climate & ESG sectors.

TMX Group is a company that operates several markets to provide investment opportunities for its clients. TMX Group provides listing markets, trading markets, clearing facilities, depository services, technology solutions, data products, and other services to the worldwide financial community. TMX Group operates offices across North America (Montreal, Calgary, Vancouver, and New York), as well as in key international markets including London and Singapore. The company has four segments namely: global solutions, insights, and analytics, which derives the key revenue; capital formation; derivatives trading and clearing; and equities and fixed income trading and clearing.

Investor Legal Name: Tokio Marine Future Insurance Fund I, L.P.
Description: Founded in 2021, Tokio Marine Future Fund is a corporate venture capital arm of Tokio Marine Holdings based in Palo Alto, California. The firm prefers to invest in companies operating in the insurtech, fintech, mobility, cybersecurity, artificial intelligence, machine learning, healthcare, sustainability & climate change sectors across North America, Europe, Latin America, Africa, and Asia.

Dating back to 1879, Tokio Marine is Japan's oldest insurance company and was its property and casualty insurer in terms of market share for many decades. After mergers of its smaller rivals in the past few years, the company is now roughly the same size in the domestic non-life market as MS&AD and Sompo Holdings, but it remains the listed Japanese insurer in terms of market capitalization due to its larger overseas business portfolio. The majority of its overseas business is in the U.S., where it has purchased four specialty insurers since 2008: Philadelphia Consolidated, Delphi Financial, HCC and PURE. It is a member of the Mitsubishi keiretsu group and holds minority stakes in a number of group companies that also rank among its shareholders.

Mr. Tom Chiu serves as Venture Partner at Enspire Capital. Mr. Chiu serves as a Board Member at Sand Hill Angels. He has spent over 20 years in various high-tech industries including mobile software, consumer electronics, wireless, patent sales/license, semiconductors, and embedded systems. He is currently the founder of IPforAsia, an intellectual property marketplace to bridge Greater China and large U.S. corporations. He worked in Shanghai from 2003-2007 as a founding member of Philips/NXP Software. Prior to the expatriate assignment, he was the lead of the Philips Connected Home initiative which later became the blueprint of the Digital Living Network Alliance (DLNA). He also represented Philips in WiFi Alliance as a secondary board member and Chair of the DLNA China Task Force. He has held various director positions at Sina.com, Philips, and NXP. He has been an active investor for over 12 years. He serves on several advisory boards and has a passion to work with startups in mobile, internet, location, and eCommerce space. He serves as Advisor at AppAddictive. He has a BS degree in Computer Science and an MBA in Product Marketing. He also received NYSE Series 7 Stock and Dealer license in 1988.
Provider of mobile internet services.

Mr. Tom Rutledge is a Co-Founder of Wapanda. He is an Angel Investor. He also served as Head of Fixed Income at Magnetar Capital. He is a 30-year Wall Street credit veteran with capital markets experience at Merrill, Deutsche Bank and J.P. Morgan. Before joining Wapanda, Tom was a private credit specialist at Magnetar Capital, leading investments in trade finance, last-mile warehouses, and structured solutions. Tom is also an active angel investor and advisor, with early-stage stakes in several VC-backed companies, including sectors such as fin-tech (Alto, Reggora), prop-tech (Getaway, HomeLight, Bevi), marketing-tech (Magellan.ai, Elsy, WEVO), second-chance employment (HonestJobs) and therapeutic psychedelics (Eleusis).
Founded in 2009, TomorrowVentures is a venture capital firm based in Palo Alto, California. The firm seeks to invest in the consumer, media, and technology sectors.
Manufacturer of communication cables. The company manufactures and sale communication cables and optical fibers along with other cable products in China.
Mr. Tony Agnello is an Angel Investor.

Mr. Tony Jamous is a Co-Founder and serves as the Chief Executive Officer at Oyster HR. Mr. Tony Jamous is a Co-Founder of Nexmo and served as the Chief Executive Officer and President. He spent 12 years in the wholesale messaging industry at mBlox and Paymo where he opened mobile messaging and payment services in more than 82 markets.

Topcon sells ophthalmic instruments, medical equipment, machine control and GPS-related systems. The firm operates in three segments: eye care, smart infrastructure, and positioning. The eye care business sells ophthalmic instruments and systems for eye examination, measurement, treatment, and eyeglass lens processing. The smart infrastructure business sells positioning products that use GPS, laser, and image analysis technologies based on the firm's optical technology. The positioning business sells products related to global navigation satellite systems, or GNSS, to the construction and agriculture industries, including GNSS surveying, machine control, and precision agriculture solutions. North America, Europe, and Japan contribute the largest proportion of its revenue.

Founded in 1999, Topmark Partners is a venture capital firm based in Tampa, Florida. Topmark Partners is an investment firm that spun out of Stonehenge Capital Company. The firm prefers to invest in technology-enabled firms. The firm changed its name from Stonehenge Growth Equity Partners to Topmark Partners.

Founded in 2012, Topping Capital is an early stage venture capital firm based in Xi'an, China. The firm seek to make investments in areas such as information technology, biomedicine, new energy, and new materials.
Founded in 1995, Topspin Venture was a venture capital firm based in Roslyn Heights, New York.

Founded in 2005, Torch Hill Investment Partners is an growth/expansion investment firm based in Washington DC, District of Columbia. The firm prefers to invest in the supply chain integrity, aerospace, defense, security service, satellite, and information technology sectors.

Founded in 2018, Toronto Innovation Acceleration Partners is a non-profit venture capital investment firm based in Toronto, Ontario. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the health science technology sector across Canada.
Founded in 2002, TorQuest Partners is a private equity firm based in Toronto, Canada. The firm seeks to invest across North America.

Founded in 1875, Toshiba is Japan's largest semiconductor manufacturer and its second-largest diversified industrial conglomerate. After the accounting scandal in 2015, Toshiba reorganized into six major segments: energy systems and solutions; infrastructure systems and solutions; building solutions; retail and printing solutions; storage and electronic devices solutions; and digital solutions. Toshiba is the second-largest manufacturer of NAND flash memory with a market share of 16.5% in 2017, and it concentrates business resources in this area.

Total System Services based in Columbus, Georgia, provided payment-processing services in the U.S. and abroad. In 2013 TSYS provided processing services for 28% of domestic consumer credit card accounts and 59% of domestic commercial credit card accounts. The company had operating segments in North America Services, International Services, and Merchant Services, plus the newer NetSpend segment, which dealt in prepaid debit and payroll cards and arrived via a 2013 acquisition.

TotalFinaElf was an explorer of specialty chemicals and oil products. The company offered production of crude oil and natural gas along with development activities in gas and electricity and operations in coal mining. It was founded in 2000 and was headquartered in Cedex, France. The company used to acquire other companies whose businesses can be integrated into its existing operations.
Mr. Touraj Parang serves as Chief Operating Officer, President & Board Member at Serve Robotics.

Founded in 1975, Townsend Ventures is a real estate firm based in Hunt Valley, Maryland. The firm seeks to invest in industrial, advanced manufacturing, bog data, real estate technology, clean technology & climate technology sectors.

Founded in 1937, Toyota is one of the world's largest automakers, with 10.56 million units sold at retail in fiscal 2023 across its light-vehicle brands. Brands include Toyota, Lexus, Daihatsu, and truckmaker Hino; market share in Japan is about 51% excluding mini-vehicles, while US share is around 15%. The firm also owns 3.3% of Denso, a parts supplier, about 20% of Subaru, and holds investments in many other firms, including shares of Uber Technologies, Joby Aviation, Aurora Innovation, Isuzu Motors, and about 5% in each of Mazda and Suzuki. Fiscal 2024 sales excluding financial services were JPY 41.8 trillion. Toyota also has a financing arm and manufactures homes and boats.

TP ICAP GROUP provides broking professional intermediary services to match buyers and sellers of different financial, energy, and commodities products. Its role includes creating liquidity and price discovery in markets and providing insight and context to the clients. The company provides proprietary over-the-counter (OTC) pricing information in the world, including data on financial, energy, and commodity products. Its clients include banks, insurance companies, pension funds, asset managers, hedge funds, central banks, energy producers and refiners, risk and compliance managers, and charities. The company's segments include Global Broking, which generates key revenue, Energy & Commodities, Liquidnet, Parameta Solutions, and Corporate.

Founded in 1970, TPP Capital Advisors is a venture capital firm based in Tokyo, Japan. The firm seeks to invest in seed, early-stage and later-stage companies. The firm prefers to invest in the business-to-business, business-to-consumer and information technology sectors.

TR Capital is a firm which offers consulting, real estate management and brokerage services to the public agencies and private property owners. As a broker, TRA brings together buyers, sellers and developers to create value from Transit Oriented Development and Public-Private Partnerships. It was founded in 1996 and is based in Boston, Massachusetts.

Founded in 2007, TR Capital is a leading pan-Asian secondary private equity firm headquartered in Hong Kong, with six offices across Asia. The firm specializes in providing liquidity solutions to investors through direct and GP-led single-asset or multi-asset secondary transactions, targeting mature, high-quality private equity assets. Focused on innovative leaders in the Technology, Next-Generation Consumer, and Healthcare sectors, it employs an active investment approach, partnering closely with GPs and portfolio companies to drive growth and deliver shorter risk-adjusted returns through strategic value creation.

Tradus was a provider of online consumer trading platforms. The company's platform used to allows buying and selling on the internet with over 1,200,000 members. The company was founded in 1997 and is headquartered in Oslo, Norway.

Traeger designs, sources, sells and supports wood pellet-fueled barbeque grills sold to retailers, distributors and directly to consumers. It produces and sells the pellets used to fire the grills and also sells Traeger-branded rubs, spices and sauces, as well as grilling accessories including covers, barbeque tools, trays, liners and merchandise. The company's geographical segments include North America and the rest of the world, of which majority of revenue is from North America.

Trane Technologies manufactures and services commercial and residential HVAC systems and transportation refrigeration solutions under its prominent Trane, American Standard, and Thermo King brands. The $20 billion company generates approximately 70% of sales from equipment and 30% from parts and services. While the firm is domiciled in Ireland, North America accounts for over 80% of its revenue.

Transform-X is a manufacturer and distributor of communication equipment. The company offers its services to obtain and develop technologies for the fifth-generation wireless sector. It was founded in 2017 and is headquartered in Tucson, Arizona. The purpose and vision of Transform-X are to acquire selected, market-leading, revenue-based companies, while simultaneously securing technologies that will advance their competitive edge and margins beyond the capabilities of other market participants.

Founded in 2016, Transformation Capital is a growth and expansion firm based in Boston, Massachusetts. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the healthcare sector across the United States. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 2007, TransLink Capital is a venture capital firm based in Palo Alto, California. The firm seeks to invest in early to later-stage companies operating in the ag-tech, automotive, blockchain, component, consumer, digital health, e-commerce, enterprise, fintech, gaming, infrastructure, mobility, retail, robotics, and semiconductor sectors across North America, Western Europe, and Asia. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 2010, Transmedia Capital is a venture capital investment firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage companies operating in the digital media, business intelligence, SaaS, enterprise, mobile, business intelligence, fintech, blockchain, enterprise, robotics, artificial intelligence, commerce, marketplace, content, marketing, and social sectors.

Transocean is an international provider of offshore contract drilling services for oil and gas wells. Its segment involves contracting mobile offshore drilling rigs, related equipment, and work crews to drill oil and gas wells.

Provider of implantable wireless diagnostic and monitoring products. The company offers Sleuth ECG Monitoring System, an implantable wireless system to capture electrocardiogram data for diagnosing cardiac arrhythmias, as well as to monitor the electrical activity of the heart and transmit data from the patient's home to monitoring centers.

TransUnion is one of the three leading credit bureaus in the United States, providing the consumer information that is the basis for granting credit. The company also provides fraud detection, marketing, and analytical services. The company operates in over 30 countries, and about a quarter of its revenue comes from international markets.

Provider of sales and marketing services for the insurance sector. The company provides a turnkey, direct-to-consumer sales capability to insurance carriers and leverages and integrates digital, data and direct marketing services that combined with licensed sales execution capabilities deliver new policyholders to carriers seeking to acquire and manage large numbers of customers in three primary insurance verticals: health, life and auto.

Travelers offer a broad product range and participate in both commercial and personal insurance lines. Its commercial operations offer a variety of coverage types for companies of any size but concentrate on serving midsize businesses. Its lines are roughly evenly split between auto and homeowners insurance. Travelers derive 6% of their premiums from foreign markets.
Founded in 2015, Traverse Venture Partners was a venture capital firm based in Washington, District of Columbia. The firm focused on developing real estate.

Mr. Travis Kalanick is a Co-Founder of CloudKitchens. Mr. Kalanick is the Founder and serves as Chief Executive Officer at 10100 Fund. He serves as Chief Executive Officer at Knowlarity. He co-founded and served as Chief Executive Officer and Board Member at Uber. He also serves as a Board member at StyleSeat. He served as a Board Member at Kareo. Prior to joining Uber, he served as Head of P2P Initiatives at Akamai Technologies. He has a successful history of experience in the areas of consumer internet, transportation, and enterprise content delivery. Prior to founding Uber, he was the founder of Red Swoosh, an enterprise delivery company that was sold to Akamai Technologies in 2007. He was also the founder of Scour.net, the world's first P2P filesharing search engine, and is an active angel investor. He received a degree in Computer Engineering and Business Economics from the University of California, Los Angeles (UCLA).

Tredegar through its subsidiaries engaged in the manufacture of polyethylene plastic films, polyester Films, and aluminum extrusions. polyethylene plastic films manufacture plastic films, elastics and laminate materials which are utilized in personal care materials, surface protection films, and specialty and optical lighting applications. It operates through PE films, flexible packaging films, and aluminum extrusion segments. Aluminum extrusions generate the majority of revenue and produce high-quality, soft-alloy, and medium-strength aluminum use for building and construction, automotive, consumer durables, machinery and equipment, electrical, and distribution markets. It generates revenue from the United States, Asia, and Brazil.

TreeHouse Foods is the largest pure-play private-label manufacturer in the US. Much larger in the past following the 2016 acquisition of Ralcorp, Conagra's former private-label business, the company has since divested several businesses to focus on high-growth categories. At present, the company produces and sells snacks (crackers, pretzels, cookies, and so on), beverages and drink mixes (such as non-dairy creamer, coffee, and tea), and a select number of grocery products (pickles, refrigerated dough, hot cereal, cheese, and pudding). Its most important sales channel is through retail grocery stores that sell its products under their own brands, with co-manufacturing and food away from home as much smaller channels of distribution for its fare.
Founded n 1999, Trellis Partners is a venture capital firm based in Cedar Creek, Texas. The firm seeks to invest in the information technology businesses.
Mr. Trémolières Pierre is an Angel Investor.
Founded in 1993, Trendlines is a venture capital firm based in Misgav, Israel. The firm seeks to make investments in the medical technology and agrifood technology sectors.
Founded in 2007, Trestle Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Exton, Pennsylvania. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage companies with a focus on the technology sector.

Trevi Health Capital was an investment firm that provided healthcare-focused alternative asset management through a variety of funds on a global scale. The firm offered private equity capital to growth-stage and middle-market healthcare companies with an emphasis on healthcare information technology, healthcare services, and medical technology. The firm was founded in 2005 and was headquartered in New York, New York.
Founded in 2014, Tri State Angel Investment Group is a venture capital based in Ashland, Kentucky. The firm prefers to invest across the Kentucky-Ohio-West Virginia tri-state region.

Founded in 2004, Triathlon Medical Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Cincinnati, Ohio. The firm prefers to invest in life sciences, medical devices, biotechnology, and diagnostic companies based in the Midwest of the United States region. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Tribune is one of the country's largest media companies. It reaches more than 80% of U.S. households and is the only media organization with newspapers, TV stations, and Web sites in the nation's top three markets. Tribune's newspapers include the Los Angeles Times, Chicago Tribune, and Newsday. Its broadcasting group operates more than 20 television stations, superstation WGN on national cable, an AM radio station, and the Chicago Cubs baseball team. It adds those companies to its portfolio which will expand its advertising networks in print and other media and also its metadata capabilities by extending the business into new areas of music and automotive. The company was acquired by Sinclair Broadcast Group on May 8, 2017.
Tribune Ventures was corporate venture arm of Tribune Media. The firm used to specialize in the in new media and technology sectors.

Trifork Group is an international IT group focusing on the development of software solutions. It focuses on three vertical business areas, namely digital health, fintech, and smart buildings, and three horizontal areas, namely cloud operations, cyber protection, and smart enterprise. The company comprises two main segments, Trifork and Trifork Labs. The company generates the majority of its revenue from the Trifork segment. The Trifork segment services are delivered within three sub-segments: inspire (organizing conferences and training on software development), build (development of software in customer projects), and run (delivery and operation of software products and related services for customers). Geographically, the company derives its key revenue from Denmark.

Founded in 1999, Triginta Capital is a private equity firm based in Dusseldorf, Germany. The firm seeks to invest in B2B, B2C, retail, information technology, manufacturing, marketing technology, digital health, e-commerce, SaaS, industrials, material & resources sectors based in the Austria, Germany & Switzerland regions.

Founded in 2009, Trilantic North America is a private equity firm based in New York, New York. The firm prefers to invest in growth-stage companies through buyouts. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in business products, business services, consumer products, consumer services, energy, financial services, business-to-business payments, infrastructure, impact investing, and technology sector firms based in the North American region. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).
Founded in 2006, Trilogy Equity Partners is a venture capital firm based in Bellevue, Washington. The firm invests in early-stage companies across Pacific Northwest.

TriMas is a United States-based company that designs, manufactures and distributes engineered and applied products. The company operates through three segments namely: the packaging segment manufactures and distributes closure and dispensing systems. The aerospace segment supplies blind bolts, fasteners, rivets and other products for the aerospace industry. The specialty product segment manufactures and distributes steel cylinders, wellhead engines, compression systems, industrial sealing and fasteners.

Trimble provides a technology solutions provider that enables office and mobile professionals to connect their workflows and asset lifecycles to drive a more productive, sustainable future. The company has four reportable segments: buildings and infrastructure, geospatial, resources and utilities and transportation. The company generates the majority of its revenue from the buildings and infrastructure segment, which primarily serves customers working in architecture, engineering, construction, design, asset management, operations and maintenance.

Founded in 1993, Trinity Hunt Partners is a private equity firm based in Dallas, Texas. The firm seeks to invest in the business services and consumer services sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Trinity Industries sells and leases railroad products and railcar maintenance services in North America. The company operates under the name TrinityRail in three main segments: railcar leasing and management services, which owns railcars and provides fleet management and administration services; rail products, which builds, sells, and modifies freight and tank railcars and their components; and all other, which sells highway products such as guardrail and other highway barriers. Customers include railroads, leasing companies, and shipping companies in the industries of agriculture, construction, consumer products, energy and chemicals.

Founded in 1986, Trinity Ventures is a venture capital investment firm based in Menlo Park, California. The firm prefers to invest in early-stage companies. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Manufacturer of modules and components for communication application. The company provides its services to communications companies worldwide. It provides customer premise equipment, wireless local area networks, worldwide interoperability for microwave access networks, global positioning satellite, bluetooth, cable television, microwave radio, satellite, ground station and optical communications for the network's market. The company seeks to strengthen and expand its core business through acquisitions.

Developer of wellness products, skincare and other products primarily targeted for pregnant women. The company also develops the soft and smooth assets. The soft and smooth assets include all rights, interests, and legal claims to that certain inventions entitled which is a novel medical applicator that is capable of delivering medicants and internal devices within the body in an atraumatic fashion

Founded in 2013, Tritium Partners is a private equity firm based in Austin, Texas. The firm focuses mainly on lower-middle market companies operating in technology and services sectors including fintech, financial services, internet marketplaces, software, data & analytics, supply chain & logistics, and tech-enabled business services based in the North American region. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Mr. Troy Carter is a Co-Founder & serves as Chief Executive Officer at Q&A. Mr. Carter is an Angel Investor . He serves as Senior Advisor at The Raine Group. He is also a Co-Founder of Place. XYZ. He served as Independent Director at Focus Impact Partners. He also served as an Advisor at Partnered. He co-founded and served as Chief Executive Officer at Atom Factory. and was a Co-Founder and served as a General Partner at Cross Culture Ventures. He served as an Advisor at MaC Venture Capital. He serves as a Board Member at SoundCloud.

TruBridge is a provider of healthcare solutions and services for community hospitals, clinics, and other healthcare systems. It provides services such as Electronic health records & information systems, revenue cycle management, population health, and data management, etc. The segments of the company are RCM, EHR, and Patient Engagement. The company derives maximum revenue from the RCM segment.

Founded in 2009, True West Capital Partners is a mezzanine investment firm based in Los Angeles, California. The firm seeks to invest in United States-based companies operating in business services, consumer, food, healthcare, niche manufacturing, transportation, and logistics sectors.

TrueBlue is a provider of staffing and workforce management solutions. Its reportable segments include PeopleReady offers industrial staffing services. PeopleManagement offers contingent and productivity-based on-site industrial staffing services and PeopleScout offers recruitment process outsourcing, talent advisory services and managed service provider services. It generates maximum revenue from the PeopleReady segment.

Tsinghua Holdings is a corporation based in Beijing, China. Established in 2003, the firm together with its subsidiaries, engages in information technology (IT); energy conservation and environmental protection; life sciences; and technical service and knowledge industry businesses. The assets are managed by the Board of Directors.

TTM Technologies manufactures technology solutions, including mission systems, radio frequency (RF) components/RF microwave/microelectronic assemblies, quick-turn and technologically printed circuit boards (PCB). The company is based in the United States and derives roughly half of its revenue domestically. The company organizes itself into two segments: printed circuit boards and RF&S Components. The printed circuit boards segment, which contributes the majority of revenue, offers a range of printed circuit boards as well as layout design and simulation, and testing services. TTM Technologies' products are used in manufacturing, networking, telecommunications, computing, aerospace, and medical fields.
TTP Ventures was a member of TTP Group, a leading technology development and services company. The firm preferred to invest in early stage IT and clean-tech companies in the UK.

Founded in 2000, TTV Capital is a venture capital firm based in Atlanta, Georgia. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage companies operating in the financial services ecosystem with a focus on financial technology. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Tucows is a corporate parent, allocating capital and providing efficient shared services to its three businesses. The company offers Mobile Service Enabler (MSE) solutions, as well as professional services to other retail mobile providers. The company is also a distributor of Internet services, including domain name registration, digital certificates and email. He founded Streamlined Ventures with a vision of building a thought-leading investment platform rooted in the philosophical belief that founders of companies are the true heroes of entrepreneurial value creation in our society. He is a seasoned venture capitalist, angel investor, and entrepreneur with over 25 years of entrepreneurial and early-stage investment experience across more than 500 companies. At Streamlined, He has led seed investments in almost 20 companies, each valued at over $ 1 Bn, including iconic companies such as Doordash (IPO), Applovin (IPO), Rappi, Forge (IPO), EasyPost, OpenGov (acquisition), FLYR Labs, Rescale, Flip, Speechify, Medable, Bolt, TubiTV (acquisition), etc. Over the last 25 years, he has seed/angel invested in nearly 150 companies. He is also an investor in numerous venture capital funds. In addition, he helped co-found the full lifecycle investment firm Cota Capital. Before founding Streamlined Ventures, he was a senior member of the investment team for 12 years at Globespan Capital and helped build the firm. They had invested in early-stage rounds of numerous iconic companies, including Palo Alto Networks (IPO), Roku (IPO), Redfin (IPO), UpWork (IPO), BladeLogic (IPO), Virident (acquisition), Q1 Labs (acquisition), Virtusa (IPO), etc.. Before his institutional venture capital investment career, he was a top-ranked Wall Street research analyst at FAC Equities/First Albany. He was recognized by The Wall Street Journal and Fortune Magazine as a Wall Street All-Star. Before that, he received an MBA degree after starting a chemical trading business in India. He also has a bachelor's degree in organic chemistry.

He was also an investor of Thousand Eyes (Private, Sold to Cisco). Umesh holds a Bachelor's in Technology from Indian Institute of Technology, Mumbai and a Master's in Engineering from Stanford University. He has served on several advisory boards at Stanford University, Sutter Pacific Group and Palo Alto Medical Foundation.
