Operator of a network of healthcare organizations. The company is engaged in providing analytics, contracting, consulting, network development, clinical, financial, and operational management, and supply chain management services to its clients.
Founded in 2007, VKRM is a venture capital investment firm based in Los Altos, California. The firm prefers to invest in enterprise services & software, education, and various internet sectors

Founded in 2005, VMG Partners is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm prefers to make investments in seed-stage, early-stage, and later-stage companies in consumer products, beauty, personnel care, food and beverage, pet products & services, software, consumer services, financial services, manufacturing, health & wellness, and technology-based sectors in the United States. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

VMware is an industry titan in virtualizing IT infrastructure and became a stand-alone entity after spinning off from Dell Technologies in November 2021. The software provider operates in three segments: licenses; subscriptions and software as a service and services. VMware's solutions are used across IT infrastructure, application development and cybersecurity teams and the company takes a neutral approach to being cohesion between cloud environments. The Palo Alto, California, firm operates and sells on a global scale, with about half its revenue from the United States, through direct sales, distributors and partnerships.

21Vianet Group started as AsiaCloud in 1999, subsequently it moved to the data center business with its first self-developed data center opening in 2010. The company listed (as 21Vianet) on the Nasdaq in April 2011, subsequently changing its name to Vnet Group in 2021. It originally focused on providing data center services such as colocation and cloud services to retail clients in China but added hyperscale customers in 2019 and now counts large Chinese hyperscalers such as Alibaba Cloud, Tencent Cloud, Huawei Cloud and JD Cloud as customers. At the end of December 2021 it had 78,540 self-built cabinets with the majority in Beijing, Shanghai, and the Greater Bay area. It also operated partnered data centers with around 4,397 cabinets and had 222 MW of wholesale capacity contracted or under MOU.

Provider of carrier-class multimedia and voice-over-IP solutions for communication service providers. The company offers proven trunking, peering, access gateway and service delivery solutions, thereby enabling flexible deployment of next-generation networks.

Provider of on-demand software for corporate communications and public relations. The company's motive is to help companies reach across social networks, online and through the media. Its cloud marketing addresses areas of online marketing, includes social media marketing, search marketing, email marketing and publicity.

Vodafone operates mobile and fixed-line networks and businesses in more than 20 countries. Its largest market is Germany, where it is the second mobile operator after Deutsche Telekom and owns a cable network after acquiring Kabel Deutschland in 2013 and Liberty Global Germany in 2019. In the UK it acts mainly as a mobile operator, being the second largest player after BT Group. In 2024 Vodafone divested its Spanish and Italian divisions, given their low returns on invested capital.

Volcano was a designer, developer and manufacturer of medical devices. The company operated in two segments: medical and industrial. It offered intravascular ultrasound (IVUS) and fractional flow reserve (FFR) products. It sold its products through direct sales force and distributors. The company grew by making periodic small acquisitions. It was established in 2000 and was based in San Diego, California.

Founded in 2010, Volition Capital is a growth equity firm based in Boston, Massachusetts. The firm prefers to invest in business-to-business (B2B) and software-as-a-service (SaaS) sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Volkswagen is the second-largest automotive original equipment manufacturer by vehicle sales globally, selling 9.4 million vehicles in 2023. 80% of group revenue is generated by its four vehicle segments-core (Volkswagen, SEAT, Skoda, and VW commercial), progressive (Audi, Lamborghini, and Bentley), sports luxury (Porsche), and Traton commercial vehicles (Traton, Scania, Navistar, MAN, and VW truck and bus). It also has a vehicle software business (Cariad), batteries, and power engineering production and financial services.
Vollin Holdings is a principal investment firm. The company is headquartered in Tortola, United Kingdom.

Founded in 2010, Volta is a private startup studio and investment boutique based in Reykjavik, Iceland. The firm focuses on companies operating in information technology, commercial services, big data, climate tech, fintech, gaming, mobile, and health tech sectors.

Vonage Holdings is a North American technology company that provides cloud communication services to businesses and consumers. For businesses, the company provides unified communications (as a service), which consists of integrated voice, text, video, data, and mobile applications over Voice over Internet Protocol network. For consumer service customers, there is a home telephone replacement service. This can include services such as voicemail, call waiting, and call forwarding. This service is delivered over the Internet. The company generates the vast majority of its revenue within the United States.

VOXX International manufacturer and distributor in the automotive electronics, consumer electronics, and biometrics industries. The consumer electronic products primarily consist of finished goods sold to retail and commercial customers, consisting of premium audio and other consumer electronic products. Automotive products, some of which are manufactured by the Company, are sold both to OEM and aftermarket customers. Biometric products, primarily consisting of finished goods, are sold to retail and commercial customers.

Founded in 1981, VSS Capital Partners is a private equity firm based in New York, New York. The firm prefers to invest in lower middle-market companies operating in the education, business services, and healthcare sectors based in North America. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).
Founded in 1997, Vulcan Capital Management is a private equity investment firm based in New York, New York. The firm prefers to invest in oil & gas, coal, power and energy sectors.

Operator of a credit union catering to the communities of Jacksonville and surrounding areas in Florida. The company offers services like loan planning, retirement planning, refinancing, home loan consolidation and insurance to its clients.

Founded in 2019, W Investments Group is a private equity firm based in Saint-Lambert, Canada. The firm focuses on private equity and real estate investments. The firm seeks to invest in industrial, manufacturing, and technological companies. The firm also prefers to invest in residential, commercial, and industrial projects.

Manufacturer of specialty chemicals, materials and technologies intended to serve chemical processing, food, beverage, personal care and pharmaceutical industries. The company offers catalysts, additives, silica-based chemicals and adsorbents across North America and Europe, the Middle East and Africa, thereby providing clients with technologies that enhance their products and processes.

WR Hambrecht + Co. is an investment bank providing advisory, research, underwriting and investments services to technology and emerging growth companies. The firm also raises capital and does venture capital investments. It aims to help companies of all sizes efficiently access capital at the lowest possible cost in order to accelerate disruptive growth. It uses data science to help find startups to review and to conduct due diligence. The firm is headquartered in San Francisco, California with an additional office in New York, New York. It was founded in 1998.
Founded in 2017, W2 Labs is an incubator based in Chippenham, United Kingdom. The firm organizes a ten-week program for startups and scale-ups in the United Kingdom.

WageWorks Inc is a provider of tax-advantaged programs in the United States. The company specialises in consumer-directed benefits such as health savings accounts, health and dependent-care flexible spending accounts, health reimbursement arrangements, and commuter benefit services, including transit, parking, and wellness programs. With the help of WageWorks, employees use pretax dollars to pay for healthcare, dependent care, and commuter expenses and save money on their payroll tax. The company was acquired by HealthEquity (NAS: HQY) on August 30, 2019.

Wakefield Group was an investment firm that preferred to invest in the companies based in Southeast of the United States and operating in the technology, healthcare, e-commerce, infrastructure, business services and media sectors focusing on . The firm was founded in 1988 and was based in Charlotte, North Carolina.

Founded in 2021, Walden Catalyst is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm prefers to invest in early-stage companies operating in data, deep tech, artificial intelligence, quantum, cloud, and digital biology sectors across the United States, Europe, and Israel region. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 1974, Walden Venture Capital is a venture capital firm based in Woodside, California. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the software, healthcare, and media sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Walmart serves as the preeminent retailer in the United States, with its strategy predicated on superior operating efficiency and offering the lowest-priced goods to consumers to drive robust store traffic and product turnover. Walmart augmented its low-price business strategy by offering a convenient one-stop shopping destination with the opening of its first supercenter in 1988. Today, Walmart operates over 4,600 stores in the United States (5,200 including Sam's Club) and over 10,000 stores globally. Walmart generated over $440 billion in domestic namesake sales in fiscal 2024, with Sam's Club contributing another $86 billion to the company's top line. Internationally, Walmart generated $115 billion in sales. The retailer serves around 240 million customers globally each week.

Mr. Walter Danco is an Angel Investor. Mr. Danco served as Independent Program Director at Techstars. Previously he was a Co-Founder and Chief Executive Officer at BuysideFX. A veteran of financial markets, he worked at Morgan Stanley, Nomura, Goldman Sachs and Lehman Brothers before switching to the buyside in 1992. In 2000, Ty founded eSecLending, which has become the largest independent securities lending agent in the world. Having been an institutional asset manager, at one point overseeing more than $60B in investments, he is painfully aware of the operational problems of managing complex portfolios distributed over many clients. A graduate of Middlebury College and Wharton Business School, Ty was a member of the US Winter Olympic Team in 1980 and 1984. He still works with the luge team integrating technology that improves the performance of athletes and racing sleds.
Walter Financial is an asset management firm based in Quebec, Canada. The firm prefers to invest in the consumer and business, and products and services sectors.

Mr. Walter Kortschak is the Founder of Firestreak Ventures. Mr. Kortschak is the Founder of WMAS Management Group. He is the Founder and serves as Managing Partner at Kortschak Investments. He serves as a Board Member at Torpago. He serves as a Board Member at Vatom. He served as Advisor at Root-1. He served as a Board Member at Elliptic and Comet. He also served as Advisor & Board Member at Wishlife. He serves as Chairman Emeritus and Founding Investor at SignalFire. He also served as a Senior Advisor at Summit Partners. He joined Summit Partners in 1989 and has served as a director of more than 40 companies, including 20 public companies. He has invested in several industry-defining companies, notably E-TEK Dynamics (NASDAQ: ETEK, later merged with JDS Uniphase in a transaction valued at over $18 billion), an early leader in optical networking; as the initial investor in McAfee (NYSE: MFE, later acquired by Intel), an anti-virus and network security firm and one of the pioneering companies using the Internet business model for distributing software; and HMT Technology (NASDAQ: HMTT, later acquired by Komag) and Diamond Multimedia Systems (NASDAQ: DIMD, later acquired by SONICblue), both early technology buyout and recapitalization transactions in Silicon Valley. Other notable technology investments include AltoCom (acquired by Broadcom), Finisar, NetCom Systems (acquired by Bowthorpe), and Xylan (NASDAQ: XYLN, later acquired by Alcatel). Before Summit, he was a Vice President and an Associate at Crosspoint Venture Partners. He received an FBS in civil engineering, with Honors and High Scholarship, from Oregon State University, an MS in civil engineering from the California Institute of Technology, and an MBA with Honors, from the University of California, Los Angeles. He has consistently appeared on the Forbes Midas List of top 100 venture capitalists and is a founder and advisory board member of the USC Kortschak Center for Learning and Creativity at the University of Southern California and a member of the Board of Trustees at the California Institute of Technology. He is also a past director of the National Venture Capital Association.

Mr. Walter Winshall served as Board Member at AgaMatrix. He is an Angel Investor. He serves as Board Member at SnowShoe, MOCA Systems, RISE Robotics and Percent Pledge. He also served as Board Member at Startup Institute. He also serves as Advisor at HelpAround. He serves as Board Member at QED Labs. Mr. Walter Winshall was the Founder and served as Principal at Collaborative Seed & Growth Partners. He is Principal in Collaborative Seed and Growth Partners, LLC, an investment firm specializing in the commercialization of technology. He also served as a Board Member at PatientsLikeMe. He is also a director at a number of early-stage companies. Previously, he was a co-founder and Chairman of SilverPlatter International, NV, a company providing information services for libraries, which was acquired by the Dutch publishing company Wolters Kluwer in 2001. He graduated from MIT in electrical engineering and from the Harvard Law School.
Founded in 2014, Wamda Capital is a venture capital firm based in Dubai, United Arab Emirates. The firm seeks to invest in the software, internet of things, and artificial intelligence sectors.
Founded in 1985, Wand Partners is a private equity firm based in Key Biscayne, Florida. The firm focuses on specialty financial services sectors.

Operator of a real estate development and investment firm intended to strengthen communities, connect people and enact positive change. The company's platform is committed to assisting and participating in vibrant communities, shared spaces and built environments that are economically and environmentally sustainable, along with takes underutilized spaces and transform it into a community-centric hub where people can gather, grow, create and celebrate together, enabling the society to get access to philanthropic initiatives in a simplified way.

Warner Bros. Discovery was formed in 2022 through the combination of WarnerMedia and Discovery Communications. It operates in three global business segments: studios, networks, and direct-to-consumer. Warner Bros. Pictures is the crown jewel of the studio's business, producing, distributing, and licensing movies and television shows. The network's business consists of basic cable networks, such as CNN, TNT, TBS, Discovery, HGTV, and the Food Network. Direct-to-consumer includes HBO and the firm's streaming platforms, which have now been consolidated to Max and Discovery+. Much of the DTC content is created within the firm's other two business segments. Each segment operates with a global reach, with Max available in over 70 countries.

WarnerMedia is a provider of media and entertainment services. The company offers cable network, filmed entertainment and publishing services. It has businesses in television networks and film and TV entertainment. The company operates through three segments: Turner, Home Box Office and Warner Bros. The company was founded in 1990 and is headquartered in New York, New York.

Supplier of hearing aid products and accessories. The company offers a wide range of hearing aid products and accessories via its online store consisting of comprehensive product offering to audiologists, hearing aid dispensers, hearing aid manufactures, earmold labs and all make repair labs.
Manufacturer of pharmaceuticals and consumer health care products.

WarnerMedia Investments was the corporate venture capital arm of WarnerMedia and was based in New York, New York. The firm was specialized in seed, early stage and later stage investments. It focuses on investing in companies operating in the media and information technology sectors.

Founded in 1975, Wasatch Global Investors is an asset management firm based in Salt Lake City, Utah. The firm seeks to invest in multiple assets, high-growth companies, mutual funds, and small-cap value companies. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).
Wasserstein Adelson Ventures was a venture capital firm based in New York, New York. The firm invested in companies that operated in the information technology sector.

Founded in 2005, Water Street Healthcare Partners is a private equity firm based in Chicago, Illinois. The firm prefers to invest through buyouts and growth capital. The firm prefers investing in commercial, healthcare, and manufacturing services. life sciences, and wellness sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 1978, Watermill Group is a private equity firm based in Boston, Massachusetts. The firm prefers to invest in the aerospace, automotive, building products & services, industrial distribution, metals & fabrication, packaging, chemicals, rubber, and plastics sectors companies based in the United States, Canada, Mexico, and the United Kingdom. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Founded in 2000, Watershed Capital is an asset management firm and is based in Lagos, Nigeria. The firm offers investment advisory services to institutional investors, high-net-worth individuals, and leaders of the industry.
Founded in 2013, Watson Fund is a venture capital firm based in Seattle, Washington. The firm prefers to invest in early-stage startups operating in the life sciences and healthcare sectors.

Watts Water Technologies is a U.S.-based company that provides safety, energy efficiency, and water conservation products. Its product portfolio includes residential and commercial flow control products, which are sold for plumbing and hot water applications; HVAC and gas products, including commercial boilers, water heaters, heating solutions, and heating systems; drainage and water reuse products, including drainage products and engineered rainwater-harvesting solutions; and water quality products, including point-of-use and point-of-entry water filtration, conditioning, and scale prevention systems. The company generates the majority of its revenue from markets in the Americas and in Europe, the Middle East, and Africa.

Founded in 2007, Waveland Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Austin, Texas. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the business products and services, and information technology sectors.

Mr. Wayne Boulais is a Co-Founder and serves as General Partner at Tensility Venture Partners. He served as Board Member at DialogTech and Dirtt Environmental Solutions. He also served as a Board Member at Anokiwave and Advisor at Hyde Park Venture Partners. Previously, he serves as General Partner at Apex Venture Partners. He serves as Advisor at Energy Foundry. He was a general partner with an investment focus in wireless, enterprise applications, and cleantech. Prior to joining Apex, he was a founding member of the Marsh & McLennan Capital C&I Fund. He was also a partner at Marsh's, Mercer Management Consulting (now Oliver Wyman) developing growth strategies for high-tech clients. Prior to Mercer, He led engineering development teams for Raytheon Corporation. He received his MBA from MIT's Sloan School of Management, and an MS and a BS in Engineering from the University of Massachusetts. He currently serves on the boards of Enkata Technologies, IfByPhone, and IQS. He is a board observer of CombineNet. He is also a board member of the Illinois Venture Capital Association and a supporting member of Chicago's Clean Energy Trust. His previous investments included Broadbeam (acquired by MobileAware), eCredit (acquired by Fidelity Ventures), Imaging Portals (acquired by MWA Intelligence), and RMI Corporation (acquired by NetLogic Microsystems). He serves as Advisor at Videate.
Founded in 2011, Wayra is an accelerator firm based in Madrid, Spain. The firm has been Telefónica's open innovation program to connect Telefónica with the entrepreneurial ecosystem worldwide.
Provider of capital pool services. The company offers brokerage, investment and management consultancy services.
Founded in 2010, Webb Investment Network is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm prefers to invest in technology-based sectors.
Provider of integrated internet services to both large and medium-sized traditional businesses and internet start-ups. The company offers e-commerce and web hosting services.

WeCommerce Holdings was a operator of a holding company based in Victoria, Canada. The company was engaged in acquisitions and investments in leading e-commerce enablement businesses. The company was acquired by Tiny (Holding Companies) through a reverse merger, resulting in the combined entity trading on the TSX stock exchange under the ticker symbol TINY for an undisclosed amount on April 17, 2023.

Founded in 1979, WEDGE Group is a private equity firm based in Houston, Texas. The firm seeks to invest in across multiple sectors with a focus on manufacturing, trucking, food processing, engineering, construction, and oilfield services. The firm also invests in value-add cash-flow real estate assets across the United States, with a preference towards office buildings and hotels.

Mr. Wei Guo is a Founding Partner of UpHonest Capital. Mr. Guo was the Founding Partner of Weis Fund. Mr. Guo has been recognized by some entities as one of the most active Chinese investors in Silicon Valley, where his fund has invested in more than 120 startups. His AI investments include RoboTerra, a company that specializes in educational robotics; MoBagel, a business intelligence solution that covers the Internet of Things' data analytics process; and Mashgin, which is building a self-checkout kiosk using object recognition technology to identify retail store items. He co-founded OnePiece Work. He holds BS. He is an active angel investor in Silicon Valley, focusing on early stage cross-sector investments. Since 2015, he has invested in over 300 Silicon Valley startups, over 70 companies with valuation greater than 100 million USD and 100 companies valued over 50 million USD. Wei's portfolio companies include Instacart, grocery delivery company with 39 billion USD valuation; Checkr, automated employee background check with 4.6 billion USD valuation; Hims & Hers, telehealth platform IPOed in 2021.

Founded in 2003, Weinberg Capital Group is a family office based in Cleveland, Ohio. The firm seeks to invest in middle-market companies throughout North America, focusing on manufacturing, business services, medical and healthcare, aviation services, consumer products, and value-added distribution industries. The firm also seeks to invest in real estate properties including retail, multi-family, office, and industrial.
Weiss Peck & Greer Venture Partner was a venture capital firm founded in 1970. The firm was sold to Robeco in 1998 and in 2000 it split into two firms - Lightspeed Venture Partners and Opus Capital.

Wejchert Capital is a venture capital investment firm based in Monaco. The firm has an additional office in Warsaw. The firm prefers to invest in early-stage, distressed, and opportunistic firms. The firm prefers to invest in companies operating in the space, financial technology, food technology, and the football sectors.

WELL Health Technologies is a practitioner-focused digital healthcare company. It has seven reportable segments that are grouped into three key business units: Canadian patient services which includes primary and specialized MyHealth. WELL Health USA patient services include primary circle medica, primary WISP, specialized CRH medical and specialized provider staffing and SaaS and technology services. It generates the majority of its revenue from the Well Health USA patient and provider services unit.
Founded in 1936, Wellcome Trust is a limited partner based in London, United Kingdom. The firm prefers to invest in mental health, climate and health, and infectious diseases sectors.

Wellington Financial was a privately held specialty finance firm that provides term, amortizing loans, growth debt capital and acquisition capitals. The firm focused on firms operating in the automotive, biotechnology, healthcare, business service, light manufacturing, oil, gas service, technology, manufacturing, clean tech and environmental service sectors. It was founded in 2000 and was based in Toronto, Canada.
Founded in 2002, Wells Fargo Capital Finance is a lender and debt provider based in Santa Monica, California.

Founded in 2014, Wells Fargo Innovation Incubator is an incubator headquartered in Golden, Colorado. The firm prefers to invest in companies operating in the agriculture, commercial buildings, and housing technology sectors.

Operator of a healthcare agency intended to offer comprehensive, equitable health and wellness solutions to patients. The company specializes in offering a range of services, from wellness and employer service solutions to advanced care for complex medical and behavioral conditions.

Founded in 1957, Wendel Group is a family office investment firm based in Paris, France. The firm seeks to make growth-stage investments in mobile infrastructure, packaging and labels, paints, coatings and finishing products, and security services sectors.

Founded in 2009, Werth Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Woodbridge, Connecticut. The firm seeks to invest in seed to late-stage Healthcare companies, across the pharmaceuticals, biotechnology, equipment, distribution, facilities and managed health care spaces.

Wesco Distribution is an industrial distributor that has three reportable segments, electrical and electronic solutions, communications and security solutions and utility and broadband solutions. The company offers more than 1.5 million products to its 140,000 active customers through a distribution network of 800 branches, warehouses and sales offices, including 43 distribution centers. Wesco generates approximately 74% of its sales in the United States, but it has a global reach, with operations in 50 other countries.
Founded in 1972, Wesley Clover is a venture capital firm based in Los Angeles, California. The firm prefers investing in early-stage technology companies and real estate properties.

Founded in 2007, West Avenue Capital is a venture capital firm based in Darien, Connecticut. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage companies. The firm prefers to invest in aerospace, commodities, financial services, and technology sectors.

Founded in 2011, West Capital Advisors was a venture capital firm based in Cincinnati, Ohio. The firm provided venture capital and advisory services and also managed the West Capital Partners program, a venture asset class investment vehicle for high net worth individuals and family offices.

Founded in 2001, West Coast Capital is a private equity firm based in Dundonald, United Kingdom. The firm prefers to invest through means of buyouts, debt, and growth capital. The firm prefers to invest in B2C, retail, transportation, and e-commerce sectors.

Provider of medical-research services. The company is an independent, non-profit medical research organization with a mission of lowering healthcare costs by developing patient-centered technology that is accessible when and where it is needed.
Founded in 2013, West Hill Capital is a private equity investment firm based in London, United Kingdom. The firm provides financial services through West Hill Corporate Finance.

West Pharmaceutical Services is based in Pennsylvania, U.S., and is a key supplier to firms in the pharmaceutical, biotechnology, and generic drug industries. West sells elastomer-based packaging components (including stoppers, seals, and plungers), non-glass containment solutions, and auto-injectors for injectable drugs. The company reports in two segments: proprietary products (about 80% of total revenue) and contract-manufactured products (about 20% of total revenue). It generates approximately 55% of its revenue from international markets and 45% from the United States.

Provider of communication and network infrastructure services intended to facilitate proper communication protocols. The company offers a diverse portfolio of services including unified communications, automated notifications, cloud collaboration, digital media and specialty agent services, enabling clients to effectively communicate, collaborate and connect with their audiences.

Westbury Partners was a private equity firm which preferred to invest in the defense and security, information technology, business process outsourcing, government services and specialty manufacturing sectors. The firm was founded in 1995 and was headquartered in Hauppauge, New York.

Westell Technologies Inc is a provider of wireless network infrastructure solutions. It is organized into the following operating segments, In-Building Wireless (IBW), Intelligent Site Management (ISM), and Communications Network Solutions (CNS). IBW segment solutions enable cellular and public safety coverage in stadiums, arenas, malls, buildings, and other indoor areas not served well or at all by the existing macro outdoor cellular network. ISM segment solutions include a suite of remote units, which provide machine-to-machine communications that enable operators to remotely monitor, manage, and control physical site infrastructure and support systems. Geographically, it derives a majority of revenue from the US.

Western Union provides domestic and international money transfers through its global network of about 600,000 outside agents. The company handled over 270 million transactions in 2023 and is the largest money transfer company in the world.

Westlake is a manufacturer and supplier of chemicals, polymers and building products. Its performance and essential materials segment offers a wide range of essential building blocks for making products utilized in everyday living, including olefins, vinyl chemicals, polyethylene and epoxies. Its housing and infrastructure products segment produces key finished goods for building products, pipe and fittings and global compounds businesses.

Founded in 1991, Weston Presidio is a private equity investment firm based in Boston, Massachusetts. This firm focuses on growth equity investments, primarily in the consumer, business services, and industrial growth sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Westport Fuel Systems is an organization engaged in the engineering, manufacturing and supply of alternative fuel systems and components for transportation applications. It has three operating segments; the original equipment manufacturers segment-design, manufacture and sell alternative fuel systems, components and electronics and related engineering services, to OEMs that serve light-duty, medium-duty, and heavy-duty customers, the Independent aftermarket segment includes IAM products, conversion kits, and components allow for the conversion of vehicles after being sold to the end-user through a network of dealers and installers and corporate includes public company activities, corporate oversight, financing and capital allocation.

WestRock manufactures corrugated packaging and consumer packaging, such as folding cartons and paperboard. After the merger of RockTenn and MeadWestvaco in the fall of 2015, WestRock became the largest North American producer of solid bleached sulfate and the second-largest producer of containerboard, which is used in the production of shipping containers.

Founded in 2004, WestView Capital Partners is a private equity investment firm headquartered in Boston, Massachusetts. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in business services, software, information technology services, consumer, healthcare technology, outsourcing, and growth industrial sectors. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

WEX is a provider of corporate payment solutions. The company operates three business segments, mobility, benefits and corporate payments. The mobility segment, the largest segment by revenue, provides fleet vehicle payment solutions, transaction processing and information management services for commercial and government fleets. The corporate payments segment offers business-to-business payment processing and transaction monitoring services. The benefits segment generates revenue from healthcare payment products and its consumer-directed software platform. Wex's largest end market is the United States of America.
Founded in 2007, WGI Group is a venture capital firm based in New York, New York. The firm prefers to make early-stage investments in technology startups.

Wheatley Partners was a private equity firm that was based in Jericho, New York and was founded in 1992. The firm used to focuses on investments in firms operating in the information technology, business service, medical technology, healthcare and education sectors.

Where Food Comes From is a third-party food verification company. It offers food production audits and uses verification processes to ensure that claims made by food producers and processors are accurate. The company supports farmers, ranchers, vineyards, wineries, processors, retailers, distributors, trade associations and restaurants with a wide variety of value-added services provided through its family of verifiers, including IMI Global, International Certification Services, Validus Verification Services and others. The company operates in two segments: verification and certification and software sales and related consulting. It generates the majority of its revenue from verification and certification.

Founded in 2008, White Road Investments is a growth equity investment firm based in Emeryville, California. The firm seeks to invest in companies operating in the consumer products and healthcare sectors.

Founded in 1990, Whitecap Venture Partners is a corporate venture capital investment arm of Whitecastle Investments based in Toronto, Canada. The firm seeks to invest in seed-stage, early-stage, and later-stage companies operating in B2B, commercial products, B2C, healthcare, software as a service, manufacturing, life sciences, fintech, food technology, and technology sectors based in the Northeast United States and Canada.

Founded in 1993, WI Harper Group is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California with additional offices in Beijing and Taipei. The firm invests in early to growth-stage companies across the United States, Greater China, and the Asia Pacific. The firm prefers to invest in companies operating in the fields of healthcare, biotech, artificial intelligence, robotics, fintech, sustainability, and new media. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).
Wiest International was a venture capital firm based in Berlin, Germany.

Founded in 2013, WiL is a venture capital firm headquartered in Palo Alto, California. The firm seeks to invest in seed-stage, early-stage, and later-stage companies. The firm prefers to invest in consumer products, consumer services, information technology, TMT, infrastructure, wellness, mobile, e-commerce, SaaS, industrials, artificial intelligence, machine learning, and technology-based sectors in the United States and Asia. The firm has an additional office in Tokyo, Japan. This firm is a Registered Investment Adviser (RIA).

Mr. Will Guidara is an Angel Investor. Mr. Guidara serves as Operating Partner at Sonoma Brands Capital. Mr. Guidara is the former co-owner of Make It Nice, a hospitality group that includes Eleven Madison Park, the NoMad restaurants, and Made Nice. Under Mr. Guidara's leadership, Eleven Madison Park received numerous accolades, including four stars from the New York Times, and three Michelin stars, and in 2017 was given the highest ranking on the list of the World's 50 Best Restaurants. At The NoMad New York, Guidara and business partner Daniel Humm received a three-star review from The New York Times, one Michelin star, and a James Beard Foundation award. Mr. Guidara has been immersed in the restaurant industry since the age of thirteen and is a graduate of the School of Hotel Administration at Cornell University. Mr. Guidara began his dining room training at Spago Beverly Hills and attended culinary school in the north of Spain.

Willdan Group is a provider of professional technical and consulting services to utilities, private industry and public agencies at all levels of government. It operates in the business segments of energy and engineering and consulting. It generates the majority of its revenue from the energy segment, which includes services such as audits and surveys, program design, master planning, benchmarking analysis, design engineering, construction management, performance contracting, installation, advances in software and data analytics and other services. All of its revenue is derived from the domestic markets.

William Blair Venture Partners was a venture capital firm that used to seek investment opportunities in the United States based companies operating in the fields of business and financial services, consumer, health care products and services and technology sectors.

Dr. William Bryant serves as a Board Partner at Threshold Ventures. Dr. Bryant served as Board Member at Pro.com. He serves as Board Member at Remitly. Mr. Yuchun Lee serves as Board Member and Member of Audit and Finance Committee and Management Development and Compensation Committee at Vertex Pharmaceuticals. He serves as Executive Chairman at DSP Concepts. He is a Co-Founder and serves as Chief Executive Officer at Allego. Mr. Lee served as an Executive in Residence at General Catalyst. He serves as the Chairman at Clarabridge. He served as Entrepreneur-in-Residence and Executive Advisor at Summit Partners. He works closely with the Summit team to help identify and build leading technology companies with a focus on enterprise software and data analytics. Yuchun currently serves as Executive Chairman of the Board of Clarabridge, a company backed by Summit in 2013. Yuchun is the founder and former CEO of Summit portfolio company Unica Corporation, a software company focused on meeting the needs of marketers seeking to embrace technology to reach new customers. As Unica's CEO since its inception in 1992, Yuchun chose Summit as a growth equity partner in 1999. Yuchun guided Unica to a successful IPO in 2005 and under his leadership, the company became a global provider of enterprise marketing management solutions serving more than 1,500 businesses worldwide. In 2010, Unica was acquired by IBM. Yuchun remained with IBM until 2012, serving as Vice President and General Manager of IBM's Enterprise Marketing Management Group, with a global responsibility focusing on the needs of Chief Marketing Officers. Yuchun holds both Bachelor and Master of Science degrees in electrical engineering and computer science from MIT and an MBA from Babson College. He serves as Entrepreneur-in-Residence and Executive Partner at General Catalyst Partners. Prior to Allego, Lee served as vice president and general manager of IBM's Enterprise Marketing Management Group, with a global responsibility focusing on the needs of Chief Marketing Officers. He joined IBM in 2010 as part of its acquisition of Unica, a company that Lee co-founded to meet the needs of marketers seeking to leverage technology to reach new customers. As Unica's CEO since its inception in 1992, Lee's vision and strategy guided the company through a successful IPO in 2005 and ultimately to its acquisition by IBM for over $500M. A respected thought leader in technology and marketing, Lee currently is an Executive in Residence (XIR) at General Catalyst Partners, a venture firm that makes early stage and growth equity investments. He is also on the board of Vertex Pharmaceutical (NASDAQ: VRTX) and CEO of Clarabridge, a market leader in Customer Experience Management. He is a co-inventor of six technology patents and co-authored the book "Solving Data Mining Problems Through Pattern Recognition," and wrote a chapter for the Inside The Minds Books Series titled, "The DNA of Smart Business Growth." Prior to founding Unica, Lee held senior-level positions with Digital Equipment Corporation and M.I.T.'s Lincoln and Media Labs. He holds both Bachelor and Master of Science degrees in Electrical Engineering and Computer Science from M.I.T. and a Master of Business Administration degree from Babson College.

Since 2012, He have invested in 200+ startups which consist of 100+ direct investments and 100+ SPV investments through AngelList, FundersClub, Microventures, TheSyndicate.com, etc. From these investments and his own experience as a startup founder, He could see a pattern of what in general works.

Mr. Zachary Aarons is a Co-Founder and serves as a General Partner at MetaProp . Mr. Aarons serves as a Board Member at Billy. He serves as a Board Member at HouseAccount. He has been working at the intersection of real estate and venture capital for the past decade. He is the most active early-stage PropTech investor in the United States, having funded over 60 startups in the space as an individual as well as 40 startups (and counting) through MetaProp NYC's venture capital funds. In 2010, while working as a Project Manager for internationally renowned large-scale mixed-use real estate developer Millennium Partners, he began investing in early-stage PropTech companies, quickly becoming the most active angel investor in the space with over 50 portfolio companies. In 2015, he parlayed his experiences in the real estate and technology sectors to found MetaProp, devoting his career to the mission of utilizing technology to make real estate more affordable, accessible, sustainable, and resilient. Since founding MetaProp, he and his team have invested in 175 PropTech companies. In addition to early-stage investing, he has worked on large-scale mixed-use development projects in cities like Boston and Los Angeles with Millennium Partners. He has experience with real estate development, commercial asset management, property marketing, and commercial leasing. Before joining Millennium and founding MetaProp NYC, he was a Senior Associate at ENIAC Ventures, a seed-stage mobile technology fund, and the founder of Travelgoat, an online and offline walking tour business. He began his career as an analyst at boutique investment bank Peter J. Solomon Company. Within the community, he serves on the Technology Committee for the Real Estate Board of New York and previously served on the Technology and Real Estate Council for the Urban Land Institute. He has previously served on numerous Non-Profit Boards, including The Tenement Museum and Flamenco Vivo. Outside of work, he currently serves on the Board of Trustees of The Tenement Museum. He is an Assistant Adjunct Professor at the Columbia Graduate School of Architecture, Planning and Preservation. He currently serves on the Investment Committee for Van Wickle Ventures, the student-run venture capital fund at Brown University. He is an Assistant Adjunct Professor at the Columbia Graduate School of Architecture, Planning, and Preservation at Columbia University. He graduated Magna Cum Laude with an A.B. from Brown University in Ancient Studies and earned an MBA from Columbia Business School. He serves on the Technology Committee for the Real Estate Board of New York and the Technology and Real Estate Council for the Urban Land Institute. Previously, he was the Treasurer of the Board of Directors for The Lowline and Flamenco Vivo Carlota Santana. He graduated Magna Cum Laude with an A.B. from Brown University in Ancient Studies and earned an MBA from Columbia Business School. He has been featured in dozens of international publications and media, including The Wall Street Journal, The New Yorker, The Real Deal, Curbed, Commercial Observer, Propmodo, The Information, TechCrunch, Bisnow, Forbes, The Real Estate Weekly, Crain's, and Cheddar. He is a frequent speaker at global PropTech events including the Urban Land Institute, MIPIM, Realcomm, Argus Connect, SuperReturn International, and the Columbia/Goodwin Real Estate Capital Markets Conference. In 2017, he was honored as "Investor of the Year" at the Global PropTech Awards and is frequently listed in Business Insider's Seed 100 as one of the 100 top seed investors in the United States.

Mr. Zachary Bogue serves as a Board Member at Planet. He serves as an Advisor at Upside. He is a Co-Founder and serves as Managing Partner at Data Collective and DCVC and DCVC Bio. He serves as a Board Member at CH4 Global, Vium, Oklo, and Recursion Pharmaceuticals.
Mr. Zachary Sherman is an Angel Investor. He co-founded and served as Chief Executive Officer & Board Member at Vector. He founded Seatgeek and DerbiltU.

Mr. Zachary Weinberg is a Co-Founder & serves as Chief Executive Officer at Curie.Bio. Mr. Weinberg is an Angel Investor. He also serves as an Advisor at Great Oaks Venture Capital. He was a Co-Founder & served as President & Chief Operating Officer at Flatiron. Before co-founding Flatiron, he was Co-Founder, President & COO of Invite Media, an advertising technology company based in NYC. He also serves as a General Partner at Operator Partners. Before starting Curie.Bio, he spent the first 15 years of my career starting software companies. First with Invite Media, which was sold to Google in 2010, and then Flatiron Health, which we sold to Roche in 2018. He holds a degree in Economics and Entrepreneurship from the University of Pennsylvania (Wharton).

Zagg Inc is a manufacturer of smartphone and other mobile accessories. The company's product portfolio includes screen protection, power management solutions, mobile keyboards, personal audio, and cell phone cases sold under the InvisibleShield, mophie, ZAGG, IFROGZ, Gear4, and HALO brands. The largest product by revenue is its screen protectors followed by power management to make the vast majority of revenue. ZAGG Brands has operations in the United States, Ireland, the U.K., and China.

Zebra Technologies is a leading provider of automatic identification and data capture technology to enterprises. Its solutions include barcode printers and scanners, mobile computers, and workflow optimization software. The firm primarily serves the retail, transportation logistics, manufacturing, and healthcare markets, designing custom solutions to improve efficiency at its customers.

Manufacturer and supplier of optics and optoelectronics equipment intended to serve a range of industries including medical, photography, hunting, and other related industries. The company develops products for a range of optical applications including consumer optics, industrial metrology, microscopy, medical technology, planetariums, semiconductor manufacturing technology, and vision care, thereby enabling clients with precise equipment as per their operational requirements.
Zen Investments is a commercial real estate, finance, health care business manager and general investing group. It was founded in 2006 and is based in Bucks County, Pennsylvania.

Developer of cloud-based encoding software intended to provide customers with a reliable encoding of live and on-demand video. The company's software has various features including fast encoding speeds, easy API integration, high scalability, and works on all devices, thereby enabling customers to have access to video encoding power without having to pay for, manage and scale expensive hardware and software.

Founded in 2014, ZenStone Venture Capital is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm prefers to invest in the consumer, real estate, financial service, internet of things, and small & medium business service sectors.

Founded in 2017, ZeroGravity Capital is a venture capital firm headquartered in Chantilly, Virginia. The firm seeks to invest in early-stage companies. The firm prefers to invest in emerging data analytics, artificial intelligence, and machine learning technology.

Ziff Davis is a focused digital media and internet company whose portfolio includes brands in technology, entertainment, shopping, health, cybersecurity, and martech. It has two reportable segments: digital media and cybersecurity, and martech. The company's brands include Mashable, Ookla, Offers.com, IGN, and VPN, among others. The majority of revenue is generated from digital media.
Zilkha Venture Partners was an early stage venture capital firm based in Menlo Park, California. The firm was focused in seed and first round investments in IT and bio-technology companies.

Zillow Group is an Internet-based real estate company that offers its customers an on-demand experience for selling, buying, renting, or financing with transparency and ease. The group works with real estate agents, brokers, builders, property managers and landlords to pair technology with top-notch service. The group has brands such as Zillow, Trulia, StreetEasy, Hotpads, Zillow Rentals, Zillow Home Loans, ShowingTime, Follow Up Boss, Aryeo and others.

Zimmer Biomet designs, manufactures, and markets orthopedic reconstructive implants, as well as supplies and surgical equipment for orthopedic surgery. With the acquisitions of Centerpulse in 2003 and Biomet in 2015, Zimmer holds the leading share of the reconstructive market in the United States, Europe, and Japan. Roughly two thirds of total revenue is derived from sales of large joints, another quarter comes from extremities, trauma, sports medicine, and related surgical products. The firm spun out its dental and spine businesses in 2022.

Zix is a provider of security software for organizations in the healthcare, financial services, insurance, and government sectors. Its services include email encryption, data loss prevention, and bring-your-own-device security to meet data protection and compliance needs. The firm's flagship Zix Email Encryption enables transparent encrypted email delivery through its patented Best Method of Delivery, a secure and convenient method for the recipient, and Zix Gateway, which encrypts and decrypts sensitive messages. The company derives revenue from subscription fees on a one- to three-year basis. The vast majority of the firm's revenue is generated in the United States.

Investor Legal Name: Zhejiang University Joint Innovation Investment Management Partnership Enterprise
Description: Established in 2014, ZJU Joint Innovation Investment is a venture capital firm based in Hangzhou, China. The firm seeks to invest in new energy, integrated circuits, new materials and artificial intelligence sectors.
ZMV Associates was a venture capital firm that was based in Wilmington, Delaware.

Zomedica is a veterinary health company creating products for companion animals (canine, feline and equine) by focusing on the unmet needs of clinical veterinarians. The company's product portfolio includes diagnostics and therapeutics that emphasize patient health and practice health. The company is focused on the final development and commercialization of its TRUFORMA platform, which detects thyroid disorders in dogs & cats and adrenal disorders in dogs. Its operations are comprised of two reportable segments namely diagnostic and therapeutic devices. It earns the majority of revenue from the therapeutics segment.

Founded in 2015, ZWC Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Beijing, China. The firm seeks to invest in early and growth stage companies operating in the technology, media and telecommunications (TMT), consumer and artificial intelligence sectors.

Developer of procedures to optimize microbes for industrial fermentation. The company develops new approaches to create microbial strains efficiently on an industrial scale by applying advanced biology, automation, machine learning and data architecture.
Researcher and developer of therapeutic proteins for the treatment of human diseases. The company focuses on developing a pipeline of therapeutic proteins including recothro for hemostasis.

Zynex is engaged in the manufacturing and marketing of medical devices. It operates through one primary business segment, electrotherapy and pain management products. The business activities of the company are carried out through its subsidiaries. The company designs, manufactures and markets medical devices that treat chronic and acute pain, as well as activate and exercise muscles for rehabilitative purposes with electrical stimulation. The company markets Zynex-manufactured products which include NexWave, NeuroMove, InWave E-Wave and others.

Zynga is a company that develops, markets and operates social games as live services played on mobile platforms, such as iOS and Android and social networking sites, such as Facebook. Zynga generates revenue through mobile game downloads, in-games sales of virtual goods and advertising services. Zynga's revenue is divided between online game and advertising and other, where online games account for the vast majority of total revenue. The firm's top three games account for the majority of its online game revenue. The company invests in several game categories, such as social casino, including Zynga Poker; Casual, including Words With Friends; Action Strategy, including Empires & Allies and Invest Express, including Farmville.
